ali-English Dictionary\"}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0a64e5c2-2fd1-4841-86e4-63c6c75af2c5\",\"sort\":1000046,\"type\":\"abbreviations\",\"label\":\"\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"class\":\"flex flex-row gap-2\",\"start\":0,\"end\":65,\"uuid\":\"0a64e5c2-2fd1-4841-86e4-63c6c75af2c5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"abbreviation\",\"text\":\"Ratnākara/RK\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":12,\"abbreviation\":\"0a64e5c2-2fd1-4841-86e4-63c6c75af2c5\",\"uuid\":\"8cdfd92b-710f-4756-938b-bcda38066af4\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ratnākara/RK\"}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":13}},{\"type\":\"hasAbbreviation\",\"text\":\"Ratnākaraśānti, and (RK) citations from his Sāratamā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":13,\"end\":65,\"uuid\":\"8315a2be-d3b1-4ac4-8ef3-3b298aac4294\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ratnākaraśānti, and (RK) citations from his Sāratamā\"}]}]}]}],\"bibliography\":[{\"heading\":\"Primary Sources\",\"entries\":[{\"uuid\":\"adb88bfe-4f95-49ab-aff6-c130cc84f59c\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eMitra, Rajendralala, ed. \u003cem\u003eAṣṭasāhasrikā\u003c/em\u003e. Bibliotheca Indica nos. 603, 620, 629, 645, 671, and 690. Calcutta: Asiatic Society of Bengal, 1888.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"be912b4b-4140-4cce-ae8a-98bbc31c7bfe\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWogihara, Unrai, ed. \u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkār’ālokā Prajñapāramitāvyākhyā (Commentary on Aṣṭasāhasrikā-Prajñāpāramitā) by Haribhadra Together With the Text Commented On\u003c/em\u003e. Series D, vols. I and II. Tokyo: The Toyo Bunko, 1932–35.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"c4ff9a17-6b06-47ed-b2e2-0c550f307cb9\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eVaidya, P. L., ed. \u003cem\u003eAṣṭasāhasrikā Prajñāpāramitā: With Haribhadra’s Commentary called Āloka\u003c/em\u003e. Buddhist Sanskrit Texts no. 4. Darbhanga: The Mithila Institute, 1960.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"db9832eb-d1b0-4421-a50e-6115757d7175\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eJaini, Padmanabh S., ed. \u003cem\u003eSāratamā: A Pañjikā on the Aṣṭasāhasrikā Prajñāpāramitā Sūtra by Ratnākaraśānti\u003c/em\u003e. Tibetan Sanskrit Works Series, 18. Patna: Kashi Prasad Jayaswal Research Institute, 1979. (For a Sanskrit critical edition of chapter 1, see Seton 2016, Appendix I.)\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"70ae3de5-be17-471c-a574-ca92a2e5f129\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā\u003c/em\u003e). Toh 12, Degé Kangyur vol. 33 (brgyad stong, ka), folios 1.b–286.a.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"6a3ddf33-0268-484d-994e-1334e38cad1f\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa\u003c/em\u003e. bka’ ’gyur (dpe bsdur ma) [Comparative Edition of the Kangyur], krung go’i bod rig pa zhib ’jug ste gnas kyi bka’ bstan dpe sdur khang (The Tibetan Tripitaka Collation Bureau of the China Tibetology Research Center). 108 volumes. Beijing: krung go’i bod rig pa dpe skrun khang (China Tibetology Publishing House), 2006–9, vol. 33, pp. 33–723.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"94012056-1bdf-409c-8432-7c3f93c50719\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā\u003c/em\u003e). H 11, Lhasa Kangyur vol. 29 (brgyad stong pa, a), folios 1.a–523.a. (BDRC: \u003ca href=\\\"http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/MW26071_0011\\\"\u003eMW26071\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"d36eec93-e68e-4819-a3e2-ceead205cc63\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eĀrya Vimuktisena.\u003cem\u003e mngon rtogs rgyan gyi ’grel pa\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkāra­vṛtti\u003c/em\u003e). Toh 3787, Degé Tengyur vol. 80 (shes phyin, ka), folios 13.a–212.a. \u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"3a5b6fac-de14-4102-8f18-e0293ccc62e8\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eHaribhadra. \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa’i bshad pa mngon par rtogs pa’i rgyan gyi snang ba\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAṣṭasāhasrikā­prajñā­paramita­vyākhyānābhi­samayālaṃkārālokā\u003c/em\u003e) [“Light”]. Toh 3791, Degé Tengyur vol. 85 (shes phyin, cha), folios 1.b–341.a.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"34b351d7-e53f-416d-8573-673baf59c84d\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eMaitreya-Asaṅga. [\u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa’i man ngag gi bstan bcos\u003c/em\u003e] \u003cem\u003emngon par rtogs pa’i rgyan\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkāra-\u003c/em\u003e[\u003cem\u003enāma­prajñā­pāramitopadeśa­śāstra­kārikā\u003c/em\u003e]) [\u003cem\u003eOrnament of Clear Realization\u003c/em\u003e]. Toh 3786, Degé Tengyur vol. 80 (shes phyin, ka), folios 1.b–13.a; also TPD 49: 3–30. \u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"9a7d8498-1e4c-41c1-bb10-cc09a2169939\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eRatnākaraśānti (rin chen ’byung gnas zhi ba). \u003cem\u003e’phags pa shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa’i dka’ ’grel snying po mchog\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eSāratamā­nāmaaryāṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā­pañjikā\u003c/em\u003e). Toh 3803, Degé Tengyur vol. 89 (shes phyin, tha), folios 1.a–230.a; also TPD 53: 711–1317. (For a Tibetan critical edition of chapter one, see Seton 2016, Appendix I.)\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"3311015b-d599-4d93-a99b-98566c33c757\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eRatnākaraśānti. \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa’i man ngag\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003ePrajñā­pāramitopadeśa\u003c/em\u003e). Toh 4079, Degé Tengyur vol. 138 (sems tsam, hi), folios 133.b–162.b.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null}]},{\"heading\":\"Secondary References\",\"entries\":[{\"uuid\":\"604452a7-05be-49a6-87a0-885bacfae1d0\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eKasawara, K., F. Max Müller, and H. Wenzel, eds. \u003cem\u003eThe Dharmasaṃgraha: An Ancient Collection of Buddhist Technical Terms\u003c/em\u003e. Anecdotia Oxoniensia, Aryan Series vol. I, part V. Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1885. Online at \u003ca href=\\\"https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.311567\\\"\u003eInternet Archive\u003c/a\u003e. For translation and transliteration see Ānandajoti 2017.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"8a4f20e6-5bbf-430a-9156-7728eb2163ed\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eKramer, Jowita (ed.). \u003cem\u003eSthiramati’s Pañcaskandhakavibhāṣā\u003c/em\u003e. Part I: Critical Edition, Part II: Diplomatic Edition. Beijing/Vienna: China Tibetology Publishing House/Austrian Academy of Sciences Press, 2014.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"e9dff8a2-da2a-4e03-9ea4-472b9945c0dd\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eChim Namkha Drak (mchims nam mkha’ grags). \u003cem\u003ejo bo rin po che dpal ldan a ti sha’i rnam thar rgyas pa yongs grags\u003c/em\u003e [\u003cem\u003eBiography of Atīśa, Zhö edition\u003c/em\u003e]. In \u003cem\u003emkhas dbang rag+hu wIra dang lokesha tsan+dra rnam gnyis kyis nyar tshags byas pa’i dpe tshogs\u003c/em\u003e vol. 29, edited by Raghu Vira and Lokesh Chandra: 49–237 (Roman page numbers). New Delhi, 1982. BDRC: \u003ca href=\\\"http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/MW1KG26281_EFECD3\\\"\u003eMW1KG26281_EFECD3\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"413c1221-dc67-4296-be48-27edaa320921\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eJampa Samten. \u003cem\u003ephug brag bka’ ’gyur bris ma’i dkar chag: A Catalogue of the Phug-brag Manuscript Kanjur\u003c/em\u003e. Dharamsala: LTWA, 1992. BDRC: \u003ca href=\\\"http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/W1KG15416\\\"\u003eW1KG15416\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"97757e42-7647-4693-afea-8c296b75b1c3\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eOlkha Lelung Lobsang Trinlé (’ol kha / dga’ sle lung blo bzang ’phrin las). Narthang Catalog (Detailed). \u003cem\u003ebka’ ’gyur rin po che’i gsung par srid gsum rgyan gcig rdzu ’phrul shing rta’i dkar chag ngo mtshar bkod pa rgya mtsho’i lde mig\u003c/em\u003e. Scans in: Narthang Kangyur (snar thang bka’ ’gyur), vol. 102, pp. 663–909. BDRC: \u003ca href=\\\"http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/W22703\\\"\u003eW22703\u003c/a\u003e. Transcribed in: bka’ ’gyur (dpe bsdur ma) [Comparative Edition of the Kangyur], krung go’i bod rig pa zhib ’jug ste gnas kyi bka’ bstan dpe sdur khang (The Tibetan Tripitaka Collation Bureau of the China Tibetology Research Center). 108 volumes. Beijing: krung go’i bod rig pa dpe skrun khang (China Tibetology Publishing House), 2006–9, vol. 106, pp. 71–306.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"f0b7172d-f522-40c4-9b44-eb43345d2e33\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Perfection of Wisdom in One Hundred Thousand Lines\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eŚata­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa stong phrag brgya pa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 8). Translated by Gareth Sparham. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2024.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"c46268ad-8615-4d9a-b2dc-9255cbb23d0e\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Perfection of Wisdom in Twenty-Five Thousand Lines\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003ePañcaviṃśati­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa stong phrag nyi shu lnga pa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 9). Translated by the Padmakara Translation Group. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2023.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"ecd4aaf1-1ec0-4da6-811f-dd04d2b0e194\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Perfection of Wisdom in Eighteen Thousand Lines\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAṣṭādaśa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa khri brgyad stong pa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 10). Translated by Gareth Sparham. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2022.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"ffd9aa4f-cc43-46f2-9ba2-d743dd853dae\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Perfection of Wisdom in Ten Thousand Lines\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eDaśa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003eshes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa khri pa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 11). Translated by the Padmakara Translation Group. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2018.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"a3cdd2d2-d729-4551-aaef-ba8576391c56\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Chapter on Going Forth\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003ePravrajyāvastu\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003erab tu ’byung ba’i gzhi\u003c/em\u003e, chapter 1 of \u003cem\u003eVinayavastu\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 1). Translated by Robert Miller. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2018.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"0505c90b-dae8-47a9-978e-3a3d175efffd\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000.\u003cem\u003eThe Dhāraṇī “Entering Into Nonconceptuality”\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eAvikalpapraveśadhāraṇī\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003ernam par mi rtog par ’jug pa’i gzungs\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 142). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2020.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"fed4b16a-d762-411e-9b96-0fd595747f35\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eDistinctly Ascertaining the Meanings\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eArthaviniścaya\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003edon rnam par nges pa’i chos kyi rnam grangs\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 317). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2021.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"64e422d7-a5d0-4e77-855f-8835ece1b963\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Sūtra of the Wheel of Dharma\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eDharmacakrasūtra\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003echos kyi ’khor lo’i mdo\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 337). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2018.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"6f57ed71-9e1b-43a2-910d-db05923b1dc0\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Teaching on the Purification Practices from the Path to Liberation\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eVimukti­mārga­dhuta­guṇa­nirdeśa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 306). Translated by Sue Roach. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, forthcoming.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"a1d2a513-8c8e-431a-8fd7-f41688583a4a\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Teaching of Vimalakīrti\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eVimala­kīrti­nirdeśa­sūtra\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003edri ma med par grags pas bstan pa’i mdo\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 176). Translated by Robert A. F. Thurman. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2017.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"35add0a0-92c9-432f-b859-49496ed3c72e\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eThe Ten Bhūmis\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eDaśabhūmika\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003esu bcu pa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 44, ch. 31). Translated by Peter Alan Roberts. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2021.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"a3200699-d432-4f7a-b973-9858d330aa2b\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003e84000. \u003cem\u003eUpholding the Roots of Virtue\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eKuśala­mūla­saṃparigraha\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003edge ba’i rtsa ba yongs su ’dzin pa\u003c/em\u003e, Toh 101). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2020.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"b78852ef-4e2a-4bf0-8bd6-c52eeb68db0c\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eAnālayo, Bhikkhu. “\u003ca href=\\\"https://www.buddhismuskunde.uni-hamburg.de/pdf/5-