hannyakyō\u003c/em\u003e ni tsuite,” (チベットに伝えられる三種『八千頌般若』について [“On the Threefold Textual Tradition of the Aṣṭasāhaśrikā in Tibet”]). \u003cem\u003eIBK\u003c/em\u003e 63/1 (2014): 460–455. \u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"8720e9df-970e-42a2-9ea6-2c0310dee0ad\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eSkorupski, Tadeusz. “The Buddhist Perceptions of Consciousness.” \u003cem\u003eRocznik Orientalistyczny\u003c/em\u003e 62, 1 (2009): 146–74.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"2c38f72b-408d-45bb-b153-16bd08906ed0\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eSparham, Gareth (tr. 2006). \u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkāra with Vṛtti and Ālokā: First Abhisamaya\u003c/em\u003e. Vimuktisena and Haribhadra, vol. 1. Fremont: Jain Publishing, 2006.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"a4663417-b44d-468f-8edb-a3753989b35f\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eSparham, Gareth (tr. 2008). \u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkāra with Vṛtti and Ālokā: Second \u0026amp; Third Abhisamaya\u003c/em\u003e. Vimuktisena and Haribhadra, vol. 2. Fremont: Jain Publishing, 2008.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"e66114a5-5686-4814-a3ef-42fa9aa3eb8b\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eSparham, Gareth (tr. 2009). \u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkāra with Vṛtti and Ālokā: Fourth Abhisamaya\u003c/em\u003e. Vimuktisena and Haribhadra, vol. 3. Fremont: Jain Publishing, 2009.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"7d9d5d03-e976-46ea-afec-afa8fcb433fd\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eSparham, Gareth (tr. 2011) \u003cem\u003eAbhisamayālaṃkāra with Vṛtti and Ālokā: Fifth to Eighth Abhisamaya\u003c/em\u003e. Vimuktisena and Haribhadra, vol. 4. Fremont: Jain Publishing, 2011.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"1b2a5021-06f3-4a0a-a06b-a7613a4b1e66\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eSparham, Gareth (2001). “Demons on the Mother: Objections to the Perfect Wisdom Sūtras in Tibet.” In \u003cem\u003eChanging Minds: Contributions to the Study of Buddhism and Tibet in Honor of Jeffrey Hopkins\u003c/em\u003e, edited by Guy Newland. Ithaca, NY: Snow Lion Publications, 2001. Reprint, 2017.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"2dac7875-bbab-413f-9349-725d15842044\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eTorricelli, Fabrizio, and Nickolai N. Dudka. “Manuscript LTWA No. 23476: A ‘sDe can’ Sample of the brGyad stong pa.” \u003cem\u003eThe Tibet Journal\u003c/em\u003e 24, no. 2: 29–44. \u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"51817d0c-39e1-4056-b7f1-fa36f1b91c41\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003evan der Kuijp, Leonard. “Dating the Two Lde’u Chronicles of Buddhism in India and Tibet.” \u003cem\u003eÉtudes asiatiques: Revue de la Société Suisse-Asie\u003c/em\u003e 46 (1992): 468–91.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"e4009c61-f680-4231-9643-43cec4812db8\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWalleser, Max G. L. “\u003cem\u003eAṣṭasāhasrikā-prajñāpāramitā\u003c/em\u003e.” In \u003cem\u003ePrajñāpāramitā, die Vollkommenheit der Erkenntnis, nach indischen, tibetischen und chinesischen Quellen\u003c/em\u003e. Quellen der Religionsgeschichte, Band 6, Gruppe 8, pp. 32–139. Göttingen: Vandenhoeck \u0026amp; Ruprecht; Leipzig: J. C. Hinrichs’sche, 1914. \u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"086804fa-6c05-46e5-ae2e-8799b8d1750f\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWangchuk, Dorji. \u003cem\u003eThe Resolve to Become a Buddha: A Master of the Bodhicitta Concept in Indo-Tibetan Buddhism\u003c/em\u003e. Studia Philologica Buddhica Monograph Series 23. Tokyo: The International Institute for Buddhist Studies, 2007.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"80e00802-ce32-4f58-bd9c-28c25d41c940\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eXing, Guan. \u003cem\u003eThe Concept of the Buddha: Its Evolution from Early Buddhism to the Trikāya Theory\u003c/em\u003e. London and New York: Routledge, 2004.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"bdc2926d-a8a6-4818-9837-2af106e93b1f\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eZacchetti, Stefano. \u003cem\u003eThe Da zhidu lun 大智度論 (*Mahāprajñāpāramitopadeśa) and the History of the Larger Prajñāpāramitā\u003c/em\u003e. Hamburg Buddhist Studies 14. Bochum and Freiburg: Projekt Verlag, 2021.\u003c/p\u003e \",\"workUuid\":null}]}],\"endnotes\":[{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"de25905b-998c-4b2c-a1b8-93fabe8e9d8c\",\"sort\":1000050,\"type\":\"endnotesHeader\",\"label\":\"n.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":5,\"uuid\":\"262d1a4a-2fb0-4c93-8de7-48e05b9968ca\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Notes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":5}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"aa851662-5360-4c6d-a21b-d98e738c008f\",\"sort\":1000052,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.1\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"While the Tibetan and Chinese traditions consider the Hundred Thousand to be the source of the other twenty-two because it contains the most detailed exposition, traditional scholars in Nepal see the Eight Thousand as the original scripture. Western historians, too, based on the available philological evidence, have concluded that the Eight Thousand probably represents the earliest form of the multiplicity of Prajñāpāramitā texts. Whichever the case, since all the “mother” scriptures follow the same outline, there are many similarities between them, and not only the topics discussed and the order in which they are discussed, but also the principal narrative events, appearances of different interlocutors, and other features are clearly paralleled across the texts, even if the Eight Thousand is notably less similar to the longer sūtras than they are to each other.\",\"label\":\"i.10\",\"sort\":96,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4e00c7a2-df1d-4804-be62-8ff48745d02a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-41\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":166,\"uuid\":\"aa851662-5360-4c6d-a21b-d98e738c008f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The exception within the six “mother” sūtras is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":48}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Verses that Summarize the Perfection of Wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":98},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"06219674-4701-4e07-b357-d2185d9626bd\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":98,\"end\":100}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Prajñā­pāramitā­saṃcayagāthā, Toh 13\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":100,\"end\":136},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a03fbfd7-5e99-47eb-8aea-c11b635d757a\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), because it is so condensed.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":136,\"end\":166}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"501ae3f4-3755-4267-8a9b-9560a92383a3\",\"sort\":1000058,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.2\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"While the Tibetan and Chinese traditions consider the Hundred Thousand to be the source of the other twenty-two because it contains the most detailed exposition, traditional scholars in Nepal see the Eight Thousand as the original scripture. Western historians, too, based on the available philological evidence, have concluded that the Eight Thousand probably represents the earliest form of the multiplicity of Prajñāpāramitā texts. Whichever the case, since all the “mother” scriptures follow the same outline, there are many similarities between them, and not only the topics discussed and the order in which they are discussed, but also the principal narrative events, appearances of different interlocutors, and other features are clearly paralleled across the texts, even if the Eight Thousand is notably less similar to the longer sūtras than they are to each other.\",\"label\":\"i.10\",\"sort\":96,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4e00c7a2-df1d-4804-be62-8ff48745d02a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-41\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":979,\"uuid\":\"501ae3f4-3755-4267-8a9b-9560a92383a3\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mapping the correspondences between the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":40}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":40,\"end\":54},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b7ddd25d-2133-44de-a5aa-00173e5284f1\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the longer sūtras is complicated by the former’s very different‍—and sometimes surprising‍—placing of chapter breaks (see Conze 1978, p.49). Nevertheless, for most of the middle of the text, obvious points of correspondence can be identified, and in this translation have been pointed out in the notes. Nevertheless, at the beginning and toward the end of the text (i.e. its coverage of the first, and of the last three, of the eight main topics of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":54,\"end\":512}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":512,\"end\":520},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6771b306-d1cb-480b-97d2-1729ad31653e\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), the way the subject matter is covered is markedly more compressed in comparison to the longer sūtras (see notes \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":520,\"end\":635}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.64\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":635,\"end\":639},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1a98e02b-80e7-40f8-8f37-4a1b5ad1245f\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/addcf1e1-3aa5-4b9b-9461-0d8db8ce3835\",\"entity\":\"addcf1e1-3aa5-4b9b-9461-0d8db8ce3835\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":639,\"end\":641}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.1296\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":641,\"end\":647},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"77b198ec-f7ee-4c32-ab42-66854485db08\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/cd814b9e-a04f-4c91-8644-3a67a84c6f6b\",\"entity\":\"cd814b9e-a04f-4c91-8644-3a67a84c6f6b\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":647,\"end\":653}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.1299\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":653,\"end\":659},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"54532323-763e-45a2-b2e0-e37f244df543\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/c1dc3486-4a23-4b60-8fe5-dc70b48bf5bc\",\"entity\":\"c1dc3486-4a23-4b60-8fe5-dc70b48bf5bc\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). While the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":659,\"end\":672}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":672,\"end\":680},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b55ca01e-4a46-49c0-a1e5-3f9f4edc8697\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s topics and subtopics can still just about be discerned in these parts of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":680,\"end\":756}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":756,\"end\":770},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cbb17a34-b143-4c02-b06e-3ef7d5cae706\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", especially with the help of the commentaries written partly for just that purpose, the notion that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":770,\"end\":875}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":875,\"end\":883},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ea761f86-fdd1-49c2-a68f-2bad59759c9b\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and its analysis of topics is based rather on the longer sūtras is quite clearly substantiated.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":883,\"end\":979}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"95f7d9d5-492c-444e-8c29-a2038664f370\",\"sort\":1000076,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.3\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$20\",\"label\":\"i.11\",\"sort\":109,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a0a9b633-4b61-47e1-ba52-3daa9a16ac60\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-43\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":552,\"uuid\":\"95f7d9d5-492c-444e-8c29-a2038664f370\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This manuscript, which consists of the 15 cm wide portion of a much longer birch-bark scroll, has on its recto and verso sides portions of text that, although considerably shorter, are comparable to portions of the first and fifth chapters of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":247}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":247,\"end\":261},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ab661308-22d6-41d4-98c3-292b9f308273\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". It shows evidence of having been copied from an earlier manuscript, suggesting that the text itself dates to earlier than its carbon dating, possibly as early as the first or second century \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":261,\"end\":453}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ʙᴄᴇ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":453,\"end\":456},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":453,\"end\":456,\"uuid\":\"a1a62e86-323e-47bf-b956-c18685359d44\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For more information, see Falk and Karashima 2012, p. 34. See also Zacchetti 2015, pp. 181–82.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":456,\"end\":552}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c9fd5df1-3a87-4e07-8a45-258ab531e037\",\"sort\":1000082,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.4\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Manuscript fragments found near Bamiyan in Afghanistan and dated paleographically to the second half of the third century are more closely comparable to the Eight Thousand, to a degree that could justify their description as the earliest known Sanskrit witnesses of the text. Nevertheless, the various versions of the scripture that we know today as the Eight Thousand show evidence of significant expansion and evolution over time, as can be seen by comparing the extant Chinese translations made successively between the second and tenth centuries (see below).\",\"label\":\"i.12\",\"sort\":133,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"27586848-673b-4921-9b3a-721ceafb83f9\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-45\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":54,\"uuid\":\"c9fd5df1-3a87-4e07-8a45-258ab531e037\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sander 2000, pp. 3–5. See also Zacchetti 2015, p. 182.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":54}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"285b92d5-88a0-4943-b64b-01dc0fc554a9\",\"sort\":1000084,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.5\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The complete Sanskrit text is available in three successive editions, made by Mitra (1888), Wogihara (1932–35), and Vaidya (1960), from Nepalese manuscripts. The manuscripts themselves are of relatively recent date but are based on recensions dated to the eleventh or twelfth century.\",\"label\":\"i.14\",\"sort\":151,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a0dd4407-602b-45c2-97a3-2fe00089f1a9\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-48\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":210,\"uuid\":\"285b92d5-88a0-4943-b64b-01dc0fc554a9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Wogihara and Vaidya did not edit the text themselves, as is sometimes thought; they merely reproduced Mitra’s edition without looking at the manuscripts, occasionally introducing their own typos in the process.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":210}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"762d8bf3-00fe-4b1f-bf9f-8dee6e042ce5\",\"sort\":1000086,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.6\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"There are suggestions in the Tibetan accounts of the various stages by which the successive Tibetan translations reached their present form that the numerous Sanskrit manuscripts consulted by successive translators may have not only been slightly different but also fell into two broad groups: those made before and after a revision of the text to conform to The Ornament of Clear Realization. However, the extant Sanskrit versions show no evidence of belonging to more than one principal lineage.\",\"label\":\"i.16\",\"sort\":157,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"fb8c27a4-9066-4298-8a81-ce7195e7502a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-51\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25,\"uuid\":\"762d8bf3-00fe-4b1f-bf9f-8dee6e042ce5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See below and Shōji 2014.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0e6608b4-1985-4d1a-9272-62d3bce5e938\",\"sort\":1000088,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.7\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$21\",\"label\":\"i.18\",\"sort\":166,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"66b60796-1b07-49cd-9829-b80b0383b10c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-54\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25,\"uuid\":\"0e6608b4-1985-4d1a-9272-62d3bce5e938\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Karashima 2011 and 2013a.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"791a0b44-40e2-4443-8cb2-a46d06bb9223\",\"sort\":1000090,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.8\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$22\",\"label\":\"i.18\",\"sort\":166,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"66b60796-1b07-49cd-9829-b80b0383b10c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-54\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":13,\"uuid\":\"791a0b44-40e2-4443-8cb2-a46d06bb9223\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Nattier 2010.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":13}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e2217ddc-5079-4d9c-b0b4-586d5532f53d\",\"sort\":1000092,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.9\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$23\",\"label\":\"i.18\",\"sort\":166,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"66b60796-1b07-49cd-9829-b80b0383b10c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-54\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":80,\"uuid\":\"e2217ddc-5079-4d9c-b0b4-586d5532f53d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Karashima 2010 attributes its translation to Dharmarakṣa and dates it to 265 \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":77}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ᴄᴇ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":77,\"end\":79},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":77,\"end\":79,\"uuid\":\"25c9016c-e1db-4160-9b67-8ae54b5a2de6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":80}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0ef35234-d1f8-4e07-96d2-622354d310e5\",\"sort\":1000098,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.10\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$24\",\"label\":\"i.23\",\"sort\":279,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"0e7e5b45-466a-4c5e-9ceb-431b309d62a4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-62\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":491,\"uuid\":\"0ef35234-d1f8-4e07-96d2-622354d310e5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Jampa Samten 1992, p. 12, where some of this information is set out in a note (in Tibetan) under text no. 10, the first of three versions of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":149}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":163},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"166a0a44-d9e2-4756-a8fc-568f37f9e667\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the Phukdrak Kangyur. But for a more detailed discussion see Olkha Lelung Jedrung, Lobsang Trinlé (’ol kha / dga’ sle lung blo bzang ’phrin las, 1697–1740), Narthang \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":163,\"end\":333}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dkar chag rgyas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":333,\"end\":351},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f166804c-450e-4d78-be83-a3c07f589269\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (the extensive Narthang Kangyur catalog), folios 84.b–85.a, or Pedurma vol. 106, pp. 228–29 (the latter being considerably easier to read).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":351,\"end\":491}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"735925a4-a2ad-40bc-bae5-1df68466003f\",\"sort\":1000104,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.11\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$25\",\"label\":\"i.23\",\"sort\":279,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"0e7e5b45-466a-4c5e-9ceb-431b309d62a4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-62\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":198,\"uuid\":\"735925a4-a2ad-40bc-bae5-1df68466003f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Olkha Lelung Jedrung. As an analogy, he compares the two expressions “divine flowers and divine fragrant \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":109}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"incense\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":109,\"end\":116},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a7f22c1a-24b6-4d08-9954-737b6aff3c4f\",\"uuid\":\"3dbc4cd4-93e9-48cc-ae00-96c52f41af96\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” and “divine flowers and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":142}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"incense\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":142,\"end\":149},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a7f22c1a-24b6-4d08-9954-737b6aff3c4f\",\"uuid\":\"6428650e-f78b-40a2-9f96-bb14018b1ef0\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” differing only in their degree of contraction.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":198}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6c2df32e-7f8e-4592-9b20-c0fab48ee30d\",\"sort\":1000110,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.12\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$26\",\"label\":\"i.24\",\"sort\":306,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a9e6efc3-1a66-4f28-9b50-2b6e302a5da4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-65\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":192,\"uuid\":\"6c2df32e-7f8e-4592-9b20-c0fab48ee30d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Degé \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":5}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dkar chag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5,\"end\":14},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"974c9960-24ce-4075-a508-09c95a0ab50f\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", folio 118.a. However, the statement could be taken to refer only to the name and thus to follow the opinion of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":14,\"end\":127}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Rinchen Chökyong Zangpo\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":150},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"707c77e9-456a-4996-887a-8e8cc1cd9503\",\"uuid\":\"75202f77-937f-47f3-916f-ed5532d7a3df\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as summarized in the preceding paragraph.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":150,\"end\":192}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a5f7ff08-6393-44ac-b257-1b1ae1a0fc20\",\"sort\":1000116,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.13\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$27\",\"label\":\"i.24\",\"sort\":306,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a9e6efc3-1a66-4f28-9b50-2b6e302a5da4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-65\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":64,\"uuid\":\"a5f7ff08-6393-44ac-b257-1b1ae1a0fc20\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Jampa Samten 1992, p. 12; Torricelli and Dudka 1999; Shōji 2014.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":64}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"98586d9e-6066-4d33-8aba-ce1b0845e90a\",\"sort\":1000118,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.14\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$28\",\"label\":\"i.25\",\"sort\":334,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"97fa388a-af40-4744-a0c5-d955dbcd0a45\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-68\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":68,\"uuid\":\"98586d9e-6066-4d33-8aba-ce1b0845e90a\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"LTWA manuscript 23476; see Torricelli and Dudka 1999 and Shōji 2014.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":68}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"72f2480d-97fb-45df-9cc7-0797ebdcbef7\",\"sort\":1000120,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.15\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$29\",\"label\":\"i.25\",\"sort\":334,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"97fa388a-af40-4744-a0c5-d955dbcd0a45\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-68\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":60,\"uuid\":\"72f2480d-97fb-45df-9cc7-0797ebdcbef7\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"LTWA manuscript 14523; see Torricelli and Dudka 1999, p. 33.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":60}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fe68af45-7599-4b7c-8fd4-cff9e53329a9\",\"sort\":1000122,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.16\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In summary, the Tibetan translation seems to have been very carefully checked, edited, revised, and verified against a number of Sanskrit manuscripts, and indeed with the help of one or more of the Indian commentaries (although there is no record of which), by many generations of scholars.\",\"label\":\"i.28\",\"sort\":412,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"bbdf9743-bddb-4cd6-a0a6-e224e04cc8b5\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-73\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":98,\"uuid\":\"fe68af45-7599-4b7c-8fd4-cff9e53329a9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For one indication that the commentaries consulted may have included Ratnākaraśānti’s, see \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":91}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.1359\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":91,\"end\":97},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"16d6ef7b-dfdf-4674-9249-9c8eaa9ebebf\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/03e27c41-7923-417e-9398-495bffefe96c\",\"entity\":\"03e27c41-7923-417e-9398-495bffefe96c\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":97,\"end\":98}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4aa30b5f-9f30-43dc-9e0d-44a55771d04f\",\"sort\":1000128,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.17\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2a\",\"label\":\"i.31\",\"sort\":424,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"f3fc3c5e-5cde-4c3c-8989-268312ff1a19\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-79\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":163,\"uuid\":\"4aa30b5f-9f30-43dc-9e0d-44a55771d04f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"These are just two of the twenty types of saṅgha mentioned by the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":66}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":66,\"end\":74},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f71dbf3f-b4ff-4dd8-8801-fdce12091061\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". But this distinction will hopefully suffice for the limited scope of this introduction.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":163}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"924238cc-d087-4f04-bd20-ef8521778dfc\",\"sort\":1000133,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.18\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The complexity of interpreting the language and meaning of these scriptures is witnessed by the large number of different commentaries and treatises composed over the centuries, and the variety of interpretive traditions. Schematically, these can be seen as arising in three phases.\",\"label\":\"i.33\",\"sort\":438,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"cfab8160-ad78-4fae-8ad1-2c32ffd3c851\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-82\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":671,\"uuid\":\"924238cc-d087-4f04-bd20-ef8521778dfc\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Atiśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":5},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1b7e341e-95b8-47c3-89e6-6c9610cefb0f\",\"uuid\":\"e50f4785-81c8-4111-9d35-f3bacc673734\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5,\"end\":8}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extensive Biography\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":8,\"end\":27},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fc3bb074-204e-4473-a933-9526fe8850d3\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":27,\"end\":29}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rnam thar rgyas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":29,\"end\":47},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"76490472-81a8-4045-9d54-200978a7cc0d\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") reports that he received the three traditional streams of interpreting the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":47,\"end\":124}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfection of Wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":144},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"48b59afb-9048-494e-bcd6-fafa5676f85f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" scriptures‍—the explanation by Mañjuśrī, the explanation by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":144,\"end\":205}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maitreya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":205,\"end\":213},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"34e9bd80-03ca-4582-8295-19dcf8d87219\",\"uuid\":\"90a1024a-3a69-4b8b-b8db-7d1ac35b482e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and the explanation according to sūtra and tantra‍—from Ratnākaraśānti, but does not specify what they are. In explaining the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":213,\"end\":341}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":341,\"end\":355},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3ec63aae-6afb-4d20-b989-af559e8de90f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s bodhicitta section, Ratnākaraśānti cites both \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":355,\"end\":404}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Teaching of Akṣayamati\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":404,\"end\":430},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"64aa9cfc-5855-41cc-9706-c1a3330429ef\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\",\"start\":404,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8898e17a-3258-4d82-b497-f97aefdb7e3a\",\"href\":\"/entity/work/a1242a84-bdd4-40c5-8d23-20f16fbb15a4\",\"entity\":\"a1242a84-bdd4-40c5-8d23-20f16fbb15a4\",\"type\":\"work\",\"toh\":null,\"linkToh\":\"toh175\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":430,\"end\":432}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Akṣayamatinirdeśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":432,\"end\":449},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3da8d029-411c-4de1-ad81-05b55eab0920\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", Toh 175) and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":449,\"end\":464}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maitreya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":464,\"end\":472},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"34e9bd80-03ca-4582-8295-19dcf8d87219\",\"uuid\":\"5d801da9-0f33-4656-ad4c-56dbd99c3002\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":472,\"end\":475}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":475,\"end\":483},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"56b35a6a-e29e-4e51-acee-6c08b868bc9c\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", suggesting that these might have been, respectively, the first two streams. It is not clear precisely which commentaries might constitute the “explanation according to sūtra and tantra.”\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":483,\"end\":671}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"52805295-ab41-4f56-8850-4444a31bf5bb\",\"sort\":1000154,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.19\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"First, Nāgārjuna’s treatise, The Root Verses on the Middle Way (Mūlamadhyamakakārikā, Toh 3824), clarified their explicit teachings on emptiness, and the commentary attributed to him by the Chinese tradition, Instructions on the Great Perfection of Wisdom (Dazhidu lun, *Mahāprajñāpāramitopadeśa), unpacked their terminology and general implications.\",\"label\":\"i.34\",\"sort\":442,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"d455b5a3-019a-4265-b699-b049d6a78b0a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-84\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":849,\"uuid\":\"52805295-ab41-4f56-8850-4444a31bf5bb\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Although this commentary is not mentioned by name in subsequent Indian sources, it may have been orally transmitted to some degree in India, and might possibly be included in the tradition later attributed to Mañjuśrī. It is the colophon of Kumārajīva’s (fifth century) Chinese translation that attributes it to Nāgārjuna. Lamotte (III, p. ix) argued against this attribution. However, without ruling out Nāgārjuna as a possible originator, Zacchetti (2021, pp. 94–97) suggests that multiple compilers probably contributed to the work we now know today. Importantly, Zacchetti’s analysis raises questions about the application of Western notions of authorship to Indian scriptural and commentarial literature, where subsequent interpolations made in the service of perceived authorial intentions are still attributed to an important founding figure.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":849}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0e46825f-dd36-4057-bb8a-b79f725e94ac\",\"sort\":1000158,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.20\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Next, according to some traditions, the great master Asaṅga (fourth century ᴄᴇ) found the logical coherence of the structure and content of these scriptures so difficult to grasp that he prayed to the bodhisattva Maitreya for guidance. In response to his prayers, Maitreya is said to have transmitted to Asaṅga (along with four other works) the treatise called The Ornament of Clear Realization (Toh 3786, hereafter referred to as Ornament), which reveals the implicit framework of eight topics necessary for understanding how the Prajñāpāramitā scriptures are structured around the stages and paths to awakening.\",\"label\":\"i.35\",\"sort\":457,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"5a8e8695-6b38-4735-915f-7b5080963e99\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-86\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":542,\"uuid\":\"0e46825f-dd36-4057-bb8a-b79f725e94ac\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":12},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3509c071-968b-4f4d-a6a5-edc9639f18ad\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" seems to have been formulated to match most closely the larger Perfection of Wisdom sūtras, which in Asaṅga’s time were not as clearly differentiated into recensions named by their length as they were later, but of which the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":238}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Twenty-Five Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":238,\"end\":258},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2c854089-d9ed-4bdb-ab9f-b18d4192b706\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Toh 9) is the representative version usually taken as the “root text” whose content the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":258,\"end\":348}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":348,\"end\":356},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"63f5ecad-9232-4b99-ae14-2150f2c9acb1\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" summarizes and organizes into topics. The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":356,\"end\":399}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":407},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7eac24fb-5310-487a-8347-e11d2185d633\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" has been studied in India and Tibet for centuries, but it was never translated into Chinese and is not known in East Asian traditions.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":407,\"end\":542}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cf2139a1-c01a-4ead-9449-dbf92f4be745\",\"sort\":1000168,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.21\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Finally, The Long Explanation of the Noble Perfection of Wisdom in One Hundred Thousand, Twenty-Five Thousand, and Eighteen Thousand Lines (Toh 3808), attributed by some to Vasubandhu (fourth to fifth century) and by others to Daṃṣṭrasena (eighth to early ninth century), presents the structure of the larger scriptures as involving three approaches to the topic: brief, intermediate, and detailed.\",\"label\":\"i.36\",\"sort\":470,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"395d29c2-c137-4455-90a4-c98b84fc03f3\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-88\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":865,\"uuid\":\"cf2139a1-c01a-4ead-9449-dbf92f4be745\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This tradition of explanation is often associated with not just one but two commentaries, both incorporating in their titles the Sanskrit term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":143}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bṛhaṭṭīkā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":143,\"end\":152},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":143,\"end\":152,\"uuid\":\"9918c1b2-674d-48a9-a2b5-c4e8176a7688\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the other (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":152,\"end\":165}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Toh 3807\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":173},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"baffeece-956c-460e-b5de-2486df221fda\",\"href\":\"/translation/toh3807\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") being a commentary on the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":173,\"end\":201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hundred Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":217},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fe0d9680-b927-4e0a-8210-c891951ee428\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" alone, and both using similar approaches. See \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":217,\"end\":264}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Long Explanation of the Noble Perfection of Wisdom in One Hundred Thousand, Twenty-Five Thousand, and Eighteen Thousand Lines\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":264,\"end\":393},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ff650a2b-eece-4578-a172-bd4ff1425fd8\",\"href\":\"/entity/work/009cb40f-b705-410b-91cc-7a638ff76054\",\"entity\":\"009cb40f-b705-410b-91cc-7a638ff76054\",\"type\":\"work\",\"toh\":null,\"linkToh\":\"toh3808\",\"start\":264,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1fada934-0848-42dd-8e14-817e41061ce3\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":393,\"end\":395}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ārya­śata­sāhasrikā­pañca­viṃśati­sāhasrikāṣṭādaśa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā­bṛhaṭṭīkā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":395,\"end\":481},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d8cfa7b6-aeac-4baf-9bf0-937974691cdb\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", Toh 3808). The attribution of both texts was the subject of dispute in Tibet. Some attribute Toh 3808 to Vasubandhu, but others to Daṃṣṭrasena, who lived several centuries after Vasubandhu; Toh 3807 is more often attributed to Daṃṣṭrasena but may possibly have been composed in Tibet. For more information, see the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":481,\"end\":798}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"introduction\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":798,\"end\":810},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"27f6b52d-bfc3-4b91-a25f-e7a841a9d872\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/d56046f8-3c70-4ad8-8487-65469add18ee\",\"entity\":\"d56046f8-3c70-4ad8-8487-65469add18ee\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"subtype\":\"introductionHeader\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to the translation of Toh 3808. See also Sparham 2001.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":810,\"end\":865}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4ba2bebc-e60e-41af-a1b0-a4705ce7ab22\",\"sort\":1000184,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.22\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Against this background of the Prajñāpāramitā treatises in general, Dignāga (480–540 ᴄᴇ) composed what purports to be a brief thematic summary of the Eight Thousand called The Condensed Meaning (Piṇḍārtha, Toh 3809). But Dignāga’s summary highlights only specific aspects of the Perfection of Wisdom scripture, and the difficulties that nonspecialists had in understanding the philosophical and soteriological frameworks implied in the scripture seem to have continued.\",\"label\":\"i.37\",\"sort\":478,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"5bc22a26-d2fe-40bf-8b21-cd14dcf2c610\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-91\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":86,\"uuid\":\"4ba2bebc-e60e-41af-a1b0-a4705ce7ab22\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The commentary is nevertheless said to follow more closely, rather, the longer sūtras.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":86}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8ec68791-a4c8-45d4-a180-7d17772133cd\",\"sort\":1000186,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.23\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In the eleventh century, Ratnākaraśānti composed The Quintessence of the Eight Thousand (Aṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā­pañjikāsārottamā, hereafter Quintessence). It has been preserved in Tibetan translation in the Tengyur (Toh 3803), and incompletely in a Sanskrit edition by Padmanabh Jaini, published in 1979. As the only other commentary on the Eight Thousand, it addresses matters that Haribhadra had not covered and disputes some things that he had. But aside from unpacking the scripture, Ratnākaraśānti aimed to show‍—through his many commentaries‍—how central the Perfection of Wisdom is to both Mahāyāna and tantric practice, as in the concluding lines of his opening verses to The Instructions on the Perfection of Wisdom (Prajñāpāramitopadeśa, Toh 4079):\",\"label\":\"i.39\",\"sort\":516,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"8ac05c81-29ae-4f24-aae6-b27d0219e213\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-94\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":508,\"uuid\":\"8ec68791-a4c8-45d4-a180-7d17772133cd\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Jaini’s (1979) edition was made from two incomplete Sanskrit palm-leaf manuscripts that had been discovered at Sakya Monastery by Rāhula Sāṅkṛtyāyana during his second journey to Tibet in 1936, and photographed by him and Gendun Chöphel during his fourth journey in 1938 (see Sāṅkṛtyāyana 1937, MS nos. 200 and 201 pp. 24–5). While large parts are intact there are numerous missing passages, and in the notes to this translation citations from passages missing in Sanskrit are given from the Tibetan instead.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":508}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4aaa8ed5-f790-44e2-95ee-bf49b585780b\",\"sort\":1000188,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.24\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In this way, through the efforts of Indian scholars, the Eight Thousand came to be understood as one of the foundational scriptural authorities for the practice of both the Mahāyāna and Vajrayāna. Furthermore, since each commentator attempted to prove that the scripture aligns with his own philosophical position, it slowly became the interpretive battleground for different scholastic attempts to systematize the Indian Mahāyāna Buddhist logic of practice. Despite their different philosophical perspectives, the commentaries provide excellent access to the scripture’s meaning. Yet even when a commentary explains the esoteric meaning, the relevance and application of this meaning is not always perfectly clear in the words in the scripture itself. So serious scholastic study began to focus more on individual treatises than on the actual scriptures.\",\"label\":\"i.41\",\"sort\":544,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"60a49521-60c5-40a0-9e04-5144035aa9a9\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-97\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":352,\"uuid\":\"4aaa8ed5-f790-44e2-95ee-bf49b585780b\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to the eleventh-century Indian Buddhist scholar Advayavajra, the three Buddhist philosophical schools‍—known as Sautrāntika, Yogācāra, and Madhyamaka‍—all practiced the method of the transcendent perfections that was introduced in this scripture. In other words, based on its views the followers of Sautrāntika were able to practice Mahāyāna.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":352}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9a6ab0ac-eeac-4205-8e92-718d323af0a7\",\"sort\":1000190,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.25\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"From the eighth century onward, Indian scholastic study of the Perfection of Wisdom seems to have increasingly read the scriptures through the lens of one particular treatise, namely the Ornament. The Ornament itself is a brief independent treatise that provides a versified outline of topics within the mother Prajñāpāramitā scriptures themselves. The outline has eight chapters, which include a total of seventy main topics and twelve hundred subtopics to be realized along the path. But the Ornament neither expands on these topics, nor explains how they are to be interpolated into the Mother Prajñāpāramitā scriptures themselves. Commentaries on the Ornament are required to show where exactly the individual Ornament headings should be inserted into the scriptures and how those headings shed light on each stage of Mahāyāna practice.\",\"label\":\"i.42\",\"sort\":550,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"8cbd3bc2-fa79-4f35-8f18-43aa4dccb633\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-99\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":468,\"uuid\":\"9a6ab0ac-eeac-4205-8e92-718d323af0a7\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":12},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7a8c94f8-f4b1-406a-af81-77a534faabc4\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is attributed in the Indo-Tibetan tradition to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":60}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maitreya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"34e9bd80-03ca-4582-8295-19dcf8d87219\",\"uuid\":\"97369843-2a3f-4cb8-a5bf-470362580671\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", who taught it to Asaṅga as one of the “five treatises of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":127}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Maitreya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":135},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"34e9bd80-03ca-4582-8295-19dcf8d87219\",\"uuid\":\"a8bd00f6-956f-4747-b128-f4c83e3b1cca\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":135,\"end\":138}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byams chos sde lnga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":138,\"end\":157},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":138,\"end\":157,\"uuid\":\"80870ab5-2869-42b1-b980-7aff1e92a550\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). According to Makransky 1998 (p. 369 n3) and Brunnhölzl 2010 (vol. 1, p. 692 n98), this attribution was first made by Haribhadra (late eighth to early ninth century). For more about the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":157,\"end\":345}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":353},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ab4df376-a1c1-4cd5-8b49-a3fe3d847181\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and its history (especially with regard to its final chapter on the kāyas) see the introduction to Makransky 1998.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":353,\"end\":468}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5a5db32b-4da0-4f32-bd22-e1633e7cc395\",\"sort\":1000202,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.26\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"So helpful was the guidance of these two commentators that when the seven (or eight, see above) different teams of Tibetan translators each translated or retranslated the Eight Thousand into Tibetan between the eighth and sixteenth centuries, they all based their translations on the glosses and explanations that the two commentaries provided. Later, when the Ornament became the focus of Tibetan scholastic education in the different schools and lineages of Tibet, the Tibetans made direct reference to these same two commentaries in their own subcommentaries, sub-subcommentaries, and textbooks. In this way, the Tibetan tradition absorbed the Indian Prajñāpāramitā literature into its own works and continued to expand upon the topics. Over time, the Tibetans came to focus mainly on studying the Ornament without making any reference to the scriptures themselves, since to achieve a serviceable understanding of the Ornament alone is said to take years of dedicated, single-pointed study.\",\"label\":\"i.45\",\"sort\":602,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"c28263a8-41fc-48c0-a83a-1ca77f1b3507\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-103\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":181,\"uuid\":\"5a5db32b-4da0-4f32-bd22-e1633e7cc395\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tibetans primarily study the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":29}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":29,\"end\":37},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"665a2f32-d4dc-471f-9f76-a841f7646f53\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" through Haribhadra’s short \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":37,\"end\":65}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Commentary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":65,\"end\":75},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9caaf330-f39b-45de-b285-958d04f39d5d\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":75,\"end\":77}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vivṛtti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":77,\"end\":84},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":77,\"end\":84,\"uuid\":\"e13c7be5-d3f9-4f4e-bceb-7d2eb7153208\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":84,\"end\":86}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’grel pa don gsal\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":103},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":103,\"uuid\":\"634b7291-9b58-4163-bfbe-0e510fbe5d59\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", Toh 3793) and virtually no one studies the actual Prajñāpāramitā scriptures.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":103,\"end\":181}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7362476a-667e-481f-adb8-17584536d5ce\",\"sort\":1000212,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.27\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2b\",\"label\":\"i.47\",\"sort\":623,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"ed4e9bb4-d4c7-4732-ab3a-0767cb52687a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-106\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":160,\"uuid\":\"7362476a-667e-481f-adb8-17584536d5ce\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"At less than seven hundred words (in English), the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":51}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heart Sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":51,\"end\":62},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"144034ac-70b7-46b2-92c7-8bbfa7848d2f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is one of the genre’s shortest scriptures, a fact that has clearly contributed to its popularity.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":62,\"end\":160}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e9aba872-d0d1-442e-b3cb-37175fb89a3c\",\"sort\":1000216,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.28\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2c\",\"label\":\"i.47\",\"sort\":623,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"ed4e9bb4-d4c7-4732-ab3a-0767cb52687a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-106\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":343,\"uuid\":\"e9aba872-d0d1-442e-b3cb-37175fb89a3c\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In the strictest Tibetan monastic university curricula, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":60}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"18b301c4-849f-41af-bdec-b63d91d6655b\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is studied daily for three to six years. This is a sign of the scripture’s continued relevance today, but is also the reason why few students outside the monastic universities have any real idea about the purpose of studying the Perfection of Wisdom literature so seriously.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":343}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5083d08e-6cee-4b21-83b1-ef909c73035f\",\"sort\":1000222,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.29\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Some of the scripture’s Mahāyāna themes‍—such as how a bodhisattva transcends cyclic existence through engendering a mindset of awakening “free of duality and free from creating duality”‍—will certainly be familiar to many readers; these themes will be summarized chapter by chapter below. But the way that the scripture communicates these subjects may come as a surprise. That is to say, the meaning is often communicated only indirectly through the repartee of the dialogues, the negations of opposites, elusive implications, paradoxical statements, esoteric references to unspecified practices, play on words, and the use of heuristic etymologies.\",\"label\":\"i.49\",\"sort\":649,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"507ffe02-a2f3-49af-939f-0243c071f747\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-111\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":246,\"uuid\":\"5083d08e-6cee-4b21-83b1-ef909c73035f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The wordplay is sometimes difficult to understand, in part because the terms in question were in other early Indic natural languages (Prākrits) rather than the Sanskrit in which the text survives. Some of these are discussed in Schmithausen 1979.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":246}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a59196c6-4a4b-41db-9e90-3aeb38d23e7e\",\"sort\":1000224,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.30\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The few translations of the Eight Thousand into modern languages that have been made are mostly incomplete and not readily available. The first and most complete was a French translation made by Eugène Burnouf between 1837 and 1839 from two of the manuscripts sent from Nepal by B. H. Hodgson. Burnouf lamented that he had been unable to consult any commentarial works, but nevertheless produced a painstaking and remarkable translation, comparing his manuscripts with others of the Twenty-Five Thousand and Hundred Thousand-Line sūtras and with the Tibetan text. Of the Eight Thousand’s thirty-two chapters, he completed the first twenty-seven and most of the twenty-eighth, but apart from a few extracts his translation remained unpublished until recently.\",\"label\":\"i.51\",\"sort\":662,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"bccf9e49-b675-4e45-a8d0-39c69b10961c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-115\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":123,\"uuid\":\"a59196c6-4a4b-41db-9e90-3aeb38d23e7e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Ducœur 2022, particularly on Burnouf’s methodology (pp. 5–12). See also Feer 1899 for Burnouf’s manuscript translation.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":123}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f96106b3-2f7f-40b7-b977-8e5e59b26309\",\"sort\":1000226,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.31\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Given the Eight Thousand’s significance, it is perhaps surprising that this is the first complete English translation. It is based primarily on the Sanskrit text (edited by Mitra in 1888 and reproduced by Vaidya and Wogihara), and only secondarily on the Tibetan version in the Degé Kangyur. We have nevertheless consistently consulted the Tibetan and have recorded in the footnotes all substantial inconsistencies between the Sanskrit and Tibetan, mentioning which of the two readings was translated and why it was followed. Our reasons for relying more on the extant Sanskrit than on the Tibetan stem from considerations of history, meaning, and usefulness.\",\"label\":\"i.54\",\"sort\":680,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"377999e9-0d6e-4e99-994b-747741a7e056\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-120\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":232,\"uuid\":\"f96106b3-2f7f-40b7-b977-8e5e59b26309\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"On Edward Conze’s 1958 English version, see above and, in more detail, below. Mention should also be made here of a recent unpublished English translation of the Chinese translation of an early, abbreviated version of the scripture.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":232}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cf6bc1a7-dbaa-4682-9c6e-eec81128d7e7\",\"sort\":1000228,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.32\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Given the Eight Thousand’s significance, it is perhaps surprising that this is the first complete English translation. It is based primarily on the Sanskrit text (edited by Mitra in 1888 and reproduced by Vaidya and Wogihara), and only secondarily on the Tibetan version in the Degé Kangyur. We have nevertheless consistently consulted the Tibetan and have recorded in the footnotes all substantial inconsistencies between the Sanskrit and Tibetan, mentioning which of the two readings was translated and why it was followed. Our reasons for relying more on the extant Sanskrit than on the Tibetan stem from considerations of history, meaning, and usefulness.\",\"label\":\"i.54\",\"sort\":680,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"377999e9-0d6e-4e99-994b-747741a7e056\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-120\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":52,\"uuid\":\"cf6bc1a7-dbaa-4682-9c6e-eec81128d7e7\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Introduction, “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Extant Texts, Sanskrit\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":41},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c6b38fd4-460d-4922-9b6e-839d0dff942d\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/a0dd4407-602b-45c2-97a3-2fe00089f1a9\",\"entity\":\"a0dd4407-602b-45c2-97a3-2fe00089f1a9\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"introduction\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":41,\"end\":48}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.5\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":51},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5c8480b2-6f9c-4f46-aa5f-ec14fbbbdf17\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/285b92d5-88a0-4943-b64b-01dc0fc554a9\",\"entity\":\"285b92d5-88a0-4943-b64b-01dc0fc554a9\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":51,\"end\":52}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cb24586c-b357-41ca-9ee4-e64c54c0fa86\",\"sort\":1000234,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.33\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Third, we hope that having a translation of the Eight Thousand made primarily from the Sanskrit will make it easier to study the text through English translations of the two Sanskrit commentaries by Haribhadra and Ratnākaraśānti. Without reference to the Sanskrit text, English translations of the Sanskrit commentaries would make little sense, because what they both clarify is the terminological and syntactic ambiguities of the sūtra’s original Sanskrit text, and not any ambiguities introduced by the choices made in the Tibetan translation. The extant Tibetan translation of the Eight Thousand did indeed follow Ratnākaraśānti’s and Haribhadra’s commentaries on many points, but a translation of the Sanskrit still provides a better starting point than the Tibetan for understanding the commentarial tradition.\",\"label\":\"i.57\",\"sort\":696,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"40ee6dd5-f04a-44d8-bb2d-ed5dd1590845\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-125\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":542,\"uuid\":\"cb24586c-b357-41ca-9ee4-e64c54c0fa86\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For instance, the translation of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":33}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pramāṇavantī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":33,\"end\":45},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":33,\"end\":45,\"uuid\":\"28195849-f74b-4691-bf6c-3a4129409066\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":45,\"end\":49}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mtho zhing tshad dang ldan pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":78},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":78,\"uuid\":\"a421f6d1-1a92-4d82-a634-72ff0e9cbd1d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":78,\"end\":80}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"30.8\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":84},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1e694607-09cb-4723-907d-8f6ddb041259\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/5e033895-feb4-49b6-a6d6-8d89c49078b0\",\"entity\":\"5e033895-feb4-49b6-a6d6-8d89c49078b0\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") could only have come from Ratnākaraśānti’s gloss of that word: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":84,\"end\":149}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pramāṇavantī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":161},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":183,\"uuid\":\"d17bb358-9d7d-4166-94b0-23f9b29a43e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":161,\"uuid\":\"e11f50d0-73d0-4933-b615-81bbe2477e58\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ti pṛthūni tuṅgāni ca\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":161,\"end\":183},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":161,\"end\":183,\"uuid\":\"d17bb358-9d7d-4166-94b0-23f9b29a43e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The earlier Tibetan translation of Ratnākaraśānti’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":183,\"end\":237}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Quintessence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":237,\"end\":249},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"dcc00abd-e081-4336-bfcd-3972c5160a25\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" commentary enshrines an earlier translation of this term: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":249,\"end\":308}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tshad dang ldan pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":326},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":363,\"uuid\":\"b314768e-a8e6-4eda-8236-9f92478e24c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":326,\"uuid\":\"f2184e09-eda7-4911-95db-97b67d2db8f7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni yangs shing mtho ba’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":326,\"end\":363},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":326,\"end\":363,\"uuid\":\"b314768e-a8e6-4eda-8236-9f92478e24c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Since Haribhadra is silent on this term, this earlier Tibetan translation was likely based on a Tibetan translator’s own interpretation, rather than a traditional Indian source.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":542}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"081759ca-f904-4d63-abd8-1eb6aa98bceb\",\"sort\":1000250,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.34\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The primary concern in this English translation of the Eight Thousand has been to create a text that can serve as a basis for the traditional study that it deserves, while still being accessible to those who wish, as Paul Harrison puts it, “to read the English as English and make some sense of it.” For Sanskrit prose, the Eight Thousand is stylistically clunky and repetitive at the sentence level. But to facilitate in-depth study with Haribhadra and Ratnākaraśānti’s commentaries, which take the text sentence by sentence, the translation must match the Sanskrit and Tibetan versions sentence by sentence too, even if this has led to a style that could also be considered clunky for English prose.\",\"label\":\"i.58\",\"sort\":703,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"c43691d8-70d1-44af-bcc0-a7e589ece232\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-128\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":280,\"uuid\":\"081759ca-f904-4d63-abd8-1eb6aa98bceb\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Harrison 2006, p. 136. Although this translation agrees with Harrison’s statement here and his general approach in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":123}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vajracchedikā Prajñāpāramitā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":151},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"955836c8-4921-4507-9305-c44d821a80ec\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", there are additional concerns in translating the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":151,\"end\":202}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":202,\"end\":216},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d478833c-bda1-48c1-a98a-8f6aca2e2755\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", because it must coalesce with its long commentarial tradition.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":216,\"end\":280}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b0c42265-694d-42dd-b177-0c8aeee759ea\",\"sort\":1000256,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.35\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“The Sūtra itself was meant to be memorized, the translation is meant to be read. Lengthy repetitions, stereotyped phrases, and the piling up of synonyms were of great assistance to memory, but they irritate and distract the modern reader, and obscure from him the meaning of the text.…The reproduction of the literary conventions and of the stylistic peculiarities of Buddhist Sanskrit diction was not one of my aims. It would be of little, or no, value to scholars, and it bewilders the general reader.”\",\"label\":\"i.62\",\"sort\":721,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"f26d4f33-a351-42ba-8a88-5dc1421173e3\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-133\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":36,\"uuid\":\"b0c42265-694d-42dd-b177-0c8aeee759ea\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conze, 1958, preface; 1975, p. xvii.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":36}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ca612793-6e1d-4e22-b82f-4189ec5618f0\",\"sort\":1000258,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.36\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“A Bodhisattva who does not become afraid when this deep and perfect wisdom is being taught should be recognized as not lacking in perfect wisdom.”\",\"label\":\"i.65\",\"sort\":728,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"13187b5e-a513-41b3-aedf-d5253725bf3c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-137\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"ca612793-6e1d-4e22-b82f-4189ec5618f0\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conze, 1973, p. 93.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8827af62-4386-4aae-9e2f-6817b162c363\",\"sort\":1000260,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.37\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“O Blessed One, when this profound perfection of wisdom is being discussed, taught, and expounded in this way, if a bodhisattva great being’s mindset does not become deflated, depressed, dejected, or sunk in despondency, and his or her mental attitude does not become discouraged, shattered, frightened, terrified, or stricken with terror, then that bodhisattva great being has firm conviction with an altruistic disposition. Hence, one should recognize him or her to be never lacking the perfection of wisdom.”\",\"label\":\"i.67\",\"sort\":733,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"606eff9b-3bfe-47f9-a009-44ab5c0f899d\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-140\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":5,\"uuid\":\"8827af62-4386-4aae-9e2f-6817b162c363\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"1.19\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e59fbec5-9777-4b7a-93fb-3d4eeb3bb4bd\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/3d80563a-5f99-4863-883d-022cd6ff17e7\",\"entity\":\"3d80563a-5f99-4863-883d-022cd6ff17e7\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":5}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"744bbe4e-92d0-4436-896a-ee1cbffaebcd\",\"sort\":1000263,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.38\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2d\",\"label\":\"i.69\",\"sort\":756,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"5f780414-9feb-463a-b26a-4b11d2cdaa05\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-142\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":689,\"uuid\":\"744bbe4e-92d0-4436-896a-ee1cbffaebcd\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Quintessence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":12},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"bdc386c4-c5c0-438b-94f3-859ac0c0da13\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (F.19.a–20.b): \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":28}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom ldan ’das\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":42},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":42,\"uuid\":\"35e60d79-9687-4dc3-94ec-5326ac6102ba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pa la \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":42,\"end\":69},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":42,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de ltar\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":76},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":42,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":76,\"uuid\":\"415c5495-d1db-4fd9-b8f4-ffb8f32ccba6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni dmigs pa dang rnam pa ji ltar bshad pa ltar ro| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":76,\"end\":141},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":76,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zab mo\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":141,\"end\":147},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":76,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":141,\"end\":147,\"uuid\":\"254b7941-b183-42a4-9b80-c382406f661b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni mos par dka’ ba’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":183},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":183,\"end\":215},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":183,\"end\":215,\"uuid\":\"40ba7c35-81c8-47d3-ad5a-198ecb1bf5c9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni drod ’bring dang chen po’i mtshan nyid do| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":275},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bshad pas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":275,\"end\":284},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":275,\"end\":284,\"uuid\":\"0cc2b8ee-9812-4e87-8894-64bed45f61c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni tshig las so| | \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":304},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ston pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":304,\"end\":311},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":304,\"end\":311,\"uuid\":\"1c9a5d1e-437e-48b4-adcc-308a6fcd1701\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni don las so| | |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":311,\"end\":330},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":311,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nye bar ston pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":330,\"end\":345},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":311,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":330,\"end\":345,\"uuid\":\"54138271-a10b-4c92-b53c-38dec4be10de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni don la’o| |de yang shes pa skyes pas zhi gnas skyes par \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":405},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems ma zhum\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":405,\"end\":417},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":405,\"end\":417,\"uuid\":\"33ffae39-5384-4cf8-b526-4f4a86334554\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pas don snga ma bzhin du bshad do| |bsams pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":417,\"end\":486},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":417,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"lhag pa’i bsam\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":486,\"end\":500},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":417,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":486,\"end\":500,\"uuid\":\"0dc068de-5582-493e-aede-592389050ad0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" pa’o| |des na gcig tu nges pa zhes bya ba’i don to| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":500,\"end\":554},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":500,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mos pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":554,\"end\":560},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":500,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":554,\"end\":560,\"uuid\":\"bd7002d4-aa5d-4672-92a4-c9b4ed040ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni zhi gnas dang lhag mthong gi stobs kyis nges par skyes pa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":560,\"end\":626},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":560,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma bral bar\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":626,\"end\":637},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":560,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":626,\"end\":637,\"uuid\":\"ad5b3119-b767-4594-996f-123c6b557f12\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni des gong nas gong du ’gro ba yin no\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":637,\"end\":688},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":637,\"end\":688,\"uuid\":\"de765f9c-0552-4554-a08d-5d3244c27d3b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":688,\"end\":689}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c6b12135-a5f5-4fad-be9f-a42a235121bd\",\"sort\":1000289,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.39\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The words Conze omits in his paraphrase are thus ones that the commentarial tradition holds to be meaningful. Omitting them forecloses the possibility that in English translation Ratnākaraśānti’s commentary could clarify the scripture’s esoteric meaning according to the received tradition. Where Ratnākaraśānti comments on the nine experiences (i.e., “deflated,” “depressed,” and so on, up to “stricken with terror”), Conze saw nothing but a “repetition” or “piling up of synonyms,” and abbreviated them all into the single word “afraid.” Yet according to Ratnākaraśānti these nine words correspond to nine emotional difficulties progressively overcome through the nine stages of meditation practice. Furthermore, Ratnākaraśānti situates the particular degree of tranquility and insight achieved here with a specific stage and level of the bodhisattva’s path.\",\"label\":\"i.70\",\"sort\":771,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"79c7e5cd-18df-4c56-ac43-75a2528bb0b7\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-144\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":9,\"uuid\":\"c6b12135-a5f5-4fad-be9f-a42a235121bd\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.91\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":8},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5d28c702-1d09-49a0-a160-6e1089c7fcf5\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/e1f4d304-29f6-4b49-ba36-27b01ce2fd7e\",\"entity\":\"e1f4d304-29f6-4b49-ba36-27b01ce2fd7e\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":8,\"end\":9}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f317de23-d0fa-47bb-a25c-d78ca4b7e3ed\",\"sort\":1000293,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.40\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"This is just one example of how Conze’s mixture of translation and paraphrase, pioneering though it was, distorts the meaning to be gleaned from certain esoteric passages, misrepresents the scripture’s use of language, and cannot be read alongside Ratnākaraśānti’s commentary. Among many other such instances, his rendering of chapter 5 omits the multiple repetitions of very long refrains, completely altering the nature of the chapter and its performative effect on a reader. Needless to say, general readers, Buddhist practitioners, and scholars who unwittingly rely on Conze’s paraphrases‍—as though they are full translations‍—are being misled.\",\"label\":\"i.71\",\"sort\":776,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"82b72150-4d68-4306-af3a-bca73f652b14\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-146\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1219,\"uuid\":\"f317de23-d0fa-47bb-a25c-d78ca4b7e3ed\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"$2e\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1219}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"aa5e5a0b-23ab-45fa-bfa4-522f4b9aa3cc\",\"sort\":1000297,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.41\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2f\",\"label\":\"i.77\",\"sort\":820,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"2fe6c279-0c82-4fcb-bef3-b90722d3b876\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-154\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":543,\"uuid\":\"aa5e5a0b-23ab-45fa-bfa4-522f4b9aa3cc\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Cherry-picking comments or passages from the commentaries, as we have done in this translation, is certainly not ideal and runs the risk of producing many misconceptions about them. For the time being, however, it must suffice, since it is certainly better than nothing, while the project of translating the commentaries and making them available in full is a daunting one that 84000 may not complete for many years. At the very least, these footnotes may increase readers’ interest in reading the full texts of the commentaries in the future.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":543}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8fd64f49-7f76-4b30-a5a1-aadb361ba06f\",\"sort\":1000299,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.42\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Second, wherever a choice was necessary for brevity or clarity, Ratnākaraśānti’s comments, which have never been translated before, took precedence over Haribhadra’s comments, because an English translation of Haribhadra’s commentary already exists and can be independently consulted. But when Ratnākaraśānti’s comments are extant only in Tibetan translation rather than in Sanskrit, Haribhadra’s commentary is often provided, since the Tibetan translation of Ratnākaraśānti’s commentary systematically excludes information concerning Sanskrit grammar and etymologies that are helpful for understanding his overall comments.\",\"label\":\"i.79\",\"sort\":832,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"341bf0ad-ad81-4ed5-a295-b56931586a70\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-157\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":469,\"uuid\":\"8fd64f49-7f76-4b30-a5a1-aadb361ba06f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Gareth Sparham’s translation of Haribhadra’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":45}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Light\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":45,\"end\":50},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ce8e6459-7ab6-4257-9a4d-b9c17411163c\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" commentary uses Conze’s translation for the root text without quoting it \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":50,\"end\":124}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"in extenso\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":134},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":134,\"uuid\":\"4abe72bc-629e-405b-ba2b-de788418b5e4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Zh-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", making it difficult sometimes to figure out where the relevant passages are. Since Sparham cites the page numbers from Wogihara’s edition within his translation, the page numbers from Wogihara have been provided in the notes to help English readers navigate Sparham’s translation and to help Sanskrit readers read the edition itself.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":134,\"end\":469}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5fcaf946-89f6-4aee-9f77-761b7a1940f4\",\"sort\":1000305,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.43\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Second, wherever a choice was necessary for brevity or clarity, Ratnākaraśānti’s comments, which have never been translated before, took precedence over Haribhadra’s comments, because an English translation of Haribhadra’s commentary already exists and can be independently consulted. But when Ratnākaraśānti’s comments are extant only in Tibetan translation rather than in Sanskrit, Haribhadra’s commentary is often provided, since the Tibetan translation of Ratnākaraśānti’s commentary systematically excludes information concerning Sanskrit grammar and etymologies that are helpful for understanding his overall comments.\",\"label\":\"i.79\",\"sort\":832,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"341bf0ad-ad81-4ed5-a295-b56931586a70\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-157\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":9,\"uuid\":\"5fcaf946-89f6-4aee-9f77-761b7a1940f4\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.23\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":8},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ca8ada14-d504-4961-b001-5cbd3a07f19e\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/8ec68791-a4c8-45d4-a180-7d17772133cd\",\"entity\":\"8ec68791-a4c8-45d4-a180-7d17772133cd\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":8,\"end\":9}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ef3779ff-8ffd-4a4e-844f-d300f38beb42\",\"sort\":1000309,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.44\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Finally, the notes do not include philosophical digressions, because Haribhadra and Ratnākaraśānti‍—who adhere to the two different philosophical positions of Madhyamaka and Yogācāra, respectively‍—are implicitly claiming authority for their own position by showing that various aspects of the scripture should be interpreted from the perspective of their own schools. Their philosophical comments that digress from explaining the scripture have generally not been included, but when their philosophical statements overlap with their exegesis, we have added notes about how the two commentators diverge without explaining or trying to resolve those differences. For instance, notes point out that Haribhadra and Ratnākaraśānti disagree about the main referent of the term prajñāpāramitā in the title and as a topic, which they define in divergent ways. But these notes stop short of fully explaining these interpretive differences and their underlying philosophical reasons.\",\"label\":\"i.81\",\"sort\":848,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"db155e99-9887-41c8-b773-d812f668025b\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-161\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":313,\"uuid\":\"ef3779ff-8ffd-4a4e-844f-d300f38beb42\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The disagreement grew from the fact that the term was used somewhat vaguely within the scripture itself to refer to a path, a goal, a text, and even a mother-like goddess. Hence, the clarification of the term’s meaning became a primary concern for commentators seeking to interpret the rest of its subject matter.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":313}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6588678b-7315-4260-abf2-6cc4b79c3d94\",\"sort\":1000311,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.45\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$30\",\"label\":\"i.82\",\"sort\":854,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a86eae2c-5769-4976-bfd5-39cd5f57bdc1\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-163\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":441,\"uuid\":\"6588678b-7315-4260-abf2-6cc4b79c3d94\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Sanskrit text in the footnotes has been extracted from Wogihara’s edition of Haribhadra’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":94}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Āloka\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":94,\"end\":99},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0c935408-417d-41db-b134-095f7797294b\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and from Greg Seton’s unpublished Sanskrit and Tibetan edition of Ratnākaraśānti’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":99,\"end\":183}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sāratamā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":183,\"end\":191},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c7a5d8b3-85cb-4631-9a23-33231d79d417\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". However, the folio numbers given for the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":191,\"end\":234}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāratmā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":234,\"end\":241},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d326d94d-69ec-4366-b426-54edadc014ec\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" citations‍—whether provided in Sanskrit or (where the Sanskrit is missing) in Tibetan‍—are those of the Tibetan translation of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":241,\"end\":373}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāratmā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":373,\"end\":380},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5ae1d688-c5d2-4fd6-b889-0f37f9ac60aa\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":380,\"end\":382}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"snying po mchog\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":382,\"end\":397},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"698c295a-b009-4dcb-a6d2-d98cb72c0d2c\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") in the Degé Tengyur (Toh 3803, volume 89).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":441}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9188f3a4-d534-46e8-b762-6504c4071b55\",\"sort\":1000323,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.46\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"A sense of how the commentators interpret the term “perfection of wisdom” to fit their respective religious frameworks may be useful, for an understanding not just of the relative benefits of different renderings in English, but also of the essence of these commentators’ soteriological and philosophical debate. In this regard, it may help to sketch out their heuristic analysis (nirvacana) and grammatical unpacking (vyākaraṇa) of the term.\",\"label\":\"i.86\",\"sort\":880,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4ff793f1-9059-45d3-8191-3489817feccf\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-170\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":293,\"uuid\":\"9188f3a4-d534-46e8-b762-6504c4071b55\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The notion that all heuristic analysis (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":40}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirvacana\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":40,\"end\":49},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":40,\"end\":49,\"uuid\":\"aec6a2b6-8b0b-4f28-814a-95b9b771a083\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") involves merely fanciful, folk etymology is a misconception. In fact, heuristic analysis conveys important information about usage that needs to be considered when translating certain terms, especially those whose main referents are disputed.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":293}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5287dc44-94d8-4325-9d49-0fda7251563b\",\"sort\":1000327,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.47\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$31\",\"label\":\"i.87\",\"sort\":887,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4606e2e8-3305-4ae6-b9d9-b1524fd526b6\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-172\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":482,\"uuid\":\"5287dc44-94d8-4325-9d49-0fda7251563b\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In brief, Haribhadra breaks down the grammatical etymology of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":62}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pāramitā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":62,\"end\":70},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":62,\"end\":70,\"uuid\":\"86fa8156-932e-44c6-9887-e1f8107f3916\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":70,\"end\":74}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pāram\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":79},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":79,\"uuid\":\"748ba5ca-e842-4680-8e5a-cb02e4ff4720\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"+\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":80}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"iḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":82},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":82,\"uuid\":\"07f4b6fb-61fe-4e6e-aaa7-11e6bc96867c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"+\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":83}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":85},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":85,\"uuid\":\"9776433b-c240-4e3f-b146-a0c5cb653f1a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—i.e., the state of one who goes to or reaches the other shore‍—where he explains the compound as consisting in a secondary (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":85,\"end\":211}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kṛt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":214},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":214,\"uuid\":\"74d91df5-c9af-4d33-a8b6-7feb4414c44a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") suffix -\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":214,\"end\":224}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"iḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":226},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":226,\"uuid\":\"f91ac57f-fcc2-4541-9ce9-55158f35472f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (derived from the verbal root √\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":258}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":258,\"end\":259},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":258,\"end\":259,\"uuid\":\"edd1d684-6b3f-4014-98d4-26332fe10bc6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") in the sense of “he goes” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":288}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"eti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":291},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":291,\"uuid\":\"2ddcc0b8-cc20-463e-8caa-43df404bafcb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") to “the other shore” in the accusative case, based on a known exception to the rule that normally dictates all such declined endings be removed when forming a compound. Cf. Wogihara, p\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":291,\"end\":477}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". 23.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":477,\"end\":482},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":477,\"end\":482,\"uuid\":\"782503f0-537f-482a-a3f7-d91e4b72e4f1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"26740329-dea4-408d-ae1c-7c2a16f70f47\",\"sort\":1000346,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.48\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$32\",\"label\":\"i.87\",\"sort\":887,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4606e2e8-3305-4ae6-b9d9-b1524fd526b6\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-172\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":233,\"uuid\":\"26740329-dea4-408d-ae1c-7c2a16f70f47\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The idea here is that naming a seed “apple” (i.e., apple seed)‍—even though no apple is perceived in the seed‍—is a figurative usage of the word “apple” that is based on the fact that a particular seed produces the fruit of an apple.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":233}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3113759b-7880-416f-833d-8f9905088f01\",\"sort\":1000348,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.49\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$33\",\"label\":\"i.87\",\"sort\":887,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4606e2e8-3305-4ae6-b9d9-b1524fd526b6\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-172\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":495,\"uuid\":\"3113759b-7880-416f-833d-8f9905088f01\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It should be noted that, although Haribhadra designates a buddha’s nondual knowledge as the true body of knowing (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":114}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"jñānadharmakāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":129},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":129,\"uuid\":\"bd5f49d8-d96c-49a4-92ca-0fcb773c74e3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), this body, for him, is only nominally called an “ultimate reality” in that it perceives the ultimate reality (i.e., the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":129,\"end\":252}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"svabhāvikakāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":252,\"end\":266},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":252,\"end\":266,\"uuid\":\"29f7745f-dbc4-475b-9010-b4e78ed695f8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). In actuality, it still falls within “conventional reality” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":266,\"end\":329}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"samvṛtisatya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":329,\"end\":341},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":329,\"end\":341,\"uuid\":\"7aacbdda-1b64-499e-9776-d3155e2bf7ac\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), because of its connection to appearances through the enjoyment and creation bodies (i.e. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":341,\"end\":433}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"saṃbhogakāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":445},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":445,\"uuid\":\"d9de9058-c92a-4dbd-9632-62b476f5a053\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":445,\"end\":450}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirmāṇakāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":450,\"end\":461},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":450,\"end\":461,\"uuid\":\"63c64a35-2f19-4358-b350-a0701c8aa238\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Cf. Makransky 1998, pp. 235–37.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":461,\"end\":495}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0a8f5986-79c3-4e62-b03c-9e2d912b30c8\",\"sort\":1000360,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.50\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$34\",\"label\":\"i.88\",\"sort\":899,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"396c2b26-8dfb-4c77-8c1a-f8769b713446\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-176\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":836,\"uuid\":\"0a8f5986-79c3-4e62-b03c-9e2d912b30c8\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Like Haribhadra, Ratnākaraśānti clearly suggests that the compound term be split as the “going to + wisdom’s other shore” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":123}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñāpāram\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":134},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":134,\"uuid\":\"fdfb1902-3281-46d6-bc57-e31fac6c3358\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"+\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":134,\"end\":135}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"itā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":135,\"end\":138},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":135,\"end\":138,\"uuid\":\"b91b8980-5939-47fd-814f-f7016ac21210\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), where the other shore itself \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":138,\"end\":170}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"consists in\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":170,\"end\":181},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":170,\"end\":181,\"uuid\":\"35b1aaf9-85b4-4ba9-a8ea-e54b5042937a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" wisdom. However, since Ratnākaraśānti’s Sanskrit comments exist only in a relatively imprecise Tibetan translation, it is not entirely clear whether he means that the final \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":181,\"end\":355}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"itā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":355,\"end\":358},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":355,\"end\":358,\"uuid\":\"0cb2e829-3ce9-4df6-813a-a795a17839b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" be interpreted grammatically as (a) a form of the Sanskrit verb √\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":358,\"end\":424}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":424,\"end\":425},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":424,\"end\":425,\"uuid\":\"27f0d395-ae95-450e-99a5-b0a40a4ffd85\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" combined with the abstract suffix \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":425,\"end\":460}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"-tā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":460,\"end\":463},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":460,\"end\":463,\"uuid\":\"3d8c83ed-649c-4519-a395-6f9cb70505f0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (similar to Hari but with different effect) to mean “the state of going” or (b) a feminine form of the past participle meaning “gone” or “set out for” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":463,\"end\":616}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"itā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":616,\"end\":619},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":616,\"end\":619,\"uuid\":\"d3f078f8-e5ba-4df2-a500-79465316da2e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Either way, Ratnākaraśānti’s additional remarks show that he interprets the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":619,\"end\":698}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"itā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":698,\"end\":701},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":698,\"end\":701,\"uuid\":\"d31191c6-4ed7-40a8-8669-6abb2c48de84\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as “the state of going to” or “the state leading to”‍—i.e., the path‍—rather than “the state once one has reached” it, i.e., the goal.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":701,\"end\":836}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"beb4e600-ec75-433b-95ea-8aa7a2d64395\",\"sort\":1000378,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.51\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$35\",\"label\":\"i.88\",\"sort\":899,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"396c2b26-8dfb-4c77-8c1a-f8769b713446\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-176\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":196,\"uuid\":\"beb4e600-ec75-433b-95ea-8aa7a2d64395\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The idea behind naming the fruit (or result) after the seed (or cause) is like saying, after eating an omelet with many ingredients, that one has had “eggs” (a cause of that omelet) for breakfast.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":196}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"81a6f613-1221-408c-bb41-1ded241d4490\",\"sort\":1000380,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.52\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"With regard to the immanence of the perfection of wisdom, it is telling that the Eight Thousand recommends bodhisattvas to “go about life in this perfection of wisdom.” Although some alternate translations of the Sanskrit verb √car take it to suggest that bodhisattvas should “practice this perfection of wisdom,” the English verb “to practice”‍—whether taken in the sense of practicing the piano or practicing medicine‍—wrongly implies that some mental effort or special focus or activity is always required to exercise the perfection of wisdom.\",\"label\":\"i.90\",\"sort\":924,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a0240790-17e6-4bd0-8690-35911b7e1f7a\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-182\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":250,\"uuid\":\"81a6f613-1221-408c-bb41-1ded241d4490\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conze’s translation “they should course in perfect wisdom” gives the opposite impression from the verb (√\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"car\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":108},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":108,\"uuid\":\"4ae66eab-315a-429c-a7d9-43162af38360\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" + locative), as if bodhisattvas must undertake some special mystical activity called “coursing” that no ordinary being understands how to do.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":250}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cdc0e104-6abc-4b1e-b68d-e027a8dc9509\",\"sort\":1000384,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.53\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In fact, that bodhisattvas should “go about life” means that they should do whatever they do in life (i.e., sit, walk, eat, sleep, and so on) “in this perfection of wisdom.”\",\"label\":\"i.91\",\"sort\":933,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"f64a7b45-84bc-45a1-956c-5711b33a7425\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-184\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":217,\"uuid\":\"cdc0e104-6abc-4b1e-b68d-e027a8dc9509\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"That is not to say, of course, that the actions bodhisattvas choose to do are entirely uninfluenced by their commitment to the perfection of wisdom. See, for example, the comment by Ratnākaraśānti mentioned in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":210}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.1194\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":210,\"end\":216},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"896ad0d2-853a-409b-a3e4-0e87ba94aceb\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/9851e49a-f87b-4476-bba9-d17e46de84aa\",\"entity\":\"9851e49a-f87b-4476-bba9-d17e46de84aa\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":216,\"end\":217}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1cd16664-7e18-4b19-91a6-c641d0fdeb7c\",\"sort\":1000388,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.54\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$36\",\"label\":\"i.92\",\"sort\":941,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"3096ba3b-a647-489c-9b20-8673274fb8aa\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-187\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":700,\"uuid\":\"1cd16664-7e18-4b19-91a6-c641d0fdeb7c\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Although Conze and others translate \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":36}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"citta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":41},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":41,\"uuid\":\"e0f5adc1-6567-47c3-9b91-6eae0045ad28\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", respectively, as “thought” or as “mind,” “heart,” and so on, these terms exclude either the cognitive or affective aspect of the word, and are often forced to fit unfamiliar contexts that make no sense except in Buddhist-English jargon. For instance, can one “give rise” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":41,\"end\":315}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"utpāda\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":315,\"end\":321},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":315,\"end\":321,\"uuid\":\"dcfb751d-1769-4fd2-ac6a-34e064c516b5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":321,\"end\":323}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bskyed\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":329},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":329,\"uuid\":\"9472cdb3-ef23-4c48-b4f2-7030d0e291aa\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") to a mind or heart, except in some metaphorical sense? Yet a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":329,\"end\":392}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":392,\"end\":399},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"27db2ed3-7414-4fe4-b08e-02810500cd61\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", by its nature, is something that can arise, be given rise to, and be developed and expanded. One need only look at how French translates \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":538}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"citta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":538,\"end\":543},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":538,\"end\":543,\"uuid\":\"7fc3415f-6a06-497e-bc5c-364ce8a2c57f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":543,\"end\":547}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"esprit\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":547,\"end\":553},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":547,\"end\":553,\"uuid\":\"5a18f8f6-3037-4eb7-a580-5df5ae9e2fe4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Zh-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and German as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":553,\"end\":568}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"geist\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":568,\"end\":573},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":568,\"end\":573,\"uuid\":\"9246564b-5a53-4401-b720-fea99df66b52\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Zh-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to see how much less our words “mind” or “heart” are able to account for both the cognitive and affective aspects of the term.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":573,\"end\":700}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"df82cc93-1bec-448a-8051-e0f78d0639fc\",\"sort\":1000404,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.55\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$37\",\"label\":\"i.92\",\"sort\":941,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"3096ba3b-a647-489c-9b20-8673274fb8aa\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-187\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":345,\"uuid\":\"df82cc93-1bec-448a-8051-e0f78d0639fc\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The scripture also uses the term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":34}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":34,\"end\":41},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"8194bc46-2c2a-4956-bedf-d724ad6033ab\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":41,\"end\":44}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"citta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":49},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":49,\"uuid\":\"6e3f0f84-5b04-4e77-ae6d-b3e832ab042f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") in the positive sense as a synonym of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":89}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":89,\"end\":113},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"2e001dc9-0b16-4ed0-a17a-2e93f4c9ab97\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":115}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"samādhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":115,\"end\":122},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":115,\"end\":122,\"uuid\":\"f632839b-b527-4671-839e-15d9e8d4bce6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). This usage was common especially in the context of the three trainings, which in early scriptures were listed as discipline, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":122,\"end\":250}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":250,\"end\":257},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"4ade8942-e276-413e-9b94-4a7669bc4a1d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and wisdom instead of the more usual discipline, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":257,\"end\":308}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":332},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"1a31ec83-4093-401b-bfa1-34840428342e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and wisdom.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":332,\"end\":345}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"04d55738-cc45-48df-91f7-6d3a5caf8e7b\",\"sort\":1000418,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.56\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Whether or not the translation of key terms such as “mindset” actually captures the full cognitive and affective implications of the Sanskrit, an effort has been made in this translation to use terminology amenable to both Haribhadra’s and Ratnākaraśānti’s interpretations, as well as to the traditions of Nāgārjuna and Asaṅga on which they respectively rely. The translation also attempts to dovetail more closely with the general spirit of the traditional definitions and the use of clever heuristic etymologies. For instance, one might heuristically answer the question “What is a mindset of awakening?” as follows: At the level of aspiration, the “mindset of awakening” is a mind set on awakening, i.e., the wish to attain complete awakening for the sake of all beings. At the level of engagement, the “mindset of awakening” is the mindset while awakening through the six perfections. At the ultimate level, the “mindset of awakening” is nondual wisdom inseparable from compassion.\",\"label\":\"i.98\",\"sort\":1097,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a90e3f72-ac16-4525-b6c3-b08c0347e8cb\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-195\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":608,\"uuid\":\"04d55738-cc45-48df-91f7-6d3a5caf8e7b\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It is worth keeping in mind that Indian scholars, such as Haribhadra, Ratnākara, Prajñākaramati, Abhayākaragupta, and others, agree about the general usages of the term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":170}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":170,\"end\":190},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"2393476d-3bae-4940-853e-4dd4aec644c9\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":190,\"end\":193}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhicitta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":193,\"end\":203},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":193,\"end\":203,\"uuid\":\"8a236d21-01ea-493a-ac84-f35fa1e3ea3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). But they disagree about what each usage’s precise referent is and whether it is a type of primary consciousness or a secondary mental state. For more on these different interpretations, see, for example, Padmakara Translation Group 2007, pp. 53–55. For more about the Sanskrit term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":203,\"end\":488}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"citta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":488,\"end\":493},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":488,\"end\":493,\"uuid\":\"f7c9b729-703b-4708-a01e-9a194df84913\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", cf. Skorupski 2009, p. 165, n45, n59. For a taxonomy of various usages of the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":493,\"end\":578}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhicitta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":578,\"end\":588},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":578,\"end\":588,\"uuid\":\"1cd41132-697e-49a7-baaf-1d1341fe658a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", see Wangchuk 2007.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":588,\"end\":608}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a29a7dda-d022-412c-a21b-53cf7c5f4e27\",\"sort\":1000428,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.57\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$38\",\"label\":\"i.100\",\"sort\":1124,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"fcef58e6-39be-4d30-963b-eec5c643f110\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-199\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1259,\"uuid\":\"a29a7dda-d022-412c-a21b-53cf7c5f4e27\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This problem is of far less prominence in the translation of other Prajñāpāramitā scriptures. The three Sanskrit terms used in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":131}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":131,\"end\":139},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0255f4db-e383-485f-810b-c74fb852d743\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to distinguish the three kinds of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":139,\"end\":174}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":174,\"end\":184},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":174,\"end\":184,\"uuid\":\"3794f2c0-91a8-4668-9eb6-93c6f425b232\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" outlined here are hardly found at all in the text of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":184,\"end\":242}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":242,\"end\":256},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9a58c20e-bfa2-48cc-8244-46bba33b5bba\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":256,\"end\":259}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Knowing of all the aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":285},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"724b610b-e35d-4730-a9c1-ec17d130cf6b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":285,\"end\":288}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvākārajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":302},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":302,\"uuid\":\"10b7b637-063d-4963-ad12-76be768dea36\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") occurs only once apart from in the heading of the first chapter (see \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":302,\"end\":373}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.65\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":373,\"end\":377},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2bacb2b3-a2ad-41fc-b90f-8dc45a488b03\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/6268941f-41a7-4f3c-9b6a-b80740f30837\",\"entity\":\"6268941f-41a7-4f3c-9b6a-b80740f30837\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). “Knowing of the paths” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":404}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mārgajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":404,\"end\":414},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":404,\"end\":414,\"uuid\":\"8eacc0d6-4195-44b8-b02a-379893497a39\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") is not found at all. By contrast, in the long Prajñāpāramitā sūtras (the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":414,\"end\":489}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hundred Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":489,\"end\":505},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f13b5c8d-129a-4365-9180-c9da54d9790f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":505,\"end\":507}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Twenty-Five Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":507,\"end\":527},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f01cb2e9-7d9a-4c0a-93be-3119a6e59543\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":527,\"end\":533}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eighteen Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":533,\"end\":550},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"41ca02c0-dbd2-4678-b093-d845e19e31d4\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") the differentiation into three is made much clearer by the very frequent use of distinct terms for them in the source texts. See the introduction to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":550,\"end\":701}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Perfection of Wisdom in Twenty-Five Thousand Lines\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":701,\"end\":755},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fb93b5a6-2530-4725-8e03-90e4e657ecdc\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":755,\"end\":757}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i.95\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":757,\"end\":761},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"29c0d996-2733-41d5-a70d-9eed7aa634e5\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/dc8a4832-f791-44ef-9fd3-3c95026149c0\",\"entity\":\"dc8a4832-f791-44ef-9fd3-3c95026149c0\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"subtype\":\"introduction\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In the translation of that text (and of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":761,\"end\":807}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hundred Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":807,\"end\":823},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b38bcc69-4841-440f-8b6e-2e3deb45e8d8\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":823,\"end\":835}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":835,\"end\":845},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":835,\"end\":845,\"uuid\":\"ccd191df-41b4-47fe-ad1c-9987bba1959e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":845,\"end\":847}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"thams cad shes pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":847,\"end\":864},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":847,\"end\":864,\"uuid\":\"208f7420-930f-4455-bc38-bb84e3001509\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") by itself has been rendered “knowledge of all the dharmas” whenever (as is mostly the case) it denotes what is here‍—in the translation of the present text‍—termed the “complete knowing” of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":864,\"end\":1060}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Disciple\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1060,\"end\":1068},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"9a525dc9-bb41-486a-b1a7-53ee264d3184\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Vehicle. The differentiation into three terms, in the longer sūtras, of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1145}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1145,\"end\":1159},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ab0a6620-72d7-4986-93ff-f78843482b8e\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s single term is sometimes taken as one example of evidence for the longer sūtra’s later evolution.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1159,\"end\":1259}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a240bd9b-44e3-48e0-b036-c1d39a4fb292\",\"sort\":1000464,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.58\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Second, although some Buddhist texts seem to describe the buddha’s knowing all the aspects of everything as something like a divine omniscience, many Mahāyāna Buddhist scholars sought to qualify this suggestion in different ways, such as saying that a buddha knows everything by knowing their single nature. Here, too, one might ask what kind of knowing of the nature is entailed? Certainly, it is not merely intellectually knowing the nature of everything, but rather the uninterrupted knowing of that nature and all its possible manifestations. Granted, such knowing enables a buddha to “know” infinite things but not necessarily in an intentional way, as terms like “all-knowing” might imply.\",\"label\":\"i.101\",\"sort\":1151,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"21942ec6-6635-4873-809b-51e5927bf321\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-201\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":98,\"uuid\":\"a240bd9b-44e3-48e0-b036-c1d39a4fb292\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For a discussion of some of the different Buddhist explanations of this term, see McClintock 2010.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":98}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"94344965-8f74-4a9b-bad9-7d5f65628cf0\",\"sort\":1000466,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.59\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$39\",\"label\":\"i.104\",\"sort\":1174,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"6fcd0ee7-e734-4be1-b46c-81a1ab2ed0ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-206\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":143,\"uuid\":\"94344965-8f74-4a9b-bad9-7d5f65628cf0\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Note, however, that “thing” has also been used in some passages to render the Tibetan \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":86}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dngos po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":94},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":94,\"uuid\":\"682cd30f-3a31-4d86-b24c-3288ed6d5f7e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", Sanskrit \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":94,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"vastu\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":110},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":110,\"uuid\":\"2659bc53-40b0-4c78-ae4e-4dcd6ef732a1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". See \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":110,\"end\":116}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.391\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":121},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"11f37c93-6e1c-4a9a-9798-f044e947b2c2\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/0707f95e-a4f4-44d2-8ee8-7e4e84c2e105\",\"entity\":\"0707f95e-a4f4-44d2-8ee8-7e4e84c2e105\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the end of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":121,\"end\":137}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.472\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":137,\"end\":142},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b87eb32c-ee07-4f56-809e-b3c4670fb157\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/27250556-a415-467d-a573-ebe86ab422f7\",\"entity\":\"27250556-a415-467d-a573-ebe86ab422f7\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":142,\"end\":143}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5aca95b2-fad0-4090-9ce8-d7f54479d46f\",\"sort\":1000476,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.60\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3a\",\"label\":\"i.108\",\"sort\":1269,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"a41bc113-4bff-411e-a14d-5d06af99d38b\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-211\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":567,\"uuid\":\"5aca95b2-fad0-4090-9ce8-d7f54479d46f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Most Tibetans followed Haribhadra, so they translated the negation here as meaning “without” or “lacking” any \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":110}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":110,\"end\":117},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"c1127977-3a67-4e69-a1d4-06e6ec88d8c5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":117,\"end\":119}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems med pa/ sems ma chis pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":147},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":147,\"uuid\":\"bf8083a9-8e35-4fa2-9b8a-a7ea6f39abae\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), i.e., as a nonimplicative negation (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":186}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"med dgag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":194},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":194,\"uuid\":\"d655e2f9-c40e-4ab6-ad62-a6980372cc15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). But some Tibetans, inspired by Ratnākara perhaps, translated it as a “nonmindset” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":194,\"end\":280}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems ma yin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":280,\"end\":294},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":280,\"end\":294,\"uuid\":\"eb776de8-f133-477b-967a-bee449b0c4b0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\")‍—i.e., something that is “not” a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":294,\"end\":329}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":329,\"end\":336},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"de493f75-ce12-4f1e-b814-ddaa0e57f8a7\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—suggesting an exclusion or implicative negation (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":336,\"end\":387}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma yin dgag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":387,\"end\":398},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":387,\"end\":398,\"uuid\":\"559a39ab-bdd0-4d2c-8e07-c604fb83b9d5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). For an example see F.45.a.4 in the Tibetan translation of Ārya Vimuktisena’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":398,\"end\":478}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vṛtti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":478,\"end\":483},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c8d2b896-285a-4e8b-a91b-6e8e158fd55c\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Toh 3787), where Ngok Lotsāwa translates \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":483,\"end\":526}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"acittam\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":526,\"end\":533},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":526,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"75b09e1d-fe2a-4b0f-9fce-a70a8ad981ec\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as “not a mind” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":533,\"end\":551}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems ma yin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":551,\"end\":565},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":551,\"end\":565,\"uuid\":\"15f055a4-89e6-4826-9934-026b5201a633\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\").\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":565,\"end\":567}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5149435c-5cc5-4191-ba04-8439754c6bd2\",\"sort\":1000496,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.61\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"VIII. The fruit of the buddha’s body of qualities and awakened activity (dharmakāya, ’bras bu chos sku) The “buddha’s body of qualities” refers to the state of a buddha who has all the undefiled qualities that result from cultivating the four practices (IV–VII). This is the final realization of the three objective goals and is covered from halfway through chapter 29 through chapter 30 of the Eight Thousand. Its four subtopics include the four aspects of the buddha’s body: (i) the natural body, (ii) the wisdom truth body, (iii) the enjoyment body, and (iv) the emanation body.\",\"label\":\"i.120\",\"sort\":1551,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"2d9788df-7ca7-4821-9399-52d8889de9a7\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-241\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":290,\"uuid\":\"5149435c-5cc5-4191-ba04-8439754c6bd2\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"These four bodies are based on Haribhadra’s explanation, which is more common in Tibetan lists of the seventy topics. Ratnākaraśānti divides these four topics differently, namely (1) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":183}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"natural body\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":183,\"end\":195},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0c06ba3e-efda-4685-b775-759637a9db8e\",\"uuid\":\"ce4dcfcc-e622-47d2-98de-a14ffc19fa98\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (2) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":195,\"end\":201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"enjoyment body\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":215},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9f72a614-4918-4c15-b189-26405b2aac3a\",\"uuid\":\"76bd84d4-d78a-4a71-a5a7-792c11d51c5c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (3) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":221}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emanation body\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":221,\"end\":235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"5702e490-14a4-44c4-ae3d-50a5e1bd75bd\",\"uuid\":\"75346460-4e41-4219-837e-a17ad1095831\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and (4) a buddha’s body of qualities and his activity.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":290}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"24b52f99-8559-4de5-bff8-58469ca42a22\",\"sort\":1000504,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.62\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Generally speaking, one can understand the first half of the Eight Thousand, namely, chapters 1–16, to involve the bodhisattva from the initial stage of his or her mindset of awakening up to realization of the actual nature (tathatā) where the stage beyond regressing is attained. The second half, chapters 17–32, concerns similar topics but for a bodhisattva on the stage beyond regressing up to the final awakening as a tathāgata. In addition to the main content of each chapter, the summary will highlight the notable structural elements and stylistic differences, often centered around a play on words or a negation in the form xy is not y that expresses the seeming paradox of nonduality.\",\"label\":\"i.123\",\"sort\":1585,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"f40c8abd-9bfd-4360-818f-64040d1b4f31\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-249\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":623,\"uuid\":\"24b52f99-8559-4de5-bff8-58469ca42a22\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In his dissertation, Shì Hùifēng explains the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":60},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"52d76358-dc28-4259-aed2-3776ff2a5321\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to have the chiastic rhetorical structure “XY is ~Y” or “XY is not Y.” Shì’s conclusions are well considered and persuasive, but difficult to explain here and not directly relevant to summarizing the content. For ease, a simple rule of thumb for readers might be to regard the internal structure of each different chapter as involving a different rhetorical device, often with humorous undertones, such as its own setup, punchline, and so on, aimed at evoking various insight responses in the readers, rather than laughter, amusement, groans, or other responses.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":623}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"68296564-3f60-4021-af97-a45f9f512112\",\"sort\":1000508,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.63\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3b\",\"label\":\"i.126\",\"sort\":1777,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"b60af8e5-8be1-4c46-9c17-aea9dadc81a8\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-270\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":186,\"uuid\":\"68296564-3f60-4021-af97-a45f9f512112\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here and in what follows, the “Perfection of Wisdom” (capitalized) refers to the scripture (or scriptures), while the “perfection of wisdom” (lower case) refers to the practice or state.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":186}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"addcf1e1-3aa5-4b9b-9461-0d8db8ce3835\",\"sort\":1000510,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.64\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Chapter 1: Going About Life in the Knowing of All Aspects\",\"label\":\"1.\",\"sort\":10006,\"type\":\"translationHeader\",\"uuid\":\"473a1d26-1504-4ded-b63b-a021ae517be2\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-chapter-1\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":887,\"uuid\":\"addcf1e1-3aa5-4b9b-9461-0d8db8ce3835\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This first chapter of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":26}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":26,\"end\":40},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e579cd19-3666-4240-9e77-9b911d65b488\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" corresponds in content to Chapters 1–13 of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":40,\"end\":88}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Twenty-Five Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":108},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"82c6e079-6283-4c8f-9f35-62c2fb1613d0\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":113}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hundred Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":129},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a7ec66b6-f04f-4553-9b84-7734738ff5dd\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and to Chapters 1–21 of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":129,\"end\":159}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eighteen Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":159,\"end\":176},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c9e5ecd5-5d6e-4310-808f-70fa80a7e9d0\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Some of the points within it that correspond to where new chapters begin in the long sūtras are marked in footnotes below. However, this first chapter is one of the two sections of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":176,\"end\":363}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":377},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"66480ec4-9981-4cc2-a6e7-e8916998823b\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that, compared to the long sūtras, are the most different in length and content‍—not just because of a different level of repetitive phrasing, but also because of differences in the content and order of the discussions. The other such section is Chapter 29 and the last parts of Chapter 28 (see \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":673}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.1296\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":673,\"end\":679},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"bd2fad99-247b-4bca-ab6b-3167f3ad4d81\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/cd814b9e-a04f-4c91-8644-3a67a84c6f6b\",\"entity\":\"cd814b9e-a04f-4c91-8644-3a67a84c6f6b\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":679,\"end\":684}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.1299\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":684,\"end\":690},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"13de0f90-a863-435e-b347-d8b706713ebe\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/c1dc3486-4a23-4b60-8fe5-dc70b48bf5bc\",\"entity\":\"c1dc3486-4a23-4b60-8fe5-dc70b48bf5bc\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), i.e. the end of the scripture apart from the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":738}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sadāprarudita\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":738,\"end\":751},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c7fa2a32-c71f-43ed-8ce3-d769f5bfd939\",\"uuid\":\"d6663ba6-eab5-4a83-a9c2-7d37a55711b3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" narrative and the entrusting. Put succinctly, it is at the beginning and end that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":751,\"end\":838}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":838,\"end\":852},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3b26e9f9-429c-49c8-9c5d-860666daf952\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the longer sūtras differ most.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":852,\"end\":887}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6268941f-41a7-4f3c-9b6a-b80740f30837\",\"sort\":1000530,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.65\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Chapter 1: Going About Life in the Knowing of All Aspects\",\"label\":\"1.\",\"sort\":10006,\"type\":\"translationHeader\",\"uuid\":\"473a1d26-1504-4ded-b63b-a021ae517be2\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-chapter-1\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":2834,\"uuid\":\"6268941f-41a7-4f3c-9b6a-b80740f30837\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Despite this chapter having the term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":38}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":38,\"end\":60},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"3f48b8bb-ae75-4a83-9f43-1295da1b7be2\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” in its title, only the term “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":95}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"state of complete knowing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":95,\"end\":120},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f1f21402-d1eb-4ca2-b32a-df9dbdf949a5\",\"uuid\":\"b04329ea-901b-49c6-b80c-269760044a01\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":120,\"end\":123}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":133},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":133,\"uuid\":\"df3e2244-ea8c-4bbf-a500-afa6a59a17af\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") or its counterpart term “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":133,\"end\":164}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of someone who has complete knowing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":164,\"end\":207},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"984c7a94-e1eb-45a9-8a0d-4a56573a3727\",\"uuid\":\"0ba41a03-9beb-4f02-9838-6b2df793525c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":207,\"end\":210}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvajñajñāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":210,\"end\":223},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":210,\"end\":223,\"uuid\":\"16423926-eae6-433f-8011-346b6b01b910\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") appear in the body of the chapter. Indeed, the title term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":223,\"end\":284}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":306},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"797e3464-c0b2-4a9c-a403-aa46b7784af8\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” is not to be found either in this chapter or in the main part of the scripture. It appears to have been borrowed from the title of the first chapter of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":306,\"end\":464}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":464,\"end\":472},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0fa89f28-d314-4a15-909f-b4ef7e835b4e\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—which is used in the commentaries by Haribhadra (Hari) and Ratnākaraśānti (Ratnākara or RK) as an outline for explaining this entire scripture from the perspective of their divergent philosophical positions of, respectively, Mādhyamika and Yogācāra. See also the introduction \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":472,\"end\":750}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“State of Complete Knowing”\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":750,\"end\":777},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8ecb7cc5-6ede-481a-abb4-f67478db1620\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/3943853c-cbcc-4778-9cac-78bc7f4dc03c\",\"entity\":\"3943853c-cbcc-4778-9cac-78bc7f4dc03c\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"introductionHeader\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":777,\"end\":782}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.112\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":782,\"end\":787},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"55023dab-a3e2-4a8d-94d2-855a940ebb6a\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/84fcf4b5-f95f-421f-8f45-e95189da9d3c\",\"entity\":\"84fcf4b5-f95f-421f-8f45-e95189da9d3c\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In order to show how the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":787,\"end\":814}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":814,\"end\":828},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"19d03fd5-4ef8-4bb1-ae5a-dd5f8b444672\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s single term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":828,\"end\":844}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"state of complete knowing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":844,\"end\":869},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f1f21402-d1eb-4ca2-b32a-df9dbdf949a5\",\"uuid\":\"4f4dcc7a-da95-44a0-af17-1f2e561f4006\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":869,\"end\":872}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":872,\"end\":882},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":872,\"end\":882,\"uuid\":\"d84ee030-c6e6-4c47-8092-89238c11d86e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") corresponds, in different parts of the scripture, to only one of the three types of complete knowing to be realized according to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":882,\"end\":1017}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1017,\"end\":1025},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c84766d4-43a7-4dc4-b1d0-3ffe53244e1f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—namely the “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1025,\"end\":1039}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1039,\"end\":1061},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"ebf892e4-b973-448d-9628-937e7889265f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1061,\"end\":1064}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvākārajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1064,\"end\":1078},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1064,\"end\":1078,\"uuid\":\"e9c1d8a2-811d-463b-976c-a6b9c52305e7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), the “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1078,\"end\":1086}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all the paths\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1086,\"end\":1110},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e8dd1ed0-b8ec-4610-a817-2f3c9cb4fd02\",\"uuid\":\"36c53956-0bf5-41a4-93b7-ca522ce3fd46\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1110,\"end\":1113}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mārgajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1113,\"end\":1123},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1113,\"end\":1123,\"uuid\":\"21385107-9fb1-4d75-abd6-bc7fc21b9a52\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), and the “complete knowing (i.e., of the constituents)” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1123,\"end\":1182}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvajñatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1182,\"end\":1192},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1182,\"end\":1192,\"uuid\":\"513a32b5-a264-4cf9-b587-23a8f135bef8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\")‍—their comments variously associate the term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1192,\"end\":1240}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"state of complete knowing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1240,\"end\":1265},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f1f21402-d1eb-4ca2-b32a-df9dbdf949a5\",\"uuid\":\"7ab5f12a-4196-4c2f-aff6-58cfec35e906\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” with the fruition of either a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1265,\"end\":1297}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciple\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1297,\"end\":1305},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"63871d2d-1b6e-4a9a-8e1d-6495de426d62\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1305,\"end\":1309}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy one\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1309,\"end\":1319},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"3b719e92-d3e3-472c-813e-d486818ca23a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1319,\"end\":1323}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"solitary realizer\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1323,\"end\":1340},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91eb4850-6549-4ee5-ae57-ec33c68112f1\",\"uuid\":\"db6a42da-bcf6-4412-bc0e-51266525f6e5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", a bodhisattva, or a buddha, as explained in the respective schools. Among these three terms, Hari and Ratnākara agree that “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1340,\"end\":1470}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1470,\"end\":1492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"444c83e9-9f06-4c23-a67a-7e54bfef7ca3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” refers exclusively to a buddha’s knowing of everything, including both the nature of things and their diverse manifestations. But they disagree about the fundamental relationship between the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1492,\"end\":1685}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1685,\"end\":1707},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"06834276-d95f-4f1b-8d18-7e501978572e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the perfection of wisdom. For Hari, the two terms are perfect synonyms. But Hari holds that, like naming an “apple seed” after its fruit, the name “perfection of wisdom” can sometimes be applied, in a figurative sense, to wisdom at different stages along the five paths insofar as they are causes of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1707,\"end\":2016}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"actual\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2016,\"end\":2022},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2016,\"end\":2022,\"uuid\":\"3168e8cf-2e51-4090-a5e4-030d9373d81f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" perfection of wisdom that is a buddha’s knowing. For Ratnākara, these two terms are not perfect synonyms. The “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2022,\"end\":2134}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2134,\"end\":2156},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"769942b2-4277-4db1-ab5b-d0b21e135738\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” refers exclusively to a buddha’s knowing, whereas the term “perfection of wisdom” refers exclusively to the wisdom of noble ones at different stages, beginning on the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2156,\"end\":2325}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"path of seeing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2325,\"end\":2339},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"6f632c62-dd2f-4261-a93d-6db315e8a6bf\",\"uuid\":\"25e8bfc4-a01b-4cd5-8153-1a220bd94fb7\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2339,\"end\":2341}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"darśanamārga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2341,\"end\":2353},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2341,\"end\":2353,\"uuid\":\"f1ecc288-649a-48ed-8fb7-e8facdeec109\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and ending with the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2353,\"end\":2375}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"path of cultivation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2375,\"end\":2394},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"80e88a46-a897-465d-884c-b724b1404eb0\",\"uuid\":\"4a2edcf7-0a01-48ef-94d5-74915f52f48a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2394,\"end\":2396}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhāvanāmārga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2396,\"end\":2408},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2396,\"end\":2408,\"uuid\":\"ecef7880-4c9c-42d3-be68-431033c841d7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") just before the attainment of the complete awakening of a buddha. Even though Ratnākara acknowledges that the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2408,\"end\":2525}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"perfection of wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2525,\"end\":2545},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2525,\"end\":2545,\"uuid\":\"3a6a8279-0ded-492b-b158-e52d41b215ca\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"distinct\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" can refer to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2545,\"end\":2559}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"buddhahood\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2559,\"end\":2569},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3e1a9707-a0c5-4477-a334-9910a8f20bd9\",\"uuid\":\"b520431c-4c87-49d5-9ed0-11e19f927a9b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", he says that usage is figurative. Although Hari’s and Ratnākara’s diametric opposition should be kept in mind when reading certain passages and their corresponding footnotes below, the two commentators do not diverge much in their basic reading of this scripture.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2569,\"end\":2834}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"06af8d56-9a24-4d6f-b1c4-425f4e0b610e\",\"sort\":1000596,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.66\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Homage to all buddhas, bodhisattvas, noble disciples, and solitary realizers.\",\"label\":\"1.1\",\"sort\":10012,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"ebda8847-d437-4b14-8ca1-981527180324\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-418\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":105,\"uuid\":\"06af8d56-9a24-4d6f-b1c4-425f4e0b610e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This homage (one shared by only a handful of Kangyur texts) appears in the Tibetan, but not the Sanskrit.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":105}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1129dad4-86ef-43db-a16b-84f05c8b2a34\",\"sort\":1000598,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.67\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":3026,\"uuid\":\"1129dad4-86ef-43db-a16b-84f05c8b2a34\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.4.b–5.a), the term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"blessed one\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":57},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"d260e5de-ed63-44ab-ba2c-0467362cab57\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":57,\"end\":60}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhagavān\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":68,\"uuid\":\"0add4989-aa08-47bb-ad87-7c0669a45317\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") can (be understood through creative etymology to) mean that he conquers the four \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":151}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"māras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":151,\"end\":156},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cca61a77-75d5-4500-a990-23b3336c569d\",\"uuid\":\"349cdafd-8234-442e-81ce-3d6479041987\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":156,\"end\":158}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhaṅgād\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":158,\"end\":165},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":158,\"end\":165,\"uuid\":\"d7ebf894-36c5-4479-bff1-429a6addff85\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":167}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom pas na\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":167,\"end\":178},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":167,\"end\":178,\"uuid\":\"7f9225bc-dfc1-4ff5-acb9-a44583f9865e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), or his wisdom conquers the four \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":178,\"end\":213}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"māras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":213,\"end\":218},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cca61a77-75d5-4500-a990-23b3336c569d\",\"uuid\":\"ba30c286-5785-49bd-ae48-fddc001c1453\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":220}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":220,\"end\":228},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":220,\"end\":228,\"uuid\":\"40877b9a-3ae3-4feb-9a5e-e16ab428162b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":228,\"end\":230}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":236},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":236,\"uuid\":\"7618ea41-6f91-4f96-ac4d-b8ec139aedf5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), or else he is the container (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":236,\"end\":268}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āśritatvād\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":268,\"end\":278},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":268,\"end\":278,\"uuid\":\"92e2ee7a-e90c-4547-a80b-d33377b8ccea\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") for these blessed qualities. What are they? The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":278,\"end\":328}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":328,\"end\":339},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"cca64342-8c4f-415b-b9ca-4b49bad1c186\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" possesses (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":339,\"end\":351}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"vat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":351,\"end\":354},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":351,\"end\":354,\"uuid\":\"6d1030fe-d233-4ebb-9a8a-6da5669b2da5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") the six blessed qualities, beginning with mastery (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":354,\"end\":407}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"aiśvaryaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":407,\"end\":416},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":407,\"end\":416,\"uuid\":\"97590c0d-c553-4d5b-b3c7-3825a4967179\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":416,\"end\":418}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang phyug\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":418,\"end\":429},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":418,\"end\":429,\"uuid\":\"c53a8e37-4b98-4488-9967-4972f8d718b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and so on. As (Vasubandhu’s) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":429,\"end\":460}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vyākhyāyukti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":460,\"end\":472},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a67a5a60-17b0-4ab4-a99d-2e968ab01649\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" teaches, “Now, his six blessed qualities (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":472,\"end\":515}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhaga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":515,\"end\":520},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":515,\"end\":520,\"uuid\":\"0832da0b-9d1c-41ce-bfd5-88ddc51665cf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") are (a) mastery, (b) beauty, (c) celebrity, (d) glory, (e) knowing, and (f) effort.” To explain these six “blessed qualities” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":520,\"end\":649}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhaga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":649,\"end\":654},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":649,\"end\":654,\"uuid\":\"708cba27-a382-42c2-a72e-dc2b2b1ff1b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") of a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":654,\"end\":661}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":661,\"end\":672},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"33c571b7-0eae-4ec2-bc66-ef5cdeb81b5d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":672,\"end\":674}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhagavān\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":674,\"end\":682},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":674,\"end\":682,\"uuid\":\"6a0c8e23-737b-4708-9f53-0c342cbdfce7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"): (a) He has the blessed quality of self-mastery, because he is not dependent on anyone and has eliminated the obscurations together with the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":682,\"end\":825}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"habitual tendencies\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":825,\"end\":844},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a9cfa25e-788c-45ad-b792-12eb4d66502d\",\"uuid\":\"6451e208-4bcc-4466-aad8-2c07efae729a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". (b) He has the blessed quality of beauty, because his unsurpassable body is adorned with the thirty-two \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":844,\"end\":950}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"signs\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":950,\"end\":955},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"5475bf32-88c2-4471-9cf6-eff28ffb3061\",\"uuid\":\"0ecf4bff-ec19-438b-a9c7-b7a9d52d28ef\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and eighty marks. (c) He has the blessed quality of celebrity, because his renown is known in all cardinal and intermediate directions. (d) He has the blessed quality of glory (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":955,\"end\":1133}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"śṛīḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1133,\"end\":1137},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1133,\"end\":1137,\"uuid\":\"bc7fc196-32e6-40ae-a5be-b5da12f9f75c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") upon which many blessed qualities depend, because the succession of worldly and spiritual blessed qualities depend on his blessed qualities. (e) He has the blessed quality of knowing, because he has the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1137,\"end\":1342}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"knowing of all aspects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1342,\"end\":1364},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"uuid\":\"9b0e7254-956c-426d-9fbf-8d4c82d3bcff\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of everything knowable, and that knowing is pure, free of entanglement, and free of obstruction. (f) He has the blessed quality of doing heroic deeds, because he uninterruptedly does deeds for the sake of all others in every way. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1364,\"end\":1599}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bdud bzhi bcom pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1599,\"end\":1621},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1599,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1621,\"end\":1625},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1599,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1621,\"end\":1625,\"uuid\":\"8699d089-a3ed-4680-9a71-aa691266ce20\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1625,\"end\":1626},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1625,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ldan\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1626,\"end\":1630},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1625,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1626,\"end\":1630,\"uuid\":\"a55eb80b-569c-46dc-bc7c-a619c9222464\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1630,\"end\":1631},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1630,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’das\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1631,\"end\":1635},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1630,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1631,\"end\":1635,\"uuid\":\"f809ed4c-dceb-4fe5-9ecf-d96bd6517669\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" sam| shes rab kyis bdud bzhi bcom pa dang ldan pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1635,\"end\":1690},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1635,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1690,\"end\":1694},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1635,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1690,\"end\":1694,\"uuid\":\"83c19a14-7c9d-4c82-8dc0-6a88af2aa2ed\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1694,\"end\":1695},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1694,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ldan\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1695,\"end\":1699},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1694,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1695,\"end\":1699,\"uuid\":\"54eb2734-be05-4326-860c-fe3626086d9c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1699,\"end\":1700},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1699,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’das\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1700,\"end\":1704},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1699,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1700,\"end\":1704,\"uuid\":\"19feceb3-1b4b-4d59-b3ad-00c7caf63e63\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" so| |yang na ’di dag brten pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1704,\"end\":1739},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1704,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1739,\"end\":1743},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1704,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1739,\"end\":1743,\"uuid\":\"4b368155-9435-4e19-ab31-0ed5cc29e32b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1743,\"end\":1744},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1743,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ldan\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1744,\"end\":1748},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1743,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1744,\"end\":1748,\"uuid\":\"aae670cf-3afb-47fd-a3f4-86edc58e1162\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1748,\"end\":1749},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1748,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’das\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1749,\"end\":1753},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1748,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1749,\"end\":1753,\"uuid\":\"215d5118-2ec5-46ae-aee5-5f7bbf456de2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"$3c\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1753,\"end\":2904},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1753,\"end\":2904,\"uuid\":\"7b5699fe-3ea8-4cb3-b790-bea667f84f1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 20. Note: The above translation omits the Sanskrit grammatical comment.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2904,\"end\":3026}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"878933d3-acc1-4ed3-8303-e73285f08705\",\"sort\":1000664,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.68\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1511,\"uuid\":\"878933d3-acc1-4ed3-8303-e73285f08705\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Sanskrit term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"arhat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":23},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":23,\"uuid\":\"f81d93a3-9ab8-4a2d-9681-9f7bca58d571\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" refers to someone who has realized the goal of overcoming \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":82}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":103},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"125dbc1e-e471-4340-8a21-ef1a483f6f8f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" through the vehicle of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":103,\"end\":131}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciples\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":131,\"end\":140},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"fe1369ff-e70c-4483-8f07-5c0519f3a698\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and possesses the fifteen qualities that follow in the main text. This term has been translated throughout as “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":140,\"end\":253}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy one\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":253,\"end\":263},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"6964343c-2c29-4154-bbbc-7d15263e2985\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” or simply “worthy” (when connected with a person). According to Ratnākara (F.5.b), the four main heuristic etymologies for the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":397}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"arhat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":402},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":402,\"uuid\":\"68fdfee9-3336-4d5e-9d65-148e5ad3dae1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are (a) “someone who has eliminated the enemies” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":402,\"end\":453}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ari\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":453,\"end\":456},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":453,\"end\":456,\"uuid\":\"1534aad5-f927-4c1a-9aa5-4f027443ee8e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"+\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":456,\"end\":457}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"hatavān\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":457,\"end\":464},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":457,\"end\":464,\"uuid\":\"0f0fe515-1d5a-4bc2-b8fd-90c7edc307c2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), which are the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":464,\"end\":481}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":481,\"end\":502},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"dab0feac-367d-4306-b159-61fd2f8632f5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":502,\"end\":504}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kleśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":504,\"end\":509},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":504,\"end\":509,\"uuid\":\"b31c9fe8-0286-42da-ba85-7850ad86456a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"); (b) “someone who is free of arising” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":509,\"end\":550}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"arohat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":550,\"end\":556},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":550,\"end\":556,\"uuid\":\"6024e144-6a69-4bbf-b8ee-a414c18bfbc5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), i.e., lacking rebirth; (c) “someone who worships” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":556,\"end\":610}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ārādha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":610,\"end\":616},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":610,\"end\":616,\"uuid\":\"c075202c-1030-4f90-bf87-e5f7f3772500\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ?) the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":616,\"end\":624}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tathāgata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":624,\"end\":633},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ba88d417-b0e3-432a-babf-877a261cff8b\",\"uuid\":\"ad133810-558a-4413-8549-70c6d21a9afe\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" through the perfect offering of practice; and (d) “someone who is worthy,” i.e., worthy of the generosity (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":633,\"end\":741}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"niṇḍārha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":749},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":749,\"uuid\":\"c7b3bcb1-2544-407b-93b8-fba4c5aa6326\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") of others and worthy of the veneration (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":749,\"end\":791}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pūjārha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":791,\"end\":798},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":791,\"end\":798,\"uuid\":\"11ed3e95-c2c5-48e4-8fc2-d42e2e49e7a9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") of others. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":798,\"end\":815}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dgra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":815,\"end\":819},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":815,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":815,\"end\":819,\"uuid\":\"ed03d9a6-6be8-42df-8f88-a9a1d614f032\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":819,\"end\":820},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":819,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":820,\"end\":824},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":819,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":820,\"end\":824,\"uuid\":\"bb62b328-d8d2-45d0-aebe-7d6a8fa386e9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":824,\"end\":825},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":824,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":825,\"end\":827},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":824,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":825,\"end\":827,\"uuid\":\"329c1e36-6050-4b16-ba42-4274335edb50\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" nyid ni nyon mongs pa’i dgra rnams bcom pa dang ldan pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":827,\"end\":888},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":827,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dgra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":888,\"end\":892},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":827,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":888,\"end\":892,\"uuid\":\"7325b687-458f-4da6-bda7-d7889663237b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":892,\"end\":893},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":892,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":893,\"end\":897},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":892,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":893,\"end\":897,\"uuid\":\"d7f35f34-a13c-4999-a001-8a8a2e5a7768\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":897,\"end\":898},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":897,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":898,\"end\":900},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":897,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":898,\"end\":900,\"uuid\":\"1485be23-b413-4b31-be7e-b8477b1f70d7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| |yang na mi skye zhing yang skye ba med pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":900,\"end\":951},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":900,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dgra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":951,\"end\":955},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":900,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":951,\"end\":955,\"uuid\":\"64472267-0ff9-430f-bd81-5fe3dba3af6e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":955,\"end\":956},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":955,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":956,\"end\":960},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":955,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":956,\"end\":960,\"uuid\":\"6540aa97-674b-431f-aa76-f0d37bd404a9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":960,\"end\":961},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":960,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":961,\"end\":963},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":960,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":961,\"end\":963,\"uuid\":\"59a4aad0-5e1d-49a4-8438-063ec71e3401\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| |yang na de bzhin gshegs pa la sgrub pa’i mchod pa yang dag par mchod pas mchod par byed pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":963,\"end\":1063},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":963,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dgra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1063,\"end\":1067},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":963,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1063,\"end\":1067,\"uuid\":\"932d8d3b-76b9-4e3f-afa4-df0b6f231b64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1067,\"end\":1068},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1067,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1072},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1067,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1072,\"uuid\":\"f562a447-47f2-4c9a-88fc-48588f2b581b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1072,\"end\":1073},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1072,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1073,\"end\":1075},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1072,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1073,\"end\":1075,\"uuid\":\"78c3d81d-8ac2-463c-a212-9565781ef396\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| |yang na lha dang mi rnams kyis mchod pa dang| sbyin gnas su ’os pas na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1075,\"end\":1151},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1075,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dgra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1151,\"end\":1155},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1075,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1151,\"end\":1155,\"uuid\":\"bb31ee0d-54a0-4a0f-8f03-1b4ddbe69df8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1155,\"end\":1156},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1155,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1156,\"end\":1160},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1155,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1156,\"end\":1160,\"uuid\":\"475b4ffe-a320-41f1-9cbf-27ec5601d41e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1160,\"end\":1161},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1160,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1161,\"end\":1163},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1160,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1161,\"end\":1163,\"uuid\":\"31d8e1fa-b011-46ac-a35a-565d6162ac3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1163,\"end\":1165},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1163,\"end\":1165,\"uuid\":\"cae64235-95c0-4b87-a6d2-ea39cced9c64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Note: This fourth etymology is closer to normal Sanskrit usage of the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1165,\"end\":1242}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"arhat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1242,\"end\":1247},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1242,\"end\":1247,\"uuid\":\"6e581a28-8246-4f56-92d1-f67a4d815933\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and thus has been adopted as the general translation throughout this scripture. However, keep in mind that Tibetan \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1247,\"end\":1363}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dgra bcom pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1363,\"end\":1375},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1363,\"end\":1375,\"uuid\":\"b1dc41fb-bfda-48bc-935a-0651438e29bf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is based on the first etymological meaning, i.e., “eliminator of the enemies.” For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 22–23.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1375,\"end\":1511}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fe462982-6a3a-4b98-91e0-4c3b3cc314d9\",\"sort\":1000729,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.69\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":3478,\"uuid\":\"fe462982-6a3a-4b98-91e0-4c3b3cc314d9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.5.b–6.a), because of their quality of meriting the generosity and veneration of others, they have “eliminated the worldly inﬂuences,” which entail a ﬂow \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":179}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"away\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":179,\"end\":183},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":179,\"end\":183,\"uuid\":\"1ff0347e-49e9-41b5-b9df-4cf6635794a2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" from the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":183,\"end\":193}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"virtuous\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":193,\"end\":201},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"803ba49d-1a79-42c7-a363-0cde26f4d5e4\",\"uuid\":\"0b394908-6e3a-4964-bc79-6c90010f5abc\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" roots and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":212}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"toward\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":212,\"end\":218},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":212,\"end\":218,\"uuid\":\"ab63b50b-6eed-413c-84ad-14f60a20e134\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"emphasis\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" cyclic birth (in the world) and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":251}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":251,\"end\":272},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"9d0343ca-e719-4610-ab7a-366d6eb30865\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". There are four types of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":272,\"end\":298}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worldly influences\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":316},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"86981a5b-d566-434a-8400-2956eadee2b8\",\"uuid\":\"7a51897d-1ed2-43a1-882f-22a792c36e1b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\": (a) worldly inﬂuence from desire, i.e., the ﬁve sense pleasures; (b) worldly inﬂuence from existence, i.e., the three types of existences; (c) worldly inﬂuence from \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":316,\"end\":483}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":483,\"end\":492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"3b4f94f2-fb4a-471d-aaa2-33ece56e3ffc\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", i.e., imputed and coemergent \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":492,\"end\":523}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":523,\"end\":532},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"837ded2e-0726-4533-a28d-960bd0618338\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; and (d) worldly inﬂuence from wrong views, i.e., the sixty-two wrong views‍—all these are “eliminated.” Corresponding to those four, when the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":532,\"end\":676}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worldly influences\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":676,\"end\":694},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"86981a5b-d566-434a-8400-2956eadee2b8\",\"uuid\":\"c2bad2aa-d266-43d6-b4ae-f6b70b016ce3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are eliminated, one actualizes (a) the mass of discipline and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":694,\"end\":757}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":757,\"end\":781},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"8bea6c3f-45cd-4426-94c4-16bbf374508f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (b) the mass of liberation, (c) the mass of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":781,\"end\":827}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"seeing the knowing of liberation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":827,\"end\":859},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"efacd175-91b7-484b-bfa8-68325bbdd6b2\",\"uuid\":\"7bc54d1e-f833-43b3-81ff-d30692c830e2\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and (d) the mass of wisdom. Furthermore, there arise (a) accurate \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":859,\"end\":927}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":927,\"end\":951},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"dbd0a5f7-feef-4caa-bf6f-b9d30a6bbc9e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (b) knowing that what has been eliminated will not arise (again), (c) accurate liberation, and (d) accurate view. Furthermore, there arise (a) full knowing of the cause of desire, (b) full knowing of the cause of the constituents of experience, (c) full knowing of the cause of the conditioning factors, and (d) full knowing of the cause of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":951,\"end\":1294}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1294,\"end\":1315},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"6d2ce98d-10ef-490b-8d8e-db79194d64d3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Furthermore, there arise (a) the abandonment of the truth of the source of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1315,\"end\":1392}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1392,\"end\":1401},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"6209e82c-9b68-47de-b626-f13274ba2aa2\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (b) the actualization of the truth of cessation, (c) the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1401,\"end\":1460}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"cultivation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1460,\"end\":1471},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"08ff4aa9-bae0-47bc-b36c-93ba28c249f0\",\"uuid\":\"a46c7523-82f6-40ec-84e8-762c02eb4768\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the truth of the path, and (d) the full knowing of the truth of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1471,\"end\":1539}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1539,\"end\":1548},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"b9f5761e-1c46-4df1-8959-bff87c490de6\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1548,\"end\":1554}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de bas na mchod par ’os pa dang| sbying nas su gyur pa’i yon tan gyis \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1554,\"end\":1624},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1554,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zag pa zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1624,\"end\":1637},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1554,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1624,\"end\":1637,\"uuid\":\"9721b3af-46b3-47d3-9473-174af72847d4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces smos te| skye ba dang| nyon mongs pa’i dge ba’i rtsa ba ni zag pa ste| |de dag ni (a) ’dod pa’i zag pa dang| (b) srid pa’i zag pa dang| (c) ma rig pa’i zag pa dang| (d) lta ba’i zag pa dang| rnam pa bzhi pa’o| |de yang go rims ci lta ba bzhin du (a) ’dod pa’i lnga dang| (b) srid pa’i gsum dang| (c) ma rig pa’i kun brtags pa dang| (d) lhan cig skyes pa dang lta ba drug cu rtsa gnyis te| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1637,\"end\":2031},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1637,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zag pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2031,\"end\":2037},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1637,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2031,\"end\":2037,\"uuid\":\"25515ca5-2aca-4166-ad34-2628060cc463\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ’di rnams \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2037,\"end\":2048},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2037,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2048,\"end\":2054},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2037,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2048,\"end\":2054,\"uuid\":\"a2b5f31e-adc0-4343-a28d-dca0980d77b2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" s na \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2054,\"end\":2060},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2054,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zag pa zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2060,\"end\":2073},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2054,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2060,\"end\":2073,\"uuid\":\"fc4afdee-85b8-417c-9e43-fededefbe8cf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| de yang go rims bzhin du (a) tshul khrims dang| ting nge ’dzin gyi phung po gnyis dang| (b) rnam par grol ba’i phung po dang| (c) rnam par grol ba’i ye shes mthong ba’i phung po dang| (d) shes rab kyi phung po zag pa zad pa mngon sum du byed pa’o| yang (a) yang dag pa’i ting nge ’dzin dang| (b) zad la mi skye ba’i ye shes dang| (c) yang dag pa’i rnam par grol ba dang| (d) yang dag pa’i lta ba’o| yang (a) ’dod pa’i rgyu yongs su shes pa dang| (b) phung po’i rgyu yongs su shes pa dang| (c) ’du byed kyi rgyu yongs su shes pa dang| (d) nyon mongs pa’i rgyu yongs su shes pa’o| yang (a) sdug bsngal kun ’byung ba’i bden pa spang ba dang| (b) ’gog pa’i bden pa mngon sum du bya ba dang| (c) lam gyi bden pa bsgom pa dang| (d) sdug bsngal gyi bden pa yongs su shes pa’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2073,\"end\":2845},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2073,\"end\":2845,\"uuid\":\"6236a23e-79ca-4178-96f8-6103f7d57e34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 23. Note: Both commentators comment on each of the next fifteen words, but Hari’s interesting comments have not been included because it would make these notes too long and an English translation of them is available in Sparham 2006, i., pp. 177–81. The translation “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2845,\"end\":3163}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worldly influences\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3163,\"end\":3181},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"86981a5b-d566-434a-8400-2956eadee2b8\",\"uuid\":\"54276b21-c7cf-421f-8f32-13eb4d582c5c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3181,\"end\":3184}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āsrava\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3184,\"end\":3190},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3184,\"end\":3190,\"uuid\":\"d3a0431a-82bd-4316-9812-14d81cc4962f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3190,\"end\":3191}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āśrava\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3191,\"end\":3197},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3191,\"end\":3197,\"uuid\":\"8863b510-5ce7-4a8d-8cfd-0c4678e171a2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3197,\"end\":3199}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zag pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3199,\"end\":3205},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3199,\"end\":3205,\"uuid\":\"6919ff52-3c00-4295-91f3-f7e2956d4d12\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") derives from the etymology of the Skt./Pali term, in which the prefix \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3205,\"end\":3277}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3277,\"end\":3278},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3277,\"end\":3278,\"uuid\":\"92bbb2c5-9547-4f52-ae90-f880ef9bb4d7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" can be interpreted either as meaning “away” or “toward,” i.e., an “outflux” or “inflow.” Cf. BHSD and PTSD \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3278,\"end\":3386}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āsrava\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3386,\"end\":3392},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3386,\"end\":3392,\"uuid\":\"737be7fe-0d5c-4b40-a5c5-c3c4cc215ddb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" for more information about the word and the three or four kinds of worldly influence.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3392,\"end\":3478}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"645530a0-0f21-4714-9e0c-2f7a7514384e\",\"sort\":1000783,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.70\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":2496,\"uuid\":\"645530a0-0f21-4714-9e0c-2f7a7514384e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.6.a–b), because of their quality of eliminating \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":74}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worldly influences\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":92},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"86981a5b-d566-434a-8400-2956eadee2b8\",\"uuid\":\"dcc700c3-af01-4d6b-93ab-28d33b94d662\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", they “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":92,\"end\":100}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"had no emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":100,\"end\":128},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b174fd68-32f5-4727-acaf-302a6bd3e16b\",\"uuid\":\"f0196ebb-ff00-473a-8caa-5c1d79d422e5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” which are of four types: (a) emotional defilement associated with karma, which is what brings about \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":128,\"end\":231}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":231,\"end\":240},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"2baabaa9-c27b-4e7b-b47a-33c443091300\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" through emotional defilement; (b) emotional defilement associated with maturation, which brings about emotional defilement; (c) emotional defilement associated with the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":240,\"end\":410}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":410,\"end\":431},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"857c204c-7464-40fe-9cab-b7785b9d7c5f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" themselves, which is what brings about \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":431,\"end\":471}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":471,\"end\":492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"20020bdb-ff49-418b-b08f-4279e1a05552\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; and (d) emotional defilement associated with birth, which is emotional defilement. In the cessation of those, there is cessation of (a) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":492,\"end\":631}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":631,\"end\":652},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"2bcccdb7-17e2-4a60-ba9d-a0b72898a5fe\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" associated with karma,” i.e., due to the cessation of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":707}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":707,\"end\":716},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"805e98f8-b028-4482-948c-8d2af5fdeb62\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the karmic conditioning factors cease; (b) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":716,\"end\":762}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":762,\"end\":783},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"a7a3a0f9-89b7-4401-b9fa-1d617a43b3c2\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" associated with maturation,” i.e., due to the cessation of karmic conditioning factors, consciousness, name and form, the sense organs, contact, and feeling all cease; (c) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":783,\"end\":957}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":957,\"end\":978},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"ce2d186e-f779-4606-bd5e-8f66e1249f93\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" associated with \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":978,\"end\":995}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":995,\"end\":1016},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"22083ec7-f39b-4962-ab30-d566bf7bc900\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” i.e., due to the cessation of feeling, craving, grasping, and becoming all cease; and (d) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1016,\"end\":1110}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1110,\"end\":1131},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"71ed3798-4dea-411a-b8a3-8e1fcab4afbe\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" associated with birth,” i.e., due to the cessation of becoming, birth, aging, and death all cease. These “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1131,\"end\":1238}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1238,\"end\":1259},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"e11f088f-57f9-4c72-b4f5-f74bf699292f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” are (different types of) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1259,\"end\":1286}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1286,\"end\":1295},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"43e57c4c-0c0b-4f23-a8a0-123b65b1ae01\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1295,\"end\":1301}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de bas na zag pa zad pa nyid kyis rnam par dag pa’i yon tan ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1301,\"end\":1364},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1301,\"end\":2438,\"uuid\":\"90e2fefb-30f0-491e-add8-de24e6b0b0b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nyon mongs pa med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1364,\"end\":1384},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1301,\"end\":2438,\"uuid\":\"90e2fefb-30f0-491e-add8-de24e6b0b0b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1364,\"end\":1384,\"uuid\":\"6f1b1b07-c016-4f18-83ff-3dfa6e1522c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"$3d\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1384,\"end\":2438},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1384,\"end\":2438,\"uuid\":\"90e2fefb-30f0-491e-add8-de24e6b0b0b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 23–24.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2438,\"end\":2496}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"60d69938-6322-4b4f-83a4-5e4fd9535313\",\"sort\":1000815,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.71\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1480,\"uuid\":\"60d69938-6322-4b4f-83a4-5e4fd9535313\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.6.b), because of their quality of becoming free from \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":79}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":88},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"b3c4c5d4-e339-4f33-8545-ffc2d1887594\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" due to emotional defilement, these \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":124}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy ones\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":135},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"a426c938-0c2e-4e6b-b089-0fcc3ed7d19c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":135,\"end\":137}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"had become self-controlled\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":137,\"end\":163},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"136071b2-0ae6-4d14-b8c0-ea6216ec6ef0\",\"uuid\":\"5a2ca710-8d95-401e-a6b1-8ef3568ab93c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” meaning (a) in control over the magical powers, (b) in control over the faculties (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":163,\"end\":249}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":249,\"end\":257},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":249,\"end\":257,\"uuid\":\"1675a863-9dc5-44d1-8e7d-7d0d359ae3c2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), (c) in control over samādhi, and (d) in control over wisdom (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":257,\"end\":321}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":321,\"end\":327},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":321,\"end\":327,\"uuid\":\"1cc69e65-e491-4786-a5cb-30dc7a40a87c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). In what way are they in control? (a) They have a special control over the world of beings and their environment. (b) Insofar as they are dear to the world, they have control over those beings through achieving control (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":327,\"end\":549}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":549,\"end\":554},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":549,\"end\":554,\"uuid\":\"9ac8c06a-f8dd-42ea-95f0-ea8094680477\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") of their conduct. (c) They have control over their minds. And (d) they have achieved control over themselves (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":554,\"end\":666}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rang la dbang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":666,\"end\":679},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":666,\"end\":679,\"uuid\":\"c2940ba7-e5c9-46f9-b057-35ac2446b2ef\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") in the manner (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":679,\"end\":696}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bzhin du\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":696,\"end\":704},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":696,\"end\":704,\"uuid\":\"ec91c3d3-e660-4d76-88d2-86c960927711\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":704,\"end\":706}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tathā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":706,\"end\":711},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":706,\"end\":711,\"uuid\":\"d6b7febe-ccf9-4177-b63b-6305edd7259d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") of liberation from bondage through eliminating all karma and maturations. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":711,\"end\":791}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de bas na nyon mongs pa med pas sdug bsngal med pa’i yon tan ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":791,\"end\":855},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":791,\"end\":1426,\"uuid\":\"b8be4d71-d809-40a1-b32d-84196cf05137\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang du gyur pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":855,\"end\":871},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":791,\"end\":1426,\"uuid\":\"b8be4d71-d809-40a1-b32d-84196cf05137\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":855,\"end\":871,\"uuid\":\"b466b33c-36d2-42c7-852d-45f3f95e309c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes smos so |(a) |rdzu ’phrul la dbang ba dang| (b) dbang po la dbang ba dang|(c) ting nge ’dzin la dbang ba dang|(d) shes rab la dbang ba’o| |ji ltar de dag la dbang ba yin zhe na? go rims ji lta ba bzhin du (a) sems can dang snod kyi ’jig rten dag la khyad par du dbang du gyur pa dang|(b) spyod pa la dbang thob pas ’jig rten dga’ ba nyid kyis de dag dbang du ’gyur ba dang| (c) de dag gi sems dbang du gyur pa nyid dang| (d nyon mongs pa dang| las dang rnam par smin pa thams cad bcad pas ’ching ba las grol ba bzhin du rang la dbang thob pa nyid do\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":871,\"end\":1426},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":871,\"end\":1426,\"uuid\":\"b8be4d71-d809-40a1-b32d-84196cf05137\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 24.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1426,\"end\":1480}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"208347bf-2e79-438b-9c74-c8a57a923696\",\"sort\":1000839,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.72\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":2647,\"uuid\":\"208347bf-2e79-438b-9c74-c8a57a923696\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.6.b), the “liberated \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":47}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":47,\"end\":54},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"70bd60f4-3b1f-4796-92a0-7a04c3068dfc\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” results from having abandoned all \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":54,\"end\":90}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":90,\"end\":111},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"0921d0a6-9e68-4586-8dba-8abf4a7564e3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":111,\"end\":113}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kleśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":118},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":118,\"uuid\":\"83207772-7488-413c-b88f-a2c8a9ef4f54\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") connected with the different aspects of craving. And “their discernment is liberated” because they have abandoned all primary and secondary \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":260}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":260,\"end\":281},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"e528c386-8453-456c-84aa-1c81c580494f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":281,\"end\":283}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kleśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":283,\"end\":288},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":283,\"end\":288,\"uuid\":\"f08ef8e1-73a0-40b3-8f1e-85e28aa083b4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") connected with \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":305}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":305,\"end\":314},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"7c30d7f1-8c73-48b1-b7f2-6f0fde1dda44\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that hinders it. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":314,\"end\":336}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":336,\"end\":337},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":336,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems shin tu rnam par grol ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":337,\"end\":366},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":336,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":337,\"end\":366,\"uuid\":\"2511c688-aec6-492d-81fb-48f3093845f0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni sems rnam par grol ba’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":366,\"end\":408},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":366,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab shin tu rnam par grol ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":408,\"end\":441},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":366,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":408,\"end\":441,\"uuid\":\"f816dbc4-bb9f-4c7f-ad61-42420b8e78f4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni shes rab rnam par grol ba’o| de la srid pa’i phyogs kyi nyon mongs pa spangs pas ting nge ’dzin dang snyoms par ’jug pa thob pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":441,\"end\":588},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":441,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems rnam par grol ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":588,\"end\":609},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":441,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":588,\"end\":609,\"uuid\":\"40ad688a-be49-4e8d-8c3c-1ce155a48178\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| |ma rig pa’i phyogs kyi nyon mongs pa dang| nye ba’i nyon mongs pa spangs pas thob pa dgra bcom pa thob pa’i lam gyi ye shes ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":609,\"end\":741},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":609,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab rnam par grol ba’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":767},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":609,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":767,\"uuid\":\"9b7bc5fe-4777-4095-8aeb-144ee45878c9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" o.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":767,\"end\":770},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":767,\"end\":770,\"uuid\":\"92f15a22-0a1a-477b-9260-cf709f5f79de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 24. According to Hari (9), generally the liberation of a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":770,\"end\":877}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":877,\"end\":884},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"6f2ffd69-9be4-4590-ba32-86c717ab4aac\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" refers to the attainments of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":884,\"end\":914}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":914,\"end\":938},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"19a8d085-0f6b-4217-8118-ba65a88272ed\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" due to the relinquishing of all primary and secondary \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":938,\"end\":993}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":993,\"end\":1014},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"724ef3f3-06fb-4671-ad15-a09b83133d86\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" related to craving and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1014,\"end\":1038}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1038,\"end\":1047},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"05337226-31a9-47c3-9b86-9a80e0dfa820\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", whereas the liberation of discernment refers to the knowing of someone on the noble path. Hence, by lacking the aspects of craving and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1047,\"end\":1184}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1184,\"end\":1193},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"ed951491-21c4-4834-ab4f-79cf28a6e060\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the pairing of liberation of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1193,\"end\":1224}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1224,\"end\":1231},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"0c01265a-4f3a-4c49-a803-12d935cc5984\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and discerment means, respectively, that one lacks attachment and one lacks \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1231,\"end\":1308}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1308,\"end\":1317},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"a6c05a40-1e15-469a-8e11-58d988216cbe\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For this reason, after one attains that state, one can say both parts together‍—namely, they had “utterly liberated their \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1317,\"end\":1441}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1441,\"end\":1448},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"e815703b-99ad-47e1-85ee-1b9b9b278182\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” and “utterly liberated their discernment”‍—by liberating the emotional obscurations through meditative attainments. Hari: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1448,\"end\":1572}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tṛṣṇāvidyā­pakṣa­sarva­kleṣopakleśa­prahāṇāt samādhisamāpattayaś \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1572,\"end\":1637},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1572,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"e94b221c-92fe-4f15-aff9-7340fe5c3bde\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"cetovimuktir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1637,\"end\":1649},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1572,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"e94b221c-92fe-4f15-aff9-7340fe5c3bde\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1637,\"end\":1649,\"uuid\":\"cc1cd309-1553-4d64-9937-bdba1e4a05df\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", arhanmārgajñānaṃ \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1649,\"end\":1668},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1649,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"e94b221c-92fe-4f15-aff9-7340fe5c3bde\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñāvimuktir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1668,\"end\":1682},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1649,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"e94b221c-92fe-4f15-aff9-7340fe5c3bde\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1668,\"end\":1682,\"uuid\":\"574931e3-c5d4-45fe-a57a-43f3845d3196\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" iti kṛtvā tṛṣṇāvidyāpakṣāṇāṃ abhāvena yathākramaṃ rāgavirāgād avidyāvirāgāc cetaḥprajñā­vimuktiḥ. atas tallābhāt samāpatti­kleśāvaraṇa­vimuktyā sarvathobhaya­bhāga­vimuktāḥ \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1682,\"end\":1856},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1682,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"e94b221c-92fe-4f15-aff9-7340fe5c3bde\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suvimuktacittāḥ suvimuktaprajñāḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1856,\"end\":1888},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1856,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"e94b221c-92fe-4f15-aff9-7340fe5c3bde\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1856,\"end\":1888,\"uuid\":\"2aee7a5f-e651-4736-863f-d57b8952e0c4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Note: In early Buddhist literature, the word “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1888,\"end\":1936}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1936,\"end\":1943},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"434d86a5-6588-4958-9128-5f404a6d0a98\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1943,\"end\":1946}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"citta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1946,\"end\":1951},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1946,\"end\":1951,\"uuid\":\"7bc25751-1539-42bc-8292-691dab917ee6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") was sometimes used as a synonym of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1951,\"end\":1988}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1988,\"end\":2012},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"40f86fbd-46d8-4445-a885-0caf0ca56b1f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2012,\"end\":2014}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"samādhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2014,\"end\":2021},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2014,\"end\":2021,\"uuid\":\"de58209e-22af-44d1-aa09-335a093c2e6a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), in the sense of a mind being set upon an object‍—especially in the context of the three trainings of the path, namely, ethical conduct (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2021,\"end\":2160}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"śīla\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2160,\"end\":2164},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2160,\"end\":2164,\"uuid\":\"f3076a94-41ad-4d30-9239-d02d73cb1254\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2164,\"end\":2167}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2167,\"end\":2191},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"e8729a72-3647-4b6c-ac4f-664fec69c736\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2191,\"end\":2192}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2192,\"end\":2199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"25fc860c-99ce-4c22-b3e9-2e2bbcf772a5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2199,\"end\":2201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"samādhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2201,\"end\":2208},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2201,\"end\":2208,\"uuid\":\"76b74f46-c207-47bf-b6fa-5a6ce9938b07\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"=\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2208,\"end\":2209}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"citta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2209,\"end\":2214},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2209,\"end\":2214,\"uuid\":\"672e8e20-2f25-436b-b16d-d836ac949be6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), and wisdom (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2214,\"end\":2229}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2229,\"end\":2235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2229,\"end\":2235,\"uuid\":\"f227a6da-a3dc-4a89-97b3-47c03439809a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). So one can understand here that when the mind is perfectly set, i.e., settled, it is liberated from craving. Note that here the English translation “discernment” for \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2235,\"end\":2404}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2404,\"end\":2410},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2404,\"end\":2410,\"uuid\":\"4132f165-6f5c-488d-a4b0-d3c0d259be2f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is used in place of the rendering “wisdom” that we have (somewhat reluctantly) used elsewhere throughout this translation, and will be used subsequently only when the term refers to the mental faculty that can be afflicted by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2410,\"end\":2637}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2637,\"end\":2646},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"3fad083d-850e-4372-aa9a-94ea1444208d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2646,\"end\":2647}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"24673f44-ecbf-4e64-bbd8-7869e7c15fe2\",\"sort\":1000910,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.73\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":2884,\"uuid\":\"24673f44-ecbf-4e64-bbd8-7869e7c15fe2\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Sanskrit term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ājāneya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":25},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":25,\"uuid\":\"5667211f-ca3a-426d-919a-8ea8f37979c6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":25,\"end\":27}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"cang shes pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":27,\"end\":39},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":27,\"end\":39,\"uuid\":\"c6754052-6492-4617-a352-23a81435149b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") has been translated as “noble” but can also mean a “good breed” of person or animal. According to Ratnākara (F.6.b–7.a), the term “noble” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":39,\"end\":180}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ājāneya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":180,\"end\":187},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":180,\"end\":187,\"uuid\":\"5027f441-2f14-4a26-b8cf-f15a45ed1bb2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":187,\"end\":189}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"cang shes pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":189,\"end\":201},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":189,\"end\":201,\"uuid\":\"78de2bec-2b5f-4412-9bfb-15c4c2cc6cf0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") refers to fearlessness (in the face of challenges). There are five types: (a) noble like a bull unafraid of lightning and so on; (b-c) noble like a horse or elephant unafraid in battle; (d) noble like a lion unafraid when attacked by another; and (e) noble like a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":467}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy one\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":467,\"end\":477},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"9f8eb4ea-7bd4-41a6-80c3-b8e380ecd3aa\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":477,\"end\":479}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"arhat\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":479,\"end\":484},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":479,\"end\":484,\"uuid\":\"2b9b2c51-6e76-47f9-a5c0-d2c996806c4e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") unafraid of death. In correspondence with these, they possess the four benefits of freedom from fear of anxiety: (a) they gain the ease that is free of the fear of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":484,\"end\":650}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":650,\"end\":659},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"cfbccc53-1f4b-4be0-81f8-600c010b4051\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", because they have no misery, complaint, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":659,\"end\":701}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":701,\"end\":710},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"9ab28e2f-0b79-42f0-baf1-4c93c9a71819\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", or distress; (b) they gain freedom from terror, because, without fear of anxiety, they do not fear being disgraced by themselves, others, misfortune, lacking livelihood, loss, misery, or death; (c) they gain freedom from fear itself, because, without anxiety about the eight worldly concerns, they cannot be sullied by seeking or avoiding gain or loss, fame or infamy, praise or blame, or happiness or \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":710,\"end\":1114}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1114,\"end\":1123},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"81124b54-7783-4816-b6f2-c9f3f60742bb\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; and (d) they gain the comfort of freedom from the fear of unknowing, because their knowing is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1123,\"end\":1219}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"never lacking\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1219,\"end\":1232},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e77994-e832-43f0-898f-17c9988c9ae9\",\"uuid\":\"7736ba47-6dbb-4844-8128-4839302724ff\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", uncertain, or mistaken. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1232,\"end\":1262}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1262,\"end\":1263},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1262,\"end\":2667,\"uuid\":\"2b4e4088-25bd-4785-bd05-2d47d5f57a70\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"cang shes pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1263,\"end\":1275},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1262,\"end\":2667,\"uuid\":\"2b4e4088-25bd-4785-bd05-2d47d5f57a70\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1263,\"end\":1275,\"uuid\":\"ef6cfcba-c340-42c2-b356-e1a0c6ab3de8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"$3e\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1275,\"end\":2667},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1275,\"end\":2667,\"uuid\":\"2b4e4088-25bd-4785-bd05-2d47d5f57a70\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 24–25. Note: The translation of RK’s commentary combines each statement and reason into a single sentence for ease, even though these were explained by RK in two blocks.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2667,\"end\":2884}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"07d40714-85d8-461a-8bd9-e6077fa2c791\",\"sort\":1000936,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.74\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1045,\"uuid\":\"07d40714-85d8-461a-8bd9-e6077fa2c791\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Sanskrit term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mahānāga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":26},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":26,\"uuid\":\"daf90716-5bbe-4b47-9974-ad44e26cbc06\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":26,\"end\":28}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"glang po chen\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":41},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":41,\"uuid\":\"a53337fb-79ca-4281-bb6a-2080f037f4c2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") has been translated as “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":41,\"end\":67}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"exemplary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":67,\"end\":76},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ba9676ee-5941-4097-9aec-0f5be27570f3\",\"uuid\":\"de685563-3e2d-4dd7-bbc0-62d5ecb81da4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” based on the commentary, but literally means “elephants.” According to Ratnākara (F.7.a), “elephant” is a figurative expression for the greatest of leaders (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":76,\"end\":235}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gtso bo chen po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":250},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":250,\"uuid\":\"0475a83d-6047-4284-a250-058e6bc86460\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Among their great accomplishments, some of these \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":250,\"end\":302}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy ones\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":302,\"end\":313},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"0a2e4167-f382-4b82-b10b-2d093c74dafe\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" possess the threefold knowledge. Others have attained experiential knowledge (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":313,\"end\":392}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratisaṃvid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":392,\"end\":403},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":392,\"end\":403,\"uuid\":\"a80a4bcc-1208-4e18-9fc5-606d0fbffa92\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Others have realized the six extraordinary knowledges (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":403,\"end\":461}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"abhijñā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":461,\"end\":468},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":461,\"end\":468,\"uuid\":\"94e33e38-0721-4163-a304-a92a16c7941f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Others have completely understood how to unpack and explain things. Others have attained independence. At the final point, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":468,\"end\":594}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy ones\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":594,\"end\":605},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"78cacb86-463a-4fbc-867e-17bdf28c5eb9\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":605,\"end\":610}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"exemplary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":610,\"end\":619},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ba9676ee-5941-4097-9aec-0f5be27570f3\",\"uuid\":\"e6605716-865d-4028-8e05-b458cd2e8d07\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" because they have accomplished the Sage’s Dharma. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":619,\"end\":674}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"glang po chen po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":674,\"end\":690},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":674,\"end\":991,\"uuid\":\"62d748ca-a7b9-4c74-96db-af8ed86a22a3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":674,\"end\":690,\"uuid\":\"f5b69384-15da-4a89-8d04-938b385965bd\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni gtso bo chen po ste| kha cig ni gsum rig pa dang| kha cig ni so so yang dag par rig pa thob pa| kha cig ni mngon par shes pa drug pa thob pa| kha cig ni kun shes pa brda sprod pa| kha cig ni gcig pur gnas pa thob pa ste| mthar thug pa thub pa’i chos rnyed pa’i phyir glang po chen po’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":991},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":991,\"uuid\":\"62d748ca-a7b9-4c74-96db-af8ed86a22a3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 25.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":991,\"end\":1045}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2bd7bdb2-0a0e-47d4-917f-fe5118b428e5\",\"sort\":1000959,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.75\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1073,\"uuid\":\"2bd7bdb2-0a0e-47d4-917f-fe5118b428e5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.7.a), these two phrases mean that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":64}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy ones\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":64,\"end\":75},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"644e6926-5c2c-43e9-8ccc-21aa3b636f25\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" have perfected the practice in every regard. “The task” is the liberation from all \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":75,\"end\":159}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":159,\"end\":168},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"e4ece183-64b6-49cb-ae18-0f1faeee6fa2\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" through perfecting \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":168,\"end\":188}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ethical discipline\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":188,\"end\":206},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"db80746c-d186-4671-a39d-729913d0a7c8\",\"uuid\":\"3a1fd65c-7095-4597-afea-2e877da58e87\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", concentration, and wisdom, because this must be ascertained. “The work” is the way of living life‍—with few desires, with contentment, with ascetic qualities, and amid the causes of joy and so on‍—because of living life according to one’s deepest wish. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":206,\"end\":465}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bya ba byas pa| byed pa byas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":465,\"end\":496},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":465,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":465,\"end\":496,\"uuid\":\"0ce442a1-a749-4ba3-a395-7c2223530f07\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni rnam pa thams cad kyi sgrub pa yongs su rdzogs pa’o| |de’i phyir tshul khrims ting nge ’dzin dang| shes rab yongs su rdzogs pas sdug bsngal thams cad las rnam par thar ba ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":496,\"end\":686},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":496,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bya ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":686,\"end\":692},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":496,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":686,\"end\":692,\"uuid\":\"3a08e5c0-99c1-4a22-823c-c4714b5c6f22\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ste nges par bya ba yin pa’i phyir ro| |’dod pa chung bas ’tsho ba dang| chog shes pas ’tsho ba dang| sbyangs pa’i yon tan gyi mig gis ’tsho ba dang| yang dag par mgu bar byed pas ’tsho ba la sogs pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":692,\"end\":896},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":692,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byed pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":896,\"end\":903},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":692,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":896,\"end\":903,\"uuid\":\"e86281ea-7f36-40fd-817d-59b97adf3bed\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ste| rang dgar spyod pa yin pa’i phyir ro| |de gnyi ga yongs su rdzogs pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":903,\"end\":981},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":903,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bya ba byas pa dang byed pa byas pa’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":981,\"end\":1017},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":903,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":981,\"end\":1017,\"uuid\":\"98ebaa1e-06bf-4101-87c1-ad41094141c7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1017,\"end\":1019},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1017,\"end\":1019,\"uuid\":\"8dbdd1c6-d31c-41eb-ba0f-364c77b2e3e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 25.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1019,\"end\":1073}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ee27689d-ffba-4f9d-a894-fab229faded6\",\"sort\":1000976,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.76\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1960,\"uuid\":\"ee27689d-ffba-4f9d-a894-fab229faded6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.7.a–b), the four types of burdens being laid down by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":79}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy ones\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":90},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"132bb858-ba28-4390-9506-e01c10d77932\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" indicate the different types of happiness that they enjoy, namely, (a) the burden of the constituents of experience (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":90,\"end\":208}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"skandha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":208,\"end\":215},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":208,\"end\":215,\"uuid\":\"bc2f2bbc-4d05-4e7b-8a39-a1f0e52e0ec3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") that is renounced because they have renunciation through their complete knowing of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":300}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suffering\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":300,\"end\":309},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca\",\"uuid\":\"fe94e617-18b5-4efe-8e18-f4dc39367f49\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and hence they enjoy the happiness of being free of the constituents of experience; (b) the burden of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":309,\"end\":417}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":417,\"end\":438},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"6200f4d5-a619-4ab5-8967-e427e8929645\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is given up because they have given up by eliminating the cause, and hence they enjoy the happiness of liberation; (c) the burden of promises that has been brought to completion because they themselves have been brought to completion through cultivating the path, and hence they enjoy the happiness of full awakening; and (d) the burden of heroic deeds that has been perfected, because they have become perfected through actualizing the cessation, and hence they enjoy the happiness of tranquility. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":438,\"end\":947}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":947,\"end\":948},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":947,\"end\":1726,\"uuid\":\"43fee1ec-5476-4b15-955d-b42a7cfc5cf2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"khur bor ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":948,\"end\":959},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":947,\"end\":1726,\"uuid\":\"43fee1ec-5476-4b15-955d-b42a7cfc5cf2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":948,\"end\":959,\"uuid\":\"088b0d3c-2772-4063-b342-f410d0ba6e9f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la khur ni bzhi ste| (a) phung po’i khur dang| (b) nyon mongs pa’i khur dang| (c) dam bca’ ba’i khur dang| (d) brtson pa’i khur ro| (a) |yongs su dor ba’i phyir dang| (b) rab tu spang ba’i phyir dang| (c) mthar phyin dang| (d) yongs su rdzogs par bya ba’i phyir| de dag go rims bzhin du (a) bor ba ste| yongs su dor ba dang| spangs pa dang| mthar phyin pa dang| yongs su rdzogs pa’o| (b) |de yang sdug bsngal yongs su shes pa dang| kun ’byung pa spangs pa dang| lam bsgoms pa dang| ’gog pa mngon sum du byas pas so| (c) |de bor bas phung po med pa’i bde ba dang| rnam par grol ba’i bde ba dang| rdzogs pa’i byang chub kyi bde ba dang| nye bar zhi ba’i bde ba thob pa’o| (d) |de bas na khur bor ba nyid kyis khur por ba’i bde ba thob pa’i yon tan bstan to\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":959,\"end\":1726},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":959,\"end\":1726,\"uuid\":\"43fee1ec-5476-4b15-955d-b42a7cfc5cf2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 26. Note: The translation of RK’s commentary combines the statements, reasons, and benefits into four sentences, even though the Tibetan has RK’s explanation in three separate blocks.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1726,\"end\":1960}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f568d5d7-2887-4642-8505-4cd1d964d0d1\",\"sort\":1000990,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.77\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":663,\"uuid\":\"f568d5d7-2887-4642-8505-4cd1d964d0d1\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.7.b), the attainment of one’s own beneﬁt has two aspects, namely, getting rid of what is harmful and attaining the beneﬁt. Among these, the ﬁrst is when, because of getting rid of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":206}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":206,\"end\":215},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"362433be-848c-4108-9b6c-3f2ae76709f4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", one gets rid of all the obscurations of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":257}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"emotional defilements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":257,\"end\":278},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"uuid\":\"2d6dc869-9959-4869-b72e-67d43e31c59b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The second is when, because of giving rise to knowledge (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":278,\"end\":337}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rig pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":337,\"end\":343},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":337,\"end\":343,\"uuid\":\"921ca3ec-5bc6-4483-9f74-47fc956ddfaa\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), one achieves nirvāna. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":343,\"end\":372}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":372,\"end\":373},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":372,\"end\":662,\"uuid\":\"b7098e6b-1670-4bc5-a74c-4b93c3e4d0a4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bdag gi don rjes su thob pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":373,\"end\":400},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":372,\"end\":662,\"uuid\":\"b7098e6b-1670-4bc5-a74c-4b93c3e4d0a4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":373,\"end\":400,\"uuid\":\"001bf69b-5251-4d9f-8393-922bceaabc03\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni rang gi don thob pa la rnam pa gnyis te| gnod pa spangs pa dang| don thob pa’o| |de la dang po ni ma rig pa spangs pas nyon mongs pa’i sgrib pa thams cad spangs pa’o| |gang yang rig pa bskyod pas mya ngan las ’das pa thob pa ste| de ni gnyis pa’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":400,\"end\":662},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":400,\"end\":662,\"uuid\":\"b7098e6b-1670-4bc5-a74c-4b93c3e4d0a4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":662,\"end\":663}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"411806d0-8ac1-40b8-a4df-60e0bce60733\",\"sort\":1001002,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.78\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1591,\"uuid\":\"411806d0-8ac1-40b8-a4df-60e0bce60733\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.7.b), these are the causes for persons to have nine types of “worldly ties”: because of their connection with worldly existence, there is (a) wrong view, (b) clinging, (c) doubt, (d) jealousy, (e) miserliness, (f) aversion, (g) pride, (h) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":265}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ignorance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":265,\"end\":274},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"uuid\":\"e75b0087-ffce-4948-8ffc-41bbdb6a869f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and (i) desire for the world. “Exhausted” means destroyed. Out of those, the ﬁrst three (a−c) are “exhausted” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":274,\"end\":387}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":387,\"end\":393},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":387,\"end\":393,\"uuid\":\"bbef0853-b6c2-47b0-9b42-cbbf9831a814\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") by the accurate view without worldly inﬂuence (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":393,\"end\":442}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"anāsravaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":442,\"end\":451},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":442,\"end\":451,\"uuid\":\"3b95e612-72b0-45c0-a082-2a9a48f68023\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). The middle three, (d−f)‍—and part of the ninth, (i), which concerns the desire realm‍—are exhausted by concentrating in the samādhi without worldly inﬂuence. The remainder, (g−i), are exhausted through knowing on the path of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":451,\"end\":679}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy ones\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":679,\"end\":690},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"a7f86b52-1011-44fe-9558-efb03cd6ef26\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":696}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"srid par kun tu sbyor ba yongs su zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":696,\"end\":736},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":696,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":696,\"end\":736,\"uuid\":\"e73d3612-df21-4a78-a877-3ee444957185\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni srid par kun tu sbyor ba ni dgu ste| skyes bu srid par sbyor bar byed pa dang| srid par ’ching bar byed pa’i phyir (a) lta ba dang| (b) mchog tu ’dzin pa dang| (c) the tshom dang (d) phrag dog dang|(e) ser sna dang| (f) khong khro dang|(g) nga rgyal dang|(h) ma rig pa dang|(i) srid pa’i ’dod chags so| |lta ba la sogs pa yang yin kun tu sbyor ba yang yin pas lta ba la sogs pa kun tu sbyor ro| |’di dag \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":736,\"end\":1156},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":736,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yongs su zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1156,\"end\":1171},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":736,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1156,\"end\":1171,\"uuid\":\"126d8d44-86f0-4125-97e7-2c75617b6eb7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" gang yin pa de ni de skad du brjod do| |yongs su zad pa ni rab tu nyams pa’o| (a−c) |de las dang po gsum ni zag pa med pa’i yang dag par lta bas zad pa’o| (d−f) |bar ma gsum dang dgu pa’i phyogs gcig ’dod pa’i khams kyi phyogs ni zag pa med pa’i ting nge ’dzin la snyoms par ’jug pas \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1171,\"end\":1456},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1171,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1456,\"end\":1462},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1171,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1456,\"end\":1462,\"uuid\":\"864c04fe-93a1-41f1-9521-227a36f9b920\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| (g−i) |lhag ma gsum ni dgra bcom pa’i lam gyi ye shes kyis \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1462,\"end\":1525},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1462,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1525,\"end\":1531},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1462,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1525,\"end\":1531,\"uuid\":\"40875a35-ee5f-44cc-9827-203e83983ceb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1531,\"end\":1533},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1531,\"end\":1533,\"uuid\":\"458d1742-b90b-4fed-bcb7-4df1b9a85a3c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 26–27.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1533,\"end\":1591}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"90ffdda0-7614-4241-818d-468d7a4f74c4\",\"sort\":1001021,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.79\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":299,\"uuid\":\"90ffdda0-7614-4241-818d-468d7a4f74c4\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.7.b–8.a), the term “accurate understanding” here indicates their firm belief in the qualities of the Three Jewels, in the teachings of the three vehicles, in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":188}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"four truths\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":188,\"end\":199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1cfd14aa-6bcf-4933-88fc-6f08baeebd29\",\"uuid\":\"d66c66d5-a8d5-41d7-8c08-3cb1f1730d57\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":199,\"end\":212}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"thirty-seven factors in awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":212,\"end\":245},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c542957b-778b-4c58-9fd1-cd0bce29cc00\",\"uuid\":\"62f925ef-7d04-44f6-92a7-a4444d3c8a7e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 27.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":245,\"end\":299}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"411bbe0e-c251-4cb7-b89d-0218573d47fa\",\"sort\":1001027,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.80\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":687,\"uuid\":\"411bbe0e-c251-4cb7-b89d-0218573d47fa\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.8.a), they were able to concentrate themselves in the nine concentrations (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":101}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"samādhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":101,\"end\":108},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":101,\"end\":108,\"uuid\":\"da4cdc35-4efd-4ab0-97e7-f4e13996b47a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), to remain in them, to get up from them, and to stop them as they wished, whenever they wished, and to whatever extent they wished, in the order of ascending, descending, and so on. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":296}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yang dag pa’i shes pas sems shin tu rnam par grol ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":296,\"end\":348},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":296,\"end\":633,\"uuid\":\"88ccaf77-8de8-484f-9d45-b58a4cf7d5c6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":296,\"end\":348,\"uuid\":\"91b7f0a2-d7ad-4e41-971a-5d147e9cbc34\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la yang dag pa’i shes pa ni yang dag pa’i rtog pa des sems shin tu rnam par grol ba’o| |yang dag par mos pa ste gang du mos she na dkon mchog gsum gyi yon tan dang| theg pa gsum dang ldan | |pa ston pa dag dang| bden pa bzhi dang| byang chub kyi phyogs kyi chos rnams la’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":348,\"end\":633},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":348,\"end\":633,\"uuid\":\"88ccaf77-8de8-484f-9d45-b58a4cf7d5c6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 27.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":633,\"end\":687}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9afe2818-6a0a-487f-84cb-ea3d9a38f626\",\"sort\":1001034,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.81\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Thus did I hear at one time. The Blessed One was dwelling at Vulture Peak near Rājagṛha together with a great monastic gathering of one thousand two hundred and fifty monks. They were all worthy ones‍—that is, they had eliminated the worldly influences, they had no emotional defilements, they had become self-controlled, they had utterly liberated their mindsets, they had utterly liberated their discernment, they were noble, they were exemplary, they had completed the work to be done, they had accomplished the tasks, they had laid down their burdens, they had attained the benefits for themselves, they had completely exhausted the ties to worldly existence, they had the mindset utterly liberated through accurate understanding, and they had succeeded in reaching the supreme perfection of mastery over all their mental faculties‍—with the exception of one single person, the venerable Ānanda.\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":10019,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c925f1d-7500-47c6-b369-64db9a95a9ec\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-421\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1046,\"uuid\":\"9afe2818-6a0a-487f-84cb-ea3d9a38f626\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The translation “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":17}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"venerable\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":17,\"end\":26},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91107107-3f31-4442-8365-9099041efadf\",\"uuid\":\"39d77512-ce7c-43ba-a94b-e352246ab543\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” is based on the Pali \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":26,\"end\":49}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āyasmant\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":57},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":57,\"uuid\":\"e2b07720-3f44-4e74-b8a2-2dd1cbd52ccb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Pi-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" because it has become somewhat of a standard English term. That said, according to Ratnākara (F.8.a), the Sanskrit term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":57,\"end\":178}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āyuṣmant\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":178,\"end\":186},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":178,\"end\":186,\"uuid\":\"ba298e48-41f8-4935-ba9d-810de493a691\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" literally means “full of life” and should be understood as follows: “Life” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":263}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āyus\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":267},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":267,\"uuid\":\"fa8ce6ed-f9a9-418e-a017-8f3d426b1de2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), the first part of the Sanskrit compound word, refers to something people want because it brings joy. When someone is “full of” (-\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":267,\"end\":399}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mant\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":403},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":403,\"uuid\":\"b72db094-7150-48f7-adfc-01cf83256f18\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") that, he or she is cheerful. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":403,\"end\":438}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tshe dang ldan pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":438,\"end\":455},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":438,\"end\":590,\"uuid\":\"f4afe4fa-838a-4c3a-9087-f15c9648357a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":438,\"end\":455,\"uuid\":\"36dfcec4-db08-445b-9cba-d40cb55bcbed\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba’i khyad par ni dga’ bar bya ba’i phyir te| ’jig rten na tshe ’di ’dod pa yin no| |de bas de dang ldan pa ni dga’ ba yin no\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":455,\"end\":590},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":455,\"end\":590,\"uuid\":\"f4afe4fa-838a-4c3a-9087-f15c9648357a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 27. According to Hari (11), since it refers to someone whose life is desired, the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":590,\"end\":728}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"venerable\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":728,\"end\":737},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":728,\"end\":737,\"uuid\":\"4dd2ea71-7575-4426-bd59-05441b0cf3b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"distinct\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91107107-3f31-4442-8365-9099041efadf\",\"uuid\":\"3d8e20c1-2e32-4dee-9fea-bc281fd7b803\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is an expression venerating the welfare and happiness (of being a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":737,\"end\":804}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"monk\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":804,\"end\":808},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1edbce5c-7c22-429e-9fa2-11fdfaa759bb\",\"uuid\":\"fd7ea11b-3a3d-4872-a38a-c7503dfc28c8\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Hari: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":808,\"end\":817}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ākāṃkṣitāyur bhavato ity āyuṣmān hita­sukha­pūjāvācakaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":817,\"end\":872},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":817,\"end\":872,\"uuid\":\"4a0be9f2-a775-41f2-8cc5-282108fe0711\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For information on the slightly different understanding of the epithet in Paḷi sources, see, e.g., PTSD \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":872,\"end\":978}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āyusmant\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":978,\"end\":986},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":978,\"end\":986,\"uuid\":\"333396f6-8bc7-4efb-b1bc-c89cce70289d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Pi-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“feeling vitality”) with PTSD \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":986,\"end\":1018}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āyasmant\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1018,\"end\":1026},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1018,\"end\":1026,\"uuid\":\"57145b30-bdee-4c53-8a1a-cac410aafe56\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Pi-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“old, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1026,\"end\":1034}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"venerable\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1034,\"end\":1043},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91107107-3f31-4442-8365-9099041efadf\",\"uuid\":\"1937b3fd-29a1-44cd-bbe7-2c3425521d6a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1043,\"end\":1046}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"04fbd67e-4f90-4df1-a865-879f20da1f4d\",\"sort\":1001061,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.82\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"At that time, the Blessed One addressed the elder, the venerable Subhūti: “Subhūti, starting from the perfection of wisdom, please illuminate for the bodhisattva great beings the way that bodhisattva great beings should go completely beyond cyclic existence in the perfection of wisdom.”\",\"label\":\"1.3\",\"sort\":10084,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"010cb041-fa21-402d-9ec7-5a763164553d\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-437\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":615,\"uuid\":\"04fbd67e-4f90-4df1-a865-879f20da1f4d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This point corresponds to the beginning of Chapter 3 in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":60}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Twenty-Five Thousand, Hundred Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":98},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b5bc661c-d772-4d79-a58e-e3f8f88e5333\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and of Chapter 6 in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":98,\"end\":124}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eighteen Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":141},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"db83de0a-cbc0-49f1-841d-75b02bc63ef2\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". It comes so early in this chapter because the three long sūtras contain a long and detailed scene-setting introduction (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":141,\"end\":263}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nidāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":269},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":269,\"uuid\":\"0c60ae37-c52b-4821-82f5-504747d6160e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") (here in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":269,\"end\":284}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eight Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":298},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a18f482f-5c08-4d8d-95f3-ab9f0af01751\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" represented only by the opening “Thus did I hear…” statement and a brief description of the qualities of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":408}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciple\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":408,\"end\":416},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"f79808db-d7f8-4068-a0b9-10f4b23ca22c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" attendants), followed by the Buddha’s dialogue with \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":416,\"end\":469}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāriputra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":469,\"end\":478},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3df1bcb6-86da-4978-8191-8dbd8f56b919\",\"uuid\":\"2aa6e400-b7b8-43c0-827b-f7533e409e9b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and other \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":478,\"end\":489}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciples\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":489,\"end\":498},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"8ba4ec19-264a-4c76-a02c-1c54bbc20377\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" covered in Chapter 2 in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":498,\"end\":527}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Twenty-Five Thousand and Hundred Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":527,\"end\":568},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1b6bfae3-1191-4a5d-adb1-6453adb55113\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and in Chapters 2–6 in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":568,\"end\":597}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Eighteen Thousand\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":597,\"end\":614},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"325c8853-161c-4275-9a7a-1384ad5186a1\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":614,\"end\":615}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"93695e01-2b4e-4ccc-a94f-0058e4f56173\",\"sort\":1001081,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.83\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"At that time, the Blessed One addressed the elder, the venerable Subhūti: “Subhūti, starting from the perfection of wisdom, please illuminate for the bodhisattva great beings the way that bodhisattva great beings should go completely beyond cyclic existence in the perfection of wisdom.”\",\"label\":\"1.3\",\"sort\":10084,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"010cb041-fa21-402d-9ec7-5a763164553d\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-437\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":7005,\"uuid\":\"93695e01-2b4e-4ccc-a94f-0058e4f56173\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.8.b–9.a), the word “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"venerable\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":55},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91107107-3f31-4442-8365-9099041efadf\",\"uuid\":\"b8bd0bad-c4af-4e36-89b3-ee51592c85a3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” is as explained previously. An “elder” is worthy of offerings or veneration, because he or she is a leader (in the community). As a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":55,\"end\":189}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worthy one\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":189,\"end\":199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012\",\"uuid\":\"c3423857-287e-4dd8-a733-1fbb0e3f0469\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":199,\"end\":201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":208},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"0b12222f-a3d2-49ac-a955-d8d51a56d62f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is foremost among those who abide without conﬂict. The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":208,\"end\":264}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":264,\"end\":275},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"e0d4ba61-6fcc-425a-b572-8c4dd1c17459\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" “addressed” him for a purpose. “What is that?” He says, “Please \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":275,\"end\":340}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illuminate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":340,\"end\":350},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"6cf316fc-7948-48cd-85a2-ab05223841e4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” and so on. In this sentence, the word “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":350,\"end\":391}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":391,\"end\":398},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"5810dc24-c2fe-449d-b9e3-4faad946a84c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” is in the vocative to request something of him alone. “Please \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":398,\"end\":462}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illuminate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":462,\"end\":472},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"479d6f58-9770-4110-a0a5-e5804d9f0951\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” means make yourself have the presence of mind to explain. Although a request (for teaching) should be made to a guru and not to a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":472,\"end\":604}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciple\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":604,\"end\":612},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"47336207-842d-40ee-acb0-3d833a555f52\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", this request is made just to ensure that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":612,\"end\":659}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciples\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":659,\"end\":668},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"00ada60e-292c-4bfa-b81a-267c9637f59d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" respect the Dharma, since it will be explained later that the elder \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":668,\"end\":737}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":737,\"end\":744},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"0d794e11-8649-4b14-8004-000c1ac935b7\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" stands on the ground of having accomplished the task of the perfection of wisdom. Starting with what topic? The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":744,\"end\":857}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":857,\"end\":868},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"d4ef89ee-37bf-4b37-844f-126e23960119\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" says “starting with the perfection of wisdom.” Here, the perfection of wisdom refers to the dharmakāya and its activity (i.e., the final of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":868,\"end\":1013}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1013,\"end\":1021},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"dd609b50-52e0-4d62-817c-1ec48a28d19a\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s eight realizations), because (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1021,\"end\":1054}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1054,\"end\":1061},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"087fbddf-f8fd-45c9-847e-066f516cc4f1\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is to start with) the fruit of the perfection of wisdom. He should explain “starting with” that fruit‍—i.e., about it‍—because it is the supreme goal of persons. One might wonder for whose sake he should “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1061,\"end\":1267}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illuminate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1267,\"end\":1277},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"9ab05998-d4a1-4d6f-a358-44c461e3e582\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” this. So the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1277,\"end\":1292}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1292,\"end\":1303},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"02be9ab8-6216-4ae6-b8f3-7d9030ce9305\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" says “for the bodhisattva \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1303,\"end\":1330}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1330,\"end\":1342},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e\",\"uuid\":\"184f44c8-6e29-40bf-ad78-c7485ed30f1a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” meaning for their sake. Then, one might wonder about the nature of what is to be \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1342,\"end\":1426}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illuminated\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1426,\"end\":1437},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"90cd34ba-202d-4a01-8194-3bfba311c893\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". So he says “the way that” and so on. “The way that” means the manner in which, i.e., through hearing, contemplating, and cultivating. “In the perfection of wisdom” means in the three kinds of complete knowing (i.e., the first three of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1437,\"end\":1678}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1678,\"end\":1686},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f00099b3-7191-45ad-a3dd-ff9a54286a6f\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s eight realizations). It says “in” it because the perfection of wisdom is the path and the path is the basis for going. In it, one should “go beyond,” i.e., go completely beyond. One might ask, “Where is one to go?” First, the practice, then the culminating practice, then the successive practice, and the final (instantaneous) practice (i.e., the fourth through seventh of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1686,\"end\":2066}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2066,\"end\":2074},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"56c6cd68-5c69-4760-8c05-b39148ff156a\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s eight realizations). One should go completely (through those). Thus, the eight realizations are all explained through this pair of terms (i.e., the terms “perfection of wisdom” and “going beyond”). “Who should go beyond?” He says the bodhisattva \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2074,\"end\":2323}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2323,\"end\":2335},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e\",\"uuid\":\"754c2b16-753e-4743-a891-ac50fe64d224\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—meaning those who have developed the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2335,\"end\":2374}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2374,\"end\":2394},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"d1bde0bf-5bd3-4955-9e94-2af58b84f176\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"… With the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2394,\"end\":2405}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2405,\"end\":2416},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"b5de02b3-8afc-4dc7-a441-adc355724f6e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s two terms, namely “bodhisattva” and “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2416,\"end\":2456}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great being\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2456,\"end\":2467},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e\",\"uuid\":\"61236566-80ba-44b2-95fb-6de433c2241b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” he teaches the development of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2467,\"end\":2504}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2504,\"end\":2524},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"3adfd9aa-526c-4ae0-9383-bc5af142db89\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (the first subtopic). In the first term, “bodhisattva,” \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2524,\"end\":2581}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sattva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2581,\"end\":2587},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2581,\"end\":2587,\"uuid\":\"8d6f46c7-6adf-42c5-ae94-83b90c94128d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" means the person who has the intention, wish, and desire for the highest \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2587,\"end\":2661}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2661,\"end\":2666},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2661,\"end\":2666,\"uuid\":\"a0700f0d-b501-466b-a3ce-cb749716ab21\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", i.e., perfect, complete awakening. In the second term, “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2666,\"end\":2724}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great being\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2724,\"end\":2735},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e\",\"uuid\":\"97c4027d-5edd-4f47-9e17-614b713ac5ff\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” the word “great” refers to any desire to achieve the most supreme awakening on behalf of sentient beings. So “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2735,\"end\":2848}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"great being\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2848,\"end\":2859},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e\",\"uuid\":\"66c2693c-c111-4731-965a-bc3b289b3d73\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” refers to a being of great courage. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2859,\"end\":2901}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2901,\"end\":2902},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2901,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tshe dang ldan pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2902,\"end\":2919},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2901,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2902,\"end\":2919,\"uuid\":\"8bf488c1-5292-4160-b88c-1416d1ec9696\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni snga ma bzhin no| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2919,\"end\":2953},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2919,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnas brtan\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2953,\"end\":2963},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2919,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2953,\"end\":2963,\"uuid\":\"36b468ee-1051-4ca6-8e21-169cfb42c392\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes smos pa ni mchod pa’i don te glang po chen po yin pa’i phyir ro| |de yang dgra bcom pa nyid yod na nyon mongs pa med pa la gnas pa’i mchog yin pa’i phyir ro| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2963,\"end\":3128},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2963,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bka’ stsal te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3128,\"end\":3141},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2963,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3128,\"end\":3141,\"uuid\":\"1b78fb44-843a-4062-b505-70587c965bb4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni rab tu sbyar ba’i phyir ro| |ji ltar zhe na? \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3141,\"end\":3202},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3141,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"spobs par gyis shig\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3202,\"end\":3221},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3141,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3202,\"end\":3221,\"uuid\":\"c568d7f4-0a71-4df4-b731-404d370449c9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" |ces bya ba la sogs pa gsungs te| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3221,\"end\":3256},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3221,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rab ’byor\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3256,\"end\":3265},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3221,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3256,\"end\":3265,\"uuid\":\"4ec9cad5-a856-45db-b2b1-ef842ddc57fa\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni bod pa’i tshig go| |de nyid la gsol ba gdab pa’i phyir| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3265,\"end\":3337},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3265,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"spobs par gyis shig\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3337,\"end\":3356},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3265,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3337,\"end\":3356,\"uuid\":\"2e079635-72e3-4f2b-85a5-faed7e3e53f2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni khyed kyi blo mngon du phyogs par gyis shig pa yin no| |gal te yang bla ma la gsol ba gdab cing slob ma la ma yin pa de lta mod kyis| gsol ba gdab pa de ni chos la gus pa bya ba nyid de| de ltar yang gnas brtan rab ’byor ni shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa la bya ba byas par gnas pa yin no| |zhes ’chad par ’gyur bas so| |gang gis dbang du byas she na| gsungs pa \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3356,\"end\":3735},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3356,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab kyi pha ral tu phyin pa las brtsams te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3735,\"end\":3782},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3356,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3735,\"end\":3782,\"uuid\":\"5bb65a9e-148b-40ea-afd3-a36c89a1c359\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" | zhes gsungs te| shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa’i ’bras bu yin pa’i phyir shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa ste| chos kyi sku | |mdzad pa dang bcas pa’o| |de las \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3782,\"end\":3947},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3782,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"btsams pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3947,\"end\":3956},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3782,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3947,\"end\":3956,\"uuid\":\"fa880108-6564-4d6f-8e8c-ff2cc5633c3d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni skyes bu dam pa’i don gyi phyir te| thabs las byung ba nyid yin pas de bstan zhes bya ba’i don to| |gang gi phyir spobs par byed ce na| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3956,\"end\":4096},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3956,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byang chub sems dpa’ sems dpa’ chen po rnams\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4096,\"end\":4140},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3956,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4096,\"end\":4140,\"uuid\":\"350d6863-3b46-484b-ad5f-02ccd111622f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes gsungs te| de rnams kyi don zhes bya ba’i don te| |gang gi phyir de’i don gyi phyir rgyu mtshan dang| rgyu mtshan can gyi ’brel ba ste| de bas ’brel ba tsam smra bar ’dod pa’i drug po khyad par brjod par ’dod pa ni bzhi bar ’gyur ro| |de nas gang gi bdag nyid du spobs par bya zhe na? gsungs pa| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4140,\"end\":4442},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4140,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ci nas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4442,\"end\":4448},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4140,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4442,\"end\":4448,\"uuid\":\"0e61b872-ae55-42f3-b7e6-0a4a3adce78f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pa ste| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4448,\"end\":4477},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4448,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ci nas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4477,\"end\":4483},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4448,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4477,\"end\":4483,\"uuid\":\"63caf2f4-31d2-4cbd-8d7d-f95ffc64c419\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni bar du’o| |thob pa dang bsam pa dang bsgom pa’i rang bzhin gyi shes rab kyi pha rol phyin pa thams cad mkhyen pa nyid rnam pa gsum yin te| gang gi phyir de ni lam yin te| lam yang ’gro ba’i gzhi ste| nges par ’byung ba dang ba dang ma lus pa ’gro bar gyis shig pa’o| |’gro ba des cir ’gyur zhe na? sbyor ba dang| sbyor ba’i rab dang| sbyor ba’i go rims dang| sbyor ba’i mtha’o| |de dag lus pa med par gyis shig pa’o| |de ltar tshig gnyis pi de ni mngon par rtogs pa brgyad rab tu ston cig pa’i| |gang nges par ’byung bar ’gyur zhe na? byang chub sems dpa’ sems dpa’ chen po zhes gsungs so| |byang chub tu sems bskyed pa nyid ces bya ba’i don to|… |de bas na bcom ldan ’das kyis dang po’i tshig gnyis po ’dis \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4483,\"end\":5207},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4483,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems bskyed pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5207,\"end\":5221},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4483,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5207,\"end\":5221,\"uuid\":\"55713f77-23b6-473c-8dd2-6d74024bf895\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" gsungs so| | \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5221,\"end\":5235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5221,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byang chub\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5235,\"end\":5245},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5221,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5235,\"end\":5245,\"uuid\":\"17773a30-e28e-4be7-ad10-e6bd85bbe025\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni yang dag par rdzogs pa’i byang chub| khyad par du gyur pa de la ’dis sems pa dang| bsam pa dang ’dod pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5245,\"end\":5356},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5245,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems dpa’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5356,\"end\":5365},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5245,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5356,\"end\":5365,\"uuid\":\"a2dc61f7-b777-42b6-95e9-7890fbbdbc60\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" o| |sems can thams cad kyi mchog tu byed par ’dod pa gang yin pa de ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5365,\"end\":5437},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5365,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"chen po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5437,\"end\":5444},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5365,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5437,\"end\":5444,\"uuid\":\"6e31096e-0ba5-4f55-a331-648aa36c7aea\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ste| sems can chen po ni ’dir \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5444,\"end\":5475},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5444,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems dpa’ chen pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5475,\"end\":5492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5444,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5475,\"end\":5492,\"uuid\":\"2474c252-1780-4b95-a81c-9d5b37311f20\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5492,\"end\":5494},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5492,\"end\":5494,\"uuid\":\"f3cda03f-214a-41de-acc8-7487ab342c15\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 28–29. According to Hari, since \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5494,\"end\":5578}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5578,\"end\":5585},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"5d244455-68dd-4e28-b9b3-0de5371e0df5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is there, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5585,\"end\":5600}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5600,\"end\":5611},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"680ed4c8-f103-47cb-874f-1a695eaf27a8\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", under the auspices of a Dharma teaching, says to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5611,\"end\":5662}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5662,\"end\":5669},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"08b4e5f1-9d87-4bbc-aaad-2cdf8c6a1a3f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5669,\"end\":5671}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illuminate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5671,\"end\":5681},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"4765be10-2a92-4908-86b6-8e8f6802fa75\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” and so on. This means come face to face (with the perfection of wisdom, so that you can be courageously eloquent about it), in all respects, with the special knowledges of things, meanings, expressions, and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5681,\"end\":5890}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5890,\"end\":5902},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"4b630e44-791e-44c8-8d85-d492972b8b80\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Hari: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5902,\"end\":5910}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratibhātv\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5910,\"end\":5920},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5910,\"end\":6060,\"uuid\":\"13067d43-6346-4cf1-a87a-3cdcafe4fbf9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5910,\"end\":5920,\"uuid\":\"b33c7b6b-ea05-4e33-adb9-0cf4e7c4702b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ityādi. dharma­deśanādhikārād vidyamānatve ’pi he subhūte viśiṣṭa­dharmārtha­nirukti­pratibhāna­pratisaṃvit sarvathā \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5920,\"end\":6038},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5920,\"end\":6060,\"uuid\":\"13067d43-6346-4cf1-a87a-3cdcafe4fbf9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6038,\"end\":6040},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":5920,\"end\":6060,\"uuid\":\"13067d43-6346-4cf1-a87a-3cdcafe4fbf9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6038,\"end\":6040,\"uuid\":\"be99e1b6-15ce-46de-ac1b-31fb82b9390f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" tavābhimukhībhavatu\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6040,\"end\":6060},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6040,\"end\":6060,\"uuid\":\"13067d43-6346-4cf1-a87a-3cdcafe4fbf9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Note: RK is explaining how this single sentence by the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6060,\"end\":6117}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6117,\"end\":6128},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"b1017235-1d99-4eb8-b461-f60091ee6e5c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is suggesting he explain all eight of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6128,\"end\":6171}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6171,\"end\":6179},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b1ede4fc-03cd-48a9-82be-fce3cf502d7a\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s eight realizations. RK’s comments also include a justification of some grammar that has not been translated here. Hari gives an extensive commentary on the entire sentence that is very much worth reading but is too long and complex to include here. The particular manner in which \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6179,\"end\":6462}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6462,\"end\":6469},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"614de987-c48d-4deb-847b-f0376ecd56ba\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" will “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6469,\"end\":6476}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illuminate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6476,\"end\":6486},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"ba98f989-f50f-4d47-946f-c59a9b8b5b36\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” the perfection of wisdom provides the crucial context for understanding the first chapter, and arguably the whole scripture. For a brief overview of Ratnākara’s and Hari’s divergent explanations of the scripture’s topic as implied by this opening sentence, see Seton 2016, pp. 235–70. Note: Ratnākara is suggesting that the first sentence introduces the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6486,\"end\":6842}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6842,\"end\":6850},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4fa5e7e5-962a-4119-a8bb-9986c76f9292\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s first subtopic, “developing the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6850,\"end\":6885}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6885,\"end\":6905},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"22efc759-00f6-4769-90f3-c5ff4fbabbfa\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” which he explains in terms of twenty-two similes that can be subdivided into eighty dispositions.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6905,\"end\":7005}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4943e454-e79c-4a57-912d-4cf9ca2affb9\",\"sort\":1001200,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.84\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then, indeed, the venerable Śāriputra wondered to himself, “Will the elder, the venerable Subhūti, expound the perfection of wisdom to bodhisattva great beings on his own‍—by virtue of his previously developed reserve of strength in wisdom and illumination, that is to say, by virtue of his being blessed with the power of wisdom and illumination‍—or through the Buddha’s miraculous power?”\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"sort\":10103,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"45169038-69a3-463d-903b-8ca55f5a6267\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-440\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":928,\"uuid\":\"4943e454-e79c-4a57-912d-4cf9ca2affb9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Hari (28), \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":24}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":24,\"end\":36},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"ca15fd08-3b8c-469b-8efb-065f2181d853\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":38}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratibhāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":38,\"end\":48},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":38,\"end\":48,\"uuid\":\"fc07ea2d-884f-4ddb-863a-c0feaff80f60\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") is coherent, fluid expression. Hari: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":87}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratibhānaṃ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":98},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":118,\"uuid\":\"2d8c630c-c76c-4add-96d4-1b6b9474c60f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":98,\"uuid\":\"73fdead9-0966-4086-8fc9-06b773cfaf2b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" yuktamuktābhidhānaṃ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":98,\"end\":118},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":98,\"end\":118,\"uuid\":\"2d8c630c-c76c-4add-96d4-1b6b9474c60f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Cf. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":124}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Kośabhāṣya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":134},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"74b99215-7d81-4f7a-8bd5-d663cc7cc6b3\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Pradhan 418, pp. 17–18): “The special knowledge of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":134,\"end\":187}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":187,\"end\":199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"0310b057-49fb-4b45-8875-d515cec8817a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":199,\"end\":201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratibhāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":211},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":211,\"uuid\":\"f51ff407-8025-4506-9cc4-c74b83533ecd\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":216}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"beyond regressing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":216,\"end\":233},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0b8cae9c-affc-4153-9e88-da1b28c8ac37\",\"uuid\":\"c75f36e2-d95a-4969-8370-5afd817b84a6\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", intuitive knowing at play in coherent, fluid expressions, and clarifications arising from the mastery of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":233,\"end\":340}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":340,\"end\":364},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"07a8cb0b-9c5b-46fc-8b44-63aa12b4c002\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".” (Note that the translation “wisdom (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":364,\"end\":403}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":403,\"end\":409},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":403,\"end\":409,\"uuid\":\"43854e18-b823-429a-89b0-2156475ef1b6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":409,\"end\":415}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":415,\"end\":427},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"a7e9b4e4-474d-409c-9a35-bd70e75ac328\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”‍—rather than the Tibetan interpretation “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":427,\"end\":470}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":470,\"end\":482},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"uuid\":\"5919b293-d69b-4068-a525-afc6c13b3946\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of wisdom”‍—is based on Ratnākara’s (D11.b) gloss of the Sanskrit compound term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":482,\"end\":563}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prajñāpratibhāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":563,\"end\":579},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":563,\"end\":579,\"uuid\":\"67005860-d128-41f8-be7e-747b934111b6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 35.) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":579,\"end\":635}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yuktamukta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":635,\"end\":645},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":635,\"end\":645,\"uuid\":\"a45e8278-f951-41e7-ac83-058851c840d3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Tib. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":645,\"end\":652}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rigs pa dang grol ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":672},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":672,\"uuid\":\"60449d1a-f287-45e9-a2fe-14e07669ede1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") as a quality of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":672,\"end\":690}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratibhāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":700},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":700,\"uuid\":\"da40f789-1305-4996-aea0-a3fd22f82005\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is mentioned in a wide variety of canonical texts, including the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":700,\"end\":766}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vinayavibaṅgha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":766,\"end\":780},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"53f56284-0a26-447a-ad24-24f82761424a\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":780,\"end\":782}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Toh 3\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":782,\"end\":787},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6b171d08-533f-48b0-951a-2a20d85f15d1\",\"href\":\"/translation/toh3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":787,\"end\":793}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vinayottaragrantha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":793,\"end\":811},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"93962617-7339-4760-9d48-c696b8edf634\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":811,\"end\":813}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Toh 7a\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":813,\"end\":819},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"bac9fcf2-5016-4894-8631-9b3bcb98e61e\",\"href\":\"/translation/toh7a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and many of the Vinaya commentaries in the Tengyur. See also \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":819,\"end\":882}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Upholding the Roots of Virtue\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":882,\"end\":911},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ab7113fe-9ed6-494f-979c-f94e8360199a\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Toh 101), \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":911,\"end\":923}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"n.73\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":923,\"end\":927},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6217c70a-008c-4360-9087-c3573e57cc4c\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/43103fe8-a6c6-411a-add1-eb81e703edb2\",\"entity\":\"43103fe8-a6c6-411a-add1-eb81e703edb2\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"subtype\":\"endnotes\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":927,\"end\":928}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"792c051e-e626-4bf7-84ef-7e418f0035ec\",\"sort\":1001245,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.85\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then, through the miraculous power of the Buddha, the venerable Subhūti knew in his mind that the venerable Śāriputra was having mental ruminations of these kinds and said to the venerable Śariputra, “O Venerable Śāriputra, everything that the Blessed One’s disciples say, teach, expound, express, clarify, or elucidate should be known as the Tathāgata’s personal doing. Why is that? It is because those disciples who train in the Dharma taught by the Tathāgata actualize the true nature of things and keep it in mind. Once they have actualized the true nature of things and kept it in mind, absolutely nothing that they say, teach, expound, express, clarify, or elucidate is in conflict with the true nature of things. O Śāriputra, it is a natural outcome of the Tathāgata’s Dharma teaching itself that those noble scions, when expounding the true nature of things, do not contradict the true nature of things.”\",\"label\":\"1.5\",\"sort\":10126,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"692c9c42-379a-465d-9559-b91dcd761d9c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-442\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":570,\"uuid\":\"792c051e-e626-4bf7-84ef-7e418f0035ec\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The terms “person’s doing” and “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":32}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"natural outcome\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":32,\"end\":47},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"4b3ebecf-a9c7-4879-af93-23f6a94d45ec\",\"uuid\":\"d50366a0-9440-434f-a03c-06df5dc0090b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” are technical terms for two among the five classifications of results, namely, (1) the result of ripening (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":47,\"end\":156}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"vipākaphala\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":156,\"end\":167},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":156,\"end\":167,\"uuid\":\"d8ae1469-1f67-44d5-873f-e877591b1b5b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), (2) the result that is the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":167,\"end\":197}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"natural outcome\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":197,\"end\":212},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"4b3ebecf-a9c7-4879-af93-23f6a94d45ec\",\"uuid\":\"100c1e2b-0450-4a0d-b567-5c2a941359bb\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":212,\"end\":214}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"niṣyandaphalā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":214,\"end\":227},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":214,\"end\":227,\"uuid\":\"21cf482f-ea00-48a0-9187-aa979c59432c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), (3) the result that is predominant (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":227,\"end\":266}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"adhipatiphala\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":266,\"end\":279},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":266,\"end\":279,\"uuid\":\"0cb22f46-be1d-46cd-96a7-3957b16f7015\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), (4) the result of a person’s doing (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":279,\"end\":318}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"puruṣakaraphala\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":318,\"end\":333},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":318,\"end\":333,\"uuid\":\"c5dd674a-158b-449b-a192-fe61e2fc7d6b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), and (5) the result of divestment (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":333,\"end\":370}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"visaṃyogaphala\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":370,\"end\":384},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":370,\"end\":384,\"uuid\":\"4eafa972-d2e2-45de-9564-82a3e0f375a8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). For more on these, see, for instance, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":384,\"end\":429}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Abhidharma­samuccayabhāṣya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":429,\"end\":455},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ec5be9c8-c9ad-4443-bb50-b051859a2a59\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Tatia 1976, p. 110). For edited Tibetan text of Ratnākara’s comments on this section, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 37.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":455,\"end\":570}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"10742a4d-5564-46f8-98ce-2b52aa5e6f1e\",\"sort\":1001263,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.86\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then, through the miraculous power of the Buddha, the venerable Subhūti knew in his mind that the venerable Śāriputra was having mental ruminations of these kinds and said to the venerable Śariputra, “O Venerable Śāriputra, everything that the Blessed One’s disciples say, teach, expound, express, clarify, or elucidate should be known as the Tathāgata’s personal doing. Why is that? It is because those disciples who train in the Dharma taught by the Tathāgata actualize the true nature of things and keep it in mind. Once they have actualized the true nature of things and kept it in mind, absolutely nothing that they say, teach, expound, express, clarify, or elucidate is in conflict with the true nature of things. O Śāriputra, it is a natural outcome of the Tathāgata’s Dharma teaching itself that those noble scions, when expounding the true nature of things, do not contradict the true nature of things.”\",\"label\":\"1.5\",\"sort\":10126,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"692c9c42-379a-465d-9559-b91dcd761d9c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-442\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1693,\"uuid\":\"10742a4d-5564-46f8-98ce-2b52aa5e6f1e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.11.b–12.a), here, among the six verbs beginning with “say” and so on, the first three are talking about just the words of the scripture. “Say” means talk about the scripture and so on to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":217}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":217,\"end\":228},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"f74ee1d6-8776-4f01-891c-9ecbbbf0f036\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s assembly; “teach” means talk about this existence and so on to them; “expound” means talking about it to anyone to be tamed after going (to other assemblies) in the different directions; “express” means teach the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":228,\"end\":444}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":444,\"end\":455},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"81606dcc-b758-438e-9cfc-ec1e79bc4195\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s assembly whatever the scripture’s topics are; “clarify” means teach precisely that to others; and “elucidate” means explain it by oneself after going (to other assemblies). RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":455,\"end\":635}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":635,\"end\":636},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":635,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"smra ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":636,\"end\":643},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":635,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":636,\"end\":643,\"uuid\":\"faf5d6b8-328d-4675-a0c3-9fdadeb08a19\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pa’i tshig drug ste| |de la dang po’i gsum gyis ni mdo la sogs pa’i tshig brjod do| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":643,\"end\":749},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":643,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"smra ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":749,\"end\":756},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":643,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":749,\"end\":756,\"uuid\":\"3ab7321f-6160-49e5-8ba5-093777d38eb6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni bcom ldan ’das kyi ’khor rnams la mdo la sogs pa smra ba’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":756,\"end\":821},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":756,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ston pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":821,\"end\":828},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":756,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":821,\"end\":828,\"uuid\":\"bf3a8865-9d1b-4af3-9377-b2b40baf4e69\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni de nyid du srid pa la sogs pa smra ba’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":828,\"end\":874},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":828,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"lung ’bogs pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":874,\"end\":887},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":828,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":874,\"end\":887,\"uuid\":\"a7076655-f262-4884-aa0a-cf0e5c0afc5d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni phyogs dag tu nye bar song nas gdul bya de dag la smra ba’o| |de ltar gang dang gang nyid kyi dngos po bcom ldan ’das kyi ’khor la \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":887,\"end\":1022},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":887,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"brjod pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1022,\"end\":1030},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":887,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1022,\"end\":1030,\"uuid\":\"bb1f983e-3a71-4407-89f6-6043a80a4b06\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni bcom ldan ’das kyi ’khor la bstan pa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1030,\"end\":1075},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1030,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’chad pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1075,\"end\":1083},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1030,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1075,\"end\":1083,\"uuid\":\"333ff215-9b05-422a-a40c-155f7f050abb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni de nyid du gzhan dag la bstan pa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1083,\"end\":1124},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1083,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yang dag par rab tu ston pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1124,\"end\":1151},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1083,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1124,\"end\":1151,\"uuid\":\"0f6773be-92dd-4223-8e18-0d6dfaaab835\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni kun tu song nas rang nyid ’chad pa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1151,\"end\":1194},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1151,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"smra ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1194,\"end\":1201},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1151,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1194,\"end\":1201,\"uuid\":\"ad9d156d-a93a-4fb4-a358-8e2136426607\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" la sogs pa de dag thams cad ni de bzhin gshegs pa’i skyes bu byed pa des byin gyis brlabs pa ’am mthu yin pa’i phyir nyan thos kyis ni ma yin te| rang dbang med pas so\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1201,\"end\":1369},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1201,\"end\":1369,\"uuid\":\"f2792292-93b0-4e9e-8d68-61ece277e6c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Note: This is a well-known early Buddhist principle. For instance, according to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1369,\"end\":1455}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Mahāvibhāṣāśāstra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1455,\"end\":1472},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8770cbc3-f352-4c8f-91ca-86a9ff3e93f8\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1472,\"end\":1478}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1478,\"end\":1489},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"uuid\":\"87094349-1c97-4622-93a6-dd0389ee309d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is said to have specifically allowed abhidharma specialists to teach anything that does not contradict the nature of the truth (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1489,\"end\":1618}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dharmatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1618,\"end\":1626},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1618,\"end\":1626,\"uuid\":\"e0f140ae-b5f9-4bf0-bd9b-8c2100187bb2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and so on. For more on this principle, see Dhammajoti 2015, p. 2.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1626,\"end\":1693}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d7616bc4-f7f4-42fa-bf9a-9835e830b706\",\"sort\":1001293,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.87\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then, through the miraculous power of the Buddha, the venerable Subhūti knew in his mind that the venerable Śāriputra was having mental ruminations of these kinds and said to the venerable Śariputra, “O Venerable Śāriputra, everything that the Blessed One’s disciples say, teach, expound, express, clarify, or elucidate should be known as the Tathāgata’s personal doing. Why is that? It is because those disciples who train in the Dharma taught by the Tathāgata actualize the true nature of things and keep it in mind. Once they have actualized the true nature of things and kept it in mind, absolutely nothing that they say, teach, expound, express, clarify, or elucidate is in conflict with the true nature of things. O Śāriputra, it is a natural outcome of the Tathāgata’s Dharma teaching itself that those noble scions, when expounding the true nature of things, do not contradict the true nature of things.”\",\"label\":\"1.5\",\"sort\":10126,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"692c9c42-379a-465d-9559-b91dcd761d9c\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-442\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"d7616bc4-f7f4-42fa-bf9a-9835e830b706\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See preceding note.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"023ec220-3e5d-4100-be52-31459e650dc0\",\"sort\":1001295,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.88\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3f\",\"label\":\"1.6\",\"sort\":10177,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5d9e0b5d-f97e-4659-86b1-59b2ce26b4e4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-446\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1344,\"uuid\":\"023ec220-3e5d-4100-be52-31459e650dc0\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.12.b), the different means of valid cognition (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":73}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pramāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":73,\"end\":80},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":73,\"end\":80,\"uuid\":\"89b29c58-b541-4586-bd90-25e74602b4e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":82}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tshad ma\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":90},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":90,\"uuid\":\"cedf0401-3967-4172-98bc-ea213dd19e72\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") are connected with three verbs used here: The phrase “do not find” means not to detect any real thing, based on the meaning of the word. The meaning is that a so-called bodhisattva is not perceived because, just like a hare’s horns, it is negated by reliable evidence. The phrase “do not mentally perceive” means through direct perception. Here, based on what is born from authoritative testimony, there is nonperception and negation. The phrase “do not identify” means through inference. Undeceived, knowledgeable ordinary and noble persons negate a so-called bodhisattva by correct inference regarding the logical consequences of such a view. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":90,\"end\":741}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":743},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":743,\"uuid\":\"a0fa6881-582a-4610-ab2f-9ad1c1a2ee0e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":743,\"end\":744},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":743,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’tshal\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":744,\"end\":750},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":743,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":744,\"end\":750,\"uuid\":\"9e654230-786c-45f1-9ed8-c097ef7ebe1f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni ma dmigs pa’o| |tshad mas gnod pa yin pa’i phyir ri bong gi rva bzhin no zhes bsams so| |de nyid la \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":750,\"end\":866},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":750,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":866,\"end\":873},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":750,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":866,\"end\":873,\"uuid\":\"8fa8aaba-13c0-4761-ada4-47b610c6b987\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" bstan pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":886},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi dmigs pa yang dag par rjes su ma mthong\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":886,\"end\":928},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":886,\"end\":928,\"uuid\":\"00648099-c32c-4cfb-907f-c3e378122a7c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":945},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi dmigs\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":945,\"end\":953},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":945,\"end\":953,\"uuid\":\"3488d794-a65a-4558-a0ba-1dee301549b6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni yid ches pa’i lung las skyes pa des mi dmigs shing gnod pa yin no| | \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":953,\"end\":1038},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":953,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yang dag par rjes su ma mthong\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1038,\"end\":1068},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":953,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1038,\"end\":1068,\"uuid\":\"4dc4b07b-3b95-4473-8ff7-9509f54b1754\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni mi slu ba dang mkhas pa’i skye bo dang thun mong yin pa’i phyir dang| lta ba’i rjes su ’gro ba’i rjes su dpag pa’i gnod pas \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1208},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yang dag par rjes su ma mthong ngo\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1208,\"end\":1242},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1208,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fe6a4b53-87af-4859-8ea6-d5e6716ef36f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1208,\"end\":1242,\"uuid\":\"fbd0b262-c91e-4df3-846e-e25ca30b0741\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text of Ratnākara’s comments on this section, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 38–39, 56.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1242,\"end\":1344}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9f0be5f2-5a59-471b-b8f8-649e752da280\",\"sort\":1001315,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.89\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$40\",\"label\":\"1.6\",\"sort\":10177,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5d9e0b5d-f97e-4659-86b1-59b2ce26b4e4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-446\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":900,\"uuid\":\"9f0be5f2-5a59-471b-b8f8-649e752da280\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.13.a), he says “nor…perfection of wisdom.” This means the grasper ceases and is not there, because what is (supposedly) grasped by it is not there. But the perfection of wisdom itself does not cease, because the denial here is of what is not appearing (i.e., grasper and grasped) in pure self-illumination (i.e., the perfection of wisdom itself). RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":377}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa yang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":414},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":573,\"uuid\":\"622b563b-a2bb-46c3-a9bc-432c965682d0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":414,\"uuid\":\"7e51c8a3-4848-4853-9c7d-682db698e48d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni ’dzin pa bkag cing med de de’i gzung ba med pa’i phyir ro| |de nyid dgag pa med de gsal ba yang dag par de nyid la gsal ba med pa’i gnod pas so\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":414,\"end\":573},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":414,\"end\":573,\"uuid\":\"622b563b-a2bb-46c3-a9bc-432c965682d0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text of Ratnākara’s comments, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 39. Note: This explanation is from the perspective of RK’s Yogācāra position, which takes the perfection of wisdom to be ultimately real, pure self-\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":573,\"end\":796}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":796,\"end\":808},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"05a3d610-b8c8-4534-bb60-f3ba86a5e76a\",\"uuid\":\"390c8d4c-c8c7-4c4e-a843-f9003337db98\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Hari takes the perfection of wisdom to be a relatively real perceiver of ultimate reality.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":808,\"end\":900}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"34496d15-990a-4082-9dad-c4f5e998c98d\",\"sort\":1001324,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.90\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$41\",\"label\":\"1.6\",\"sort\":10177,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5d9e0b5d-f97e-4659-86b1-59b2ce26b4e4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-446\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":534,\"uuid\":\"34496d15-990a-4082-9dad-c4f5e998c98d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.12.a–b), the repeated word “bodhisattva” in this sentence marks the transition to the subtopic “practical instructions” (the second subtopic of the first main topic in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":198}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":198,\"end\":206},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a742c101-2d17-446b-9f6f-4a81b192fe50\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", see introduction, “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":206,\"end\":227}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Synopsis of the Text According to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":227,\"end\":265},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"17b24778-d66e-4f56-8354-64a09accd1ba\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/a807e430-cb2c-4d11-8aec-20451daea2c4\",\"entity\":\"a807e430-cb2c-4d11-8aec-20451daea2c4\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"introductionHeader\",\"start\":227,\"end\":0}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":265,\"end\":273},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"17b24778-d66e-4f56-8354-64a09accd1ba\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/a807e430-cb2c-4d11-8aec-20451daea2c4\",\"entity\":\"a807e430-cb2c-4d11-8aec-20451daea2c4\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"introductionHeader\",\"start\":265,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c6adf01c-577f-4f59-9b64-eadca68e5442\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”). RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":273,\"end\":281}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de nas \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":281,\"end\":288},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":281,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gdams ngag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":298},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":281,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":288,\"end\":298,\"uuid\":\"4ef66416-d1a2-49e6-9c69-91198972f5de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" gi skabs la babs nas| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":321},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnas brtan rab ’byor gyis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":321,\"end\":346},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":321,\"end\":346,\"uuid\":\"be07b8a2-e45a-4322-a680-09c763cea4be\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ji skad bshad pa bzhin sdud pa pos| \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":346,\"end\":383},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":346,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de nas sangs rgyas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":383,\"end\":401},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":346,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":383,\"end\":401,\"uuid\":\"37a2e3fa-588a-4d8d-a630-8720dfb090ff\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pa smras so| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":401,\"end\":436},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":401,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byang chub sems dpa’ sems dpa’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":436,\"end\":466},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":401,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":436,\"end\":466,\"uuid\":\"b7ac3b7a-cbfa-40af-8527-db4fd1c3e613\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba’i tshig gnyis ni de dang de yin zhes rtogs par byed pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":466,\"end\":533},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":466,\"end\":533,\"uuid\":\"d6aeb877-8fd3-44cf-a520-6765379da795\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":533,\"end\":534}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e1f4d304-29f6-4b49-ba36-27b01ce2fd7e\",\"sort\":1001341,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.91\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$42\",\"label\":\"1.6\",\"sort\":10177,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5d9e0b5d-f97e-4659-86b1-59b2ce26b4e4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-446\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4100,\"uuid\":\"e1f4d304-29f6-4b49-ba36-27b01ce2fd7e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.14.a–b), (a) in the phrase “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":58}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":58,\"end\":65},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"56269faa-159e-4faf-91a8-e196eaa678cb\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" does not become deflated,” the “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":65,\"end\":98}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":98,\"end\":105},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"92b746de-4bde-4866-a61a-c2f0966ba36b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”‍—in thinking about the meaning as it has just been described‍—is “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":173}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not deflated\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":173,\"end\":185},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"6d36102c-6a9b-404a-8ce3-679bb37803ba\",\"uuid\":\"8da1b485-6341-4b97-8ab7-13f903f13894\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” i.e., not especially despondent, because he or she is reflecting upon that meaning (i.e., emptiness) alone; (b) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":185,\"end\":301}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not depressed\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":301,\"end\":314},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"775db351-7635-44f1-b090-e3f651a1564a\",\"uuid\":\"9ab8fb3f-738e-42af-9826-11a2d0b61e04\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” means while subsequently applying him- or herself continuously (to that meaning), even then he or she is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":314,\"end\":421}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not deflated\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":421,\"end\":433},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"6d36102c-6a9b-404a-8ce3-679bb37803ba\",\"uuid\":\"6eafdb87-3db2-45e4-83b3-f2213e707ed6\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; (c) “not dejected” means when he or she recollects (the meaning) after recognizing that the mind has wandered elsewhere because it was naturally distracted, he or she is not upset; (d) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":621}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not sunk in despondency\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":621,\"end\":644},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"12850e8f-bca6-487d-b286-8a071e49491f\",\"uuid\":\"5e68e9e1-6706-4184-bd12-3c780b196e7b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” means as his or her \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":644,\"end\":666}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":666,\"end\":673},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"70007189-d5cb-4ca1-a06f-0843be3168b0\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" has become very stable, when it gets increasingly subtle because of not proliferating into other coarse understandings, then he or she is not upset; (e) “his or her”‍—i.e., the bodhisattva’s‍—“\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":673,\"end\":867}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mental attitude\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":867,\"end\":882},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"71984920-52bd-485c-9f8f-1b4d1cb73d33\",\"uuid\":\"40fbff12-c71a-4acf-b39e-e027302f2f3a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" does not become discouraged” means with respect to that very state, he or she still pacifies the mind in order to remain neutral even while remaining in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":882,\"end\":1036}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1036,\"end\":1060},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"4947311e-7235-4c8b-95e2-95d0598ecf19\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", because he or she sees the qualities of meditativate concentration; (f) “not shattered” means he or she does not get distracted by the lack of joy or inclination in the light of the (meaning), because of seeing the faults of distraction; (g) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1060,\"end\":1305}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not frightened\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1305,\"end\":1319},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c1107eab-0344-42d0-a10b-9fb3e60276a1\",\"uuid\":\"06b18c74-4f57-46f1-bd97-8b87e463c0a3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” means even when covetousness or dissatisfaction arise, he or she does not get afraid and also overcomes that which arises, because he or she sees the faults of distraction. (h) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1319,\"end\":1499}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not terrified\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1499,\"end\":1512},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"57efd00f-92ad-481a-a867-0f0b22f88085\",\"uuid\":\"bfd8fae3-253d-4a34-ae66-3ad4cf0f2a5d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” means he or she is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1512,\"end\":1533}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not frightened\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1533,\"end\":1547},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c1107eab-0344-42d0-a10b-9fb3e60276a1\",\"uuid\":\"45c7b464-b890-40fa-ae78-310ca870d65d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" about the formation of any mental object that occurs of its own accord automatically in his or her mind that is free of faults, and hence he or she does that (i.e., declines to get involved in them); and (i) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1547,\"end\":1757}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"not stricken with terror\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1757,\"end\":1781},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2683095c-4a8b-4b93-a0f5-cb42d263f8e2\",\"uuid\":\"06e81522-a7e3-457a-ad04-dcc16da09dce\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” means his or her \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1781,\"end\":1800}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1800,\"end\":1807},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"9c804b5c-237c-49d4-bc55-2170d6436b98\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" becomes perfectly (settled), and without any effort he or she is neither terrified nor totally frightened by any occurrence in the mind, because he or she perceives the occurrences in a natural and spontaneous way. This is the meaning. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1807,\"end\":2048}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(a) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2048,\"end\":2052},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2048,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems mi zhum pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2052,\"end\":2067},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2048,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2052,\"end\":2067,\"uuid\":\"db7aadb7-55ac-40e5-a024-d41d8a724c05\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni ji ltar thob pa de nyid la don la sems pa la \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2067,\"end\":2128},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2067,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2128,\"end\":2132},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2067,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2128,\"end\":2132,\"uuid\":\"347bb32a-dcd7-4c63-82da-b31fbef2b65e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" khyad du mi gsod \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2132,\"end\":2150},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2132,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi zhum\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2150,\"end\":2157},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2132,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2150,\"end\":2157,\"uuid\":\"aaa3fbef-3a9d-407e-a5d8-a53dec179a8a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ste| de nyid du nges par brtag pa’i phyir ro|| (b) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2157,\"end\":2209},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2157,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kun tu zhum par mi bgyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2209,\"end\":2233},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2157,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2209,\"end\":2233,\"uuid\":\"8b05ec46-6abd-49d1-9edc-932da2435891\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni sems kyi rgyun du ’jug pa la yang rjes su mi ’brang zhing zhum par mi bgyid do| (c) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2233,\"end\":2333},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2233,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi ’gong\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2333,\"end\":2341},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2233,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2333,\"end\":2341,\"uuid\":\"7aa18a3c-4142-40c0-892a-bd414ab49984\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni sems rang bzhin gyis g.yo ba’i phyir| gzhan du song ba la yang kun nas shes par byas nas sdud pa na skyo ba med pa yin no| (d) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2341,\"end\":2485},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2341,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi gsod\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2485,\"end\":2492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2341,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2485,\"end\":2492,\"uuid\":\"f323aae1-49ef-46de-b05a-7d68b7f716bc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" [F.14v] \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2492,\"end\":2501},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2492,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"par mi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2501,\"end\":2507},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2492,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2501,\"end\":2507,\"uuid\":\"773f38b3-d29d-442d-ace0-38eff6f66c42\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2507,\"end\":2508},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2507,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’gyur\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2508,\"end\":2513},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2507,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2508,\"end\":2513,\"uuid\":\"9e80c205-09da-4b84-acbc-44c769651675\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni sems shin tu brtan par gyur na yang rang bzhin gyis rtogs pa rags pa gzhan du mi ’phro ba’i phyir gong nas gong du phra mor byed pa na skyo ba med pa yin no| (e) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2513,\"end\":2692},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2513,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de’i\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2692,\"end\":2696},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2513,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2692,\"end\":2696,\"uuid\":\"6af2c8b5-aa6c-41ff-abcd-06152a2bc5ac\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni byang chub sems dpa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2696,\"end\":2736},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2696,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yid phyir phyogs par mi bgyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2736,\"end\":2765},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2696,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2736,\"end\":2765,\"uuid\":\"b0760dc6-f1af-475d-bcd1-e6a89353c1bf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni ting nge ’dzin la gnas par byas pa yin yang bar mar gnas pa’i phyir te| de lta mod kyi de nyid du sems ’dul bar byed de| ting nge ’dzin gyi yon tan rnams mthong bas so| (f) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2765,\"end\":2954},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2765,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bcom zhing phyir phyogs par mi ’gyur\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2954,\"end\":2990},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2765,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2954,\"end\":2990,\"uuid\":\"9490eec4-4af0-42e8-8381-6e9bf9d9dedb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni de la dga’ ba med pa dang| mos pa med pas rnam par g.yeng ba byed pa med par ’gyur te| rnam par g.yeng ba’i skyon rnams mthong ba’i phyir ro| (g) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2990,\"end\":3153},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2990,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi skrag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3153,\"end\":3161},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2990,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3153,\"end\":3161,\"uuid\":\"64154ec6-48d0-44ec-be1c-8ff92de61e3f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni brnab sems dang| yid mi bde ba la sogs pa skyes pa na yang \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3161,\"end\":3235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3161,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi skrag pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3235,\"end\":3246},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3161,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3235,\"end\":3246,\"uuid\":\"21189015-6af7-4bd6-b7aa-b95eade60191\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" yin te| ’on kyang de nyid ’joms pa ni yin te| g.yeng ba’i skyon mthong ba’i phyir ro| (h) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3246,\"end\":3338},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3246,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi dngang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3338,\"end\":3347},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3246,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3338,\"end\":3347,\"uuid\":\"a7ce050a-aa0d-4247-a7d5-f787ac750898\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni sems skyon med pa rang gis ngang gis ’byung ba nyid kyi don gang yin pa’i ’du byed de la \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3347,\"end\":3452},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3347,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mi dngang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3452,\"end\":3461},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3347,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3452,\"end\":3461,\"uuid\":\"5ea73afc-05d0-4dad-8151-aa7ede1bed54\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhing de byed pa zhes bya ba’i don to| (i) |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3461,\"end\":3506},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3461,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dngang bar mi ’gyur\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3506,\"end\":3525},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3461,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3506,\"end\":3525,\"uuid\":\"7aea4eb4-87aa-45d4-9094-30133c661b90\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni sems yang dag par ’gyur te| ’bad pa med par rang gi ’byung bas \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3525,\"end\":3604},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3525,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dngang ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3604,\"end\":3613},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3525,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3604,\"end\":3613,\"uuid\":\"674d9d1b-1f4b-44ce-9dcc-2efeb9b02695\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" dang| yang dag par \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3613,\"end\":3633},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3613,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dngang ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3633,\"end\":3642},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3613,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3633,\"end\":3642,\"uuid\":\"a0588f16-9bb6-4669-b85a-a63c1cbcc673\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" de med pa yin te| lhun gyis grub pa nyid ngang gis ’byung ba ’dzin zhes bya ba’i don to\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3642,\"end\":3730},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3642,\"end\":3730,\"uuid\":\"a02c0f25-d79e-4940-ab20-5379ee79a7e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text of them, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 42–43. Note: Ratnākara is suggesting here that these nine mental states correspond to the nine stages of resting the mind in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3730,\"end\":3915}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3915,\"end\":3939},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"f4008386-f7e1-4e05-8da2-8b963a550846\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", which results in tranquility (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3939,\"end\":3971}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"śamatha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3971,\"end\":3978},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3971,\"end\":3978,\"uuid\":\"ae9f0b4c-d701-4124-a2d5-6c5b33c2d097\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Below, he says that the last four of these nine stages are combined with the four stages of seeing clearly (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3978,\"end\":4089}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"vipaśyanā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4089,\"end\":4098},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4089,\"end\":4098,\"uuid\":\"c0d16e59-269a-48a8-b5c1-38c746588ac0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\").\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4098,\"end\":4100}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"53e56875-4aa0-46fd-98ee-13bab77f0dab\",\"sort\":1001415,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.92\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$43\",\"label\":\"1.6\",\"sort\":10177,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5d9e0b5d-f97e-4659-86b1-59b2ce26b4e4\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-446\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1366,\"uuid\":\"53e56875-4aa0-46fd-98ee-13bab77f0dab\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.14.b), he says this sentence in order to teach the ultimate bodhisattva and so on. “Precisely this state” refers to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":142}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":142,\"end\":166},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"52e3bc84-dae8-450a-9cee-62829a3dfade\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", which the bodhisattva has, because it is a particular type of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":166,\"end\":230}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":237},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"31b21476-af5b-428c-8109-fc51b6af085a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". “Precisely this state” refers to the perfection of wisdom that he or she alone is endowed with and “the instruction.” When someone with those two is “abiding in such a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":237,\"end\":407}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":407,\"end\":414},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"c0796853-a695-4607-9349-59d39dce1e57\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”‍—i.e., when he or she is abiding in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":414,\"end\":452}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative concentration\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":452,\"end\":476},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"uuid\":\"e0afff14-55e1-4438-87ce-a5368fd6ce44\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—then the “instruction” is not to abandon it and the “guidance” is connected to that. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":476,\"end\":567}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don dam pa nyid kyi \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":567,\"end\":587},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":567,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byang chub sems dpa’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":587,\"end\":607},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":567,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":587,\"end\":607,\"uuid\":\"09092ded-5ed9-4bc7-aafe-3a7906023813\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" la sogs pa \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":607,\"end\":619},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":607,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bstan par\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":619,\"end\":628},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":607,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":619,\"end\":628,\"uuid\":\"9a66a184-c43c-4468-be74-d6fad0ccb92b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" bya ba’i phyir \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":628,\"end\":644},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":628,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’di nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":644,\"end\":652},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":628,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":644,\"end\":652,\"uuid\":\"ddddb327-6b87-4ea8-8ee5-53873467b43a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba la sogs pa gsungs so| |ting nge ’dzin \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":702},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’di nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":702,\"end\":710},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":702,\"end\":710,\"uuid\":\"4b0047cf-de8e-44f0-9742-ccfd42a613a4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" byang chub sems dpa’ yin te| sems kyi khyad par yin pa’i phyir ro| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":710,\"end\":779},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":710,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’di nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":779,\"end\":787},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":710,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":779,\"end\":787,\"uuid\":\"7cc43c26-9f68-45ae-b2d0-e2436a0167f8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni de dang ldan pa nyid shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa dang \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":787,\"end\":861},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":787,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gdams pa yin\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":861,\"end\":873},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":787,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":861,\"end\":873,\"uuid\":\"6412e5ca-0ce5-48bd-8082-94e20c7e8219\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" no| |gang de gnyis dang yang dag par ldan pa ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":922},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de ltar gnas na\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":922,\"end\":937},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":922,\"end\":937,\"uuid\":\"d413f2df-103d-4131-9c04-d06b04793881\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la ting nge ’dzin ’di nyid la gnas na ’di mi gtong ba yin te| de nyid \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":937,\"end\":1020},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":937,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gdams pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1020,\"end\":1028},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":937,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1020,\"end\":1028,\"uuid\":\"b9a24108-1859-4701-9c8d-6a28106f7bcd\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" dang rjes su ’brel ba’i \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1028,\"end\":1053},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1028,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rjes su bstan pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1053,\"end\":1069},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1028,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1053,\"end\":1069,\"uuid\":\"f7360216-1e42-49f3-b813-0c9361b3015c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1069,\"end\":1071},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1069,\"end\":1071,\"uuid\":\"c6126015-3329-4f9f-8cb8-53b0e5f629ce\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 43. Note: Schmithausen (1977, pp. 46–47) postulates that these pronouns have problematic antecedents and were later additions to an earlier scripture. But RK treats them as pointing directly to something in a bodhisattva’s immediate experience.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1071,\"end\":1366}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"80aa8cd3-b8b0-4455-9960-933aec3d33a6\",\"sort\":1001445,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.93\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“Furthermore, O Blessed One, by going about life in the perfection of wisdom and cultivating it, a bodhisattva great being should train in such a way that, while being trained, he or she would not develop conceits even about that mindset of awakening. Why is that? It is because that mindset is free of a mindset, which is to say, it is the luminously clear essential nature of a mindset.”\",\"label\":\"1.7\",\"sort\":10234,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"4a711ae4-0e7e-402e-8cc3-6714a6e0917f\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-452\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":227,\"uuid\":\"80aa8cd3-b8b0-4455-9960-933aec3d33a6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Haribhadra (37), he or she is “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":44}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"going about life\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":60},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e47cf8c1-4e22-4e6c-af2f-a5dac51c76a0\",\"uuid\":\"a5e21307-1cae-44c3-8802-cd4fab03b0da\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” with unconcentrated knowing (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":91}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"jñāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":91,\"end\":96},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":91,\"end\":96,\"uuid\":\"436bad62-1b14-4eb0-b31a-10313a4bac8b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), and “cultivating” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":96,\"end\":118}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhāvanā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":125},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":125,\"uuid\":\"53f780e8-9925-4d0d-ab63-98b3afd1efaa\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":125,\"end\":127}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sgom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":131},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":131,\"uuid\":\"39b87edb-3492-4fb1-bf4d-82bccfb88da7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") with concentrated knowing (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":131,\"end\":160}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"jñāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":165},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":165,\"uuid\":\"bac556ce-44cd-40c5-babc-259146d1c5a2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Hari: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":174}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"caratety asamāhitena jñānena. bhāvayateti samāhitena\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":174,\"end\":226},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":174,\"end\":226,\"uuid\":\"819f3e27-a0ba-45de-9a95-ad8c9658bcb3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":227}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ba6d80cd-c5fe-4988-a877-ab29fbe2eab9\",\"sort\":1001461,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.94\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“Furthermore, O Blessed One, by going about life in the perfection of wisdom and cultivating it, a bodhisattva great being should train in such a way that, while being trained, he or she would not develop conceits even about that mindset of awakening. Why is that? It is because that mindset is free of a mindset, which is to say, it is the luminously clear essential nature of a mindset.”\",\"label\":\"1.7\",\"sort\":10234,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"4a711ae4-0e7e-402e-8cc3-6714a6e0917f\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-452\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":3106,\"uuid\":\"ba6d80cd-c5fe-4988-a877-ab29fbe2eab9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.17.b–18.a), “furthermore” means that this paragraph relies (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":86}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ltos pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":93},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":93,\"uuid\":\"85b84d6b-b3ae-450d-a44b-940e8be0c65c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") upon the practice instructions (explained in RK’s commentary on the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":93,\"end\":163}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ornament\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":163,\"end\":171},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e2b57f23-f45f-4cf0-b857-faef374919ac\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). When “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":171,\"end\":180}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"going about life\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":180,\"end\":196},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e47cf8c1-4e22-4e6c-af2f-a5dac51c76a0\",\"uuid\":\"07cd2e2d-66eb-4794-9eaa-2c47f5cbf42b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the perfection of wisdom,” the meditative reference point is the impermanence of the three noble truths and so on. His or her \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":196,\"end\":326}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative perspective\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":326,\"end\":348},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bea5dcd-33ce-40af-aca6-9c1243d8e867\",\"uuid\":\"5ac9e851-b087-46f9-8a00-0a250e5fde57\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":348,\"end\":352}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nonattachment\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":352,\"end\":365},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e8052e35-e7a0-4c24-a8c6-dcf42039f956\",\"uuid\":\"011b6771-7a73-42a9-8fee-692ba0a90540\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":365,\"end\":367}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"anabhiniveśa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":367,\"end\":379},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":367,\"end\":379,\"uuid\":\"6c3a0d6e-4236-4282-b5c3-a5bc7a77b56d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":379,\"end\":381}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mngon par zhen pa med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":381,\"end\":405},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":381,\"end\":405,\"uuid\":\"c093a9dc-1b3a-42fd-9f55-4d0d613eb655\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and so on. So he or she is “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":405,\"end\":435}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"going about life\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":435,\"end\":451},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e47cf8c1-4e22-4e6c-af2f-a5dac51c76a0\",\"uuid\":\"ddc22078-ed55-4e0c-9d99-9ad31e387b1c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” in the freedom from reference points. When “cultivating” the perfection of wisdom‍—i.e., gradually cultivating it‍—his or her meditative reference point is the noble truth of the path included within the three former truths, which is the freedom from any reference point. Hence, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":451,\"end\":736}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative perspective\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":736,\"end\":758},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bea5dcd-33ce-40af-aca6-9c1243d8e867\",\"uuid\":\"ee7b0a0d-96e0-4058-97c7-7786be8dca37\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is the freedom from “conceit” that is to be known through cultivating that. He or she should “train in such a way that” means he or she should train without conceit and without being enmeshed. In the phrase “even that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":758,\"end\":977}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":977,\"end\":997},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"5b7b78de-7acd-4974-81c4-6e72e71d0cb7\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” that “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":997,\"end\":1006}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1006,\"end\":1013},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"736ced52-aef4-4ff5-b299-270a3cef54d4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”‍—which is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1013,\"end\":1025}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"unequaled\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1025,\"end\":1034},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9212e3e6-5e47-4184-955a-8d5c84543d8c\",\"uuid\":\"cfb7bc55-39be-4fa6-a285-48e751a35eb0\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", because the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1034,\"end\":1048}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"disciples\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1048,\"end\":1057},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"uuid\":\"edeea3d8-e680-4b61-ba79-fcf75a1ae2c5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1057,\"end\":1062}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"solitary realizers\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1062,\"end\":1080},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91eb4850-6549-4ee5-ae57-ec33c68112f1\",\"uuid\":\"66521f42-cb21-4f04-ba29-4e70c89786cf\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" do not share it‍—is a vast \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1080,\"end\":1108}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1108,\"end\":1115},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"072769a3-c4c3-43a6-acc9-7e2c442d3dc8\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" because it is the source of benefiting sentient beings uninterruptedly. The term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1115,\"end\":1198}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1198,\"end\":1218},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"bda0f799-5552-46f8-a860-0a68a0e9074a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1218,\"end\":1221}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhicitta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1221,\"end\":1231},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1221,\"end\":1231,\"uuid\":\"6a82ae9a-968f-4b95-ad92-e7a12d7daeaf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") should be understood here as the “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1231,\"end\":1267}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1267,\"end\":1274},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"a3bca4e9-0acf-407d-beb0-8001c9bc1191\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” whose nature consists in “awakening” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1274,\"end\":1314}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"*bodhyātmakacittam\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1314,\"end\":1332},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1314,\"end\":1332,\"uuid\":\"0525aae5-f38e-4abc-aad2-57119bb3ccaf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). The word “even” is for emphasis. Therefore, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1332,\"end\":1383}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1383,\"end\":1390},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"60371b95-7829-4eea-9060-6dc04827b91b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of bodhisattvas is asserted to possess particular nobility compared to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1390,\"end\":1466}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1466,\"end\":1473},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"11e19f83-91e2-4ba8-9de5-b799676c1d74\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of all sentient beings. So if a bodhisattva’s \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1473,\"end\":1520}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1520,\"end\":1527},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"9cd8df88-db71-4c32-917c-59e89351621c\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" “would not \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1527,\"end\":1539}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"develop conceits\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1539,\"end\":1555},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25503faa-de94-4eee-a273-6e00ef3ad66c\",\"uuid\":\"701090b0-a525-494b-a9a1-be1f4378131e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" even about that,” then what need is there to speak of an ordinary \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1555,\"end\":1622}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1622,\"end\":1629},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"3ee4ee3f-14d4-4ce7-97da-830f1b2dd0d1\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1629,\"end\":1635}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gzhan yang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1635,\"end\":1645},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1635,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1635,\"end\":1645,\"uuid\":\"6bcdcf81-d8c8-4223-9c9c-0485a81add27\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes smos pas ni gdams ngag la ltos pa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1645,\"end\":1689},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1645,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa la spyod\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1689,\"end\":1730},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1645,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1689,\"end\":1730,\"uuid\":\"115a5269-71c1-46d5-a4fa-922852c7cb64\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ces bya ba ni bden pa gsum dang ’brel ba’i mi rtag pa nyid la sogs pa ni dmigs pa’o| |mngon par zhen pa med pa la sogs pa ni rnam pa ste| mi dmigs par \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1730,\"end\":1882},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1730,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"spyod pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1882,\"end\":1890},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1730,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1882,\"end\":1890,\"uuid\":\"2fb2730b-27f0-454e-9794-9f8b264ad42b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’o| | \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1890,\"end\":1896},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1890,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa bsgom pas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1896,\"end\":1938},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1890,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1896,\"end\":1938,\"uuid\":\"edc6098d-98bf-45ba-aac6-3ccb1a96a008\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba smos pa ni rim gyis bsgom pa zhes bya ba’i don to| |bden pa gsum gyi ’og tu lam gyi bden pa’i dmigs pa ni dmigs pa med pa’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1938,\"end\":2077},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1938,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"des rlom sems med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2077,\"end\":2097},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1938,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2077,\"end\":2097,\"uuid\":\"04f28eaa-646a-4cf2-a0eb-de70ad2e6744\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni rnam pa bsgoms pas shes par bya ba yin no| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2097,\"end\":2145},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2097,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de ltar bslab par bgyi’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2145,\"end\":2169},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2097,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2145,\"end\":2169,\"uuid\":\"0132216d-13a0-4b6b-a3b8-4fe9cabdfb7f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni mngon par zhen pa med cing rlom sems med pa de ltar bslab par bya’o| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2169,\"end\":2255},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2169,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"des kyang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2255,\"end\":2264},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2169,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2255,\"end\":2264,\"uuid\":\"e0ccb892-8549-4655-bebb-439292eee6de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya bas ni gang de’i sems mnyam pa med pa yin te| nyan thos dang| rang sangs rgyas la sogs pa dang thun mong ma yin pa’i phyir ro| |sems rgya chen po rnam pa thams cad du dus chad pa med par sems can gyi don gyi bya ba rnams kyi ’byung gnas su gyur pa’i phyir ro| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2264,\"end\":2535},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2264,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byang chub sems\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2535,\"end\":2550},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2264,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2535,\"end\":2550,\"uuid\":\"029fd280-6915-42c2-aa83-eea1f42a3456\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni byang chub kyi bdag nyid kyi \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2550,\"end\":2595},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2550,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems so\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2595,\"end\":2602},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2550,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2595,\"end\":2602,\"uuid\":\"c203159e-6314-47c1-a62f-e1a8702689a0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2602,\"end\":2605},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2602,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kyang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2605,\"end\":2610},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2602,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2605,\"end\":2610,\"uuid\":\"e695681e-ef70-4acf-865f-c5c989436fac\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" gi sgra ni lhag pa’i don to| |de’i phyir byang chub sems dpa’ rnams kyi sems ni sems can thams cad las khyad par du ’phags pa yod par ’dod de| des kyang \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2610,\"end\":2764},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2610,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rlom sems su mi byed\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2764,\"end\":2784},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2610,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2764,\"end\":2784,\"uuid\":\"01697b78-3010-4cbb-b654-f388209f702d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" na tha mal pa’i sems kyis lta smos kyang ci dgos zhes bya ba’i don to\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2784,\"end\":2854},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2784,\"end\":2854,\"uuid\":\"92359c8c-bf1e-41ab-b8a9-793ce744316f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 52. Note: See the introduction to this translation for more on the term “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2854,\"end\":2978}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2978,\"end\":2998},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"uuid\":\"7e7cbbd2-9618-4550-9e8d-d4c0ce9d62e5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2998,\"end\":3001}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bodhicitta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3001,\"end\":3011},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3001,\"end\":3011,\"uuid\":\"20ddd36c-29c2-410d-a87b-25160362f127\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), its translation, and its interpretation in India (see introduction, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3011,\"end\":3082}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“Mindset of Awakening”\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3082,\"end\":3104},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"edad17c2-29a3-4180-b1ad-f48624d0d68c\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/2986910d-9ba9-4a9a-97c5-f42a18214f8c\",\"entity\":\"2986910d-9ba9-4a9a-97c5-f42a18214f8c\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"introductionHeader\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\").\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":3104,\"end\":3106}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b6ef2f70-3f08-4316-9543-4c74ca4e1c04\",\"sort\":1001540,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.95\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“Furthermore, O Blessed One, by going about life in the perfection of wisdom and cultivating it, a bodhisattva great being should train in such a way that, while being trained, he or she would not develop conceits even about that mindset of awakening. Why is that? It is because that mindset is free of a mindset, which is to say, it is the luminously clear essential nature of a mindset.”\",\"label\":\"1.7\",\"sort\":10234,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"4a711ae4-0e7e-402e-8cc3-6714a6e0917f\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-452\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":2390,\"uuid\":\"b6ef2f70-3f08-4316-9543-4c74ca4e1c04\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.18.a), “why is that?” asks the question what is the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":78}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative perspective\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":78,\"end\":100},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bea5dcd-33ce-40af-aca6-9c1243d8e867\",\"uuid\":\"0ad1ba51-1e61-4d99-8b92-4d4aa59cfd24\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" due to which he or she does not \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":100,\"end\":133}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"develop conceits\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":133,\"end\":149},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"25503faa-de94-4eee-a273-6e00ef3ad66c\",\"uuid\":\"915f1d50-0575-4129-b562-09db194ae4f7\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" about that. “It is because” and so on expresses the answer. He says, “That \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":225}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":232},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"f641ae33-507a-4697-9b1d-26abc78009ba\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":232,\"end\":236}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":236,\"end\":253},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"82d3243e-4f0e-4644-88f9-326ff44e4576\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” because it (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":253,\"end\":267}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":267,\"end\":269},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":267,\"end\":269,\"uuid\":\"d551c55a-fcfe-44f9-aa9b-e2444829e562\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") does not appear as either (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":269,\"end\":298}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnyis la\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":306},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":298,\"end\":306,\"uuid\":\"ade65194-31a1-48bb-b769-692f3c2c2806\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") the grasped or the grasper. But one might think that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":306,\"end\":365}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":365,\"end\":372},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"fc729580-4f0a-4f78-801e-ab5773f7607f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" does not exist, so he also states that it is “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":372,\"end\":423}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"luminously clear\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":423,\"end\":439},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e\",\"uuid\":\"a713026a-28b3-487a-bca0-02ed3c353777\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":439,\"end\":440}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essential nature of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":440,\"end\":469},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a07e0ac1-ff46-4d29-bca1-939e3a0362d5\",\"uuid\":\"9097b0eb-3c71-4f7f-b957-ad7225270329\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".” One might ask, “How is that mind \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":469,\"end\":505}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"luminously clear\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":505,\"end\":521},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e\",\"uuid\":\"c4ea7998-41ae-4750-8ba4-faf5926b4e1a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"?” The mind is primordially free of attachment and so on, because those are adventitious by nature. For precisely that reason, the subsequent (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":521,\"end\":664}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"phyis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":664,\"end\":669},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":664,\"end\":669,\"uuid\":\"e3d343d5-abe4-47f2-b791-428ff4487829\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") freedom from those (i.e., attachment and so on) does not exist. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":669,\"end\":739}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":739,\"end\":740},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":739,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de ci’i slad du zhe na?\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":740,\"end\":763},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":739,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":740,\"end\":763,\"uuid\":\"abd6316c-bc75-44be-9473-bd21f494dbc7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni rnam pa gang gis de la rlom sems med pa yin zhe na? \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":763,\"end\":831},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":763,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’di ltar\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":831,\"end\":839},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":763,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":831,\"end\":839,\"uuid\":\"607b2f31-2381-426c-8548-ed82c1e84724\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pas lan smras so| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":839,\"end\":879},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":839,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems de ni sems ma mchis pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":879,\"end\":906},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":839,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":879,\"end\":906,\"uuid\":\"eaed08ea-32f6-4487-a454-3b249ea150ad\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni gzung ba dang ’dzin pa gnyis la de mi snang ba’i phyir ro| |gal te sems med na ’on kyang de \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":906,\"end\":1014},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":906,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems kyi rang bzhin ni ’od gsal ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1014,\"end\":1048},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":906,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1014,\"end\":1048,\"uuid\":\"3ce0d756-79d1-4557-9db8-82e71db8b37d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes smos so| |ji ltar ’od gsal ba yin zhe na? gang gi phyir sems ni ’dod chags la sogs pa dang dang po nas mi ldan pa yin te| de dag ni rang bzhin gyis glo bur ba yin pa’i phyir ro| |de nyid kyi phyir phyis kyang bral ba med do\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1048,\"end\":1277},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1048,\"end\":1277,\"uuid\":\"637e1653-74f6-456e-89c9-d3f1dc3665c8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text of his broader comments, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 52. According to Hari (38–39), it is a nonimplicative negation. Hence, that (relative) “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1277,\"end\":1440}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1440,\"end\":1447},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"29ff4230-2c60-42e2-8ede-bf026dedd28e\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” of awakening, which is not distinct from the perspective of the freedom from habitual fixation and so on, is ultimately “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1447,\"end\":1570}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1570,\"end\":1587},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"b0d2a22e-f1de-453f-a843-244663ce4b63\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” since the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1587,\"end\":1599}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"luminously clear\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1599,\"end\":1615},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e\",\"uuid\":\"3485bc71-2cd1-4377-8ceb-19e20b99def3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1615,\"end\":1616}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essential nature of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1616,\"end\":1645},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a07e0ac1-ff46-4d29-bca1-939e3a0362d5\",\"uuid\":\"78c8e915-f447-4339-a84f-27cafdd584c4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is free of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1645,\"end\":1657}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"identity\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1657,\"end\":1665},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"506f944c-d376-4454-839d-f5c30eb07b16\",\"uuid\":\"5feca26c-d8f9-4846-a5f7-f05fc11afe66\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is simple (i.e., partless) or complex (i.e., has parts). Note: In accordance with their respective philosophical positions of Yogācāra and Madhyamaka, Ratnākara and Hari disagree about whether the negation here is an exclusion/implicative negation (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1665,\"end\":1920}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paryudāsa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1920,\"end\":1929},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1920,\"end\":1929,\"uuid\":\"8ec80908-1dce-43a9-88e0-e694eb755fc5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1929,\"end\":1931}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma yin dgag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1931,\"end\":1942},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1931,\"end\":1942,\"uuid\":\"12e48529-3d91-4dcf-a247-465ff9ce4110\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") or an absolute, nonimplicative negation (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1942,\"end\":1985}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prasajyapratiṣedha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1985,\"end\":2003},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1985,\"end\":2003,\"uuid\":\"5bea43e1-c2b5-432a-82e2-55ddba385d66\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2003,\"end\":2005}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"med dgag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2005,\"end\":2013},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2005,\"end\":2013,\"uuid\":\"d6fac226-69fe-41e8-b937-5f0f1fb846d3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). In his \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2013,\"end\":2023}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Instructions on the Perfection of Wisdom\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2023,\"end\":2063},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"77d53edc-9dca-450a-9cde-25da9f0b5c36\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", Ratnākara explains that the negation in this sentence is an exclusion (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2063,\"end\":2136}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paryudāsa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2136,\"end\":2145},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2136,\"end\":2145,\"uuid\":\"f53ce1bd-88a9-4cfc-aeec-edcff455edca\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Hence, that “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2145,\"end\":2161}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2161,\"end\":2168},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"92cd586b-c4b3-487c-b838-e2d33e232c81\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” of awakening is, on the one hand, “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2168,\"end\":2205}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2205,\"end\":2222},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"6b9ad72f-3191-4c5c-87fa-61615dbcf286\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” insofar as there is no subject grasping or object grasped; on the other hand, it is “a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2222,\"end\":2311}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2311,\"end\":2318},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"1bc29340-29bd-4ae3-ac9b-a748e10bf43b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” insofar as it consists in nothing but reflexively aware \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2318,\"end\":2377}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"illumination\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2377,\"end\":2389},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"05a3d610-b8c8-4534-bb60-f3ba86a5e76a\",\"uuid\":\"e7d62c6c-6bb1-44a3-9401-ce7df5d7f0df\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":2389,\"end\":2390}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a692b6ec-24a8-4db6-82a2-9c36618e36cd\",\"sort\":1001604,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.96\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then the venerable Śāriputra asked the venerable Subhūti, “But, Venerable Subhūti, if that mindset is free of a mindset, does that mindset exist?”\",\"label\":\"1.8\",\"sort\":10261,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"50be37fb-3d28-40a6-a05b-3346a61a7a00\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-456\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":481,\"uuid\":\"a692b6ec-24a8-4db6-82a2-9c36618e36cd\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.18.a), “Then the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":43}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"venerable\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":52},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"91107107-3f31-4442-8365-9099041efadf\",\"uuid\":\"31ec6b66-dee3-4e5d-aae9-0a2375780529\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":53}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāriputra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":53,\"end\":62},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3df1bcb6-86da-4978-8191-8dbd8f56b919\",\"uuid\":\"65cd38be-f26a-4ddc-ad8f-b004b54e1522\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" said …” thus, he knew, but asked the question to cause \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":62,\"end\":118}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":125},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"40a9b0ee-4f1b-47df-a3a9-b37e90af2ec5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to explain it. The next sentence is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":125,\"end\":162}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":162,\"end\":169},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"c468e79e-8ff0-4f4b-9303-be6727aaccc5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s reply to his question, in which he explains it. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":169,\"end\":224}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":225},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":427,\"uuid\":\"59264b30-c3f4-41f4-a763-3a694f062058\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shA ri’i bus ’di skad ces smras so\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":259},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":224,\"end\":427,\"uuid\":\"59264b30-c3f4-41f4-a763-3a694f062058\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":259,\"uuid\":\"14b9e09e-3ebd-4494-8daa-ea9342a8d288\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni de ltar shes kyang rab ’byor gyis ston par bya pa’i phyir dris so| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":343},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":427,\"uuid\":\"59264b30-c3f4-41f4-a763-3a694f062058\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de skad ces smras pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":343,\"end\":363},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":427,\"uuid\":\"59264b30-c3f4-41f4-a763-3a694f062058\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":343,\"end\":363,\"uuid\":\"5a45d56b-5d08-4122-98bb-856a4837f530\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba la sogs pas ni rab ’byor gyis dris pa’i lan ston to\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":427},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":427,\"uuid\":\"59264b30-c3f4-41f4-a763-3a694f062058\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 52.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":427,\"end\":481}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4b1be137-8a0e-4fd1-a695-904a2cc97309\",\"sort\":1001620,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.97\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The venerable Subhūti continued, “O Venerable Śāriputra, if, in that state free of a mindset, an existence or a nonexistence is neither found nor mentally perceived, then is your questioning of my statement reasonable as you expressed it, saying, ‘If that mindset is free of a mindset, does that mindset exist?’ ”\",\"label\":\"1.10\",\"sort\":10309,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"96cf48c6-1a53-4512-b5b0-9401df59fe4b\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-460\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":747,\"uuid\":\"4b1be137-8a0e-4fd1-a695-904a2cc97309\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.18.a), “definitely not” means (an existence or \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":73}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nonexistence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":73,\"end\":85},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ab1a7cab-b996-4342-a1a8-69e0ab712c60\",\"uuid\":\"66748232-5ae8-474c-94b2-cd39c8fb577f\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") is “not mentally perceived” because there is no proof of them, and also “not found” because there is disproof of them. Their negation perfectly transcends both existence (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":85,\"end\":258}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bhāva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":258,\"end\":263},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":258,\"end\":263,\"uuid\":\"1416cbd0-c344-4b74-b24d-6dff6e5d865b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":265}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dngos po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":265,\"end\":273},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":265,\"end\":273,\"uuid\":\"4728539c-7f9d-4456-815c-279dc25ef6fa\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":273,\"end\":279}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nonexistence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":279,\"end\":291},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ab1a7cab-b996-4342-a1a8-69e0ab712c60\",\"uuid\":\"f6bf9a4c-82d9-4aec-b9c0-59944eaf4c41\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". “Does that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":291,\"end\":304}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":304,\"end\":311},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"a28c4881-5d22-43dd-8f98-80fb4f6bb154\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" exist?” asks the question “does that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":311,\"end\":349}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nonexistence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":349,\"end\":361},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ab1a7cab-b996-4342-a1a8-69e0ab712c60\",\"uuid\":\"c196e7af-aded-49b9-8cf5-faf8a36f99d4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":361,\"end\":363}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nāstitā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":370},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":370,\"uuid\":\"a24101be-8d61-4ed8-8d35-f883cc7ca9e7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":370,\"end\":372}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"med pa nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":372,\"end\":383},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":372,\"end\":383,\"uuid\":\"c5ee97b1-4434-4b69-95fc-360aeb3c56ac\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") exist?” RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":383,\"end\":397}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":398},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":693,\"uuid\":\"d961b1ed-f06e-4bb3-a5af-5511ff314aba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de ni med do\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":398,\"end\":410},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":693,\"uuid\":\"d961b1ed-f06e-4bb3-a5af-5511ff314aba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":398,\"end\":410,\"uuid\":\"4b05428f-70e6-4d84-8c93-ab92f1203fbe\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba de ni mi dmigs pa ste| sgrub par byed pa med pa’i phyir ro| |de nyid pa yang ma yin te| gnod par byed pa yod pa’i phyir ro| |dngos po dang| dngos po med pa las yang dag par ’das pa ni gnod par byed pa yin no| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":410,\"end\":633},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":410,\"end\":693,\"uuid\":\"d961b1ed-f06e-4bb3-a5af-5511ff314aba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yod dam\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":633,\"end\":640},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":410,\"end\":693,\"uuid\":\"d961b1ed-f06e-4bb3-a5af-5511ff314aba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":633,\"end\":640,\"uuid\":\"fbc772ad-e989-49a6-a02a-9fd19b2ce0a6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya ba ni ci de med pa nyid ces bya ba’i don to\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":640,\"end\":693},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":640,\"end\":693,\"uuid\":\"d961b1ed-f06e-4bb3-a5af-5511ff314aba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 52.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":693,\"end\":747}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"76007c14-7f71-4f64-8c2c-5e5a47b5927f\",\"sort\":1001644,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.98\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In response, the venerable Śāriputra asked the venerable Subhūti, “What then, Venerable Subhūti, is the state free of a mindset?”\",\"label\":\"1.11\",\"sort\":10330,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"8f46ee0a-fa43-4396-ba47-804ac4a22138\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-462\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":373,\"uuid\":\"76007c14-7f71-4f64-8c2c-5e5a47b5927f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara (F.18.a–b), even just based on \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":54}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāriputra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":54,\"end\":63},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3df1bcb6-86da-4978-8191-8dbd8f56b919\",\"uuid\":\"63b0c80c-7db9-48fa-900c-1e49b0156168\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s question, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":63,\"end\":76}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":76,\"end\":83},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"5d2a91a1-f5f5-483f-8fab-553900662740\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" thought that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":97}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāriputra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":97,\"end\":106},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3df1bcb6-86da-4978-8191-8dbd8f56b919\",\"uuid\":\"19ee7d0c-d08c-4a72-b809-10d1a7134ffa\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" was not clear, so to clarify, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":106,\"end\":137}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāriputra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":137,\"end\":146},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"3df1bcb6-86da-4978-8191-8dbd8f56b919\",\"uuid\":\"9f6c66cc-efc2-4db1-9b00-e97759113b39\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" asks, “What is the state \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":146,\"end\":172}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":172,\"end\":189},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"4923955b-292e-4f1d-a9cd-649603d27aa3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"?” RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":189,\"end\":196}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de tsam gyis kyang rab ’byor gyis bsams pas gsal por ma gyur nas| gsal bar bya ba’i phyir \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":196,\"end\":286},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":196,\"end\":319,\"uuid\":\"e6be8689-4d36-4041-a90c-66cebe1ba6ee\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dris pa ni de gang yin\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":286,\"end\":308},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":196,\"end\":319,\"uuid\":\"e6be8689-4d36-4041-a90c-66cebe1ba6ee\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":286,\"end\":308,\"uuid\":\"78091e63-b408-4de0-a490-10d6974fbb6b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" zhes bya’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":319},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":319,\"uuid\":\"e6be8689-4d36-4041-a90c-66cebe1ba6ee\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, p. 52.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":319,\"end\":373}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"73286c97-bb96-4a8d-bf87-6146294a5a9a\",\"sort\":1001660,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.99\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The venerable Subhūti then said this: “O Venerable Śāriputra, the state free of a mindset is free of changing and free of conceptualization.”\",\"label\":\"1.12\",\"sort\":10347,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"374570ad-c0fe-46dc-97b1-16fb649af570\",\"workUuid\":\"b43ac3f8-f616-4db3-a6ff-cbce4e6ad6dc\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-033-001-464\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":2054,\"uuid\":\"73286c97-bb96-4a8d-bf87-6146294a5a9a\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to Ratnākara, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":24}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":24,\"end\":31},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f\",\"uuid\":\"cfef2c1a-cefd-4df1-9a7d-8cba42b13b9a\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" replies “the state \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":31,\"end\":51}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":51,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"28037751-b381-41d8-8480-f7103d53be95\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":72}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of changing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":72,\"end\":88},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"6e5cd77d-41f5-4104-a8b7-c8814a7885fa\",\"uuid\":\"b9c75a74-c414-447b-b6ff-901adfb86dcf\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” because it is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":104}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"luminously clear\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":104,\"end\":120},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e\",\"uuid\":\"c197856e-44b4-4092-baa7-ee613169aa33\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" by nature and untainted by changes. It is also “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":120,\"end\":169}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of conceptualization\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":169,\"end\":194},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d00bb5e9-1956-4af1-a225-87b45ea5e996\",\"uuid\":\"49f71925-c3b9-4d7c-8f52-e1e87a08af2b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” because all conceptual proliferations have subsided in it and it is not the content of any representational forms (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":194,\"end\":311}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ākāra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":311,\"end\":316},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":311,\"end\":316,\"uuid\":\"af28eea2-9a4b-4460-a752-e690d4f75185\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":316,\"end\":318}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rnam pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":318,\"end\":325},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":318,\"end\":325,\"uuid\":\"5ad79762-967a-46d7-8584-ba06bdce0944\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Hence, he or she “does not create conceits even about such a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":325,\"end\":389}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":389,\"end\":396},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"2c544c96-cca3-4351-a98c-741480d686bd\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” because, in that state, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":396,\"end\":426}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":426,\"end\":433},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"4caeed06-0a7b-4750-8560-4ef815087349\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is simply nonexistent (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":457}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":457,\"end\":468},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":457,\"end\":468,\"uuid\":\"02d9ef45-4294-49d1-be7a-680da25ce0f9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\")‍—in other words, because that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":468,\"end\":500}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":500,\"end\":507},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"006245d3-194a-4719-89ea-4c603eafbb01\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is simply the emptiness of a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":507,\"end\":537}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":537,\"end\":544},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"d3559637-7f66-426a-ae8c-1ebfc39e73de\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":544,\"end\":546}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems stong pa nyid tsam las\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":546,\"end\":573},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":546,\"end\":573,\"uuid\":\"4070d10a-9606-49ae-8366-82104892d09f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Thus, the meditative reference point is “that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":573,\"end\":622}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":622,\"end\":629},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"82ad11fe-fb47-41ab-ad7b-8dd920b40c49\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":629,\"end\":633}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":633,\"end\":650},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"1368cf07-501e-46ed-a01f-8a0f55308fc4\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":650,\"end\":652}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":663},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":652,\"end\":663,\"uuid\":\"e197ea9b-f1b9-4f30-9079-64d7107c9081\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), because it is naturally \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":663,\"end\":690}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"luminously clear\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":690,\"end\":706},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e\",\"uuid\":\"6afd067c-1293-4906-9572-9a63a2352d6d\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".” The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":706,\"end\":713}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"meditative perspective\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":713,\"end\":735},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7bea5dcd-33ce-40af-aca6-9c1243d8e867\",\"uuid\":\"256e3d18-29a8-440d-bd22-4645b22988f5\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is the freedom from conceits. One should also understand here implicitly that just as the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":735,\"end\":826}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":826,\"end\":833},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"3b82bd15-3ce5-4ade-b3e7-cea836c8daae\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":833,\"end\":837}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of a mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":837,\"end\":854},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"uuid\":\"37cbf7c5-ce18-4de0-8d34-d3303697cae1\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", so too physical form and so on are free of physical form and so on. RK: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":854,\"end\":928}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"|rab ’byor gyi lan ni \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":950},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"B