pa thams cad nye bar zhi ba dang| rnam pa thams cad kyi spyod yul ma yin pa’i phyir \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1105,\"end\":1199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1105,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rnam par rtog pa med pa’o\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1199,\"end\":1224},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1105,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1199,\"end\":1224,\"uuid\":\"338b8c8b-2f1f-4adc-9f06-9e78141d8f98\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" | |de lta bas na de lta bu’i \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1224,\"end\":1254},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1224,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sems kyis kyang rlom sems su mi bya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1254,\"end\":1289},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1224,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1254,\"end\":1289,\"uuid\":\"09b85fd0-4160-4533-9bd2-ead5f89f2cae\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ste| de la yang sems med pa tsam gyi phyir te| sems stong pa nyid tsam las zhes bya ba’i don to| |\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1289,\"end\":1388},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1289,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de ltar na sems de yang sems med pa yin te rang bzhin gyis ’od gsal ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1388,\"end\":1458},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1289,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1388,\"end\":1458,\"uuid\":\"990565e3-771f-49c5-b436-34b3741ce655\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni dmigs pa’o| |de la yang \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1458,\"end\":1486},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1458,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rlom sems med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1486,\"end\":1502},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1458,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"bold\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1486,\"end\":1502,\"uuid\":\"80aca559-df26-46d0-bc42-d86db74d1fea\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"text-bold\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ni rnam pa’o| |ji ltar sems la sems med pa ste nye bar gzugs la sogs pa la yang gzugs la sogs pa med pa nyid du don gyis shes pa yin no\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1502,\"end\":1638},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1502,\"end\":1638,\"uuid\":\"68751b58-277d-44c5-9913-f5366d2f2ccc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For edited Tibetan text, see Seton 2016, Aii, pp. 52–53. According to Hari (40), it is “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1638,\"end\":1728}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of changing\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1728,\"end\":1744},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"6e5cd77d-41f5-4104-a8b7-c8814a7885fa\",\"uuid\":\"3e6e660c-c273-4e23-a575-aa1c1a295b90\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” because the freedom from a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1744,\"end\":1773}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mindset\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1773,\"end\":1780},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"uuid\":\"dea57601-cd6b-4a05-9a74-6adddfac1f3b\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" mentioned here (at the yogi’s conventional level) is a cause, step by step, for the actualization of freedom from change at the level of a buddha. It is “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1780,\"end\":1935}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"free of conceptualization\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1935,\"end\":1960},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d00bb5e9-1956-4af1-a225-87b45ea5e996\",\"uuid\":\"496b4b8f-9b04-4c64-a3f5-893a75d55ef3\",\"toh\":\"toh12\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” because it is a cause of a buddha’s actualization of freedom from error (at that level too).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1960,\"end\":2054}}]}]}],\"glossary\":[{\"uuid\":\"21c43cd9-2844-4c67-8897-2e7bcd438241\",\"authority\":\"45d6cc43-2a2f-4ab2-a1e5-0cffc70da357\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"[not] taken hold of, taken hold of\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་ཟིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anupātta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma zin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5471dac6-1971-4333-b615-2e0bf346a316\",\"authority\":\"3509bec3-2cbe-4518-ad2b-6c1e8b684e58\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSeventh of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Inner Radiance.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Ābhāsvara\",\"tibetan\":\"འོད་གསལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ābhāsvara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’od gsal\"}},{\"uuid\":\"29302329-ee8d-4682-b699-d17e2bb8dec7\",\"authority\":\"43c14e68-bc34-45dc-849c-03bc8422e5e6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe eastern buddhafield of the Buddha Akṣobhya.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Abhirati\",\"tibetan\":\"མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhirati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mngon par dga’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e175a82e-be93-4fae-871f-cb478cf466f1\",\"authority\":\"ed93efd8-26c3-4ad8-a4bf-a8084b90c75e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/ce682850-4446-4e92-b9e4-da871259b68d\\\"/\u003en.100\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"abide free of conflict\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མེད་པ་ལ་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"araṇāvihārin\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nyon mongs pa med pa la gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d15d2966-4bb6-43cf-8894-a8965280ded2\",\"authority\":\"64a50fd8-0fd0-4a50-a5f8-c081ba5ef861\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA term meaning acceptance, forbearance, or patience. As the third of the six perfections, patience is classified into three kinds: the capacity to tolerate abuse from sentient beings, to tolerate the hardships of the path to buddhahood, and to tolerate the profound nature of reality. As a term referring to a bodhisattva’s realization, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edharmakṣānti\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003echos la bzod pa\u003c/em\u003e) can refer to the ways one becomes “receptive” to the nature of Dharma, and it can be an abbreviation of \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eanutpattikadharmakṣānti\u003c/em\u003e, “forbearance for the unborn nature, or nonproduction, of dharmas.”\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"acceptance, tolerant acceptance\",\"tibetan\":\"བཟོད་པ།, བཟོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣānti, kṣānti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bzod pa, bzod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"33ab1da8-1af4-415b-bfd0-96e5055a1a47\",\"authority\":\"64a50fd8-0fd0-4a50-a5f8-c081ba5ef861\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA term meaning acceptance, forbearance, or patience. As the third of the six perfections, patience is classified into three kinds: the capacity to tolerate abuse from sentient beings, to tolerate the hardships of the path to buddhahood, and to tolerate the profound nature of reality. As a term referring to a bodhisattva’s realization, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edharmakṣānti\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003echos la bzod pa\u003c/em\u003e) can refer to the ways one becomes “receptive” to the nature of Dharma, and it can be an abbreviation of \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eanutpattikadharmakṣānti\u003c/em\u003e, “forbearance for the unborn nature, or nonproduction, of dharmas.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe third of four stages or experiences of breaking through on the path of preliminary practice.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"acceptance, tolerant acceptance\",\"tibetan\":\"བཟོད་པ།, བཟོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣānti, kṣānti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bzod pa, bzod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e62676e6-a821-4e67-94b0-13fdc3a8d3ce\",\"authority\":\"59af8757-263e-441c-90a9-dc0225d5e894\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"actual nature\",\"tibetan\":\"དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"tathatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"de bzhin nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4cfa7f72-29ce-4a21-82ba-058cd78f3560\",\"authority\":\"78e6b0ba-17db-45c3-9aa7-80db0558478f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"aggression, aggressiveness\",\"tibetan\":\"ཞེ་སྡང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"doṣa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zhe sdang\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0c9686d5-af20-4e4e-b660-2589550617ba\",\"authority\":\"e00c06d4-270e-464e-a57b-1a020464ad34\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eFifth and highest of the five pure abodes, meaning “Highest.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Akaniṣṭha\",\"tibetan\":\"འོག་མིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akaniṣṭha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’og min\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b66df17d-4a3e-460d-8f3e-fd26aa19d691\",\"authority\":\"cad43a0c-a53f-4f2e-8341-2a76e07dcb4a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eLit. “Not Disturbed” or “Immovable One.” The buddha in the eastern realm of Abhirati. A well-known buddha in Mahāyāna, regarded in the higher tantras as the head of one of the five buddha families, the vajra family in the east.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Akṣobhya\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་བསྐྱོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akṣobhya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi bskyod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"067c788d-11bb-48d8-b9e4-8022d5a88c13\",\"authority\":\"9cc9ab26-1636-4961-96a1-d51af4fbce31\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of the four gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Always Delighted\",\"tibetan\":\"རྟག་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nityapramudita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtag tu dga’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"59b38241-f13f-44f1-b7a6-d9e92f064560\",\"authority\":\"a9a90c0c-0173-431f-b38a-2cb97de433e4\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eEleventh of the thirteen levels of the god realm of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Cloudless.” In some versions of the longer Prajñāpāramitā sūtras, which list sixteen realms instead of thirteen, this god realm has the name Parīttabṛhat (Tib. \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Bo-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003echung che\u003c/foreign\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Anabhraka\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྲིན་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anabhraka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sprin med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7bd42065-689d-456d-8f83-789ac6366a8e\",\"authority\":\"2c02baf4-0ece-4579-8f66-c49bcc21f21f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA major śrāvaka disciple and personal attendant of the Buddha Śākyamuni during the last twenty-five years of his life. He was a cousin of the Buddha (according to the \u003ccite class=\\\"title break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eMahāvastu\u003c/cite\u003e, he was a son of Śuklodana, one of the brothers of King Śuddhodana, which means he was a brother of Devadatta; other sources say he was a son of Amṛtodana, another brother of King Śuddhodana, which means he would have been a brother of Aniruddha).\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eĀnanda, having always been in the Buddha’s presence, is said to have memorized all the teachings he heard and is celebrated for having recited all the Buddha’s teachings by memory at the first council of the Buddhist saṅgha, thus preserving the teachings after the Buddha’s parinirvāṇa. The phrase “Thus did I hear at one time,” found at the beginning of the sūtras, usually stands for his recitation of the teachings. He became a patriarch after the passing of Mahākāśyapa.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Ānanda\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀུན་དགའ་བོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ānanda\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kun dga’ bo\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9e6908f8-5334-46fd-bf40-67302ece77f0\",\"authority\":\"1af81df3-440c-4c37-897c-30aeb9faf235\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe placing of attention, especially on four particular objects: body, feelings, mind, and phenomena. Classified among the dharmas of the path, and figuring among the thirty-seven factors in awakening. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/78f7b789-0780-4e7f-89ea-f8200537793f\\\"/\u003en.218\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"applications of mindfulness\",\"tibetan\":\"དྲན་པ་ཉེ་བར་གཞག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"smṛtyupasthāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dran pa nye bar gzhag pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"008c3a1b-918f-46bd-86bc-88e848c59e61\",\"authority\":\"2b52f5bf-301a-4324-a183-5ca961bd8b1b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSixth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Immeasurable Radiance.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Apramāṇābha\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚད་མེད་འོད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apramāṇābha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshad med ’od\"}},{\"uuid\":\"69e8192a-4e67-4fd5-a5f6-d3078ca1a504\",\"authority\":\"147f742b-de9f-4851-ae1b-10fcfb730119\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eNinth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Immeasurable Virtue.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Apramāṇaśubha\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚད་མེད་དགེ\",\"sanskrit\":\"apramāṇaśubha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshad med dge\"}},{\"uuid\":\"760a6413-3e40-4356-a524-e8a825911f9e\",\"authority\":\"6d74dfd0-53d8-493e-911f-04831c0dd16b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eA god realm of form listed in this and other texts between the thirteenth heaven of the form realm, Bṛhatphala, and the five pure abodes of the form realm, known collectively as Śuddhāvāsa. Its name means “Being Without Conception.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Asaṃjñisattva\",\"tibetan\":\"འདུ་ཤེས་མེད་པའི་སེམས་ཅན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṃjñisattva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’du shes med pa’i sems can\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ba0e60fd-071a-4769-84d4-b1b151062016\",\"authority\":\"45fc6c39-2cc7-459a-aa9e-89fb4d15ed38\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who accepts whatever is offered\",\"tibetan\":\"གཞི་ཇི་བཞིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yāthāsaṃstarika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzhi ji bzhin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"85d8c8b9-d5b6-4cfe-a35b-b82bc083d7a9\",\"authority\":\"86342d40-a839-4dc6-bd1c-b16b32a2bff0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who dwells in the forest, wilderness area\",\"tibetan\":\"དགོན་པ་པ།, དགོན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāntāram, kāntārāṇi, āraṇyaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dgon pa, dgon pa pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2578fc88-c96f-41b1-9320-47553c135d27\",\"authority\":\"86342d40-a839-4dc6-bd1c-b16b32a2bff0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who dwells in the forest, wilderness area\",\"tibetan\":\"དགོན་པ་པ།, དགོན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāntāram, kāntārāṇi, āraṇyaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dgon pa, dgon pa pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3fcb650a-05b1-4357-b600-7a1a36a335c8\",\"authority\":\"61bb1ba2-90e3-4bdf-ade8-cabaa39e54a0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who has three robes\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་གོས་གསུམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"traicīvarika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos gos gsum pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9ccaa507-7ef0-4809-82f0-ab5e83d3da67\",\"authority\":\"20f57030-81be-469f-bcb0-d15e679e15cb\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who lives at the foot of a tree\",\"tibetan\":\"ཤིང་དྲུང་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vṛkṣamūlika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"shing drung pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"596d26fb-e519-4233-a23c-05795508d8e0\",\"authority\":\"1285d0ae-bfb7-494f-9274-1c38f51058b2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who lives in charnel grounds\",\"tibetan\":\"དུར་ཁྲོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śmaśānika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dur khrod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4d9de190-69ed-4fb2-9442-a318923d73d8\",\"authority\":\"db43ca67-3ce9-4fd1-afa1-2437c38062ce\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who lives in seclusion, contented with few desires\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་པ་ཉུང་ཞིང་ཆོག་ཤེས་པ་རབ་ཏུ་དབེན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"alpecchaḥ saṃtuṣṭaḥ praviviktaḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod pa nyung zhing chog shes pa rab tu dben pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a80bd219-b9a6-45ba-b09b-69b62740fb8f\",\"authority\":\"4d8a308f-f45a-4108-84d6-e2137bb5dbb9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who lives in the open air\",\"tibetan\":\"བླ་གབ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhyavakāśika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bla gab med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"34b49fa7-a0e4-46b3-b986-b1ef68753a28\",\"authority\":\"c0b70776-e2f1-4e72-bc08-61df6d11803b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who never eats later\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟས་ཕྱིས་མི་ལེན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"khalu­paścādbhaktika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zas phyis mi len pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6dfab12c-8f93-42f0-8c91-b9eca5382e79\",\"authority\":\"7dd47e60-44b0-4436-ae34-3ba4bb60253e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who seeks alms\",\"tibetan\":\"བསོད་སྙོམས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"piṇḍapātika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsod snyoms pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a2712332-6697-46b8-b3dc-ad1010ef044e\",\"authority\":\"e694660b-765f-4cde-9e15-1fc6075c6d79\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who stays upright\",\"tibetan\":\"ཅོག་པུ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"naiṣadyika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"cog pu ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"79702dba-0e9c-47b5-acb3-dee7e9c9143b\",\"authority\":\"5e857417-8ee3-4c9a-95b6-3455cc49245e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who uses a single seat\",\"tibetan\":\"སྟན་གཅིག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ekāsanika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"stan gcig pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ce34a26d-d673-4ddd-9e45-ffc9c57da590\",\"authority\":\"35d84484-4a4f-477a-9bce-0d5645523083\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who wears felt garments\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྱིང་པ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nāmantika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phying pa ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f15838ba-c0d1-4ec4-9eec-d36e4b86c9a4\",\"authority\":\"0fce5c11-f028-429e-b963-ad09753161b7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab\\\"/\u003en.1076\u003c/a\u003e and following notes.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ascetic who wears rags\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྱག་དར་ཁྲོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pāṃsukūlika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phyag dar khrod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e68a0709-ed66-4452-b4ce-c6444e5fb88b\",\"authority\":\"ca63bb7f-ceba-45f1-b520-ac2199b60741\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/f293ea18-7a51-49aa-b184-f1a1f975484f\\\"/\u003en.219\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp/\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"aspects of awakening\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཡན་ལག\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhyaṅga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub kyi yan lag\"}},{\"uuid\":\"99d9f306-91f3-4a57-a146-b50dab39e6f2\",\"authority\":\"d70bf5fd-41a7-4582-bc7b-b3abe624cb99\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSecond of the five pure abodes, meaning “Painless.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Atapa\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་གདུང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"atapa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi gdung ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1b7e341e-95b8-47c3-89e6-6c9610cefb0f\",\"authority\":\"907a4b01-cb5e-498b-9826-c5b08425c05d\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Atiśa, Atiśa Dīpaṃkaraśrījñāna, Dīpaṃkaraśrījñāna\",\"tibetan\":\"\",\"sanskrit\":\"atiśa dīpaṃkaraśrījñāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2c06a068-3ad3-483f-a261-d4ea2d90dc1e\",\"authority\":\"95acd478-281b-4695-964b-87226891c1b0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"atom\",\"tibetan\":\"རྡུལ་ཕྲ་མོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aṇu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rdul phra mo\"}},{\"uuid\":\"39144dcc-0557-458e-9125-94971f66e77f\",\"authority\":\"bfe00539-f153-4e11-8e05-daf233344c72\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"attached to worldly enjoyments\",\"tibetan\":\"འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཟང་ཟིང་དང་ལྡན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"lokāmiṣa­prati­saṃyukta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’jig rten gyi zang zing dang ldan pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"35c7fc73-8b93-4ff9-af78-3b2b909418a4\",\"authority\":\"bc2c8a1b-6799-4a9b-a768-246e085488c3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"attachment\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་ཆགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rāga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod chags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fd4ed926-5860-48e5-a86c-ac44fd110d9b\",\"authority\":\"a77b95a5-1094-41dd-997c-ee47575e36a7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"attack by someone else\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕ་རོལ་གྱི་གནོད་པ་བྱེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"paropakrama\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pha rol gyi gnod pa byed\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3e66b608-2ac2-4bdd-860f-2bd59296d831\",\"authority\":\"3412bfd8-94dd-4d9e-a8a1-43eb6ce85438\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"attentive mental state, attentiveness\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡིད་ལ་བྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"manasīkāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yid la byed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7bea5dcd-33ce-40af-aca6-9c1243d8e867\",\"authority\":\"bd323848-71dc-4dc7-b776-4ce60e874fb6\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"attribute, meditative perspective\",\"tibetan\":\"རྣམ་པ།, རྣམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ākāra, ākāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam pa, rnam pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"06bf8485-36ec-4c4d-9635-5e15d894fa0c\",\"authority\":\"bd323848-71dc-4dc7-b776-4ce60e874fb6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eA defining characteristic, like, for instance, the dewlap of a cow. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/1af2e9ed-1e0a-4774-b0c7-87414484171b\\\"/\u003en.881\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"attribute, meditative perspective\",\"tibetan\":\"རྣམ་པ།, རྣམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ākāra, ākāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam pa, rnam pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2a9612bf-49bd-4e08-91f7-86bd6c124c06\",\"authority\":\"78401834-1378-49c9-95a2-dc04c3db6681\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name that six hundred future buddhas will all take after attaining awakening, as foreordained by the Buddha in chapter 21.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Avakīrṇakusuma\",\"tibetan\":\"མེ་ཏོག་བཀྲམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avakīrṇakusuma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"me tog bkram pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9d70508c-0282-4103-9280-71707a95c258\",\"authority\":\"a017cc45-7e3f-460d-8577-a093c7543a2e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSecond lowest of the five pure abodes, meaning “Slightest.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Avṛha\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་ཆེ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avṛha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi che ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d20b5373-498b-464c-abb9-2ed170ffda7f\",\"authority\":\"035cf8dc-71e6-4d97-9223-b323759886d0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"become disenchanted\",\"tibetan\":\"སྐྱོ་བར་བྱེད་པར་འགྱུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saṃvegam āpatsyate\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"skyo bar byed par ’gyur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"885b4c66-bae2-4e53-a5f7-0f35f6b2800c\",\"authority\":\"4b8bdba1-f7dc-4771-b00f-9d6cc352f16a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/7193f9ab-e6a6-439f-a32b-bd9671e37ff7\\\"/\u003en.337\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/5ee86383-373a-4b3b-ac2b-a9849d3aefd5\\\"/\u003en.257\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"benefits\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོན་ཏན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"guṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yon tan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e0b9c1ff-2cea-40f6-89ee-7ed3ef312bc1\",\"authority\":\"fd9750c1-d23e-4830-b06a-6178494755ac\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"benevolence\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱམས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"maitrī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byams pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1e5dad8a-ee7f-454c-9154-37e4ac40d3e9\",\"authority\":\"f1f65190-0810-42e0-ab99-90091f84a998\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Best\",\"tibetan\":\"བཟང་མཆོག\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhadrottamā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bzang mchog\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0b8cae9c-affc-4153-9e88-da1b28c8ac37\",\"authority\":\"67fec56e-ef33-4f73-9011-b0d52844a0ed\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eDescribes a stage on the path of bodhisattvas (or bodhisattvas who have reached that stage) at which their realization is such that henceforth nothing can ever make them turn back from progressing toward the full awakening of a buddha.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"beyond regressing\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྱིར་མི་ལྡོག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avinivartanīya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phyir mi ldog pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1ed84ea2-32b5-4e94-a60b-42b6acaa355a\",\"authority\":\"f403706a-7706-43d6-ad0c-761f7db3fa88\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eDescribes a stage on the path of bodhisattvas (or bodhisattvas who have reached that stage) at which their realization is such that henceforth nothing can ever make them turn back from continuing to make progress toward the full awakening of a buddha. For the sake of brevity our English rendering follows the Sanskrit and Tibetan, but it should not be understood as implying that such bodhisattvas have already attained the full awakening of a buddha. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"beyond regressing from unsurpassed, perfect awakening\",\"tibetan\":\"བླ་ན་མེད་པ་ཡང་དག་པར་རྫོགས་པའི་བྱང་ཆུབ་ལས་ཕྱིར་མི་ལྡོག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avinivartanīyo ’nuttarāyāḥ samyaksambodheḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bla na med pa yang dag par rdzogs pa’i byang chub las phyir mi ldog pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6d9c9af5-b408-4472-8c8f-49a385e980e6\",\"authority\":\"e09afc6b-98c1-4e66-8831-415f115a618e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003e“Irresistible Thundering Melodious Voice,” the name of the tathāgata in whose buddhafield the bodhisattva Sadāprarudita is said by the Buddha Śākyamuni to be presently residing after attaining his quest for the teachings, as described in the exemplary narrative of the final chapters of this sūtra, found also in the \u003ccite xml:lang=\\\"en\\\"\u003eTwenty-Five Thousand\u003c/cite\u003e but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Bhīṣma­garjita­nirghoṣasvara\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྲ་དབྱངས་མི་ཟད་པར་སྒྲོགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhīṣma­garjita­nirghoṣasvara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgra dbyangs mi zad par sgrogs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2af3bf2d-e63e-4ab0-ad3f-b2221c96f746\",\"authority\":\"0b749701-506f-4baf-a691-2f9bdfcf9c9d\",\"definition\":\"$44\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Bimbisāra\",\"tibetan\":\"གཟུགས་ཅན་སྙིང་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bimbisāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzugs can snying po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597\",\"authority\":\"2b190410-5ef2-4a3a-a428-89d999d14336\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe honorific term applied to the Buddha Śākyamuni and other buddhas in numerous Buddhist texts. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/1129dad4-86ef-43db-a16b-84f05c8b2a34\\\"/\u003en.67\u003c/a\u003e\u003c!--note 65--\u003e for Ratnākaraśānti’s explanation of its meanings. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"blessed one\",\"tibetan\":\"བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhagavan\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bcom ldan ’das\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d48d036f-b731-4a94-bfa8-487ac298aa50\",\"authority\":\"492b7a37-a199-4508-8143-9d964e5e2607\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"blessed with the power\",\"tibetan\":\"སྟོབས་བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"balādhiṣṭhāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"stobs byin gyis brlabs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e1a0ae95-d0df-4915-aee1-35ee95f36bef\",\"authority\":\"ccf1d837-c138-401f-b29e-bc00f478ad23\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"73d373da-ddb6-4549-8f56-bfb57eab537b\",\"authority\":\"ccf1d837-c138-401f-b29e-bc00f478ad23\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d9b0a61b-2875-44ab-9a01-a735f65914de\",\"authority\":\"ccf1d837-c138-401f-b29e-bc00f478ad23\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"bd780437-3915-40e7-be2e-4114bfdc5ebc\",\"authority\":\"ccf1d837-c138-401f-b29e-bc00f478ad23\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"46d66fd1-5e77-4b75-8987-f43d0d9ea5c7\",\"authority\":\"dec9a390-0104-4b2a-aa14-c666b6ddad74\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eMost specifically in this text, the term refers to the ten or eleven serial levels or \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003ebhūmis\u003c/foreign\u003e of which the progression of bodhisattvas toward awakening is comprised from the path of seeing onward, each defined in terms of qualities possessed and obscurations eliminated (see \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/aafbb194-8854-42d1-9df1-996700bb6944\\\"/\u003en.104\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/aa10746e-eb28-486e-933a-1e9d47ae674d\\\"/\u003en.109\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/92cea5ab-062a-47b6-b310-0c6dde9a66ed\\\"/\u003en.379\u003c/a\u003e). Often also used in this text to refer to the level of bodhisattvas in general, or to more generic stages in the sequence of levels, such as the “level of nonregressing” or the “impure levels.” \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"bodhisattva level, levels of a bodhisattva\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་ས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhi­sattva­bhūmi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub sems dpa’i sa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d1d91886-d66b-4e4d-a74f-ddb2dc10c74b\",\"authority\":\"0d1f6dd0-6ffb-430e-a6db-435fe443630b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eFor the play on the two meanings of the Sanskrit term, see \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/0dd1d7a0-321d-4efe-b65e-93dd13a1ba24\\\"/\u003en.879\u003c/a\u003e\u003c!--note 872--\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"bodhisattva’s irreversible fault-free state\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་སྐྱོན་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhi­sattvanyāma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub sems dpa’i skyon med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7538360f-7e4c-4ced-8053-b01e3cc3b911\",\"authority\":\"f272c825-89ed-43e5-9f9c-b50616e9d07b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/afcfacf3-e7c1-416a-8ac2-2bc54b5e739d\\\"/\u003en.279\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"body\",\"tibetan\":\"སྐུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śarīra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sku\"}},{\"uuid\":\"16945947-8642-4545-9f4b-dc408059e451\",\"authority\":\"db36127a-581c-4efe-9ebf-172706c136f8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe principal god of the realm of form.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e  \u003cp\u003eA high-ranking deity presiding over a divine world; he is also considered to be the lord of the Sahā world (our universe). Though not considered a creator god in Buddhism, Brahmā occupies an important place as one of two gods (the other being Indra/Śakra) said to have first exhorted the Buddha Śākyamuni to teach the Dharma. The particular heavens found in the form realm over which Brahmā rules are often some of the most sought-after realms of higher rebirth in Buddhist literature. Since there are many universes or world systems, there are also multiple Brahmās presiding over them. His most frequent epithets are “Lord of the Sahā World” (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esahāṃpati\u003c/em\u003e) and Great Brahmā (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003emahābrahman\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brahmā\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brahmā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"de329cfc-68c0-4cbf-9369-db8d0fa432e4\",\"authority\":\"55a600c9-c2f9-48a7-9b19-39a5ff3282f4\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eFirst and lowest of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Stratum of Brahmā.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brahmakāyika\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་རིས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brahmakāyika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs ris\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ac62b307-b113-4054-b510-51d781a9a567\",\"authority\":\"68c5b143-54b4-4c0d-b64d-a9b30967e69d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThird of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Retinue of Brahmā.” In some texts it is a synonym of Mahābrahma.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brahmapārṣadya\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་འཁོར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brahmapārṣadya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs ’khor\"}},{\"uuid\":\"31f35796-b134-4ba5-83f7-f3edb4a5f6c4\",\"authority\":\"15013434-829b-4924-b806-195c6192a240\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSecond of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Brahmā Priest.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brahmapurohita\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་པའི་མདུན་ན་འདོན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brahmapurohita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs pa’i mdun na ’don\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5210665a-85fd-492a-89c7-8ae7ca5d12d3\",\"authority\":\"caa09862-01a8-4085-9494-d2cce3c709c7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"break through to understanding, broke through to understanding\",\"tibetan\":\"རྟོགས་པར་ཁོང་དུ་ཆུད་པར་གྱུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gatiṃgatāḥ saṃvṛttāḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtogs par khong du chud par gyur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cd13c16b-1c44-4de6-ac16-1cef12ae2179\",\"authority\":\"6a9bbb29-903d-467f-b8d9-e31a19d63481\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThirteenth and highest of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Great Fruition.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Bṛhatphala\",\"tibetan\":\"འབྲས་བུ་ཆེ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bṛhatphala\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’bras bu che\"}},{\"uuid\":\"03b36254-58d2-41ec-ae1e-6cb6a9533c84\",\"authority\":\"4552fd86-fa93-4c48-a35e-50c3b610f5a2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of the four gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brightly Colored Blossoms\",\"tibetan\":\"མེ་ཏོག་སྣ་ཚོགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"puṣpacitra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"me tog sna tshogs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1622ff41-65d3-42bb-b276-34df9519a734\",\"authority\":\"ee073b1b-14cf-4325-8578-e21b3d3703e8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/18edbd46-bb10-42f7-8ee4-b5689245f34e\\\"/\u003en.483\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"buddha eye, eye of a buddha\",\"tibetan\":\"སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་སྤྱན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"buddhacakṣus\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sangs rgyas kyi spyan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3e1a9707-a0c5-4477-a334-9910a8f20bd9\",\"authority\":\"ba5cb14b-400f-4c2b-919d-461bdc1b5a1a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"buddhahood\",\"tibetan\":\"སངས་རྒྱས་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"buddhatva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sangs rgyas nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"bbab6a7c-0f7d-4cee-aaab-b4e99998a044\",\"authority\":\"a2ea7fb9-17d7-43b5-bf52-4f817aa79f58\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"can be relied upon\",\"tibetan\":\"བརྟེན་པར་བགྱིད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"āśrayaṇīyā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"brten par bgyid pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"41818727-cb09-44a4-9bdf-d2020ed24de6\",\"authority\":\"df2daae1-8eea-4aeb-aa4d-b79f01608447\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"cannot be led astray\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་འཕྲོགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṃhārya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ’phrogs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"60675101-5552-4e21-affb-f8174ce0fbfc\",\"authority\":\"ef2d3669-e536-432a-acf7-019f0a743c58\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"carpenter\",\"tibetan\":\"ཤིང་མཁན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"palagaṇḍa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"shing mkhan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"957e3930-f634-46cd-b984-00365824da56\",\"authority\":\"bed9f761-13b1-473c-bcd4-7421476282f5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"caulked\",\"tibetan\":\"མིག་ཚགས་བྱ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ākoṭitā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mig tshags bya\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b95ee0ed-0883-427c-8ab4-cc125bf3a224\",\"authority\":\"299b34a9-49b5-46e1-8991-354e5ccc4e90\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"challenging questions\",\"tibetan\":\"བརྒལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pratyanuyoga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"brgal ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cbe161d6-bda8-48a6-a029-e57fb233281c\",\"authority\":\"1aa943b1-57ac-4423-9a08-8624079f32fc\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"clear mindset that trusts\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་དང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prasannacitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems dang ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685\",\"authority\":\"7f207445-e881-4565-ae08-b63deee9f0c8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe term used in the long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras to denote the knowing of a buddha. It includes the thirty-nine aspects of dwelling as a buddha together with thirty-seven aspects of the fruition of a disciple and thirty-four of the fruition of a bodhisattva to make one hundred and ten aspects in all. See notes \u003c\u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/e4aa9d05-9318-426c-a033-8575dc18b0b6\\\"/\u003en.626\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/a70deeb3-66b9-4ef3-8ba1-79a2fcdeffaf\\\"/\u003en.631\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/b1cbb855-2f3d-4d9e-ba90-a66843002f70\\\"/\u003en.637\u003c/a\u003e; also Brunnhölzl 2011, vol. 2, pp. 296–97.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"complete knowing of all aspects of all things, knowing of all aspects, knowing of all the aspects, state of complete knowing\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།, རྣམ་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarvajñatā, sarvākārajñatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam pa thams cad mkhyen pa nyid, thams cad mkhyen pa nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f1f21402-d1eb-4ca2-b32a-df9dbdf949a5\",\"authority\":\"7f207445-e881-4565-ae08-b63deee9f0c8\",\"definition\":\"$45\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"complete knowing of all aspects of all things, knowing of all aspects, knowing of all the aspects, state of complete knowing\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།, རྣམ་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarvajñatā, sarvākārajñatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam pa thams cad mkhyen pa nyid, thams cad mkhyen pa nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ef32ced0-5382-4709-a435-b03b4fd4ec94\",\"authority\":\"be11b8dd-4778-46e8-ae9d-69f060ba11a8\",\"definition\":\"$46\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"complete nirvāṇa\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"parinirvāṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su mya ngan las ’das pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0faa015f-8bbb-458f-9bde-a64ace5ea668\",\"authority\":\"b3d561fa-6d30-48bb-83b0-feebc53dc285\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"components of mindsets\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་ལས་བྱུང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caitasika, cittacaitasikā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems las byung ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"140592e9-5e5e-49f2-a96e-416e9da31ac5\",\"authority\":\"943f8980-5ce2-4057-a3ae-0ffb9571f0ec\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA state of deep \u003cspan\u003econcentration\u003c/span\u003e in which the mind is absorbed in its object to such a degree that conceptual thought is suspended. It is sometimes interpreted as settling (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eāhita\u003c/em\u003e) the mind in equanimity (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esama\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"concentrated\",\"tibetan\":\"མཉམ་པར་བཞག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"samāhita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mnyam par bzhag pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ba1a42d5-f4a3-4c72-8f5d-f87f36b9c4a3\",\"authority\":\"95e659ed-65f2-47e3-b3cc-ee6029b7a48b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn epithet used to refer to a buddha.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"conqueror\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"jina\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyal ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a9dcd797-e573-4380-928d-315c5a937d64\",\"authority\":\"f2f8087a-7057-49ce-bbcd-c026d2fac596\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"constituents underlying the clinging to existence\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉེ་བར་ལེན་པའི་ཕུང་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ūpādānaskandha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nye bar len pa’i phung po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8df35a77-da33-4cc6-bd50-2c4e26946da9\",\"authority\":\"23226215-5e0e-4408-aa7f-59c6cfce80a6\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"conventional expression\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐ་སྙད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vyavahāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tha snyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"09c05b6d-a329-4c05-b87e-7cf90d70f4e1\",\"authority\":\"29baeb19-29e5-4deb-808a-9981baa5608c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"correct viewpoint\",\"tibetan\":\"ལྟ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dṛṣṭi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lta ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c6734b49-014c-4fb7-8f2c-2381175fc086\",\"authority\":\"848036a6-cb5a-45af-a863-a2de132cfe3c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"corrupter of bodhisattvas\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་སུན་འབྱིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhi­sattvadūṣin\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub sems dpa’ sun ’byin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"15c39eb4-e0fe-4564-ae38-569372760af0\",\"authority\":\"772371c7-7080-4de4-86bf-0bdefef5ee0b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"counterfeit\",\"tibetan\":\"གཟུགས་བརྙན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prativarṇikā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzugs brnyan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2b1f1c71-ea37-4fb7-938a-c0acd5a8c4d0\",\"authority\":\"6de4d0ef-60c1-49fa-801d-e4484304c2a8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee notes \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17\\\"/\u003en.1094\u003c/a\u003eand \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/c4ede759-d915-49a8-b469-b3579ecfec25\\\"/\u003en.1100\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"crowded, full of people\",\"tibetan\":\"འདྲེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ākīrṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dres pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"08ff4aa9-bae0-47bc-b36c-93ba28c249f0\",\"authority\":\"4251774f-9945-4aa6-b04a-72ddd579467e\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"cultivate, cultivation\",\"tibetan\":\"བསྒོམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhāvanā, bhāvayatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsgom pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4a39048e-b820-4771-8627-1eaf765d95bc\",\"authority\":\"c3948116-f8e1-499b-9daf-907e83dffa69\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"cut the ties to worldly existence\",\"tibetan\":\"སྲིད་པར་ཀུན་ཏུ་སྦྱོར་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་ཟད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pari­kṣīṇabhava­saṃyojana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"srid par kun tu sbyor ba yongs su zad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"70c46af5-0c80-4d15-a018-cac10ce06459\",\"authority\":\"358d1f13-838f-44a7-9595-04699ebf2524\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA state of involuntary existence conditioned by afflicted mental states and the imprint of past actions, characterized by suffering in a cycle of life, death, and rebirth. On its reversal, the contrasting state of nirvāṇa is attained, free from suffering and the processes of rebirth.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"cyclic existence\",\"tibetan\":\"འཁོར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saṃsāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’khor ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4c374c63-a45e-4842-bb17-d09113e278f4\",\"authority\":\"757a4905-8898-445d-939e-84e46874e21a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"deathless dimension\",\"tibetan\":\"བདུད་རྩིའི་དབྱིངས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"amṛta­dhātudvāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdud rtsi’i dbyings\"}},{\"uuid\":\"40841ac7-4cac-4f1c-82c2-bf1806fb2cb4\",\"authority\":\"757e714c-b394-4719-95ea-df413de354f4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"decoy\",\"tibetan\":\"བཅོས་བུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāraṇḍavaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bcos bur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4c94a4b6-cfe3-4a16-b4b9-df24e6f8b5df\",\"authority\":\"c30875d0-7183-468a-98a1-4c6a5e2359d7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"dedication of rejoicing\",\"tibetan\":\"རྗེས་སུ་ཡི་རང་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་བསྔོ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anumodanā­pariṇāmana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rjes su yi rang ba yongs su bsngo ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2d02adec-81cc-4588-8fac-3bc3550be67b\",\"authority\":\"2d056103-a37a-40ce-b8e1-790f0c5f2125\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"defend\",\"tibetan\":\"བསྐྱབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"āvaraṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bskyab pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"39b22918-3623-4e61-b135-20b615ebbd49\",\"authority\":\"05a459e9-242c-4628-b101-18fe862c9beb\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"deformed\",\"tibetan\":\"རྡུམ་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kuṇṭha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rdum po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"39672c9c-5efd-495f-9952-6c1b0682c8cb\",\"authority\":\"05c826f8-3b10-4f3c-bcca-38d72328625b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"deluded sense of grandeur\",\"tibetan\":\"ལོག་པའི་ང་རྒྱལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mithyāmāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"log pa’i nga rgyal\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ff293643-80a4-40e0-95cb-0149b659984a\",\"authority\":\"51f8041e-7261-4c4a-a6da-5416f1b23cea\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe deities ruled over by Māra. The term can also refer to the devas in his paradise, which is sometimes identified with Paranirmitavaśavartin, the highest paradise in the realm of desire. This is distinct from the four personifications of obstacles to awakening, also known as the four māras (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edevaputramāra\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003emṛtyumāra\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eskandhamāra\u003c/em\u003e, and \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ekleśamāra\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"demon cohort\",\"tibetan\":\"བདུད་ཀྱི་རིས་ཀྱི་ལྷ་དག\",\"sanskrit\":\"mārakāyika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdud kyi ris kyi lha dag\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b87a4b94-ba4f-4882-bbd2-3bbb715c4244\",\"authority\":\"67eb4adf-0f25-42cb-88f6-75cd74d5dd3e\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"depart for the ascetic life\",\"tibetan\":\"མངོན་པར་བྱུང་ནས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhiniṣkramya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mngon par byung nas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"25503faa-de94-4eee-a273-6e00ef3ad66c\",\"authority\":\"3c1319e5-95bc-431e-b1f0-b17d4914f7c5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"develop conceits\",\"tibetan\":\"རློམ་སེམས་སུ་བགྱིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"manyeta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rlom sems su bgyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ea400c56-f5af-4899-8997-425cbffa9950\",\"authority\":\"68f4d098-9df0-4226-afb9-e443b97c6d23\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"develop the proper mindset, development of the proper mindset\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་བསྐྱེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"cittotpāda, cittotpādam utpādayati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems bskyed\"}},{\"uuid\":\"19c22f6b-4f9d-4fe3-831a-83322887fb21\",\"authority\":\"02a3306b-becf-430d-8419-8616bebbf0c4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"developed reserve of strength\",\"tibetan\":\"སྟོབས་བསྐྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"balādhāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"stobs bskyed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"414181c7-78f4-481f-bbac-ff5cbd9f39e2\",\"authority\":\"dfe3ecde-1019-43da-ad16-5f4c94700605\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma guide\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་ཀྱི་ཚུལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmanetrī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos kyi tshul\"}},{\"uuid\":\"147c30d7-64bf-4790-a767-8458e2edd12e\",\"authority\":\"5b2ed3c9-0e7b-459e-8cc5-95afa7a3810a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eSpeaker or reciter of scriptures. In early Buddhism a section of the saṅgha would consist of \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ebhāṇakas\u003c/em\u003e, who, particularly before the teachings were written down and were only transmitted orally, were a key factor in the preservation of the teachings. Various groups of dharmabhāṇakas specialized in memorizing and reciting a certain set of sūtras or vinaya.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma teacher\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་སྨྲ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmabhāṇaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos smra ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f89a2785-7003-4bea-98aa-20782b9b7b3f\",\"authority\":\"82e2c496-99ed-4af1-affd-198fdc447964\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma teachings\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་སྟོན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmadeśanā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos ston pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"050f79f1-4606-4f4b-8231-f0273d900eb6\",\"authority\":\"9bdd81a2-4092-4257-b0c9-6e21e1b993f5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma treasury\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་ཀྱི་མཛོད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmakośa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos kyi mdzod\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d51a0333-62e7-495a-b5c7-c8180ed89159\",\"authority\":\"c26ec362-8c4a-43ce-881f-39480d8c4b5b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma’s true nature, true nature of things\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་རྣམས་ཀྱི་ཆོས་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmāṇāṃ dharmatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos rnams kyi chos nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8ea02329-4d61-49a0-8072-b3dc4aa7c7e3\",\"authority\":\"9b50a946-139b-491d-8fbc-8b2ea2bfbbaf\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn eighth- to ninth-century Tibetan translator, reviser, and editor.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharmataśīla\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་ཉིད་ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmataśīla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos nyid tshul khrims\"}},{\"uuid\":\"27250080-c9f1-438d-b068-fe9b2c37bb40\",\"authority\":\"a98141d1-4884-4201-ae9a-efa646c007ad\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe bodhisattva from whom Sadāparudita seeks the teaching on the perfection of wisdom in the exemplary narrative of the final chapters of this sūtra, found also in the \u003ccite xml:lang=\\\"en\\\"\u003eTwenty-Five Thousand\u003c/cite\u003e but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharmodgata\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་འཕགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmodgata\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos ’phags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"266be7ce-6591-4f96-814d-dc90c4a16741\",\"authority\":\"2c7622e1-403c-40c9-9ae6-c73ee42212f9\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"difficult to fathom\",\"tibetan\":\"བལྟ་དཀའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"duravagāha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"blta dka’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"36b3fbd8-77b7-46ae-ae91-c68df9ccc63d\",\"authority\":\"ea89062a-6b9d-4fcd-93f7-d19fcc9b1f02\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eDīpaṃkara was the buddha in the past under whose guidance the Buddha Śākyamuni, in a distant previous life, first made the vow to attain buddhahood and from whom he received the foreordaining of his future attainment (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003evyākaraṇa\u003c/foreign\u003e). In many texts he is counted as the fourth in a lineage of twenty-seven buddhas who preceded Śākyamuni.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dīpaṃkara\",\"tibetan\":\"མར་མེ་མཛད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dīpaṃkara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mar me mdzad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6675bd2e-6c67-4a17-a019-27fec94abc16\",\"authority\":\"1699619f-8ace-45ce-9337-2b832558d9be\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe capital city in the royal palace of which the Buddha Śākyamuni, in a distant previous life as a bodhisattva, studied under the Buddha Dīpaṃkara.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dīpavati\",\"tibetan\":\"མར་མེ་ཅན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dīpavati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mar me can\"}},{\"uuid\":\"26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243\",\"authority\":\"b662e79b-4cff-4567-b74a-1c23d3f1fea7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eA “disciple” refers to someone who “listens” to the teachings of the Buddha and “causes others to listen” to those teachings, i.e., by repeating them. The word \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003eśrāvaka\u003c/foreign\u003e is taken as a causative construction in the second case.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"disciple\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉན་ཐོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śrāvaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nyan thos\"}},{\"uuid\":\"52752661-3a09-44a2-987c-621472602bd0\",\"authority\":\"84e675d7-6b71-4e27-9a9f-d0c540d58687\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"dishonesty\",\"tibetan\":\"གཡོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śāṭhya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"g.yo\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9700f5f2-a159-44eb-a3e7-bbc3ef1b7588\",\"authority\":\"1e28bf6a-977f-4a82-a446-194539307299\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"display of a buddha\",\"tibetan\":\"སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་རྣམ་པར་རོལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"buddha­vikrīḍita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sangs rgyas kyi rnam par rol ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c0d45733-639d-481f-8fdf-6b5c5ae57984\",\"authority\":\"b23003a0-76db-4c64-b39d-b99b2a50f531\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"dissipated\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣīṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"89dd6689-01ff-4bc5-a2ea-a5666c7a72e3\",\"authority\":\"7244b57f-723a-403e-9710-8836e352e5ec\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"dissipation\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2261b026-7bf0-4081-9715-fea6e8237195\",\"authority\":\"d5dab423-1927-4edd-9b6e-b123e8034319\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"dissuade\",\"tibetan\":\"འདུན་པ་ཟློག་པར་བྱེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vicchandayiṣyati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dun pa zlog par byed\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d5496651-412a-48c9-b30f-c1366e4ce8b6\",\"authority\":\"b66d7baf-2ee6-4e0b-bfef-4067043d6bba\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"does not uphold\",\"tibetan\":\"རྗེས་སུ་འཛིན་པར་མི་འགྱུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anugrahīṣyati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rjes su ’dzin par mi ’gyur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7705331c-b980-477b-a7b4-1f1bfcef9209\",\"authority\":\"03d312a7-9405-4022-9d7d-ed7cf595ba3e\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"drinkable water\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆུའི་དགོན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pānīya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chu’i dgon pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"02f47f04-862d-4b90-82e9-f287aedfc7ad\",\"authority\":\"0844520a-ad9a-487a-8f82-ca3951c0ba6c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn important scholar-teacher (1003–1064) and disciple of Atiśa.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dromtön Gyalwai Jungné\",\"tibetan\":\"འབྲོམ་སྟོན་རྒྱལ་བའི་འབྱུང་གནས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’brom ston rgyal ba’i ’byung gnas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"afefa815-1f96-45fd-94c2-6ffbb231e8e1\",\"authority\":\"dd2986a5-dd80-488e-bd25-2ae04f63093c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"dwell with ease\",\"tibetan\":\"ལེགས་པར་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"susthita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"legs par gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0a30bc25-73be-43de-8c14-c859073ce19f\",\"authority\":\"60ea771c-0a46-4dd8-ab8d-27921600eae7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eagerness\",\"tibetan\":\"འདུན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"chanda\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dun pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b48cabc9-2f55-443e-bc3c-9d984c195db5\",\"authority\":\"37a52b45-6ddb-41ac-ac30-a68bac9c0fab\",\"definition\":\"$47\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eighteen distinctive qualities of a buddha\",\"tibetan\":\"སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཆོས་མ་འདྲེས་པ་བཅོ་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aṣṭādaśāveṇika­buddha­dharma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sangs rgyas kyi chos ma ’dres pa bco brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6645bcac-da93-43d6-8ee0-7330f77e4742\",\"authority\":\"775a38ad-19c1-4d3e-b761-cbeef284bd10\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eEighteen aspects of the earthquake that accompany a tathāgata’s realization of perfect awakening. Note that the Tibetan term is “eight great signs.” See also \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/f059a41a-2c11-4352-b06d-13ec1e6bdb18\\\"/\u003en.870\u003c/a\u003e\u003c!--note 863--\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eighteen great signs\",\"tibetan\":\"ལྟས་ཆེན་པོ་བཅྭ་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aṣṭādaśa­mahā­nimittam\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ltas chen po bcwa brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2a2dc97d-419e-4d8c-b230-79d2cb378213\",\"authority\":\"e3685c95-a735-4cb3-a0e7-d0d5dc0b3295\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eIn the context of Buddhist philosophy, one way to describe experience in terms of eighteen elements (eye, form, and eye consciousness; ear, sound, and ear consciousness; nose, smell, and nose consciousness; tongue, taste, and tongue consciousness; body, touch, and body consciousness; and mind, mental phenomena, and mind consciousness).\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis also refers to the elements of the world, which can be enumerated as four, five, or six. The four elements are earth, water, fire, and air. A fifth, space, is often added, and the sixth is consciousness.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"element\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khams\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5702e490-14a4-44c4-ae3d-50a5e1bd75bd\",\"authority\":\"9692559e-037d-4ec3-acf1-df2ebffe2597\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"emanation body\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྲུལ་པའི་སྐུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nairmāṇikakāya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sprul pa’i sku\"}},{\"uuid\":\"612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0\",\"authority\":\"c87671dd-3ffd-410d-a94d-fca04ee8ccc2\",\"definition\":\"$48\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"emotional defilements\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉོན་མོངས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kleśa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nyon mongs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a4bc79cb-434c-49fb-88f6-f0970444d657\",\"authority\":\"463d39e1-c0de-4f86-8f48-e1c50b3c7d4f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eUsed specifically in the context of “enclosing” relics in a stūpa\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"enclose\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་འཛིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"parigṛhṇīyād\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su ’dzin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"bb81289a-6f28-427c-897b-ab8835bb5493\",\"authority\":\"44f1fe6a-101c-43f4-80d7-26b291ddefd9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eMeditation (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003eyoga\u003c/foreign\u003e) here is glossed as “meditative concentration” (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003esamādhi\u003c/foreign\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"engage in meditation\",\"tibetan\":\"རྣལ་འབྱོར་དུ་བྱེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yogam āpadyate\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnal ’byor du byed\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9f72a614-4918-4c15-b189-26405b2aac3a\",\"authority\":\"3467af23-ec7c-47ca-ae1a-7636b24a4165\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"enjoyment body\",\"tibetan\":\"ལོངས་སྤྱོད་རྫོགས་པའི་སྐུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saṃbhogikakāya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"longs spyod rdzogs pa’i sku\"}},{\"uuid\":\"46c907ec-4d2d-4f0a-b574-a377d39e0602\",\"authority\":\"ca3a370f-1342-44b4-bb77-8d9b677a0ce9\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"enlightening\",\"tibetan\":\"གསལ་བར་བགྱིད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avabhāsakarin\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gsal bar bgyid pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9b79e93c-7837-4794-9ee9-9fa7a9bf805b\",\"authority\":\"6039d7d8-7338-4d12-ba9b-81706d37c5f8\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"equal to the unequaled\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་མཉམ་པ་དང་མཉམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asamasama\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi mnyam pa dang mnyam pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"76aa6a9e-107d-4134-94f6-e4853818eb61\",\"authority\":\"da04a8fb-0625-43cd-8eef-26022aa33270\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"essential nature\",\"tibetan\":\"རང་བཞིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prakṛtiḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rang bzhin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a07e0ac1-ff46-4d29-bca1-939e3a0362d5\",\"authority\":\"a46a2aee-71a5-4f96-8a0b-f6d0611efe11\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"essential nature of a mindset\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་ཀྱི་རང་བཞིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"cittaprakṛti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems kyi rang bzhin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5f3bedb9-60b1-420a-bfe9-02b42dbbcb85\",\"authority\":\"4bf3573e-c4fb-4688-8365-5e3a80ff9293\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eternalism\",\"tibetan\":\"རྟག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śāśvata\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtag pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"db80746c-d186-4671-a39d-729913d0a7c8\",\"authority\":\"b38659ed-9407-4d7d-b9f4-1586169f4bc2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eMorally virtuous or disciplined conduct and the abandonment of morally undisciplined conduct of body, speech, and mind. In a general sense, moral discipline is the cause for rebirth in higher, more favorable states, but it is also foundational to Buddhist practice as one of the three trainings (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003etriśikṣā\u003c/em\u003e) and one of the six perfections of a bodhisattva. Often rendered as “ethics,” “discipline,” and “morality.”\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ethical discipline\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śīla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshul khrims\"}},{\"uuid\":\"066eea31-9548-4976-9942-4a2a4873c36f\",\"authority\":\"de89f075-9bca-4219-b126-4bb4d7f2edb4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"exaltedness\",\"tibetan\":\"དབང་ཆེ་བར་གྲགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"maheśākhya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbang che bar grags pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"14edc247-014d-4709-ae85-40b31fbf888d\",\"authority\":\"3bd26db2-9cf8-46bc-acfd-95f009efa744\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"excellent ability\",\"tibetan\":\"དབང་ཕྱུག\",\"sanskrit\":\"aiśvarya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbang phyug\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1c168449-161c-4018-8155-fb3aa5f9be29\",\"authority\":\"f416e6e9-e642-4eed-9f06-1730616ad8da\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"excellent qualities of a buddha\",\"tibetan\":\"སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཡོན་ཏན་ཕུན་སུམ་ཚོགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"buddha­guṇasaṃpad\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sangs rgyas kyi yon tan phun sum tshogs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ba9676ee-5941-4097-9aec-0f5be27570f3\",\"authority\":\"e477ee3a-5cd2-416e-a7b8-f876ee8db3e8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/07d40714-85d8-461a-8bd9-e6077fa2c791\\\"/\u003en.74\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"exemplary\",\"tibetan\":\"གླང་པོ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahānāga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"glang po chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"616b778d-a0da-4baa-81ab-a8f7014cdd73\",\"authority\":\"77a6dd81-2e17-481c-9466-178fddf332d2\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"exhaust\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣīna, paryātta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a806e6f1-726d-42ca-a907-ce1b4f2fb8d6\",\"authority\":\"eb6e3cab-ba91-4984-866e-26dd63167b27\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"expansive\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆེན་པོར་གྱུར་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahadgata\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chen por gyur pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1c2bda21-a975-473a-81eb-d7e02622cf2f\",\"authority\":\"bb33ae70-3a5d-4305-ae31-77faee902cba\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"extremely lustrous, lustrous\",\"tibetan\":\"གཟི་བརྗིད་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahaujaska\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzi brjid chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5f16e036-e9a2-47ee-a53c-0c96250e9857\",\"authority\":\"d446af6c-b807-4c2d-ae67-641d4f0de5f9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/f293ea18-7a51-49aa-b184-f1a1f975484f\\\"/\u003en.219\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"factors in awakening\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཕྱོགས་ཀྱི་ཆོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhi­pakṣa­dharmāḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub kyi phyogs kyi chos\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0469046c-c58d-4e26-a1fd-ab5e6054490d\",\"authority\":\"a6df7d8c-5670-4fee-82f3-e46b62ccfcd3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"familial lineage\",\"tibetan\":\"རུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gotra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8f060324-d310-4924-8622-147385a88d47\",\"authority\":\"e3741278-a4ef-4fc3-be7f-ee5c03a73040\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"fettered\",\"tibetan\":\"བཅིངས་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"baddha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bcings ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b725a967-b194-43e0-af4b-6a83f546339e\",\"authority\":\"557eae60-59b1-4995-b025-02d8d854f402\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"field\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྱོད་ཡུལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gocara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spyod yul\"}},{\"uuid\":\"14d822fc-e184-4e5e-affd-9e3b08918c08\",\"authority\":\"c899da45-ebc2-4d83-9730-bfb49a68c113\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"firm conviction, has firm conviction, resolved\",\"tibetan\":\"མོས་པ།, མོས་པ།, མོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhimucyate, adhimukta, adhimukti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mos, mos pa, mos pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"609d5abe-76ed-41e8-a714-30ff92acba34\",\"authority\":\"c899da45-ebc2-4d83-9730-bfb49a68c113\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"firm conviction, has firm conviction, resolved\",\"tibetan\":\"མོས་པ།, མོས་པ།, མོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhimucyate, adhimukta, adhimukti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mos, mos pa, mos pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b1a5e818-1156-4126-81de-80e24b2a308b\",\"authority\":\"c899da45-ebc2-4d83-9730-bfb49a68c113\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"firm conviction, has firm conviction, resolved\",\"tibetan\":\"མོས་པ།, མོས་པ།, མོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhimucyate, adhimukta, adhimukti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mos, mos pa, mos pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"81a0ce86-ce18-4d56-9cf7-be1e6dcd8946\",\"authority\":\"eeef01e2-1ae0-4321-baf9-d058cea1a265\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"firm grounding\",\"tibetan\":\"གཏིང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gādha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gting\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f65668aa-2d7e-44c5-b625-5469abb565d7\",\"authority\":\"50a431b4-e905-49bb-81a9-a24f51cbd3f0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/18edbd46-bb10-42f7-8ee4-b5689245f34e\\\"/\u003en.483\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"five eyes\",\"tibetan\":\"མིག་ལྔ།, སྤྱན་ལྔ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pañcacakṣuḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mig lnga, spyan lnga\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ee84bfce-1a1b-4b04-8759-abc580dabf71\",\"authority\":\"08d0c8b6-7e73-419a-bf7b-483e29fe818c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/baaa4005-5f68-4b47-b32a-be2c32e3e045\\\"/\u003en.516\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"five karmic deeds that ripen immediately, five karmic deeds with immediate consequences\",\"tibetan\":\"མཚམས་མ་མཆིས་པ་ལྔའི་ལས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pañca­karmānantarya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mtshams ma mchis pa lnga’i las\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6da64de4-0d9c-4307-a6dc-bf40763e25ef\",\"authority\":\"3fe8614c-58d0-4408-a037-2243b303b199\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"focused on what is beyond measure\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚད་མེད་པར་ངེས་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apramāṇaniyato\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshad med par nges ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c4e500fe-7933-4b56-b233-f8ed5cbca36d\",\"authority\":\"aed3082f-4e2a-4979-b0c2-b832f2a0d371\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"foothold\",\"tibetan\":\"གཏིང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gādha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gting\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4b894866-b26a-44f9-9f32-76c50adc4874\",\"authority\":\"f81c6176-6dad-455d-b21c-810a1434ce61\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"formless attainments\",\"tibetan\":\"གཟུགས་མེད་པའི་སྙོམས་པར་འཇུག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ārūpya­samāpatti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzugs med pa’i snyoms par ’jug pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cf4920b7-8e10-4fa5-94ec-faa94b096f50\",\"authority\":\"09dc7a3d-a558-4e80-8f4c-835bbd6ba6cb\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"foundation\",\"tibetan\":\"གཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nidāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d590480f-827b-48f0-b682-03f665f5e5e8\",\"authority\":\"d0099514-8ec5-4014-9139-eb47d42c74a0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eFour gods who live on the lower slopes (fourth level) of Mount Meru in the eponymous Heaven of the Four Great Kings (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eCāturmahā­rājika\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ergyal chen bzhi’i ris\u003c/em\u003e) and guard the four cardinal directions. Each is the leader of a nonhuman class of beings living in his realm. They are Dhṛtarāṣṭra, ruling the gandharvas in the east; Virūḍhaka, ruling over the kumbhāṇḍas in the south; Virūpākṣa, ruling the nāgas in the west; and Vaiśravaṇa (also known as Kubera) ruling the yakṣas in the north. Also referred to as Guardians of the World or World Protectors (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003elokapāla\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003e’jig rten skyong ba\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Four Great Kings\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱལ་པོ་ཆེན་པོ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"catvāro mahārāja\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyal po chen po bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"33c6ed0c-9310-41c6-b40a-0919c2be6941\",\"authority\":\"4fd43520-939f-4f26-98c3-f8e40155dada\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee notes \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/c85aa09c-b6af-40d2-917a-a131598725c0\\\"/\u003en.489\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/c4f41ec8-1a45-4cba-a188-2dd503b0e289\\\"/\u003en.490\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/1282f9e0-f815-4815-80f2-5afcb2062af7\\\"/\u003en.632\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four grounds for self-confidence\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་འཇིགས་པ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"catur­vaiśāradya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ’jigs pa bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"32f65bab-92cb-4a22-b3a4-c0c2eb9ac261\",\"authority\":\"b4dc4adf-3751-44c9-909b-5a535d9799ea\",\"definition\":\"$49\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four sublime states\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚད་མེད་པ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"catur­brahma­vihārāḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshad med pa bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1cfd14aa-6bcf-4933-88fc-6f08baeebd29\",\"authority\":\"ce1c196b-ed27-413a-81a2-19e45d3c5a2c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe four truths that the Buddha transmitted in his first teaching: (1) suffering, (2) the origin of suffering, (3) the cessation of suffering, and (4) the path to the cessation of suffering.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four truths\",\"tibetan\":\"བདེན་པ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"catuḥsatya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bden pa bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8cfc4cee-b636-4ba4-be70-bb9d82317b28\",\"authority\":\"a8e1f71c-9f29-461d-9f42-687c48d43e34\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/4465cba8-27d4-4dc4-a097-e578ba89f198\\\"/\u003en.557\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four types of experiential knowledge\",\"tibetan\":\"སོ་སོ་ཡང་དག་པར་རིག་པ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"catuḥpratisaṃvid\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"so so yang dag par rig pa bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"83ac25e2-6340-4579-a494-9221df581418\",\"authority\":\"2bcee9d1-76ca-477e-9c31-ba9770456437\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eGenerosity, kind words, meaningful actions, and practicing what one preaches.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four ways of attracting disciples\",\"tibetan\":\"བསྡུ་བའི་དངོས་པོ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"catuḥ­saṃgraha­vastu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsdu ba’i dngos po bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"10f50cd7-0cb6-47a7-ac8f-b515c644db08\",\"authority\":\"90581374-0e5e-499d-b68e-6fadef71a4ce\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"fragrant oil\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱུག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vilepana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byug pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9fea1c3a-8171-4a64-b63b-3e1024aa180b\",\"authority\":\"096a910f-d1e1-44c8-9876-f8ecf67495ee\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/cc78e3e8-83ac-4898-8794-cb8f724a1e3e\\\"/\u003en.187\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/02df0d16-01d1-4d86-86e5-ce2d119b855c\\\"/\u003en.188\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from creating duality\",\"tibetan\":\"གཉིས་སུ་བགྱིར་མ་མཆིས།, གཉིས་སུ་བྱར་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"advaidhīkāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gnyis su bgyir ma mchis, gnyis su byar med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e60b0155-5de7-4f3f-8743-f7df9bf34c12\",\"authority\":\"fa6ba879-1b5f-41a6-856d-3e94311e80a5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from dwelling, free of depending on, not dwelling\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aniśrita, asthita, asthāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a32d3e86-1f02-4a93-b38b-0b2b51096ef3\",\"authority\":\"fa6ba879-1b5f-41a6-856d-3e94311e80a5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from dwelling, free of depending on, not dwelling\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aniśrita, asthita, asthāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"46effacc-8f20-453e-940a-0e17c0d581b5\",\"authority\":\"fa6ba879-1b5f-41a6-856d-3e94311e80a5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from dwelling, free of depending on, not dwelling\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aniśrita, asthita, asthāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3d7a289b-1ecf-4ee5-9ad7-0aff502da027\",\"authority\":\"31657084-0b1c-484a-9de5-90999963f022\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from inclinations, freedom from inclinations\",\"tibetan\":\"སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།, སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apraṇihita, apraṇihita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"smon pa med pa, smon pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e0bf0c80-f45e-4aa7-9705-bc85d07eb310\",\"authority\":\"31657084-0b1c-484a-9de5-90999963f022\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from inclinations, freedom from inclinations\",\"tibetan\":\"སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།, སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apraṇihita, apraṇihita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"smon pa med pa, smon pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3712d133-eb33-4ee8-a83c-e65ad14fba3b\",\"authority\":\"ae1dc199-7873-4f6b-a146-9ab46d4af143\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from signs, freedom from signs\",\"tibetan\":\"མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།, མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ānimitta, ānimitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mtshan ma med pa, mtshan ma med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f4df1ede-b83e-4ef5-913e-760f4e1ff5a3\",\"authority\":\"ae1dc199-7873-4f6b-a146-9ab46d4af143\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free from signs, freedom from signs\",\"tibetan\":\"མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།, མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ānimitta, ānimitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mtshan ma med pa, mtshan ma med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02\",\"authority\":\"d048c2a2-47fd-4b6e-84d8-232789278567\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of a mindset\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་མ་མཆིས་པ།, སེམས་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"acitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems ma mchis pa, sems med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"82abea74-6e6c-456a-b390-8fceb82f9b05\",\"authority\":\"651ac15c-e5fe-4907-8e13-e013b748639a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of any state of being\",\"tibetan\":\"དངོས་པོ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhāva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dngos po med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4dac8d6d-9df1-4a50-8b20-a7fdb56b0d49\",\"authority\":\"f331418a-7079-4e67-8a67-c63de5be8a47\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of blameshifting\",\"tibetan\":\"གཡོ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aśāṭhyatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"g.yo med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d1711a1a-6a85-4b8c-8393-b04394cc31e2\",\"authority\":\"a8741beb-b398-4dd4-b586-eb384012ed94\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of ceasing\",\"tibetan\":\"འགག་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anirodha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’gag pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6e5cd77d-41f5-4104-a8b7-c8814a7885fa\",\"authority\":\"4057c81c-5203-420c-908d-9016e4b7d63d\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of changing\",\"tibetan\":\"འགྱུར་བ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avikāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’gyur ba med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d00bb5e9-1956-4af1-a225-87b45ea5e996\",\"authority\":\"ac0d1450-7c59-4dbb-94b1-0a8651df4ef3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of conceptualization\",\"tibetan\":\"རྣམ་པར་མི་རྟོག, རྣམ་པར་རྟོག་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avikalpa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam par mi rtog, rnam par rtog pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ff2bf7a3-8ddb-42c4-881d-3236d230220f\",\"authority\":\"12dbd790-f395-494f-bf76-131445dc51cf\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of dwelling\",\"tibetan\":\"གནས་པ་དང་བྲལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"viṣṭhitaṃ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gnas pa dang bral ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c93f25f7-d04b-4f0d-94ed-49e1707914b1\",\"authority\":\"9b0a1fab-a611-4d18-a0ea-bb626cb8b9ff\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of emotional defilement\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀུན་ནས་ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṃkleśa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kun nas nyon mongs pa ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"22d0cda8-ae20-43d1-995b-88995299df5a\",\"authority\":\"e21f6b84-c460-486b-bc9d-da372398d961\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of enmeshment\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་མ་ཟིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aparyāpannaṃ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su ma zin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3689e652-c404-47d7-a8b6-de95e649587b\",\"authority\":\"1b9c9760-4edd-4b90-b547-5500fd167473\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of inherent nature\",\"tibetan\":\"ངོ་བོ་ཉིད་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asvabhāvatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ngo bo nyid ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d7836ff1-45bf-4575-84da-6070c8a00e36\",\"authority\":\"a866d410-f67f-4517-949c-4d1d6e4aa5d2\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of mental perception\",\"tibetan\":\"དམིགས་སུ་མ་མཆིས་པ།, དམིགས་སུ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anupalabdhi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dmigs su ma mchis pa, dmigs su med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2318e292-6583-4e59-9f11-9a747a591f2b\",\"authority\":\"9dd162c7-d7a1-4a83-bc58-9c76631bdedf\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of perishing\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་ཟད་པའི་ཕྱིར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akṣayatva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi zad pa’i phyir\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d48d6a86-480e-44c0-811a-37bb68a394a9\",\"authority\":\"a322c123-3e20-42cc-b4cf-b345b88604d2\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of transmigrating\",\"tibetan\":\"མཚམས་སྦྱོར་བ་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apratisaṃdhir\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mtshams sbyor ba ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cd340d90-7265-4b1e-8dac-e06e331ff1a1\",\"authority\":\"2a680b16-7375-4087-abb9-bfa862bc6ac3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"free of worldly influences\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟག་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anāsrava\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zag pa ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"922ebc37-9627-42ce-b7f7-0e8d047cd228\",\"authority\":\"da77cbcf-525d-4a29-9ecd-87ec60b99d3c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"freedom from any false nature\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྱིན་ཅི་མ་ལོག་པ་དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avitathatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phyin ci ma log pa de bzhin nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6066c993-0a9e-4ef5-a214-be2aee11b7c8\",\"authority\":\"7a708014-062c-4cc9-9013-12cab94d6f42\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"freedom from birth\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་སྐྱེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ajāti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma skyes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"943a6002-5faa-477a-9f40-41e0575d3d81\",\"authority\":\"9f2e3fa9-9a26-4d71-889b-756ae2893aac\",\"definition\":\"$4a\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"freedom from clarification\",\"tibetan\":\"རྣམ་པར་འཇིག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avibhāvanā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam par ’jig pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"90feacf7-7b60-4d31-b659-e8b08a6b4501\",\"authority\":\"85b36131-5a6d-4492-9ff8-377429a90f5c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"freedom from conceptualizing\",\"tibetan\":\"རྟོག་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avikalpatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtog pa ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"92355df8-e464-46fa-a17b-52f382e7b2fa\",\"authority\":\"44de7bfc-0f88-4c7c-9960-9ce118fee937\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"freedom from conditioning\",\"tibetan\":\"མངོན་པར་འདུ་མི་བྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anabhisaṃskāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mngon par ’du mi byed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2e1f83fb-8f5e-44ad-81a7-d553b24ec2e2\",\"authority\":\"c4ba034e-6090-41a8-abb1-39adc00698ef\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"fruit of a worthy one, fruitional state of a worthy one\",\"tibetan\":\"དགྲ་བཅོམ་པ་ཉིད་ཀྱི་འབྲས་བུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"arhattvaphala\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dgra bcom pa nyid kyi ’bras bu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"972dafb2-701f-48fe-bcaa-da82cd54d466\",\"authority\":\"f26b2d87-6789-4d54-be2e-f0a6378b96a0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name (meaning “Musth Elephant”) of a bodhisattva in the buddhafield of Abhirati. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gandhahastin\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤོས་ཀྱི་གླང་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gandhahastin\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spos kyi glang po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"141cd5b1-456c-4ed3-92eb-6a8e9767bebc\",\"authority\":\"9303a432-193a-41a9-a594-674df01d44c8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe city in which the estate of the bodhisattva Dharmodgata is located, as described in the exemplary narrative recounting Sadāprarudita’s quest for the perfection of wisdom that forms the final chapters of this sūtra, found also in the \u003ccite xml:lang=\\\"en\\\"\u003eTwenty-Five Thousand\u003c/cite\u003e but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gandhavatī\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤོས་དང་ལྡན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gandhavatī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spos dang ldan pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4313e11f-55d0-4757-89e1-c9754c695ec7\",\"authority\":\"b8a56298-a6e1-4260-9000-895dacf2d0e1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eA woman whose name, meaning “goddess of the Ganges,” appears as the title of chapter 19, towards the end of which she makes a powerful statement and some offerings of flowers. Her future awakening is foreordained by the Buddha, who states that she first gave rise to the mindset of awakening, like him, in the presence of the Buddha Dīpaṃkara.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gaṅgadevī\",\"tibetan\":\"གང་གཱའི་ལྷ་མོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gaṅgadevī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gang gA’i lha mo\"}},{\"uuid\":\"22ebce57-bb52-45a3-b6be-0c5f7d120b64\",\"authority\":\"d2a8b240-fbcc-4308-a4e6-8f583fe743dc\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"gaping\",\"tibetan\":\"གླལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vijṛmbhamāṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"glal ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4c1f8747-2ed7-4cd3-93ec-100eef958b40\",\"authority\":\"ea722ad2-af32-486d-94be-e661e4878848\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"garlands of light\",\"tibetan\":\"མར་མེའི་ཕྲེང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dīpamālā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mar me’i phreng ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8753d337-1c4c-483e-99d5-13f15f704613\",\"authority\":\"73ba5420-3695-4491-892a-7bee53c245db\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"genuine Dharma, genuine teachings\",\"tibetan\":\"དམ་པའི་ཆོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saddharma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dam pa’i chos\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ddb07ba8-ecfb-4456-804f-2d1affedd66c\",\"authority\":\"04f8f23b-3c0a-4602-a81c-d0f30b569485\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"getting familiar with\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་སྦྱོང་བར་བྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"parijayaṃ karoti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su sbyong bar byed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e63bd4b9-8468-4f68-a27f-fdb690db445e\",\"authority\":\"7073ac1e-595f-4e39-8a4c-329319f6f736\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"getting very close\",\"tibetan\":\"བསྙེན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhyāsanna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsnyen pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e47cf8c1-4e22-4e6c-af2f-a5dac51c76a0\",\"authority\":\"9aa93106-0b6e-442e-a3ff-4ce08a08cc78\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eTranslations of the Sanskrit verb √\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003ecar\u003c/foreign\u003e sometimes suggest that bodhisattvas should “practice” the perfection of wisdom, but the English verb “to practice” wrongly implies that some mental effort, special focus, or activity is always required to exercise the perfection of wisdom. That bodhisattvas should “go about life” means that they should do whatever they do in life (i.e., sit, walk, eat, sleep, and so on) in the perfection of wisdom. See also notes \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/81a6f613-1221-408c-bb41-1ded241d4490\\\"/\u003en.52\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/f292bd6c-f578-43ce-9545-283ad17ff402\\\"/\u003en.1217\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"go about life, go about life, goes about life, goes about life, going about life\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྱོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"carana, caryā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spyod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0fd1d6b0-b105-4939-8546-65a4fb4dfdc3\",\"authority\":\"f06dbf91-3242-4307-a6ce-4b2297225b29\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"go beyond cyclic existence\",\"tibetan\":\"ངེས་པར་འབྱུང་བར་འགྱུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"niryāsyati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nges par ’byung bar ’gyur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"92a15fe2-cf71-4674-b98f-d8510bf2b3a9\",\"authority\":\"45e85493-7355-4690-b982-f729a7fb85cf\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"gone beyond\",\"tibetan\":\"ངེས་པར་འབྱུང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"niryāta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nges par ’byung ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f5b2a1db-a341-4788-af87-e95cf8cf311e\",\"authority\":\"b8d48c6e-a0e1-48a5-b7db-6e210fa1911e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Good\",\"tibetan\":\"བཟང་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhadra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bzang po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fd0b2d07-92d5-43bb-9951-18e77e49a8ff\",\"authority\":\"9f46dcdf-196a-49da-b9b0-cd44b873bd8b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"good fortune of auspicious rebirth\",\"tibetan\":\"དལ་བ་ཕུན་སུམ་ཚོགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣaṇasaṃpada\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dal ba phun sum tshogs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9ad57dee-0f91-411f-82e9-d9bd5a72e294\",\"authority\":\"8d44e37f-150c-4758-a406-0568830cf089\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"good qualities\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁ་དོག\",\"sanskrit\":\"varṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kha dog\"}},{\"uuid\":\"be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e\",\"authority\":\"a6c40c30-43ed-4634-9b0a-1d707dbc463f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn epithet very frequently appended to “bodhisattva” to signify that he or she has a magnanimous (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003emahat\u003c/foreign\u003e) attitude with strong (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003emahat\u003c/foreign\u003e) renunciation and great (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003emahat\u003c/foreign\u003e) realization. Other glosses (see \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/8feedae1-0b37-4234-979e-c9e51b9b084c\\\"/\u003en.390\u003c/a\u003e\u003c!--note 383--\u003e) explain that a “great being” is a bodhisattva replete with means, or one with a particular resolve.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"great being\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་དཔའ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahāsattva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems dpa’ chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5edca432-75cc-4168-a011-da8c0660439e\",\"authority\":\"9a756070-8289-4da7-8340-e4e06d2ade44\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eWhen the Buddhist teachings are classified according to their power to lead beings to an awakened state, a distinction is made between the teachings of the Lesser Vehicle (Hīnayāna), which emphasizes the individual’s own freedom from cyclic existence as the primary motivation and goal, and those of the Great Vehicle (Mahāyāna), which emphasizes altruism and has the liberation of all sentient beings as the principal objective. As the term “Great Vehicle” implies, the path followed by bodhisattvas is analogous to a large carriage that can transport a vast number of people to liberation, as compared to a smaller vehicle for the individual practitioner.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"great journey, great path\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།, ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahāyāna, mahāyāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"theg pa chen po, theg pa chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d41190f8-e0a4-4c2e-8194-1413404d3e9c\",\"authority\":\"9a756070-8289-4da7-8340-e4e06d2ade44\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/5fefd43b-03fd-4877-9ac4-43028ed6e35b\\\"/\u003en.167\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e  \u003cp\u003eWhen the Buddhist teachings are classified according to their power to lead beings to an awakened state, a distinction is made between the teachings of the Lesser Vehicle (Hīnayāna), which emphasizes the individual’s own freedom from cyclic existence as the primary motivation and goal, and those of the Great Vehicle (Mahāyāna), which emphasizes altruism and has the liberation of all sentient beings as the principal objective. As the term “Great Vehicle” implies, the path followed by bodhisattvas is analogous to a large carriage that can transport a vast number of people to liberation, as compared to a smaller vehicle for the individual practitioner.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"great journey, great path\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།, ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahāyāna, mahāyāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"theg pa chen po, theg pa chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5a72b881-5bcf-4a09-8e97-7778d3313a0c\",\"authority\":\"1f3aaf3e-1454-4cc9-9473-a88404da6338\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"great mass of demerit\",\"tibetan\":\"བསོད་ནམས་མ་ལགས་པའི་ཕུང་པོ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahā­puṇya­skandha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsod nams ma lags pa’i phung po chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"61d46b2b-e15f-4acb-a944-d2b6cc59f0e4\",\"authority\":\"b40c77d6-7463-43b7-88b8-fd4bbbb4fdff\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"great multitude\",\"tibetan\":\"སྐྱེ་བོ་མང་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahājana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"skye bo mang po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5381d3e6-d4c8-461e-b80f-ec5b3809795f\",\"authority\":\"0ec7046b-70b3-4837-a339-862bad4aba98\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"great task\",\"tibetan\":\"བགྱི་བ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahākṛtya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bgyi ba chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"537e7459-4b69-46f6-9545-71e3246654ca\",\"authority\":\"d02b67cb-45d9-4a15-a4a3-348f02604f5a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"greatest goal\",\"tibetan\":\"མཆོག་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"agratā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mchog nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"906cf322-811f-4af0-8086-cfc7837bdfc5\",\"authority\":\"7170f374-c41f-4a10-a22e-300dbec2b747\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"gross mindset\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vipulāni cittāni\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems rgya chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a9cfa25e-788c-45ad-b792-12eb4d66502d\",\"authority\":\"48de3e6b-b841-4e34-a0e5-a360bf30f7d1\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"habitual tendencies\",\"tibetan\":\"བག་ཆགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vāsana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bag chags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"136071b2-0ae6-4d14-b8c0-ea6216ec6ef0\",\"authority\":\"2b7209ee-4428-4a42-8af7-35e732ece19d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/60d69938-6322-4b4f-83a4-5e4fd9535313\\\"/\u003en.71\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"had become self-controlled\",\"tibetan\":\"དབང་དུ་གྱུར་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vaśībhūta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbang du gyur pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c0e446d3-a020-4375-96b7-a622b74bfd89\",\"authority\":\"7b8cabfd-6b4c-42fc-ac80-bf422892b887\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"had eliminated the worldly influences\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟག་པ་ཟད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣīṇāsrava\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zag pa zad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"dfbfa194-a6ed-4c00-a116-64dd4fda6e02\",\"authority\":\"d5a3da05-953f-46ea-91fd-9325bee03119\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/ee27689d-ffba-4f9d-a894-fab229faded6\\\"/\u003en.76\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"had laid down their burdens\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁུར་བོར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apahṛtabhāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khur bor ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b174fd68-32f5-4727-acaf-302a6bd3e16b\",\"authority\":\"b2d3b302-cf9e-4210-a084-c6c55e208e02\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"had no emotional defilements\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"niḥkleśa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nyon mongs pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4db0bb9d-79e5-48d4-991d-dfe8e8ff51f6\",\"authority\":\"21535edc-6c83-422e-8d22-7cce4c4fa9fb\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"half mile\",\"tibetan\":\"གྲགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"krośa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"grags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cb20be11-bf59-442b-a011-b53599eaa1e0\",\"authority\":\"301df2be-922b-4250-8aa4-55bc54d32961\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe second from lowest god realm of desire, presided over by the thirty-three gods of whom Śakra is the chief.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Heaven of the Thirty-Three, Heaven of the Thirty-Three Gods\",\"tibetan\":\"སུམ་ཅུ་རྩ་གསུམ་གྱི་རིས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"trāyastriṃśa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sum cu rtsa gsum gyi ris\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5d1d72f1-9235-4ab0-a383-9d79108ea211\",\"authority\":\"e8f0b0c6-293c-40a3-9546-8a8dd36b0bfd\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"heroic perseverance\",\"tibetan\":\"བརྩོན་འགྲུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vīrya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"brtson ’grus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"506f944c-d376-4454-839d-f5c30eb07b16\",\"authority\":\"6e3e2782-f474-41c6-a561-1933c7ad9478\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"identity\",\"tibetan\":\"བདག\",\"sanskrit\":\"ātman\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdag\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27\",\"authority\":\"4fd49e86-ff16-4bfb-b73b-81dd5199b3bf\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ignorance\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་རིག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avidyā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma rig pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"05a3d610-b8c8-4534-bb60-f3ba86a5e76a\",\"authority\":\"867c7d80-d1c2-40a3-a48b-4f410f5d1a3e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eTo make visible, in this text usually in the sense of how mind or awareness functions, but also in the sense of physical light.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"illuminate, illuminated, illumination\",\"tibetan\":\"གསལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prakāśa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gsal ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d\",\"authority\":\"8654b96c-6b27-41bd-a0e9-a38c6f1542ff\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThis term (in its verbal and noun forms) is used in this translation in the sense of illuminating or elucidating by speaking, i.e., by expressing something in speech with all the eloquence of a confident knowledge of what is being illuminated, hence the Tibetan rendering \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Bo-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003espobs pa\u003c/foreign\u003e (“courage,” “audacity”). The Sanskrit term has connotations of brilliance, clarity, and intelligence as well as audacity. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/4943e454-e79c-4a57-912d-4cf9ca2affb9\\\"/\u003en.84\u003c/a\u003e\u003c and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/3fee1f0e-6848-4109-8b66-b032e4e5795d\\\"/\u003en.326\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"illuminate, illuminated, illumination\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤོབས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pratibhāna, pratibhāti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spobs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"57974a4b-70aa-4113-9a22-2b735c4b5303\",\"authority\":\"708deac6-b2f5-4e61-8b43-37831801dd73\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"illusory nature of things\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྱུ་མའི་ཆོས་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"māyādharmatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgyu ma’i chos nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7545c03a-7b18-44cb-bc71-3d43fbc009eb\",\"authority\":\"38ed1609-c0b1-479c-8ec8-6db762c1f6b3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"illusory person\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྱུ་མའི་སྐྱེས་བུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"māyāpuruṣa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgyu ma’i skyes bu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f5db1ce1-2156-4425-9eeb-35f53d3e14b0\",\"authority\":\"40f4e5bf-f144-4f63-8939-d266e3c00b60\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"imitation of bodhisattvas\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་བཅོས་བུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhi­sattva­prativarṇika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub sems dpa’ bcos bu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b6d126c4-75af-4ae3-a06d-ed6e6e6a2ad7\",\"authority\":\"14d513b0-ce98-4c59-a58f-e2ba6022a2c4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"immature\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bāla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6a266dc0-0dc5-41ae-94af-31c183398592\",\"authority\":\"58bb9180-d7df-4831-9db1-071abbe51999\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"immature roots of virtue\",\"tibetan\":\"དགེ་བའི་རྩ་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་མ་སྨིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aparipakva­kuśala­mūlāḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dge ba’i rtsa ba yongs su ma smin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fc91a840-b068-4763-9ab5-5da0338e95c6\",\"authority\":\"7c35948f-0ef3-4d93-ac4b-9555d958b800\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"impediments to survival\",\"tibetan\":\"སྲོག་གི་བར་ཆད་དུ་འགྱུར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"jīvitāntarāya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"srog gi bar chad du ’gyur ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b431f6f7-952e-4e24-8c23-853585cc8a6b\",\"authority\":\"33f1eab5-5ec8-45ed-99b6-0d93465db10f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"imperishability of the imperishable\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་ཟད་པ་ལ་མི་ཟད་པ་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akṣayākṣaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi zad pa la mi zad pa nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a4f81caa-eae6-4aae-9c96-f6dcfedbbef2\",\"authority\":\"97a30104-d51c-455d-842a-c1d822101f8f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"improper means of livelihood\",\"tibetan\":\"ལོག་པས་འཚོ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mithyājīva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"log pas ’tsho ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7152f9a9-fcdb-4bfb-bc8e-1f6760863715\",\"authority\":\"bf579286-c7ed-4c46-b4df-b06cad2c725a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"improper sexual conduct, sexual misconduct\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་པས་ལོག་པར་སྤྱོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāmamithyācāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod pas log par spyod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"656c6fb9-baff-42ed-92cc-c3566df18e32\",\"authority\":\"723220d3-c9a5-42b9-b7b3-c92d74810b3c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"in accordance with reality\",\"tibetan\":\"ཇི་ལྟ་བ་བཞིན་དུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yathābhūtam\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ji lta ba bzhin du\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3af4d769-35ad-4ad1-b79d-ff27501be4d4\",\"authority\":\"2dc6ffbf-17b6-47b9-a1cc-9da8732bc7b7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"in any manner\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐམས་ཅད་ནས་ཐམས་ཅད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarvathā sarvaṃ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"thams cad nas thams cad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5a0b72c2-5c95-48bc-8de6-e0fff5efc196\",\"authority\":\"2b297b8d-d525-42a5-a4be-f1f090fd012c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"in conformity with the truth\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡང་དག་པ་ཉིད་རྗེས་སུ་རྟོགས་པས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhūtānugamena\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yang dag pa nyid rjes su rtogs pas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e522e2b8-ad22-4c6e-9a42-458d7d23c694\",\"authority\":\"2cb74e4f-5bbd-41d7-b5ae-96364eb17c48\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThis translation is applied when \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003e-bhūta\u003c/foreign\u003e is used at end of a compound.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"in effect\",\"tibetan\":\"དུ་གྱུར་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhūta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"du gyur pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"811e77ab-4e3e-4301-a50b-6ad60c9e81b3\",\"authority\":\"43c08bd8-68a4-419c-bc16-5e1d2ea576de\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"in the form of a book\",\"tibetan\":\"གླེགས་བམ་དུ་ཆུད་པར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pustakagatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"glegs bam du chud par\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a7f22c1a-24b6-4d08-9954-737b6aff3c4f\",\"authority\":\"cea8b4ea-b07a-46c6-b856-4a994b3480f0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"incense\",\"tibetan\":\"བདུག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhūpa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdug pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7dc66eda-56ca-4d72-ba4c-b461150d26ab\",\"authority\":\"30cefc4e-6273-43f8-af21-f9af2c0e2e8b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inclined to attack\",\"tibetan\":\"རྩོད་པར་འདོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vigrahītukāma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtsod par ’dod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e2e56ede-71eb-4c6e-b1e6-6860a80f08a6\",\"authority\":\"9f0571a9-3e79-4217-a974-c25a1edecac0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inclined to deny\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒོལ་བར་འདོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vivaditukāma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgol bar ’dod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"93c28f60-dfca-422d-a5a9-4073f6fa7fe2\",\"authority\":\"18e6916e-10fe-42b7-a8ef-6b52bf3edee7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inclined to dispute\",\"tibetan\":\"འགལ་བར་བྱེད་འདོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"virodhayitukāma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’gal bar byed ’dod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"db70433e-d0b9-456e-9714-172ec1fdecad\",\"authority\":\"45e433b1-28aa-44cd-aa6f-3884c5440161\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"incongruous\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕན་ཚུན་ཚོགས་པ་དང་མི་མཐུན་པར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anyonyam visāmagrī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phan tshun tshogs pa dang mi mthun par\"}},{\"uuid\":\"76cfc447-462c-4b37-8c64-a77ccf8584aa\",\"authority\":\"77dea9a2-e017-40b7-a590-0e2cacc7fcb1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn artificial mark, like, for instance, the bell on a cow. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/1af2e9ed-1e0a-4774-b0c7-87414484171b\\\"/\u003en.881\u003c/a\u003e\u003c!--note 874--\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"indication\",\"tibetan\":\"རྟགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"liṅga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"957282ee-791c-4f90-a7dd-2577ad2e1a3b\",\"authority\":\"eda797cf-2934-4c67-98cd-62f8c8fff0b2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe god who presides over the Heaven of the Thirty-Three, and appears in many Buddhist texts, frequently referred to using the epithet Śakra and addressed by his personal name Kauśika, as both protector and disciple of the Buddha. In the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras he is an important interlocutor. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Indra\",\"tibetan\":\"དབང་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"indra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbang po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"631d1efc-cfca-439f-b289-ad3721a4442c\",\"authority\":\"0398d004-4abd-41c4-8130-3d0f0138b032\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inexhaustible, undissipating\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་ཟད་པ།, ཟད་པར་མི་འགྱུར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akṣaya, akṣaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi zad pa, zad par mi ’gyur ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"500607b6-ded7-40ce-9258-334a7aeaeb99\",\"authority\":\"0398d004-4abd-41c4-8130-3d0f0138b032\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inexhaustible, undissipating\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་ཟད་པ།, ཟད་པར་མི་འགྱུར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akṣaya, akṣaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi zad pa, zad par mi ’gyur ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f1ba951c-3fef-413f-bcdf-862d76ed0412\",\"authority\":\"c56bcbcd-40ac-4736-bb7d-861bc277b477\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inexpressible\",\"tibetan\":\"བརྗོད་དུ་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anabhilāpya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"brjod du ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"33f5f374-90cb-436a-abea-e1d6afec3aa4\",\"authority\":\"a9c6698a-a999-4c5e-9c31-a6c9a432fcab\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inferior wisdom\",\"tibetan\":\"ཤེས་རབ་དམན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"hīnaprajñā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"shes rab dman pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d0454d45-c368-446c-b993-0bd0e6679719\",\"authority\":\"cae5cd7c-89ec-47f7-a872-43c8c578a552\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThis term denotes the ontological status of phenomena, according to which they are said to possess existence in their own right‍—inherently, in and of themselves, objectively, and independent of any other phenomena such as our conception and labelling. The absence of such an ontological reality is defined as the true nature of reality, emptiness.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inherent nature\",\"tibetan\":\"ངོ་བོ་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"svabhāva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ngo bo nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9283281d-0ed6-4831-9df9-d4d8da920713\",\"authority\":\"71848c67-27ef-43a4-a60c-8b00ca05db1c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"innumerable\",\"tibetan\":\"གྲངས་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṃkhyeya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"grangs med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ae3567ac-9338-444d-b649-2272372cd6dd\",\"authority\":\"cfaa0988-e30c-4bf7-9889-b2dac1e58229\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"insufficient conviction\",\"tibetan\":\"མོས་པ་དམན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"hīnādhimuktika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mos pa dman pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"14ddaf51-b185-4574-bb0d-6592ae0f380a\",\"authority\":\"3980958f-50cf-40b2-b579-c83c82fadae2\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"intense faith\",\"tibetan\":\"མངོན་པར་དད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhśraddhā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mngon par dad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"86f9a73a-b305-4559-b52c-1f3eae673abb\",\"authority\":\"0c12d9a5-5705-4fde-8ebe-49bb821f872e\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"inviolable\",\"tibetan\":\"འཁྲུག་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akopya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’khrug pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e6690dbd-1d83-47f0-b8aa-3caee5c75d7e\",\"authority\":\"db4d1851-064e-457c-9270-97e8c004e34f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003e“Powerful One,” an epithet that may refer to Śiva, Viṣṇu, Maheśvara, or other gods.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Īśāna\",\"tibetan\":\"དབང་ལྡན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"īśāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbang ldan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0ffa193c-6076-4c09-9990-63b8a598fa86\",\"authority\":\"a7b369fe-fecb-43b8-9447-c5373ac1fcf7\",\"definition\":\"$4b\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Jambu continent\",\"tibetan\":\"འཛམ་བུའི་གླིང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"Jāmbūdvīpa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dzam bu’i gling\"}},{\"uuid\":\"86598882-1218-4887-8df3-6c016aa50628\",\"authority\":\"460c2972-69e2-45fb-8ad9-428b136b5770\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn eighth-century Indian paṇḍita who participated in translation from Sanskrit into Tibetan.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Jñānasiddhi\",\"tibetan\":\"\",\"sanskrit\":\"jñānasiddhi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b929d2da-435e-4f35-b08c-ec23315f0003\",\"authority\":\"d4aa3ceb-0d43-4b3a-a1fb-2967677acb41\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Joyful\",\"tibetan\":\"དགའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nandā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dga’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cb43148b-eca9-4075-a5cb-a1e1d03682c8\",\"authority\":\"346eb7a9-884f-4376-8cd3-4b9a1c2ce88d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eIndian Buddhist scholar (ca. 740–795) who taught at Nālandā and accompanied Śāntarakṣita (725–788) to Tibet at the request of Tri Songdetsen.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kamalaśīla\",\"tibetan\":\"པདྨའི་ངང་ཚུལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kamalaśīla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pad+ma’i ngang tshul\"}},{\"uuid\":\"35279183-1623-4d46-81bb-47be5d30c36d\",\"authority\":\"d313e685-b792-4e73-87cf-85cafb75a231\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe personal name of Śakra, the god who presides over the Heaven of the Thirty-Three, and appears in many Buddhist texts, sometimes referred to using the epithet Indra, as both protector and disciple of the Buddha. In the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras he is an important interlocutor.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kauśika\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀཽ་ཤི་ཀ\",\"sanskrit\":\"kauśika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kau shi ka\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4138c2cc-c4d5-4531-b99e-96164df4fbfa\",\"authority\":\"bd95cd14-0633-4170-b5fd-43e574e18cce\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"knowing of a self-existent one\",\"tibetan\":\"རང་བྱུང་གི་ཡེ་ཤེས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"svayaṃbhūjñāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rang byung gi ye shes\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e8dd1ed0-b8ec-4610-a817-2f3c9cb4fd02\",\"authority\":\"f01dfef1-6773-4242-ade8-1a0d3a568200\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe “complete knowing” characteristic of bodhisattvas, who must know all the paths to awakening as well as their own. It is the second of the eight topics of the \u003ccite xml:lang=\\\"en\\\"\u003eOrnament\u003c/cite\u003e, and a key term in the long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras. While it is not found as such in this sūtra, according to the commentaries it is to be understood in certain specific instances of the term “the state of complete knowing” (q.v.). See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/6268941f-41a7-4f3c-9b6a-b80740f30837\\\"/\u003en.65\u003c/a\u003e, and also \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/b1cbb855-2f3d-4d9e-ba90-a66843002f70\\\"/\u003en.637\u003c/a\u003e which mentions thirty-four aspects.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"knowing of all the paths\",\"tibetan\":\"ལམ་གྱི་རྣམ་པ་ཤེས་པ་ཉིད།, ལམ་གྱི་རྣམ་པ་ཤེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"margākārajñatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lam gyi rnam pa shes pa, lam gyi rnam pa shes pa nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"984c7a94-e1eb-45a9-8a0d-4a56573a3727\",\"authority\":\"37f9ace9-a689-4c7c-8046-6716b21a2055\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"knowing of someone who has complete knowing\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པའི་ཡེ་ཤེས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarvajñajñāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"thams cad mkhyen pa’i ye shes\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4a34666f-5d46-4cf3-b840-671e08865a22\",\"authority\":\"7f981f55-b847-4d5d-931a-d6f5b6f58df6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne of the four main castes in the Indian social order, the one to which kings, rulers, and warriors belong.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"kṣatriya\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱལ་རིགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣatriya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyal rigs\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1688b8b2-358d-4c9c-886c-02b937141c4f\",\"authority\":\"858948d2-b74d-41d5-9374-9dd328a5fc4c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lack a self, no-self, not an identity\",\"tibetan\":\"བདག་མ་མཆིས་པ།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anātman, anātman, anātman\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdag ma mchis pa, bdag med, bdag med, bdag med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b9ea12ca-461a-42d6-ba89-441d4d33e69c\",\"authority\":\"858948d2-b74d-41d5-9374-9dd328a5fc4c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lack a self, no-self, not an identity\",\"tibetan\":\"བདག་མ་མཆིས་པ།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anātman, anātman, anātman\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdag ma mchis pa, bdag med, bdag med, bdag med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"eb958323-b4e6-4ab1-a537-59dc1f948e20\",\"authority\":\"858948d2-b74d-41d5-9374-9dd328a5fc4c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lack a self, no-self, not an identity\",\"tibetan\":\"བདག་མ་མཆིས་པ།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anātman, anātman, anātman\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdag ma mchis pa, bdag med, bdag med, bdag med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"df5717fb-5292-4fd3-836d-a774d4a26d45\",\"authority\":\"97b9c534-ba48-4e1c-bb1a-ad99bd25085b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lack of provisions and security\",\"tibetan\":\"གྲུབ་པ་དང་བདེ་བ་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ayogakṣema\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"grub pa dang bde ba med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"31e421ca-33eb-45e3-a862-f67e5b3f3a51\",\"authority\":\"c9638dd1-2893-472a-9be2-2aafc7ef6f26\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lackluster\",\"tibetan\":\"གཟི་བརྗིད་ཆུང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"alpaujaska\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzi brjid chung ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ec0f40ca-d8ec-461e-b9f7-7eb0563d39e5\",\"authority\":\"9bc47136-ab56-4055-a0d2-437dc7f8ebb4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lackluster perseverance\",\"tibetan\":\"བརྩོན་འགྲུས་ཞན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"hīnavīrya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"brtson ’grus zhan pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"02ebd558-a489-4c6e-a32d-ef1f799d847d\",\"authority\":\"63e7229a-51c6-4cec-b3af-4f443ab6ffa9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eOne of the ruling clans of the Vṛji Republic, centered on the important city of Vaiśālī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Licchavi\",\"tibetan\":\"ལི་ཙྪ་བཱི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"licchavi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"li ts+tsha bI\"}},{\"uuid\":\"36a20e1d-63bb-45c3-86e6-796c075b9a4d\",\"authority\":\"5e05a336-12b5-4a4d-ad6f-018c2d15a8a5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"life’s necessities\",\"tibetan\":\"འཚོ་བའི་ཡོ་བྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"jīvitapariṣkāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’tsho ba’i yo byad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b5178ed1-7a1a-45b5-a7f7-7d6a93a371ef\",\"authority\":\"7a5d262b-b6e5-4f74-a2d2-7f1c71201aab\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"likeness of bodhisattvas\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་གཟུགས་བརྙན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhi­sattva­pratirūpaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub sems dpa’i gzugs brnyan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ea37366c-4caa-4d9f-b7db-bde18445f43b\",\"authority\":\"c4e73949-950f-4960-a84b-3253fda43c13\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"limitless\",\"tibetan\":\"མུ་མ་མཆིས་པ།, མུ་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aparyanta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mu ma mchis pa, mu med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"afcbf2a8-9863-4e93-ad1a-eb8770e61809\",\"authority\":\"efd42cfb-6b26-4337-b9a4-c8d3ee9bc6c3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"livelihood\",\"tibetan\":\"འཚོ་བའི་ཡོ་བྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"jīvitapariṣkāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’tsho ba’i yo byad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"45006748-6d84-49aa-995d-80b7b8919021\",\"authority\":\"9df895db-5624-491d-9911-a84336e7f58d\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lovingly appreciated\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡིད་དུ་འོང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"priya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yid du ’ong ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e\",\"authority\":\"f9c8bf5e-0afb-4aa3-b52b-6b77994f180a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"luminously clear\",\"tibetan\":\"འོད་གསལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prabhāsvarā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’od gsal ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f3ace5f8-2bbc-4799-b325-9de48439e81f\",\"authority\":\"eda11346-38ae-4c7d-8cf1-bc03c09433fe\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"lustful thought\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་པའི་རྟོག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāmavitarka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod pa’i rtog pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"87681525-2530-4de6-8f90-3f876969cc0d\",\"authority\":\"08e8c479-af74-4140-af09-63fbfb67e6ee\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eNote that the Tibetan would be rendered “write it and put it into book form.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"made into a book, make it into a book, make the perfection of wisdom into a book\",\"tibetan\":\"བྲིས་ཏེ་གླེགས་བམ་དུ་ཆུད་པར་བྱས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pustakagatāṃ kṛtvā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bris te glegs bam du chud par byas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0cf127c3-18a3-4d2e-a1e5-d7d0cd1218ad\",\"authority\":\"3608013f-f69c-43b7-a317-dcd0f8128401\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"made prominent\",\"tibetan\":\"རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prabhāvita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rab tu phye ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"764e2eca-b833-41f2-81f8-1d67bc589328\",\"authority\":\"4d4b113d-ee61-46ce-be20-b69131daa8b2\",\"definition\":\"$4c\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"magical display\",\"tibetan\":\"རྫུ་འཕྲུལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ṛddhi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rdzu ’phrul\"}},{\"uuid\":\"691144a1-87c6-495c-bb6b-8ce8d204d2fc\",\"authority\":\"b35d9ad6-9ad5-450b-a8c3-19a94c2a89de\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"magical illusion\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྱུ་མ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"māyā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgyu ma\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a5054f16-971a-4b39-86fc-f728ba4a975d\",\"authority\":\"15d84950-f83d-4514-b91f-331e4d64e5b9\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"magical illusionist\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྱུ་མ་བྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"māyākāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgyu ma byed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a17c4e73-ca3a-4635-8da7-8fa8954e5f7b\",\"authority\":\"fb8a9cd3-6829-4a0a-9538-0a4104dc3b6e\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"magical incantation\",\"tibetan\":\"རིག་སྔགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vidyā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rig sngags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"dbbbe908-8b34-4212-bb98-569d77dd2730\",\"authority\":\"f6dfde88-1f6a-4936-a866-4ab0809153fe\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"magically created\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྲུལ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhinirmita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sprul pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2b544135-cb9d-4634-bdb3-656dc11befca\",\"authority\":\"1aaf7744-4b24-4d71-99ce-7e069434597f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"magically overpower\",\"tibetan\":\"དབང་དུ་བྱ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vaśīkaraṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbang du bya ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0c1fb0dc-c5bf-48f6-9352-1590bd80b4f9\",\"authority\":\"b2d7b1da-0595-47e4-953c-5ef6c704327a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eFourth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Great Brahmā.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Mahābrahma\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་པ་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahābrahma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs pa chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1f3abb37-b921-44c5-8ec9-f37b36ccda0f\",\"authority\":\"1aff34d4-5da6-49ab-b312-523fffccb2d7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn arhat disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, from Magadha. he had the moniker “foremost in the practice of ascetic qualities.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Mahākāśyapa\",\"tibetan\":\"འོད་སྲུང་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahākāśyapa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’od srung chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0ce324e9-f379-4ddc-8502-055af5e696bc\",\"authority\":\"0bdb7926-aba8-4e98-8a0f-dd172e756ce7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn arhat disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, from Avanti. He had the moniker “foremost in exegesis.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Mahākātyāyana\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀཱ་ཏྱཱ་ཡ་ན་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahākātyāyana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kA t+yA ya na chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b32358bd-b960-4a59-82e5-cb8abb91c901\",\"authority\":\"3adac520-7720-4880-ae09-5461382ab20e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn arhat disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, from Śrāvastī. He had the moniker “foremost in experiential knowledge.” Also spelled (Mahā-) Kauṣṭhila.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Mahākoṣṭhila\",\"tibetan\":\"ལྟོ་རིངས་ཆེན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mahākoṣṭhila\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lto rings chen po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"34e9bd80-03ca-4582-8295-19dcf8d87219\",\"authority\":\"cdfb8e4f-6d68-4c38-a3c5-5bd8897f3897\",\"definition\":\"$4d\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Maitreya\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱམས་མའི་བུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"maitreya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byams ma’i bu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"81cf9257-e262-4402-94bc-c39477bba29e\",\"authority\":\"794b7592-140a-4829-a368-727ac6756b70\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"majesty\",\"tibetan\":\"གཟི་བརྗིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"tejas\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gzi brjid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4a54a887-bdc2-4da3-978b-fba5a3ae0843\",\"authority\":\"d02f54f4-08a8-43c6-b165-a1f89818fdd7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"malevolence\",\"tibetan\":\"གནོད་སེམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vyāpāda\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gnod sems\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fa1b5e0e-0a14-4220-86ca-13d19ca5a449\",\"authority\":\"9d7e875d-2db6-4ab9-a1b6-3669ee8c55e9\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"malevolent spirit, nonhuman, superhuman spirit\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"amanuṣya, amanuṣya, amanuṣya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"99bb787a-ca20-48c4-8489-690437768aef\",\"authority\":\"9d7e875d-2db6-4ab9-a1b6-3669ee8c55e9\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"malevolent spirit, nonhuman, superhuman spirit\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"amanuṣya, amanuṣya, amanuṣya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1a7bdbc9-117c-465e-afc1-01604d1be599\",\"authority\":\"9d7e875d-2db6-4ab9-a1b6-3669ee8c55e9\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"malevolent spirit, nonhuman, superhuman spirit\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"amanuṣya, amanuṣya, amanuṣya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cca61a77-75d5-4500-a990-23b3336c569d\",\"authority\":\"1f2c5cff-2505-474f-a76d-38701fb52951\",\"definition\":\"$4e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Māra\",\"tibetan\":\"བདུད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"māra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdud\"}},{\"uuid\":\"19ab4032-1233-40ea-a87e-cf9cd2176528\",\"authority\":\"966b9d66-9522-4793-a8d0-19b884940e49\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Māra’s activity\",\"tibetan\":\"བདུད་ཀྱི་ལས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mārakarma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdud kyi las\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3d6bc85d-8d72-4494-b155-ae18f5f1978f\",\"authority\":\"ad3d2e7b-2906-437b-84e1-445e08a74266\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe god realms presided over by Māra.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Māra’s realms\",\"tibetan\":\"བདུད་ཀྱི་གནས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mārabhavana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bdud kyi gnas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e2fae2b3-0351-4880-9280-7ba1594c23e7\",\"authority\":\"8a4d67f8-2b90-4ab2-8d6c-d84c0df767f4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"medicinal herb\",\"tibetan\":\"རྩི།, སྨན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"oṣadhi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtsi, sman\"}},{\"uuid\":\"25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4\",\"authority\":\"1f935435-8218-4738-a453-aac30854a2a5\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eEssentially a deeply focused mindset whose meditative object is framed by a particular, profound conception. On the individual meditative concentrations in this scripture, see notes \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/7c2e270d-92c2-4748-8a9d-565dbc570bb4\\\"/\u003en.1377\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/3d5990c0-333e-4cc2-a98c-a20078a526b6\\\"/\u003en.1379\u003c/a.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"meditative concentration\",\"tibetan\":\"ཏིང་ངེ་འཛིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"samādhi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ting nge ’dzin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"736f3362-3366-477b-b195-2705a0c5c379\",\"authority\":\"72b9bc1c-896f-4242-998d-15fd6a7a4b90\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003e\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eDhyāna\u003c/em\u003e is defined as one-pointed abiding in an undistracted state of mind, free from afflicted mental states. Four states of \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edhyāna\u003c/em\u003e are identified as being conducive to birth within the form realm. In the context of the Mahāyāna, it is the fifth of the six perfections. It is commonly translated as “concentration,” “meditative concentration,” and so on.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"meditative state\",\"tibetan\":\"བསམ་གཏན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhyāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsam gtan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f4171767-1ef8-4563-8b75-880d7a277b4b\",\"authority\":\"e734951b-cb20-4c30-887c-fe26d2c29e3b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"meet with a downfall\",\"tibetan\":\"རྣམ་པར་འཇིག་པར་འགྱུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vyavasādam āpatsyate\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnam par ’jig par ’gyur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d5ff6646-c39d-4f4b-8a22-8ed8ce3ba0c7\",\"authority\":\"fd818933-2312-40de-a844-833c9c8df93d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA general term applied to spiritual practitioners who live as ascetic mendicants. In Buddhist texts, the term usually refers to Buddhist monastics, but it can also designate a practitioner from other ascetic/monastic spiritual traditions. In this context \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eśramaṇa\u003c/em\u003e is often contrasted with the term \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ebrāhmaṇa\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ebram ze\u003c/em\u003e), which refers broadly to followers of the Vedic tradition. Any renunciate, not just a Buddhist, could be referred to as a śramaṇa if they were not within the Vedic fold. The epithet Great Śramaṇa is often applied to the Buddha.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mendicant\",\"tibetan\":\"དགེ་སྦྱོང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śramaṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dge sbyong\"}},{\"uuid\":\"71984920-52bd-485c-9f8f-1b4d1cb73d33\",\"authority\":\"a406d2ef-b447-47ad-b1c2-4d216fb8492e\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mental attitude\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"manas\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0e166dd4-a656-4475-b775-bd17ecf51231\",\"authority\":\"00450d77-ca02-4e92-85cb-5d9c56d23d4f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mental factor\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་ལས་བྱུང་བའི་ཆོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caitasika dharma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems las byung ba’i chos\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f58dc403-82f3-4cc0-b66a-e5bfc72d65a7\",\"authority\":\"48ce895d-9b42-44b8-bf4a-a21d542a0e92\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThis is the faculty that enables the mind to maintain its attention on a referent object, counteracting the arising of forgetfulness, which is a great obstacle to meditative stability. The root \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esmṛ\u003c/em\u003e may mean “to recollect” but also simply “to think of.” Broadly speaking, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esmṛti\u003c/em\u003e, commonly translated as “mindfulness,” means to bring something to mind, not necessarily something experienced in a distant past but also something that is experienced in the present, such as the position of one’s body or the breath.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eTogether with alertness (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esamprajāna\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003eshes bzhin\u003c/em\u003e), it is one of the two indispensable factors for the development of calm abiding (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eśamatha\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ezhi gnas\u003c/em\u003e). \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mindfulness\",\"tibetan\":\"དྲན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"smṛti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dran pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4\",\"authority\":\"5edda6f4-289b-47d4-80e8-932287e9ad32\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eIn this scripture wherever the term “mindset” (\u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003ecitta\u003c/foreign\u003e) appears alone (i.e., not in a compound like \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003ebodhicitta\u003c/foreign\u003e), it may refer to the mindset of awakening, or to a proper mindset directly related to it, or to an improper mindset antithetical to it, or to the immediate content of any of these three senses of the word \u003cdistinct\u003emindset\u003c/distinct\u003e. See the introduction, \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/3096ba3b-a647-489c-9b20-8673274fb8aa\\\"/\u003ei.92\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mindset\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"citta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3edf7e6e-07aa-4706-b817-7c28c11ecf5d\",\"authority\":\"e42c9b0e-7342-4498-b32e-f37212879779\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mindset free from worldly influences\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟག་པ་མེད་པའི་སེམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anāsravacitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zag pa med pa’i sems\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f\",\"authority\":\"71c3e498-a282-46c2-a1b2-09bff483deac\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAlthough the Sanskrit word \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003ecitta\u003c/foreign\u003e (in the compound \u003cforeign xml:lang=\\\"Sa-Ltn\\\" type=\\\"term\\\"\u003ebodhicitta\u003c/foreign\u003e) has both cognitive and affective aspects difficult to render accurately in a single English word, the term \u003cdistinct\u003emindset\u003c/distinct\u003e has been adopted in the sense of a complex mental state constantly arising in each moment, shaped by particular past actions that affect the way one sees, thinks, feels, interprets, and acts moment to moment. See the introduction, \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/3096ba3b-a647-489c-9b20-8673274fb8aa\\\"/\u003ei.92\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mindset of awakening\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་སེམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhicitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub kyi sems\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1555911b-f1ee-41d3-bae0-6626043c0181\",\"authority\":\"a9646b01-6f23-4a29-9772-682c9b2581e6\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mindset that lacks trust\",\"tibetan\":\"སེམས་མ་དད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aprasannacitta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sems ma dad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"16a78887-72ec-43c3-96c5-c7ab4ac325f6\",\"authority\":\"033170bf-e8a0-4f85-9932-10becf3aafce\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"miraculous power\",\"tibetan\":\"མཐུས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anubhāva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mthus\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2d48235b-3905-4980-8c6a-1ebed1174133\",\"authority\":\"12ba7652-0529-4d33-9787-595891bea9d8\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"miraculously created\",\"tibetan\":\"མངོན་པར་སྤྲུལ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhinirmita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mngon par sprul pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8b3d0df1-bab7-4984-9231-ecc4b7e5493f\",\"authority\":\"7fdd5035-9108-4910-8f36-91b69bf5e771\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe term is used in two senses, “mixed up with” (confused or polluted by) and “mixed together with others.” See notes \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17\\\"/\u003en.1094\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/c4ede759-d915-49a8-b469-b3579ecfec25\\\"/\u003en.1100\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mixed, mixed-up\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀུན་ཏུ་འདྲེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saṃkīrṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kun tu ’dres pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1edbce5c-7c22-429e-9fa2-11fdfaa759bb\",\"authority\":\"3f54b15a-ac9f-4ecb-82cf-bce1c48f4a11\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe term \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ebhikṣu\u003c/em\u003e, often translated as “monk,” refers to the highest among the eight types of prātimokṣa vows that make one part of the Buddhist assembly. The Sanskrit term literally means “beggar” or “mendicant,” referring to the fact that Buddhist monks and nuns‍—like other ascetics of the time‍—subsisted on alms (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ebhikṣā\u003c/em\u003e) begged from the laity. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn the Tibetan tradition, which follows the Mūlasarvāstivāda Vinaya, a monk follows 253 rules as part of his moral discipline. A nun (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003ebhikṣuṇī\u003c/em\u003e; \u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003edge slong ma\u003c/em\u003e) follows 364 rules. A novice monk (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003eśrāmaṇera\u003c/em\u003e; \u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003edge tshul\u003c/em\u003e) or nun (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003eśrāmaṇerikā\u003c/em\u003e; \u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003edge tshul ma\u003c/em\u003e) follows thirty-six rules of moral discipline (although in other vinaya traditions novices typically follow only ten).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"monk\",\"tibetan\":\"དགེ་སློང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhikṣu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dge slong\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c631dfec-eda1-482a-beb9-d373eb05c177\",\"authority\":\"71c60e3c-b511-44ff-a722-86b088c327a5\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Most Joyful\",\"tibetan\":\"དགའ་མཆོག\",\"sanskrit\":\"nandottamā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dga’ mchog\"}},{\"uuid\":\"179b4e7f-2bdd-4436-afb1-14d48d876d46\",\"authority\":\"ae3792c0-d80f-4ad6-9018-fedfde50df7d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Most Patient\",\"tibetan\":\"བདེ་མཆོག\",\"sanskrit\":\"kṣamottamā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bde mchog\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f43df1f0-e329-4224-929b-cfb956aa7aae\",\"authority\":\"58cd567f-157e-44eb-8f0f-f080f8d13ece\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"mother who nurses\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་མ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhatrī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma ma\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5df5f323-69f8-42ce-88a5-d8fee60b5d11\",\"authority\":\"375885f3-07b9-4253-bafd-bd70b8bb8c9b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"motivated by sense pleasures\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་པའི་གཞིས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāmanidāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod pa’i gzhis\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fa61575c-ddb5-4f50-823e-c6faf936c117\",\"authority\":\"c8607fdd-de43-47d1-a771-6fe5f514f1cc\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eKāśi is usually understood as the city of the Kāśi people, Vārāṇasī, known for its fine textiles.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"muslin fabric from Kāśi\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀ་ཤི་ཀའི་གོས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāśikavastra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ka shi ka’i gos\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0c06ba3e-efda-4685-b775-759637a9db8e\",\"authority\":\"c0abb05b-a384-4736-b1e4-9f95c4ffd5bf\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"natural body\",\"tibetan\":\"ངོ་བོ་ཉིད་སྐུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"svābhāvikakāya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ngo bo nyid sku\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4b3ebecf-a9c7-4879-af93-23f6a94d45ec\",\"authority\":\"63605126-9038-4253-81a3-cc67e5dba315\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"natural outcome\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱུ་མཐུན་པ།, རྒྱུ་འཐུན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"niṣyanda\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyu mthun pa, rgyu ’thun pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"74b824d5-12c7-4083-8066-97d55028a5cb\",\"authority\":\"075f4092-07a0-45c5-8fa8-28b2b6b3f68f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"naturally effortless\",\"tibetan\":\"ལྷུན་གྱིས་གྲུབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anābhoga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lhun gyis grub pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7a0d3ca6-db81-4491-aca9-4bb795417c97\",\"authority\":\"269c3a22-a265-4aaa-89b7-74e31f238d0a\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nature of not existing\",\"tibetan\":\"ངོ་བོ་ཉིད་མེད་པའི་རང་བཞིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"abhāvasvabhāva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ngo bo nyid med pa’i rang bzhin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9950adcc-b7d9-4b88-9095-656f47759bbd\",\"authority\":\"1fcaecbb-b19d-4a1a-9a68-46ee78d33cda\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"negative consequence\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"doṣa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nyes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"34a76066-4934-4da1-aff3-783e78f7f249\",\"authority\":\"d5b6340d-920f-4ac8-b731-9e6dfc0aa682\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"negative propensity\",\"tibetan\":\"བག་ལ་ཉལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anuśaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bag la nyal ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"571789ba-014e-4c20-b93d-507e7821001c\",\"authority\":\"19723a22-b612-4a0a-9357-2fb32b1312c7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eThe name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Never Flowing Away\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་འབབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avivāhā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ’bab pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1a3ee47d-0c12-41ef-b0c3-880e8a471746\",\"authority\":\"7cecc342-ee9e-4f2a-ad0b-119a0f9f1ad0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"never goes close\",\"tibetan\":\"ཉེ་བར་མི་རྟོགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nopaiti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nye bar mi rtogs\"}},{\"uuid\":\"26e77994-e832-43f0-898f-17c9988c9ae9\",\"authority\":\"4756da74-3953-491c-9532-2836d0f6178c\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"never lacking\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་བྲལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avirahita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma bral ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6b13fc98-09b7-4746-87ea-7f8e8a712005\",\"authority\":\"b2ebcfca-3da9-420c-9756-1cf5f02c0f10\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003e(1059–1109)\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Ngok Loden Sherab\",\"tibetan\":\"རྔོག་བློ་ལྡན་ཤེས་རབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rngog blo ldan shes rab\"}},{\"uuid\":\"74e5b0b0-113c-4446-b539-a7fec74ead2d\",\"authority\":\"f95e6f7e-0779-4af6-a535-dea257e6dea1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe extreme philosophical view that rejects rebirth and the law of karma by considering that causes (and thus actions) do not have effects and that the self, being the same as one or all of the aggregates (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eskandhas\u003c/em\u003e), ends at death. Commonly translated as “nihilism” or, more literally, as “view of annihilation.” It is often mentioned along with its opposite view, the extreme of eternalism or permanence.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nihilism\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"uccheda\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chad pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f1854e76-8f2d-4f37-bf1b-124aa89b3a21\",\"authority\":\"47076c18-a7e5-42fb-8448-34d0d0ef898a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/e535b245-d129-406d-981e-df22f68753d9\\\"/\u003en.628\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nine incremental states of abiding\",\"tibetan\":\"མཐར་གྱིས་གནས་པའི་སྙོམས་པར་འཇུག་པ་དགུ\",\"sanskrit\":\"navānupūrva­vihāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mthar gyis gnas pa’i snyoms par ’jug pa dgu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"aa0118df-2e53-4473-85e7-b0bfd8a6873b\",\"authority\":\"b564d2ca-b53a-4ef3-bffb-fe6e2fc9224f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eFifth god realm of desire, meaning “Delighting in Emanation.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Nirmāṇarati\",\"tibetan\":\"འཕྲུལ་དག\",\"sanskrit\":\"nirmāṇarati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’phrul dga\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b2383130-0fab-4470-a4da-b8535af34c9e\",\"authority\":\"4a9c787d-e93e-4757-b5c4-65281f956020\",\"definition\":\"$4f\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"tibetan\":\"མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mya ngan las ’das pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"19009de0-0a92-4893-a82c-5ac504052794\",\"authority\":\"be0e6dc0-891e-4d28-9253-aa7a1220e9bd\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eAn unconditioned space beyond the three conditioned realms of existence in which worthy ones are said to abide. See \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/f0c7b280-283d-4c70-9c3e-e6cbf1f229e5\\\"/\u003en.229\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nirvāṇa dimension\",\"tibetan\":\"མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པའི་དབྱིངས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nirvāṇadhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mya ngan las ’das pa’i dbyings\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8e1bf387-a49c-4da0-b1cd-0adf5b685e30\",\"authority\":\"ca0ff2f0-b549-4290-b0b4-77c5d4095477\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"no possibility\",\"tibetan\":\"གནས་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asthāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gnas med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"dff74475-8897-4600-839e-010d5966b459\",\"authority\":\"3d73d30f-3355-442c-90e4-0b50f887d470\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"/entity/passage/24673f44-ecbf-4e64-bbd8-7869e7c15fe2\\\"/\u003en.73\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"noble\",\"tibetan\":\"ཅང་ཤེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ājāneya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"cang shes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c71c642f-e80f-4a1c-a2b7-c447711abfb3\",\"authority\":\"63707c86-2090-400d-bc29-81aa5b8855fa\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"non-Buddhist wandering ascetic\",\"tibetan\":\"མུ་སྟེགས་ཅན་གཞན་ཀུན་ཏུ་རྒྱུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anyatīrthyaparivrājaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mu stegs can gzhan kun tu rgyu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e8052e35-e7a0-4c24-a8c6-dcf42039f956\",\"authority\":\"d0931bb3-d04b-44b6-91f4-09db84af0163\",\"definition\":\"\u003cnote type=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e \u003cp\u003eSee also “free of attachment” and “unattached.”\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/note\u003e \",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nonattachment\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆགས་པ་མེད་པ།, མ་ཆགས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṅga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chags pa med pa, ma chags pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ab1a7cab-b996-4342-a1a8-69e0ab712c60\",\"authority\":\"469ba0d4-03f9-4e2e-b228-f082a0590bd7\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nonexistence\",\"tibetan\":\"མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nāstitā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"62baa549-d606-4ded-bd44-16fc5c2f2562\",\"authority\":\"76d10c0e-c0c2-413e-bcb3-f473c051d83f\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"nonoccurence\",\"tibetan\":\"འབྱུང་བ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṃbhava\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’byung ba med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0fb30863-ae01-49e2-8786-49b866b5448d\",\"authority\":\"32776ba5-d760-4337-b5b2-e8b95ce826d2\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"not arisen\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་སྐྱེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anutpānna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma skyes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3b01b128-95a5-4c99-bbbd-9f75cb38aeab\",\"authority\":\"2441a1c3-31d5-4391-9b16-3e0830020496\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"not assured\",\"tibetan\":\"ངེས་པ་མ་ཡིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aniyata\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nges pa ma yin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b847cb23-9087-42ca-9971-5edc1e7b756c\",\"authority\":\"e6b68914-6c4f-45c3-aad7-e7fe99d79da1\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"not be left to go astray\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆུད་ཟོས་པར་གྱུར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mā praṇaṃkṣīt\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chud zos par gyur\"}},{\"uuid\":\"21a75be0-1502-4347-b719-4db95a363cf2\",\"authority\":\"b4b1bf79-eb37-4f00-9355-577eec920eb6\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"not being found to exist\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"avidyamāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6074d31e-6c5c-40a7-9eb3-838530a2c879\",\"authority\":\"0895ed0d-95e4-4215-8908-ffb1c2948a2d\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"not being something permanent\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐེར་ཟུག་ཏུ་གནས་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"akūṭasthatā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ther zug tu gnas pa ma mchis pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6d36102c-6a9b-404a-8ce3-679bb37803ba\",\"authority\":\"a2ff3d9e-fc34-4f7e-bfe8-4affda274c01\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"not deflated\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་འགོང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"nāvalīyate\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi ’gong\"}},{\"uuid\":\"775db351-7635-44f1-b090-e3f651a156