:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 data-[state=inactive]:hidden" style="animation-duration:0s"><div class="h-0"></div><div></div><div class="h-0"></div><div class="flex flex-col gap-4 pb-8"><div class="flex gap-5"><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-6 w-6"></div><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-32 grow"></div></div><div class="flex gap-5"><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-6 w-6"></div><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-32 grow"></div></div><div class="flex gap-5"><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-6 w-6"></div><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-32 grow"></div></div></div></div><div data-state="inactive" data-orientation="horizontal" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-glossary" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-glossary" tabindex="0" data-slot="tabs-content" class="mt-2 ring-offset-background focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 pb-8 data-[state=inactive]:hidden"><div class="flex flex-col w-full"><div id="glossary" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2lanpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-5 mt-6">g.</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><h2 class="font-serif font-light text-primary scroll-m-20 text-xl @c/sidebar:mt-4 mt-6 @c/sidebar:pb-2 pb-3 @c/sidebar:text-left text-center section-title">Glossary</h2></div></div><div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-6"><div id="21c43cd9-2844-4c67-8897-2e7bcd438241" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_80d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">[not] taken hold of, taken hold of</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma zin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཟིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anupātta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5471dac6-1971-4333-b615-2e0bf346a316" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_80l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.2</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ābhāsvara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od gsal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་གསལ།</span></li><li class="italic">ābhāsvara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Seventh of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Inner Radiance.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="29302329-ee8d-4682-b699-d17e2bb8dec7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_80t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.3</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Abhirati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhirati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The eastern buddhafield of the Buddha Akṣobhya.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e175a82e-be93-4fae-871f-cb478cf466f1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.4</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">abide free of conflict</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyon mongs pa med pa la gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མེད་པ་ལ་གནས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">araṇāvihārin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/ce682850-4446-4e92-b9e4-da871259b68d"/>n.100</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="d15d2966-4bb6-43cf-8894-a8965280ded2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_81d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.5</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">acceptance, tolerant acceptance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bzod pa, bzod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཟོད་པ།, བཟོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣānti, kṣānti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A term meaning acceptance, forbearance, or patience. As the third of the six perfections, patience is classified into three kinds: the capacity to tolerate abuse from sentient beings, to tolerate the hardships of the path to buddhahood, and to tolerate the profound nature of reality. As a term referring to a bodhisattva’s realization, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dharmakṣānti</em> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">chos la bzod pa</em>) can refer to the ways one becomes “receptive” to the nature of Dharma, and it can be an abbreviation of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">anutpattikadharmakṣānti</em>, “forbearance for the unborn nature, or nonproduction, of dharmas.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="33ab1da8-1af4-415b-bfd0-96e5055a1a47" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_81l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.6</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">acceptance, tolerant acceptance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bzod pa, bzod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཟོད་པ།, བཟོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣānti, kṣānti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A term meaning acceptance, forbearance, or patience. As the third of the six perfections, patience is classified into three kinds: the capacity to tolerate abuse from sentient beings, to tolerate the hardships of the path to buddhahood, and to tolerate the profound nature of reality. As a term referring to a bodhisattva’s realization, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dharmakṣānti</em> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">chos la bzod pa</em>) can refer to the ways one becomes “receptive” to the nature of Dharma, and it can be an abbreviation of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">anutpattikadharmakṣānti</em>, “forbearance for the unborn nature, or nonproduction, of dharmas.”</p> <note type="definition"> <p>The third of four stages or experiences of breaking through on the path of preliminary practice.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e62676e6-a821-4e67-94b0-13fdc3a8d3ce" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_81t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.7</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">actual nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">de bzhin nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">tathatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4cfa7f72-29ce-4a21-82ba-058cd78f3560" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.8</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">aggression, aggressiveness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhe sdang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞེ་སྡང་།</span></li><li class="italic">doṣa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0c9686d5-af20-4e4e-b660-2589550617ba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_82d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.9</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Akaniṣṭha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’og min</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོག་མིན།</span></li><li class="italic">akaniṣṭha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fifth and highest of the five pure abodes, meaning “Highest.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="b66df17d-4a3e-460d-8f3e-fd26aa19d691" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_82l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.10</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Akṣobhya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi bskyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་བསྐྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">akṣobhya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Lit. “Not Disturbed” or “Immovable One.” The buddha in the eastern realm of Abhirati. A well-known buddha in Mahāyāna, regarded in the higher tantras as the head of one of the five buddha families, the vajra family in the east.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="067c788d-11bb-48d8-b9e4-8022d5a88c13" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_82t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.11</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Always Delighted</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag tu dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nityapramudita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of the four gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="59b38241-f13f-44f1-b7a6-d9e92f064560" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.12</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Anabhraka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sprin med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲིན་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">anabhraka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Eleventh of the thirteen levels of the god realm of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Cloudless.” In some versions of the longer Prajñāpāramitā sūtras, which list sixteen realms instead of thirteen, this god realm has the name Parīttabṛhat (Tib. <foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="term">chung che</foreign>).</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="7bd42065-689d-456d-8f83-789ac6366a8e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_83d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.13</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ānanda</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ bo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་བོ།</span></li><li class="italic">ānanda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A major śrāvaka disciple and personal attendant of the Buddha Śākyamuni during the last twenty-five years of his life. He was a cousin of the Buddha (according to the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Mahāvastu</cite>, he was a son of Śuklodana, one of the brothers of King Śuddhodana, which means he was a brother of Devadatta; other sources say he was a son of Amṛtodana, another brother of King Śuddhodana, which means he would have been a brother of Aniruddha).</p><p>Ānanda, having always been in the Buddha’s presence, is said to have memorized all the teachings he heard and is celebrated for having recited all the Buddha’s teachings by memory at the first council of the Buddhist saṅgha, thus preserving the teachings after the Buddha’s parinirvāṇa. The phrase “Thus did I hear at one time,” found at the beginning of the sūtras, usually stands for his recitation of the teachings. He became a patriarch after the passing of Mahākāśyapa.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9e6908f8-5334-46fd-bf40-67302ece77f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_83l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.14</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">applications of mindfulness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dran pa nye bar gzhag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲན་པ་ཉེ་བར་གཞག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">smṛtyupasthāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The placing of attention, especially on four particular objects: body, feelings, mind, and phenomena. Classified among the dharmas of the path, and figuring among the thirty-seven factors in awakening. See <a href="/entity/passage/78f7b789-0780-4e7f-89ea-f8200537793f"/>n.218</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="008c3a1b-918f-46bd-86bc-88e848c59e61" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_83t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.15</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Apramāṇābha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med ’od</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་འོད།</span></li><li class="italic">apramāṇābha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Sixth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Immeasurable Radiance.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="69e8192a-4e67-4fd5-a5f6-d3078ca1a504" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.16</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Apramāṇaśubha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med dge</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་དགེ</span></li><li class="italic">apramāṇaśubha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Ninth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Immeasurable Virtue.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="760a6413-3e40-4356-a524-e8a825911f9e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_84d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.17</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Asaṃjñisattva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’du shes med pa’i sems can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུ་ཤེས་མེད་པའི་སེམས་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṃjñisattva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A god realm of form listed in this and other texts between the thirteenth heaven of the form realm, Bṛhatphala, and the five pure abodes of the form realm, known collectively as Śuddhāvāsa. Its name means “Being Without Conception.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="ba0e60fd-071a-4769-84d4-b1b151062016" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_84l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.18</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who accepts whatever is offered</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhi ji bzhin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞི་ཇི་བཞིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">yāthāsaṃstarika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="85d8c8b9-d5b6-4cfe-a35b-b82bc083d7a9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_84t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.19</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who dwells in the forest, wilderness area</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgon pa, dgon pa pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགོན་པ་པ།, དགོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāntāram, kāntārāṇi, āraṇyaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="2578fc88-c96f-41b1-9320-47553c135d27" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.20</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who dwells in the forest, wilderness area</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgon pa, dgon pa pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགོན་པ་པ།, དགོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāntāram, kāntārāṇi, āraṇyaka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3fcb650a-05b1-4357-b600-7a1a36a335c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_85d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.21</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who has three robes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos gos gsum pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་གོས་གསུམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">traicīvarika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="9ccaa507-7ef0-4809-82f0-ab5e83d3da67" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_85l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.22</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who lives at the foot of a tree</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing drung pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་དྲུང་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vṛkṣamūlika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="596d26fb-e519-4233-a23c-05795508d8e0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_85t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.23</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who lives in charnel grounds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dur khrod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུར་ཁྲོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">śmaśānika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="4d9de190-69ed-4fb2-9442-a318923d73d8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.24</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who lives in seclusion, contented with few desires</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pa nyung zhing chog shes pa rab tu dben pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པ་ཉུང་ཞིང་ཆོག་ཤེས་པ་རབ་ཏུ་དབེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">alpecchaḥ saṃtuṣṭaḥ praviviktaḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="a80bd219-b9a6-45ba-b09b-69b62740fb8f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_86d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.25</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who lives in the open air</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bla gab med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བླ་གབ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhyavakāśika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="34b49fa7-a0e4-46b3-b986-b1ef68753a28" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_86l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.26</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who never eats later</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zas phyis mi len pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟས་ཕྱིས་མི་ལེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">khalu­paścādbhaktika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6dfab12c-8f93-42f0-8c91-b9eca5382e79" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_86t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.27</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who seeks alms</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsod snyoms pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསོད་སྙོམས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">piṇḍapātika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="a2712332-6697-46b8-b3dc-ad1010ef044e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.28</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who stays upright</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">cog pu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཅོག་པུ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">naiṣadyika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="79702dba-0e9c-47b5-acb3-dee7e9c9143b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_87d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.29</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who uses a single seat</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stan gcig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟན་གཅིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ekāsanika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="ce34a26d-d673-4ddd-9e45-ffc9c57da590" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_87l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.30</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who wears felt garments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phying pa ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱིང་པ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nāmantika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="f15838ba-c0d1-4ec4-9eec-d36e4b86c9a4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_87t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.31</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ascetic who wears rags</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyag dar khrod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱག་དར་ཁྲོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pāṃsukūlika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the kinds of ascetic practice, usually numbered as thirteen altogether, that were optionally followed by certain renunciant monks. See <a href="/entity/passage/48126746-a9b3-447b-832f-848e765dd8ab"/>n.1076</a> and following notes.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="e68a0709-ed66-4452-b4ce-c6444e5fb88b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.32</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">aspects of awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi yan lag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཡན་ལག</span></li><li class="italic">bodhyaṅga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"><p>See <a href="/entity/passage/f293ea18-7a51-49aa-b184-f1a1f975484f"/>n.219</a>.</p> <p/> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="99d9f306-91f3-4a57-a146-b50dab39e6f2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_88d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.33</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Atapa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi gdung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གདུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">atapa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Second of the five pure abodes, meaning “Painless.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1b7e341e-95b8-47c3-89e6-6c9610cefb0f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_88l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.34</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Atiśa, Atiśa Dīpaṃkaraśrījñāna, Dīpaṃkaraśrījñāna</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">atiśa dīpaṃkaraśrījñāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2c06a068-3ad3-483f-a261-d4ea2d90dc1e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_88t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.35</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">atom</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdul phra mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྡུལ་ཕྲ་མོ།</span></li><li class="italic">aṇu</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="39144dcc-0557-458e-9125-94971f66e77f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.36</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attached to worldly enjoyments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig rten gyi zang zing dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཟང་ཟིང་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">lokāmiṣa­prati­saṃyukta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="35c7fc73-8b93-4ff9-af78-3b2b909418a4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_89d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.37</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attachment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod chags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་ཆགས།</span></li><li class="italic">rāga</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fd4ed926-5860-48e5-a86c-ac44fd110d9b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_89l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.38</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attack by someone else</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pha rol gyi gnod pa byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕ་རོལ་གྱི་གནོད་པ་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">paropakrama</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3e66b608-2ac2-4bdd-860f-2bd59296d831" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_89t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.39</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attentive mental state, attentiveness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid la byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་ལ་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">manasīkāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7bea5dcd-33ce-40af-aca6-9c1243d8e867" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8a55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.40</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attribute, meditative perspective</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa, rnam pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པ།, རྣམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ākāra, ākāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="06bf8485-36ec-4c4d-9635-5e15d894fa0c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.41</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attribute, meditative perspective</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa, rnam pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པ།, རྣམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ākāra, ākāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A defining characteristic, like, for instance, the dewlap of a cow. See <a href="/entity/passage/1af2e9ed-1e0a-4774-b0c7-87414484171b"/>n.881</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="2a9612bf-49bd-4e08-91f7-86bd6c124c06" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8al5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.42</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Avakīrṇakusuma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog bkram pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་བཀྲམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avakīrṇakusuma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name that six hundred future buddhas will all take after attaining awakening, as foreordained by the Buddha in chapter 21.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="9d70508c-0282-4103-9280-71707a95c258" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8at5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.43</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Avṛha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi che ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཆེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">avṛha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Second lowest of the five pure abodes, meaning “Slightest.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="d20b5373-498b-464c-abb9-2ed170ffda7f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8b55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.44</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">become disenchanted</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyo bar byed par ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱོ་བར་བྱེད་པར་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃvegam āpatsyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="885b4c66-bae2-4e53-a5f7-0f35f6b2800c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8bd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.45</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">benefits</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yon tan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོན་ཏན།</span></li><li class="italic">guṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/7193f9ab-e6a6-439f-a32b-bd9671e37ff7"/>n.337</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/5ee86383-373a-4b3b-ac2b-a9849d3aefd5"/>n.257</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e0b9c1ff-2cea-40f6-89ee-7ed3ef312bc1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8bl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.46</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">benevolence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byams pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱམས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">maitrī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="1e5dad8a-ee7f-454c-9154-37e4ac40d3e9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8bt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.47</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Best</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bzang mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཟང་མཆོག</span></li><li class="italic">bhadrottamā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0b8cae9c-affc-4153-9e88-da1b28c8ac37" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8c55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.48</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">beyond regressing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyir mi ldog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱིར་མི་ལྡོག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avinivartanīya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Describes a stage on the path of bodhisattvas (or bodhisattvas who have reached that stage) at which their realization is such that henceforth nothing can ever make them turn back from progressing toward the full awakening of a buddha.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1ed84ea2-32b5-4e94-a60b-42b6acaa355a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8cd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.49</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">beyond regressing from unsurpassed, perfect awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bla na med pa yang dag par rdzogs pa’i byang chub las phyir mi ldog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བླ་ན་མེད་པ་ཡང་དག་པར་རྫོགས་པའི་བྱང་ཆུབ་ལས་ཕྱིར་མི་ལྡོག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avinivartanīyo ’nuttarāyāḥ samyaksambodheḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Describes a stage on the path of bodhisattvas (or bodhisattvas who have reached that stage) at which their realization is such that henceforth nothing can ever make them turn back from continuing to make progress toward the full awakening of a buddha. For the sake of brevity our English rendering follows the Sanskrit and Tibetan, but it should not be understood as implying that such bodhisattvas have already attained the full awakening of a buddha. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6d9c9af5-b408-4472-8c8f-49a385e980e6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8cl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.50</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Bhīṣma­garjita­nirghoṣasvara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgra dbyangs mi zad par sgrogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྲ་དབྱངས་མི་ཟད་པར་སྒྲོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhīṣma­garjita­nirghoṣasvara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>“Irresistible Thundering Melodious Voice,” the name of the tathāgata in whose buddhafield the bodhisattva Sadāprarudita is said by the Buddha Śākyamuni to be presently residing after attaining his quest for the teachings, as described in the exemplary narrative of the final chapters of this sūtra, found also in the <cite xml:lang="en">Twenty-Five Thousand</cite> but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="2af3bf2d-e63e-4ab0-ad3f-b2221c96f746" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.51</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Bimbisāra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzugs can snying po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟུགས་ཅན་སྙིང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">bimbisāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The king of Magadha and a great patron of the Buddha. His birth coincided with the Buddha’s, and his father, King Mahāpadma, named him “Essence of Gold” after mistakenly attributing the brilliant light that marked the Buddha’s birth to the birth of his son by Queen Bimbī (“Goldie”). Accounts of Bimbisāra’s youth and life can be found in <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/29750908-f0c6-4478-834a-ef1289352d3b4" title="The Chapter on Going Forth">The Chapter on Going Forth</a></cite> (Toh 1-1, <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Pravrajyāvastu</cite>).</p><p>King Śreṇya Bimbisāra first met with the Buddha early on, when the latter was the wandering mendicant known as Gautama. Impressed by his conduct, Bimbisāra offered to take Gautama into his court, but Gautama refused, and Bimbisāra wished him success in his quest for awakening and asked him to visit his palace after he had achieved his goal. One account of this episode can be found in the <a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/29e57b5c-a095-479a-b1b5-df26d1678d03" title="sixteenth chapter">sixteenth chapter</a> of <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Play in Full</cite> (Toh 95, <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Lalitavistara</cite>). There are other accounts where the two meet earlier on in childhood; several episodes can be found, for example, in <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="/entity/work/970d89cd-db7e-4287-b31a-709b483fe64d" title="The Hundred Deeds">The Hundred Deeds</a></cite> (Toh 340, <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Karmaśataka</cite>). Later, after the Buddha’s awakening, Bimbisāra became one of his most famous patrons and donated to the saṅgha the Bamboo Grove, Veṇuvana, at the outskirts of the capital of Magadha, Rājagṛha, where he built residences for the monks. Bimbisāra was imprisoned and killed by his own son, the prince Ajātaśatru, who, influenced by Devadatta, sought to usurp his father’s throne.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7bf45dd5-3e8d-4495-bc65-ecf0a51d3597" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8d55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.52</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessed one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bcom ldan ’das</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས།</span></li><li class="italic">bhagavan</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The honorific term applied to the Buddha Śākyamuni and other buddhas in numerous Buddhist texts. See <a href="/entity/passage/1129dad4-86ef-43db-a16b-84f05c8b2a34"/>n.67</a><!--note 65--> for Ratnākaraśānti’s explanation of its meanings. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="d48d036f-b731-4a94-bfa8-487ac298aa50" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8dd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.53</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessed with the power</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stobs byin gyis brlabs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོབས་བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">balādhiṣṭhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e1a0ae95-d0df-4915-aee1-35ee95f36bef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8dl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.54</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="73d373da-ddb6-4549-8f56-bfb57eab537b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8dt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.55</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d9b0a61b-2875-44ab-9a01-a735f65914de" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8e55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.56</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="bd780437-3915-40e7-be2e-4114bfdc5ebc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.57</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessing, influenced miraculously, inhabited, magically empowered, magically influenced</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, byin gyis brlabs, mthus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས།, མཐུས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhita, adhiṣṭhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="46d66fd1-5e77-4b75-8987-f43d0d9ea5c7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8el5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.58</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">bodhisattva level, levels of a bodhisattva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’i sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་ས།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattva­bhūmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Most specifically in this text, the term refers to the ten or eleven serial levels or <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">bhūmis</foreign> of which the progression of bodhisattvas toward awakening is comprised from the path of seeing onward, each defined in terms of qualities possessed and obscurations eliminated (see <a href="/entity/passage/aafbb194-8854-42d1-9df1-996700bb6944"/>n.104</a><a href="/entity/passage/aa10746e-eb28-486e-933a-1e9d47ae674d"/>n.109</a>, and <a href="/entity/passage/92cea5ab-062a-47b6-b310-0c6dde9a66ed"/>n.379</a>). Often also used in this text to refer to the level of bodhisattvas in general, or to more generic stages in the sequence of levels, such as the “level of nonregressing” or the “impure levels.” </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="d1d91886-d66b-4e4d-a74f-ddb2dc10c74b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8et5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.59</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">bodhisattva’s irreversible fault-free state</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’i skyon med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་སྐྱོན་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattvanyāma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>For the play on the two meanings of the Sanskrit term, see <a href="/entity/passage/0dd1d7a0-321d-4efe-b65e-93dd13a1ba24"/>n.879</a><!--note 872-->.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="7538360f-7e4c-4ced-8053-b01e3cc3b911" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8f55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.60</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">śarīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/afcfacf3-e7c1-416a-8ac2-2bc54b5e739d"/>n.279</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="16945947-8642-4545-9f4b-dc408059e451" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8fd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.61</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Brahmā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The principal god of the realm of form.</p> </note>  <p>A high-ranking deity presiding over a divine world; he is also considered to be the lord of the Sahā world (our universe). Though not considered a creator god in Buddhism, Brahmā occupies an important place as one of two gods (the other being Indra/Śakra) said to have first exhorted the Buddha Śākyamuni to teach the Dharma. The particular heavens found in the form realm over which Brahmā rules are often some of the most sought-after realms of higher rebirth in Buddhist literature. Since there are many universes or world systems, there are also multiple Brahmās presiding over them. His most frequent epithets are “Lord of the Sahā World” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sahāṃpati</em>) and Great Brahmā (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mahābrahman</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="de329cfc-68c0-4cbf-9369-db8d0fa432e4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8fl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.62</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Brahmakāyika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs ris</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་རིས།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmakāyika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>First and lowest of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Stratum of Brahmā.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="ac62b307-b113-4054-b510-51d781a9a567" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.63</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Brahmapārṣadya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs ’khor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་འཁོར།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmapārṣadya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Third of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Retinue of Brahmā.” In some texts it is a synonym of Mahābrahma.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="31f35796-b134-4ba5-83f7-f3edb4a5f6c4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8g55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.64</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Brahmapurohita</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs pa’i mdun na ’don</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་པའི་མདུན་ན་འདོན།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmapurohita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Second of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Brahmā Priest.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="5210665a-85fd-492a-89c7-8ae7ca5d12d3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8gd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.65</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">break through to understanding, broke through to understanding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtogs par khong du chud par gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོགས་པར་ཁོང་དུ་ཆུད་པར་གྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">gatiṃgatāḥ saṃvṛttāḥ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cd13c16b-1c44-4de6-ac16-1cef12ae2179" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8gl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.66</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Bṛhatphala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bu che</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུ་ཆེ།</span></li><li class="italic">bṛhatphala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Thirteenth and highest of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Great Fruition.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="03b36254-58d2-41ec-ae1e-6cb6a9533c84" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8gt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.67</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Brightly Colored Blossoms</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog sna tshogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་སྣ་ཚོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">puṣpacitra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of the four gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1622ff41-65d3-42bb-b276-34df9519a734" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8h55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.68</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">buddha eye, eye of a buddha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi spyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་སྤྱན།</span></li><li class="italic">buddhacakṣus</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/18edbd46-bb10-42f7-8ee4-b5689245f34e"/>n.483</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="3e1a9707-a0c5-4477-a334-9910a8f20bd9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8hd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.69</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">buddhahood</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">buddhatva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="bbab6a7c-0f7d-4cee-aaab-b4e99998a044" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8hl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.70</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">can be relied upon</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brten par bgyid pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྟེན་པར་བགྱིད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">āśrayaṇīyā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="41818727-cb09-44a4-9bdf-d2020ed24de6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.71</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cannot be led astray</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’phrogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འཕྲོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṃhārya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="60675101-5552-4e21-affb-f8174ce0fbfc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8i55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.72</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">carpenter</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing mkhan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་མཁན།</span></li><li class="italic">palagaṇḍa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="957e3930-f634-46cd-b984-00365824da56" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8id5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.73</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">caulked</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig tshags bya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་ཚགས་བྱ།</span></li><li class="italic">ākoṭitā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b95ee0ed-0883-427c-8ab4-cc125bf3a224" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8il5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.74</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">challenging questions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brgal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྒལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratyanuyoga</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cbe161d6-bda8-48a6-a029-e57fb233281c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8it5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.75</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">clear mindset that trusts</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems dang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་དང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prasannacitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="87b853be-ce96-408c-ad59-c2e67173f685" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8j55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.76</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">complete knowing of all aspects of all things, knowing of all aspects, knowing of all the aspects, state of complete knowing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa thams cad mkhyen pa nyid, thams cad mkhyen pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།, རྣམ་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvajñatā, sarvākārajñatā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The term used in the long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras to denote the knowing of a buddha. It includes the thirty-nine aspects of dwelling as a buddha together with thirty-seven aspects of the fruition of a disciple and thirty-four of the fruition of a bodhisattva to make one hundred and ten aspects in all. See notes <<a href="/entity/passage/e4aa9d05-9318-426c-a033-8575dc18b0b6"/>n.626</a>, <a href="/entity/passage/a70deeb3-66b9-4ef3-8ba1-79a2fcdeffaf"/>n.631</a>, and <a href="/entity/passage/b1cbb855-2f3d-4d9e-ba90-a66843002f70"/>n.637</a>; also Brunnhölzl 2011, vol. 2, pp. 296–97.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="f1f21402-d1eb-4ca2-b32a-df9dbdf949a5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8jd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.77</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">complete knowing of all aspects of all things, knowing of all aspects, knowing of all the aspects, state of complete knowing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa thams cad mkhyen pa nyid, thams cad mkhyen pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།, རྣམ་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvajñatā, sarvākārajñatā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>In this particular scripture, this single term is used to refer to three different levels of knowing: (a) the “complete knowing (of the constituents)” as the final result of the Disciple Vehicle that knows the five constituents of experience to be empty of personal identity; (b) the bodhisattvas’ “knowing of all the paths” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">mārgākārajñatā</foreign>) to awakening as their final result; and (c) a buddha’s “knowing of all the aspects” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">sarvākārajñatā, q.v.</foreign>) that includes knowing 110 specific aspects explained in the fourth topic of the <cite xml:lang="en">Ornament</cite>. See Introduction <a href="/entity/passage/eb7172d1-291d-4da6-800d-538ea0f1df9a"/>i.116</a>, and also notes <a href="/entity/passage/5fc3839a-9ce1-428f-ba7d-aaaded3fbe96"/>n.532</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/568d243f-4f17-416d-8921-4f540b166923"/>n.1199</a><!--1194-->. For the 110 aspects, see <a href="/entity/passage/b1cbb855-2f3d-4d9e-ba90-a66843002f70"/>n.637</a> and Brunnhölzl 2011, vol. 2, pp. 296–97.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="ef32ced0-5382-4709-a435-b03b4fd4ec94" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8jl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.78</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">complete nirvāṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su mya ngan las ’das pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">parinirvāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The final passing of a buddha into nirvāṇa, often left untranslated as parinirvāṇa. See <a href="/entity/passage/ffb43bfe-621f-46a3-8317-e511d3318647"/>n.230</a>.</p> </note>  <p>This refers to what occurs at the end of an arhat’s or a buddha’s life. When nirvāṇa is attained at awakening, whether as an arhat or buddha, all suffering, afflicted mental states (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kleśa</em>), and causal processes (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">karman</em>) that lead to rebirth and suffering in cyclic existence have ceased, but due to previously accumulated karma, the aggregates of that life remain and must still exhaust themselves. It is only at the end of life that these cease, and since no new aggregates arise, the arhat or buddha is said to attain <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">parinirvāṇa</em>, meaning “complete” or “final” nirvāṇa. This is synonymous with the attainment of nirvāṇa without remainder (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">anupadhiśeṣanirvāṇa</em>). </p><p>According to the Mahāyāna view of a single vehicle (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">ekayāna</em>), the arhat’s parinirvāṇa at death, despite being so called, is not final. The arhat must still enter the bodhisattva path and reach buddhahood (see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">Unraveling the Intent</cite>, Toh 106, <a target="_blank" href="/translation/toh106.html#UT22084-049-001-405" title="7.14">7.14</a>.) On the other hand, the parinirvāṇa of a buddha, ultimately speaking, should be understood as a display manifested for the benefit of beings; see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Teaching on the Extraordinary Transformation That Is the Miracle of Attaining the Buddha’s Powers</cite> (Toh 186), <a target="_blank" href="https://read.84000.co/translation/toh186.html#UT22084-061-006-47" title="1.32">1.32</a>. </p><p>The term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">parinirvāṇa</em> is also associated specifically with the passing away of the Buddha Śākyamuni, in Kuśinagara, in northern India. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="0faa015f-8bbb-458f-9bde-a64ace5ea668" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8jt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.79</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">components of mindsets</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems las byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ལས་བྱུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">caitasika, cittacaitasikā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="140592e9-5e5e-49f2-a96e-416e9da31ac5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8k55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.80</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">concentrated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mnyam par bzhag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཉམ་པར་བཞག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">samāhita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A state of deep <span>concentration</span> in which the mind is absorbed in its object to such a degree that conceptual thought is suspended. It is sometimes interpreted as settling (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">āhita</em>) the mind in equanimity (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sama</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ba1a42d5-f4a3-4c72-8f5d-f87f36b9c4a3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8kd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.81</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conqueror</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">jina</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An epithet used to refer to a buddha.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="a9dcd797-e573-4380-928d-315c5a937d64" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8kl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.82</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">constituents underlying the clinging to existence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nye bar len pa’i phung po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེ་བར་ལེན་པའི་ཕུང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">ūpādānaskandha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8df35a77-da33-4cc6-bd50-2c4e26946da9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8kt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.83</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conventional expression</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tha snyad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐ་སྙད།</span></li><li class="italic">vyavahāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="09c05b6d-a329-4c05-b87e-7cf90d70f4e1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8l55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.84</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">correct viewpoint</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lta ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">dṛṣṭi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c6734b49-014c-4fb7-8f2c-2381175fc086" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.85</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">corrupter of bodhisattvas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’ sun ’byin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་སུན་འབྱིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattvadūṣin</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="15c39eb4-e0fe-4564-ae38-569372760af0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.86</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">counterfeit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzugs brnyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟུགས་བརྙན།</span></li><li class="italic">prativarṇikā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2b1f1c71-ea37-4fb7-938a-c0acd5a8c4d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8lt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.87</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">crowded, full of people</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dres pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདྲེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ākīrṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See notes <a href="/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17"/>n.1094</a>and <a href="/entity/passage/c4ede759-d915-49a8-b469-b3579ecfec25"/>n.1100</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="08ff4aa9-bae0-47bc-b36c-93ba28c249f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8m55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.88</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cultivate, cultivation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsgom pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསྒོམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhāvanā, bhāvayatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4a39048e-b820-4771-8627-1eaf765d95bc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8md5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.89</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cut the ties to worldly existence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srid par kun tu sbyor ba yongs su zad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲིད་པར་ཀུན་ཏུ་སྦྱོར་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་ཟད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pari­kṣīṇabhava­saṃyojana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="70c46af5-0c80-4d15-a018-cac10ce06459" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.90</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cyclic existence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’khor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཁོར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃsāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A state of involuntary existence conditioned by afflicted mental states and the imprint of past actions, characterized by suffering in a cycle of life, death, and rebirth. On its reversal, the contrasting state of nirvāṇa is attained, free from suffering and the processes of rebirth.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4c374c63-a45e-4842-bb17-d09113e278f4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8mt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.91</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">deathless dimension</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud rtsi’i dbyings</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད་རྩིའི་དབྱིངས།</span></li><li class="italic">amṛta­dhātudvāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="40841ac7-4cac-4f1c-82c2-bf1806fb2cb4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8n55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.92</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">decoy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bcos bur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཅོས་བུར།</span></li><li class="italic">kāraṇḍavaka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4c94a4b6-cfe3-4a16-b4b9-df24e6f8b5df" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8nd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.93</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">dedication of rejoicing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rjes su yi rang ba yongs su bsngo ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྗེས་སུ་ཡི་རང་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་བསྔོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">anumodanā­pariṇāmana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2d02adec-81cc-4588-8fac-3bc3550be67b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8nl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.94</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">defend</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bskyab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསྐྱབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">āvaraṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="39b22918-3623-4e61-b135-20b615ebbd49" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8nt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.95</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">deformed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdum po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྡུམ་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">kuṇṭha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="39672c9c-5efd-495f-9952-6c1b0682c8cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8o55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.96</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">deluded sense of grandeur</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">log pa’i nga rgyal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོག་པའི་ང་རྒྱལ།</span></li><li class="italic">mithyāmāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ff293643-80a4-40e0-95cb-0149b659984a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8od5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.97</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">demon cohort</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud kyi ris kyi lha dag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད་ཀྱི་རིས་ཀྱི་ལྷ་དག</span></li><li class="italic">mārakāyika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The deities ruled over by Māra. The term can also refer to the devas in his paradise, which is sometimes identified with Paranirmitavaśavartin, the highest paradise in the realm of desire. This is distinct from the four personifications of obstacles to awakening, also known as the four māras (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">devaputramāra</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mṛtyumāra</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">skandhamāra</em>, and <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kleśamāra</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b87a4b94-ba4f-4882-bbd2-3bbb715c4244" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.98</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">depart for the ascetic life</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par byung nas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་བྱུང་ནས།</span></li><li class="italic">abhiniṣkramya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="25503faa-de94-4eee-a273-6e00ef3ad66c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.99</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">develop conceits</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlom sems su bgyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རློམ་སེམས་སུ་བགྱིད།</span></li><li class="italic">manyeta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ea400c56-f5af-4899-8997-425cbffa9950" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8p55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.100</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">develop the proper mindset, development of the proper mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems bskyed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་བསྐྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">cittotpāda, cittotpādam utpādayati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="19c22f6b-4f9d-4fe3-831a-83322887fb21" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8pd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.101</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">developed reserve of strength</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stobs bskyed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོབས་བསྐྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">balādhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="414181c7-78f4-481f-bbac-ff5cbd9f39e2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8pl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.102</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharma guide</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi tshul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་ཚུལ།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmanetrī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="147c30d7-64bf-4790-a767-8458e2edd12e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8pt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.103</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharma teacher</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos smra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་སྨྲ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmabhāṇaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Speaker or reciter of scriptures. In early Buddhism a section of the saṅgha would consist of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhāṇakas</em>, who, particularly before the teachings were written down and were only transmitted orally, were a key factor in the preservation of the teachings. Various groups of dharmabhāṇakas specialized in memorizing and reciting a certain set of sūtras or vinaya.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f89a2785-7003-4bea-98aa-20782b9b7b3f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8q55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.104</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharma teachings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos ston pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་སྟོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmadeśanā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="050f79f1-4606-4f4b-8231-f0273d900eb6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8qd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.105</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharma treasury</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi mdzod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་མཛོད།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmakośa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d51a0333-62e7-495a-b5c7-c8180ed89159" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.106</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharma’s true nature, true nature of things</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos rnams kyi chos nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་རྣམས་ཀྱི་ཆོས་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmāṇāṃ dharmatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8ea02329-4d61-49a0-8072-b3dc4aa7c7e3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8qt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.107</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharmataśīla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos nyid tshul khrims</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཉིད་ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmataśīla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An eighth- to ninth-century Tibetan translator, reviser, and editor.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="27250080-c9f1-438d-b068-fe9b2c37bb40" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8r55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.108</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dharmodgata</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos ’phags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་འཕགས།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmodgata</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The bodhisattva from whom Sadāparudita seeks the teaching on the perfection of wisdom in the exemplary narrative of the final chapters of this sūtra, found also in the <cite xml:lang="en">Twenty-Five Thousand</cite> but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="266be7ce-6591-4f96-814d-dc90c4a16741" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8rd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.109</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">difficult to fathom</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">blta dka’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བལྟ་དཀའ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">duravagāha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="36b3fbd8-77b7-46ae-ae91-c68df9ccc63d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8rl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.110</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dīpaṃkara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mar me mdzad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མར་མེ་མཛད།</span></li><li class="italic">dīpaṃkara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Dīpaṃkara was the buddha in the past under whose guidance the Buddha Śākyamuni, in a distant previous life, first made the vow to attain buddhahood and from whom he received the foreordaining of his future attainment (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">vyākaraṇa</foreign>). In many texts he is counted as the fourth in a lineage of twenty-seven buddhas who preceded Śākyamuni.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6675bd2e-6c67-4a17-a019-27fec94abc16" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8rt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.111</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dīpavati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mar me can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མར་མེ་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">dīpavati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The capital city in the royal palace of which the Buddha Śākyamuni, in a distant previous life as a bodhisattva, studied under the Buddha Dīpaṃkara.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="26e83d8b-3cde-40df-8a66-f26ecb8b6243" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8s55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.112</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">disciple</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyan thos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉན་ཐོས།</span></li><li class="italic">śrāvaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A “disciple” refers to someone who “listens” to the teachings of the Buddha and “causes others to listen” to those teachings, i.e., by repeating them. The word <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">śrāvaka</foreign> is taken as a causative construction in the second case.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="52752661-3a09-44a2-987c-621472602bd0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8sd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.113</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">dishonesty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">g.yo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཡོ།</span></li><li class="italic">śāṭhya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9700f5f2-a159-44eb-a3e7-bbc3ef1b7588" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8sl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.114</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">display of a buddha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi rnam par rol ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་རྣམ་པར་རོལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">buddha­vikrīḍita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c0d45733-639d-481f-8fdf-6b5c5ae57984" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8st5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.115</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">dissipated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣīṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="89dd6689-01ff-4bc5-a2ea-a5666c7a72e3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8t55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.116</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">dissipation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2261b026-7bf0-4081-9715-fea6e8237195" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8td5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.117</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">dissuade</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dun pa zlog par byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུན་པ་ཟློག་པར་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">vicchandayiṣyati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d5496651-412a-48c9-b30f-c1366e4ce8b6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8tl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.118</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">does not uphold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rjes su ’dzin par mi ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྗེས་སུ་འཛིན་པར་མི་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">anugrahīṣyati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7705331c-b980-477b-a7b4-1f1bfcef9209" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8tt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.119</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">drinkable water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu’i dgon pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུའི་དགོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pānīya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="02f47f04-862d-4b90-82e9-f287aedfc7ad" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8u55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.120</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Dromtön Gyalwai Jungné</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’brom ston rgyal ba’i ’byung gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲོམ་སྟོན་རྒྱལ་བའི་འབྱུང་གནས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An important scholar-teacher (1003–1064) and disciple of Atiśa.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="afefa815-1f96-45fd-94c2-6ffbb231e8e1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.121</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">dwell with ease</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">legs par gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལེགས་པར་གནས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">susthita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0a30bc25-73be-43de-8c14-c859073ce19f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.122</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">eagerness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">chanda</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b48cabc9-2f55-443e-bc3c-9d984c195db5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8ut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.123</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">eighteen distinctive qualities of a buddha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi chos ma ’dres pa bco brgyad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཆོས་མ་འདྲེས་པ་བཅོ་བརྒྱད།</span></li><li class="italic">aṣṭādaśāveṇika­buddha­dharma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/258c64c6-00f6-4bf4-9216-cf792badf008"/>n.634</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/258c64c6-00f6-4bf4-9216-cf792badf008"/>n.634</a><!--627-->.</p> </note>  <p>Eighteen special features of a buddha’s behavior, realization, activity, and wisdom that are not shared by other beings. They are generally listed as: (1) he never makes a mistake, (2) he is never boisterous, (3) he never forgets, (4) his concentration never falters, (5) he has no notion of distinctness, (6) his equanimity is not due to lack of consideration, (7) his motivation never falters, (8) his endeavor never fails, (9) his mindfulness never falters, (10) he never abandons his concentration, (11) his insight (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">prajñā</em>) never decreases, (12) his liberation never fails, (13) all his physical actions are preceded and followed by wisdom (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">jñāna</em>), (14) all his verbal actions are preceded and followed by wisdom, (15) all his mental actions are preceded and followed by wisdom, (16) his wisdom and vision perceive the past without attachment or hindrance, (17) his wisdom and vision perceive the future without attachment or hindrance, and (18) his wisdom and vision perceive the present without attachment or hindrance.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6645bcac-da93-43d6-8ee0-7330f77e4742" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8v55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.124</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">eighteen great signs</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ltas chen po bcwa brgyad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟས་ཆེན་པོ་བཅྭ་བརྒྱད།</span></li><li class="italic">aṣṭādaśa­mahā­nimittam</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Eighteen aspects of the earthquake that accompany a tathāgata’s realization of perfect awakening. Note that the Tibetan term is “eight great signs.” See also <a href="/entity/passage/f059a41a-2c11-4352-b06d-13ec1e6bdb18"/>n.870</a><!--note 863-->.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="2a2dc97d-419e-4d8c-b230-79d2cb378213" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8vd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.125</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">element</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khams</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁམས།</span></li><li class="italic">dhātu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>In the context of Buddhist philosophy, one way to describe experience in terms of eighteen elements (eye, form, and eye consciousness; ear, sound, and ear consciousness; nose, smell, and nose consciousness; tongue, taste, and tongue consciousness; body, touch, and body consciousness; and mind, mental phenomena, and mind consciousness).</p><p>This also refers to the elements of the world, which can be enumerated as four, five, or six. The four elements are earth, water, fire, and air. A fifth, space, is often added, and the sixth is consciousness.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5702e490-14a4-44c4-ae3d-50a5e1bd75bd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8vl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.126</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">emanation body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sprul pa’i sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲུལ་པའི་སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">nairmāṇikakāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="612f4775-3146-4ce3-af8a-6beba48c04c0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_8vt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.127</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">emotional defilements</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyon mongs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉོན་མོངས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kleśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/645530a0-0f21-4714-9e0c-2f7a7514384e"/>n.70</a>.</p> </note>  <p>The essentially pure nature of mind is obscured and afflicted by various psychological defilements, which destroy the mind’s peace and composure and lead to unwholesome deeds of body, speech, and mind, acting as causes for continued existence in saṃsāra. Included among them are the primary afflictions of desire (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">rāga</em>), anger (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dveṣa</em>), and ignorance (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">moha</em>). It is said that there are eighty-four thousand of these negative mental qualities, for which the eighty-four thousand categories of the Buddha’s teachings serve as the antidote.</p><p><em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Kleśa</em> is also commonly translated as “negative emotions,” “disturbing emotions,” and so on. The Pāli <em class="foreign text-pi" lang="pi-LATN">kilesa</em>, Middle Indic <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kileśa</em>, and Buddhist Hybrid Sanskrit <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kleśa</em> all primarily mean “stain” or “defilement.” The translation “affliction” is a secondary development that derives from the more general (non-Buddhist) classical understanding of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√kliś</em> (“to harm,“ “to afflict”). Both meanings are noted by Buddhist commentators. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="a4bc79cb-434c-49fb-88f6-f0970444d657" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.128</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">enclose</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su ’dzin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་འཛིན།</span></li><li class="italic">parigṛhṇīyād</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Used specifically in the context of “enclosing” relics in a stūpa</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="bb81289a-6f28-427c-897b-ab8835bb5493" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_90d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.129</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">engage in meditation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnal ’byor du byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣལ་འབྱོར་དུ་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">yogam āpadyate</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Meditation (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">yoga</foreign>) here is glossed as “meditative concentration” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">samādhi</foreign>).</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="9f72a614-4918-4c15-b189-26405b2aac3a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_90l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.130</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">enjoyment body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">longs spyod rdzogs pa’i sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོངས་སྤྱོད་རྫོགས་པའི་སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃbhogikakāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="46c907ec-4d2d-4f0a-b574-a377d39e0602" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_90t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.131</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">enlightening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsal bar bgyid pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསལ་བར་བགྱིད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avabhāsakarin</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9b79e93c-7837-4794-9ee9-9fa7a9bf805b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.132</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">equal to the unequaled</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi mnyam pa dang mnyam pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་མཉམ་པ་དང་མཉམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asamasama</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="76aa6a9e-107d-4134-94f6-e4853818eb61" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_91d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.133</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">essential nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang bzhin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་བཞིན།</span></li><li class="italic">prakṛtiḥ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a07e0ac1-ff46-4d29-bca1-939e3a0362d5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_91l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.134</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">essential nature of a mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems kyi rang bzhin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ཀྱི་རང་བཞིན།</span></li><li class="italic">cittaprakṛti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5f3bedb9-60b1-420a-bfe9-02b42dbbcb85" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_91t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.135</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">eternalism</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">śāśvata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="db80746c-d186-4671-a39d-729913d0a7c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.136</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ethical discipline</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshul khrims</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས།</span></li><li class="italic">śīla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Morally virtuous or disciplined conduct and the abandonment of morally undisciplined conduct of body, speech, and mind. In a general sense, moral discipline is the cause for rebirth in higher, more favorable states, but it is also foundational to Buddhist practice as one of the three trainings (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">triśikṣā</em>) and one of the six perfections of a bodhisattva. Often rendered as “ethics,” “discipline,” and “morality.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="066eea31-9548-4976-9942-4a2a4873c36f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_92d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.137</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">exaltedness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang che bar grags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་ཆེ་བར་གྲགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">maheśākhya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="14edc247-014d-4709-ae85-40b31fbf888d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_92l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.138</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">excellent ability</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang phyug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་ཕྱུག</span></li><li class="italic">aiśvarya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="1c168449-161c-4018-8155-fb3aa5f9be29" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_92t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.139</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">excellent qualities of a buddha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi yon tan phun sum tshogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཡོན་ཏན་ཕུན་སུམ་ཚོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">buddha­guṇasaṃpad</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ba9676ee-5941-4097-9aec-0f5be27570f3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.140</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">exemplary</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glang po chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླང་པོ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahānāga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/07d40714-85d8-461a-8bd9-e6077fa2c791"/>n.74</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="616b778d-a0da-4baa-81ab-a8f7014cdd73" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_93d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.141</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">exhaust</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣīna, paryātta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a806e6f1-726d-42ca-a907-ce1b4f2fb8d6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_93l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.142</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">expansive</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chen por gyur pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆེན་པོར་གྱུར་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahadgata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="1c2bda21-a975-473a-81eb-d7e02622cf2f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_93t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.143</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">extremely lustrous, lustrous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahaujaska</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5f16e036-e9a2-47ee-a53c-0c96250e9857" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.144</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">factors in awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi phyogs kyi chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཕྱོགས་ཀྱི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­pakṣa­dharmāḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"><p>See <a href="/entity/passage/f293ea18-7a51-49aa-b184-f1a1f975484f"/>n.219</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="0469046c-c58d-4e26-a1fd-ab5e6054490d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_94d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.145</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">familial lineage</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རུས།</span></li><li class="italic">gotra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8f060324-d310-4924-8622-147385a88d47" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_94l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.146</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">fettered</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bcings ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཅིངས་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">baddha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b725a967-b194-43e0-af4b-6a83f546339e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_94t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.147</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">field</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spyod yul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྱོད་ཡུལ།</span></li><li class="italic">gocara</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="14d822fc-e184-4e5e-affd-9e3b08918c08" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.148</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">firm conviction, has firm conviction, resolved</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mos, mos pa, mos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མོས་པ།, མོས་པ།, མོས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhimucyate, adhimukta, adhimukti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="609d5abe-76ed-41e8-a714-30ff92acba34" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_95d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.149</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">firm conviction, has firm conviction, resolved</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mos, mos pa, mos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མོས་པ།, མོས་པ།, མོས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhimucyate, adhimukta, adhimukti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b1a5e818-1156-4126-81de-80e24b2a308b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_95l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.150</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">firm conviction, has firm conviction, resolved</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mos, mos pa, mos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མོས་པ།, མོས་པ།, མོས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhimucyate, adhimukta, adhimukti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="81a0ce86-ce18-4d56-9cf7-be1e6dcd8946" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_95t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.151</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">firm grounding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gting</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཏིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">gādha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f65668aa-2d7e-44c5-b625-5469abb565d7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.152</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">five eyes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig lnga, spyan lnga</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་ལྔ།, སྤྱན་ལྔ།</span></li><li class="italic">pañcacakṣuḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/18edbd46-bb10-42f7-8ee4-b5689245f34e"/>n.483</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="ee84bfce-1a1b-4b04-8759-abc580dabf71" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_96d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.153</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">five karmic deeds that ripen immediately, five karmic deeds with immediate consequences</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshams ma mchis pa lnga’i las</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚམས་མ་མཆིས་པ་ལྔའི་ལས།</span></li><li class="italic">pañca­karmānantarya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/baaa4005-5f68-4b47-b32a-be2c32e3e045"/>n.516</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="6da64de4-0d9c-4307-a6dc-bf40763e25ef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_96l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.154</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">focused on what is beyond measure</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med par nges ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་པར་ངེས་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">apramāṇaniyato</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c4e500fe-7933-4b56-b233-f8ed5cbca36d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_96t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.155</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">foothold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gting</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཏིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">gādha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4b894866-b26a-44f9-9f32-76c50adc4874" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.156</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">formless attainments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzugs med pa’i snyoms par ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟུགས་མེད་པའི་སྙོམས་པར་འཇུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ārūpya­samāpatti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cf4920b7-8e10-4fa5-94ec-faa94b096f50" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_97d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.157</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">foundation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">nidāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d590480f-827b-48f0-b682-03f665f5e5e8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_97l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.158</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Four Great Kings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal po chen po bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་པོ་ཆེན་པོ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catvāro mahārāja</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Four gods who live on the lower slopes (fourth level) of Mount Meru in the eponymous Heaven of the Four Great Kings (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Cāturmahā­rājika</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rgyal chen bzhi’i ris</em>) and guard the four cardinal directions. Each is the leader of a nonhuman class of beings living in his realm. They are Dhṛtarāṣṭra, ruling the gandharvas in the east; Virūḍhaka, ruling over the kumbhāṇḍas in the south; Virūpākṣa, ruling the nāgas in the west; and Vaiśravaṇa (also known as Kubera) ruling the yakṣas in the north. Also referred to as Guardians of the World or World Protectors (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">lokapāla</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">’jig rten skyong ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="33c6ed0c-9310-41c6-b40a-0919c2be6941" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_97t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.159</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four grounds for self-confidence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’jigs pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འཇིགས་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catur­vaiśāradya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See notes <a href="/entity/passage/c85aa09c-b6af-40d2-917a-a131598725c0"/>n.489</a>, <a href="/entity/passage/c4f41ec8-1a45-4cba-a188-2dd503b0e289"/>n.490</a>, and <a href="/entity/passage/1282f9e0-f815-4815-80f2-5afcb2062af7"/>n.632</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="32f65bab-92cb-4a22-b3a4-c0c2eb9ac261" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.160</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four sublime states</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catur­brahma­vihārāḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The meditations on love (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">maitrī</em>), compassion (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">karuṇā</em>), joy (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">muditā</em>), and equanimity (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">upekṣā</em>), as well as the states of mind and qualities of being that result from their cultivation. They are also called the four abodes of Brahmā (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">caturbrahmavihāra</em>). </p><p>In the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Abhidharmakośa</cite>, Vasubandhu explains that they are called <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">apramāṇa</em>‍—meaning “infinite” or “limitless”‍—because they take limitless sentient beings as their object, and they generate limitless merit and results. Love is described as the wish that beings be happy, and it acts as an antidote to malice (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vyāpāda</em>). Compassion is described as the wish for beings to be free of suffering, and acts as an antidote to harmfulness (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vihiṃsā</em>). Joy refers to rejoicing in the happiness beings already have, and it acts as an antidote to dislike or aversion (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">arati</em>) toward others’ success. Equanimity is considering all beings impartially, without distinctions, and it is the antidote to both attachment to pleasure and to malice (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kāmarāgavyāpāda</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1cfd14aa-6bcf-4933-88fc-6f08baeebd29" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_98d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.161</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four truths</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bden pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེན་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catuḥsatya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The four truths that the Buddha transmitted in his first teaching: (1) suffering, (2) the origin of suffering, (3) the cessation of suffering, and (4) the path to the cessation of suffering.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8cfc4cee-b636-4ba4-be70-bb9d82317b28" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_98l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.162</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four types of experiential knowledge</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">so so yang dag par rig pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སོ་སོ་ཡང་དག་པར་རིག་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catuḥpratisaṃvid</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/4465cba8-27d4-4dc4-a097-e578ba89f198"/>n.557</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="83ac25e2-6340-4579-a494-9221df581418" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_98t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.163</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four ways of attracting disciples</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsdu ba’i dngos po bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསྡུ་བའི་དངོས་པོ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catuḥ­saṃgraha­vastu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Generosity, kind words, meaningful actions, and practicing what one preaches.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="10f50cd7-0cb6-47a7-ac8f-b515c644db08" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.164</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">fragrant oil</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vilepana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9fea1c3a-8171-4a64-b63b-3e1024aa180b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_99d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.165</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from creating duality</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnyis su bgyir ma mchis, gnyis su byar med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཉིས་སུ་བགྱིར་མ་མཆིས།, གཉིས་སུ་བྱར་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">advaidhīkāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/cc78e3e8-83ac-4898-8794-cb8f724a1e3e"/>n.187</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/02df0d16-01d1-4d86-86e5-ce2d119b855c"/>n.188</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e60b0155-5de7-4f3f-8743-f7df9bf34c12" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_99l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.166</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from dwelling, free of depending on, not dwelling</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aniśrita, asthita, asthāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a32d3e86-1f02-4a93-b38b-0b2b51096ef3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_99t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.167</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from dwelling, free of depending on, not dwelling</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aniśrita, asthita, asthāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="46effacc-8f20-453e-940a-0e17c0d581b5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9a55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.168</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from dwelling, free of depending on, not dwelling</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa, mi gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།, མི་གནས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aniśrita, asthita, asthāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3d7a289b-1ecf-4ee5-9ad7-0aff502da027" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.169</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from inclinations, freedom from inclinations</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">smon pa med pa, smon pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།, སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">apraṇihita, apraṇihita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e0bf0c80-f45e-4aa7-9705-bc85d07eb310" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9al5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.170</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from inclinations, freedom from inclinations</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">smon pa med pa, smon pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།, སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">apraṇihita, apraṇihita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3712d133-eb33-4ee8-a83c-e65ad14fba3b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9at5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.171</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from signs, freedom from signs</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshan ma med pa, mtshan ma med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།, མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ānimitta, ānimitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f4df1ede-b83e-4ef5-913e-760f4e1ff5a3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9b55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.172</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free from signs, freedom from signs</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshan ma med pa, mtshan ma med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།, མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ānimitta, ānimitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cb6afa59-9383-4e37-86f8-61ec59d8aa02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9bd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.173</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of a mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems ma mchis pa, sems med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་མ་མཆིས་པ།, སེམས་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">acitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="82abea74-6e6c-456a-b390-8fceb82f9b05" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9bl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.174</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of any state of being</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngos po med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངོས་པོ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhāva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4dac8d6d-9df1-4a50-8b20-a7fdb56b0d49" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9bt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.175</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of blameshifting</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">g.yo med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཡོ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aśāṭhyatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d1711a1a-6a85-4b8c-8393-b04394cc31e2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9c55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.176</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of ceasing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’gag pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགག་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anirodha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6e5cd77d-41f5-4104-a8b7-c8814a7885fa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9cd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.177</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of changing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’gyur ba med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགྱུར་བ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avikāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d00bb5e9-1956-4af1-a225-87b45ea5e996" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9cl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.178</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of conceptualization</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par mi rtog, rnam par rtog pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་མི་རྟོག, རྣམ་པར་རྟོག་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avikalpa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ff2bf7a3-8ddb-42c4-881d-3236d230220f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.179</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of dwelling</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnas pa dang bral ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནས་པ་དང་བྲལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">viṣṭhitaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c93f25f7-d04b-4f0d-94ed-49e1707914b1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9d55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.180</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of emotional defilement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas nyon mongs pa ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṃkleśa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="22d0cda8-ae20-43d1-995b-88995299df5a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9dd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.181</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of enmeshment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su ma zin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་མ་ཟིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aparyāpannaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3689e652-c404-47d7-a8b6-de95e649587b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9dl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.182</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of inherent nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngo bo nyid ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོ་བོ་ཉིད་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asvabhāvatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d7836ff1-45bf-4575-84da-6070c8a00e36" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9dt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.183</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of mental perception</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dmigs su ma mchis pa, dmigs su med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམིགས་སུ་མ་མཆིས་པ།, དམིགས་སུ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anupalabdhi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2318e292-6583-4e59-9f11-9a747a591f2b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9e55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.184</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of perishing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi zad pa’i phyir</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཟད་པའི་ཕྱིར།</span></li><li class="italic">akṣayatva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d48d6a86-480e-44c0-811a-37bb68a394a9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.185</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of transmigrating</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshams sbyor ba ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚམས་སྦྱོར་བ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">apratisaṃdhir</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cd340d90-7265-4b1e-8dac-e06e331ff1a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9el5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.186</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">free of worldly influences</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zag pa ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟག་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anāsrava</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="922ebc37-9627-42ce-b7f7-0e8d047cd228" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9et5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.187</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">freedom from any false nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyin ci ma log pa de bzhin nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱིན་ཅི་མ་ལོག་པ་དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">avitathatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6066c993-0a9e-4ef5-a214-be2aee11b7c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9f55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.188</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">freedom from birth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma skyes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་སྐྱེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ajāti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="943a6002-5faa-477a-9f40-41e0575d3d81" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9fd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.189</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">freedom from clarification</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par ’jig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་འཇིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avibhāvanā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The Sanskrit <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">vibhāvanā</foreign> has a range of meanings; cf. Monier-Williams: “<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">vi-°bhāvanā</foreign> f. (in rhet.) description of effects the causes of which are left to be conjectured (or accord. to some, ‘description by negatives, bringing out the qualities of any object more clearly than by positive description’),” as does its negative form <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">avibhāvanā</foreign>, cf. Monier-Williams: “<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">a-vibhāvanā</foreign>, f. or <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">a-vibhāvana</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">am</foreign>, n. (rt. <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">bhū</foreign>), non-perception, non-discrimination, imperceptibility, disappearance.” In this text it has been translated following Ratnākaraśānti’s commentary (see <a href="/entity/passage/99ebd1af-fe5c-475d-82f2-32481e3e16d5"/>n.267</a>), but an additional complication comes from the difference between the Sanskrit and the different renderings in Tibetan found in this and other texts. The Tibetan renderings follow other shades of meaning of <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">vibhāvanā</foreign>, “dissolution,” “reduction,” “[analysis by] breaking down.” See also <a href="/entity/passage/fa292672-261f-411d-9b61-84d3dd257210"/>n.1432</a> in the <cite xml:lang="en">Twenty-Five Thousand</cite>, where in this context of the Sadāprarudita-Dharmodgata narrative it is translated as “irreducibility.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="90feacf7-7b60-4d31-b659-e8b08a6b4501" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9fl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.190</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">freedom from conceptualizing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtog pa ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོག་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avikalpatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="92355df8-e464-46fa-a17b-52f382e7b2fa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.191</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">freedom from conditioning</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par ’du mi byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་འདུ་མི་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anabhisaṃskāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2e1f83fb-8f5e-44ad-81a7-d553b24ec2e2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9g55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.192</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">fruit of a worthy one, fruitional state of a worthy one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgra bcom pa nyid kyi ’bras bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགྲ་བཅོམ་པ་ཉིད་ཀྱི་འབྲས་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">arhattvaphala</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="972dafb2-701f-48fe-bcaa-da82cd54d466" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9gd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.193</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gandhahastin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos kyi glang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་ཀྱི་གླང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">gandhahastin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name (meaning “Musth Elephant”) of a bodhisattva in the buddhafield of Abhirati. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="141cd5b1-456c-4ed3-92eb-6a8e9767bebc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9gl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.194</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gandhavatī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">gandhavatī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The city in which the estate of the bodhisattva Dharmodgata is located, as described in the exemplary narrative recounting Sadāprarudita’s quest for the perfection of wisdom that forms the final chapters of this sūtra, found also in the <cite xml:lang="en">Twenty-Five Thousand</cite> but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="4313e11f-55d0-4757-89e1-c9754c695ec7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9gt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.195</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gaṅgadevī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gang gA’i lha mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གང་གཱའི་ལྷ་མོ།</span></li><li class="italic">gaṅgadevī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A woman whose name, meaning “goddess of the Ganges,” appears as the title of chapter 19, towards the end of which she makes a powerful statement and some offerings of flowers. Her future awakening is foreordained by the Buddha, who states that she first gave rise to the mindset of awakening, like him, in the presence of the Buddha Dīpaṃkara.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="22ebce57-bb52-45a3-b6be-0c5f7d120b64" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9h55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.196</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">gaping</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">vijṛmbhamāṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4c1f8747-2ed7-4cd3-93ec-100eef958b40" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9hd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.197</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">garlands of light</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mar me’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མར་མེའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">dīpamālā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8753d337-1c4c-483e-99d5-13f15f704613" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9hl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.198</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">genuine Dharma, genuine teachings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dam pa’i chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམ་པའི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">saddharma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ddb07ba8-ecfb-4456-804f-2d1affedd66c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.199</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">getting familiar with</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su sbyong bar byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་སྦྱོང་བར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">parijayaṃ karoti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e63bd4b9-8468-4f68-a27f-fdb690db445e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9i55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.200</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">getting very close</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsnyen pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསྙེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhyāsanna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e47cf8c1-4e22-4e6c-af2f-a5dac51c76a0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9id5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.201</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">go about life, go about life, goes about life, goes about life, going about life</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">carana, caryā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Translations of the Sanskrit verb √<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">car</foreign> sometimes suggest that bodhisattvas should “practice” the perfection of wisdom, but the English verb “to practice” wrongly implies that some mental effort, special focus, or activity is always required to exercise the perfection of wisdom. That bodhisattvas should “go about life” means that they should do whatever they do in life (i.e., sit, walk, eat, sleep, and so on) in the perfection of wisdom. See also notes <a href="/entity/passage/81a6f613-1221-408c-bb41-1ded241d4490"/>n.52</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/f292bd6c-f578-43ce-9545-283ad17ff402"/>n.1217</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0fd1d6b0-b105-4939-8546-65a4fb4dfdc3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9il5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.202</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">go beyond cyclic existence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nges par ’byung bar ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངེས་པར་འབྱུང་བར་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">niryāsyati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="92a15fe2-cf71-4674-b98f-d8510bf2b3a9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9it5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.203</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">gone beyond</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nges par ’byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངེས་པར་འབྱུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">niryāta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f5b2a1db-a341-4788-af87-e95cf8cf311e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9j55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.204</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Good</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bzang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཟང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhadra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="fd0b2d07-92d5-43bb-9951-18e77e49a8ff" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9jd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.205</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">good fortune of auspicious rebirth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dal ba phun sum tshogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དལ་བ་ཕུན་སུམ་ཚོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣaṇasaṃpada</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9ad57dee-0f91-411f-82e9-d9bd5a72e294" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9jl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.206</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">good qualities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kha dog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁ་དོག</span></li><li class="italic">varṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="be37efde-2f63-40d0-8e8e-e93b3b3a581e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9jt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.207</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">great being</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems dpa’ chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་དཔའ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahāsattva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An epithet very frequently appended to “bodhisattva” to signify that he or she has a magnanimous (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">mahat</foreign>) attitude with strong (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">mahat</foreign>) renunciation and great (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">mahat</foreign>) realization. Other glosses (see <a href="/entity/passage/8feedae1-0b37-4234-979e-c9e51b9b084c"/>n.390</a><!--note 383-->) explain that a “great being” is a bodhisattva replete with means, or one with a particular resolve.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="5edca432-75cc-4168-a011-da8c0660439e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9k55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.208</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">great journey, great path</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">theg pa chen po, theg pa chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།, ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahāyāna, mahāyāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>When the Buddhist teachings are classified according to their power to lead beings to an awakened state, a distinction is made between the teachings of the Lesser Vehicle (Hīnayāna), which emphasizes the individual’s own freedom from cyclic existence as the primary motivation and goal, and those of the Great Vehicle (Mahāyāna), which emphasizes altruism and has the liberation of all sentient beings as the principal objective. As the term “Great Vehicle” implies, the path followed by bodhisattvas is analogous to a large carriage that can transport a vast number of people to liberation, as compared to a smaller vehicle for the individual practitioner.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d41190f8-e0a4-4c2e-8194-1413404d3e9c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9kd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.209</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">great journey, great path</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">theg pa chen po, theg pa chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།, ཐེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahāyāna, mahāyāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/5fefd43b-03fd-4877-9ac4-43028ed6e35b"/>n.167</a>.</p> </note>  <p>When the Buddhist teachings are classified according to their power to lead beings to an awakened state, a distinction is made between the teachings of the Lesser Vehicle (Hīnayāna), which emphasizes the individual’s own freedom from cyclic existence as the primary motivation and goal, and those of the Great Vehicle (Mahāyāna), which emphasizes altruism and has the liberation of all sentient beings as the principal objective. As the term “Great Vehicle” implies, the path followed by bodhisattvas is analogous to a large carriage that can transport a vast number of people to liberation, as compared to a smaller vehicle for the individual practitioner.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5a72b881-5bcf-4a09-8e97-7778d3313a0c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9kl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.210</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">great mass of demerit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsod nams ma lags pa’i phung po chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསོད་ནམས་མ་ལགས་པའི་ཕུང་པོ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahā­puṇya­skandha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="61d46b2b-e15f-4acb-a944-d2b6cc59f0e4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9kt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.211</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">great multitude</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skye bo mang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེ་བོ་མང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahājana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5381d3e6-d4c8-461e-b80f-ec5b3809795f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9l55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.212</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">great task</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bgyi ba chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བགྱི་བ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahākṛtya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="537e7459-4b69-46f6-9545-71e3246654ca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.213</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">greatest goal</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mchog nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཆོག་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">agratā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="906cf322-811f-4af0-8086-cfc7837bdfc5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.214</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">gross mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems rgya chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">vipulāni cittāni</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a9cfa25e-788c-45ad-b792-12eb4d66502d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9lt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.215</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">habitual tendencies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bag chags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བག་ཆགས།</span></li><li class="italic">vāsana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="136071b2-0ae6-4d14-b8c0-ea6216ec6ef0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9m55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.216</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">had become self-controlled</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang du gyur pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་དུ་གྱུར་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vaśībhūta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/60d69938-6322-4b4f-83a4-5e4fd9535313"/>n.71</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="c0e446d3-a020-4375-96b7-a622b74bfd89" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9md5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.217</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">had eliminated the worldly influences</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zag pa zad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟག་པ་ཟད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣīṇāsrava</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="dfbfa194-a6ed-4c00-a116-64dd4fda6e02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.218</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">had laid down their burdens</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khur bor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁུར་བོར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">apahṛtabhāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/ee27689d-ffba-4f9d-a894-fab229faded6"/>n.76</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="b174fd68-32f5-4727-acaf-302a6bd3e16b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9mt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.219</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">had no emotional defilements</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyon mongs pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉོན་མོངས་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">niḥkleśa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4db0bb9d-79e5-48d4-991d-dfe8e8ff51f6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9n55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.220</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">half mile</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲགས།</span></li><li class="italic">krośa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cb20be11-bf59-442b-a011-b53599eaa1e0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9nd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.221</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of the Thirty-Three, Heaven of the Thirty-Three Gods</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sum cu rtsa gsum gyi ris</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུམ་ཅུ་རྩ་གསུམ་གྱི་རིས།</span></li><li class="italic">trāyastriṃśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The second from lowest god realm of desire, presided over by the thirty-three gods of whom Śakra is the chief.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="5d1d72f1-9235-4ab0-a383-9d79108ea211" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9nl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.222</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">heroic perseverance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtson ’grus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྩོན་འགྲུས།</span></li><li class="italic">vīrya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="506f944c-d376-4454-839d-f5c30eb07b16" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9nt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.223</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">identity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག</span></li><li class="italic">ātman</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b7a756de-b2ad-4958-bd7f-f0447f6f8f27" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9o55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.224</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ignorance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma rig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་རིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avidyā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="05a3d610-b8c8-4534-bb60-f3ba86a5e76a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9od5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.225</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">illuminate, illuminated, illumination</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prakāśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>To make visible, in this text usually in the sense of how mind or awareness functions, but also in the sense of physical light.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="8a7aaa5b-0e50-4e72-84aa-6d82b1f0fe9d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.226</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">illuminate, illuminated, illumination</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spobs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོབས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratibhāna, pratibhāti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>This term (in its verbal and noun forms) is used in this translation in the sense of illuminating or elucidating by speaking, i.e., by expressing something in speech with all the eloquence of a confident knowledge of what is being illuminated, hence the Tibetan rendering <foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="term">spobs pa</foreign> (“courage,” “audacity”). The Sanskrit term has connotations of brilliance, clarity, and intelligence as well as audacity. See <a href="/entity/passage/4943e454-e79c-4a57-912d-4cf9ca2affb9"/>n.84</a>< and <a href="/entity/passage/3fee1f0e-6848-4109-8b66-b032e4e5795d"/>n.326</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="57974a4b-70aa-4113-9a22-2b735c4b5303" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.227</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">illusory nature of things</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgyu ma’i chos nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྱུ་མའི་ཆོས་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">māyādharmatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7545c03a-7b18-44cb-bc71-3d43fbc009eb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9p55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.228</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">illusory person</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgyu ma’i skyes bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྱུ་མའི་སྐྱེས་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">māyāpuruṣa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f5db1ce1-2156-4425-9eeb-35f53d3e14b0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9pd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.229</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">imitation of bodhisattvas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’ bcos bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་བཅོས་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattva­prativarṇika</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b6d126c4-75af-4ae3-a06d-ed6e6e6a2ad7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9pl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.230</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">immature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bāla</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6a266dc0-0dc5-41ae-94af-31c183398592" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9pt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.231</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">immature roots of virtue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba’i rtsa ba yongs su ma smin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བའི་རྩ་བ་ཡོངས་སུ་མ་སྨིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aparipakva­kuśala­mūlāḥ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fc91a840-b068-4763-9ab5-5da0338e95c6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9q55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.232</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">impediments to survival</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srog gi bar chad du ’gyur ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲོག་གི་བར་ཆད་དུ་འགྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">jīvitāntarāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b431f6f7-952e-4e24-8c23-853585cc8a6b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9qd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.233</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">imperishability of the imperishable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi zad pa la mi zad pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཟད་པ་ལ་མི་ཟད་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">akṣayākṣaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a4f81caa-eae6-4aae-9c96-f6dcfedbbef2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.234</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">improper means of livelihood</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">log pas ’tsho ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོག་པས་འཚོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">mithyājīva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7152f9a9-fcdb-4bfb-bc8e-1f6760863715" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9qt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.235</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">improper sexual conduct, sexual misconduct</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pas log par spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པས་ལོག་པར་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāmamithyācāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="656c6fb9-baff-42ed-92cc-c3566df18e32" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9r55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.236</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">in accordance with reality</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ji lta ba bzhin du</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཇི་ལྟ་བ་བཞིན་དུ།</span></li><li class="italic">yathābhūtam</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3af4d769-35ad-4ad1-b79d-ff27501be4d4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9rd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.237</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">in any manner</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad nas thams cad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་ནས་ཐམས་ཅད།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvathā sarvaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5a0b72c2-5c95-48bc-8de6-e0fff5efc196" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9rl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.238</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">in conformity with the truth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yang dag pa nyid rjes su rtogs pas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡང་དག་པ་ཉིད་རྗེས་སུ་རྟོགས་པས།</span></li><li class="italic">bhūtānugamena</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e522e2b8-ad22-4c6e-9a42-458d7d23c694" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9rt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.239</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">in effect</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">du gyur pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུ་གྱུར་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhūta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>This translation is applied when <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">-bhūta</foreign> is used at end of a compound.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="811e77ab-4e3e-4301-a50b-6ad60c9e81b3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9s55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.240</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">in the form of a book</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glegs bam du chud par</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླེགས་བམ་དུ་ཆུད་པར།</span></li><li class="italic">pustakagatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a7f22c1a-24b6-4d08-9954-737b6aff3c4f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9sd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.241</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">incense</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">dhūpa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7dc66eda-56ca-4d72-ba4c-b461150d26ab" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9sl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.242</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inclined to attack</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsod par ’dod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩོད་པར་འདོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vigrahītukāma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e2e56ede-71eb-4c6e-b1e6-6860a80f08a6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9st5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.243</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inclined to deny</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgol bar ’dod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒོལ་བར་འདོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vivaditukāma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="93c28f60-dfca-422d-a5a9-4073f6fa7fe2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9t55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.244</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inclined to dispute</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’gal bar byed ’dod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགལ་བར་བྱེད་འདོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">virodhayitukāma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="db70433e-d0b9-456e-9714-172ec1fdecad" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9td5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.245</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">incongruous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phan tshun tshogs pa dang mi mthun par</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕན་ཚུན་ཚོགས་པ་དང་མི་མཐུན་པར།</span></li><li class="italic">anyonyam visāmagrī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="76cfc447-462c-4b37-8c64-a77ccf8584aa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9tl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.246</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">indication</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟགས།</span></li><li class="italic">liṅga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An artificial mark, like, for instance, the bell on a cow. See <a href="/entity/passage/1af2e9ed-1e0a-4774-b0c7-87414484171b"/>n.881</a><!--note 874-->.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="957282ee-791c-4f90-a7dd-2577ad2e1a3b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9tt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.247</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Indra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">indra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The god who presides over the Heaven of the Thirty-Three, and appears in many Buddhist texts, frequently referred to using the epithet Śakra and addressed by his personal name Kauśika, as both protector and disciple of the Buddha. In the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras he is an important interlocutor. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="631d1efc-cfca-439f-b289-ad3721a4442c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9u55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.248</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inexhaustible, undissipating</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi zad pa, zad par mi ’gyur ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཟད་པ།, ཟད་པར་མི་འགྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">akṣaya, akṣaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="500607b6-ded7-40ce-9258-334a7aeaeb99" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.249</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inexhaustible, undissipating</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi zad pa, zad par mi ’gyur ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཟད་པ།, ཟད་པར་མི་འགྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">akṣaya, akṣaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f1ba951c-3fef-413f-bcdf-862d76ed0412" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.250</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inexpressible</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brjod du ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྗོད་དུ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anabhilāpya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="33f5f374-90cb-436a-abea-e1d6afec3aa4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9ut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.251</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inferior wisdom</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shes rab dman pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤེས་རབ་དམན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">hīnaprajñā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d0454d45-c368-446c-b993-0bd0e6679719" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9v55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.252</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inherent nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngo bo nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོ་བོ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">svabhāva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>This term denotes the ontological status of phenomena, according to which they are said to possess existence in their own right‍—inherently, in and of themselves, objectively, and independent of any other phenomena such as our conception and labelling. The absence of such an ontological reality is defined as the true nature of reality, emptiness.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9283281d-0ed6-4831-9df9-d4d8da920713" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9vd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.253</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">innumerable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grangs med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲངས་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṃkhyeya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ae3567ac-9338-444d-b649-2272372cd6dd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9vl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.254</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">insufficient conviction</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mos pa dman pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མོས་པ་དམན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">hīnādhimuktika</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="14ddaf51-b185-4574-bb0d-6592ae0f380a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_9vt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.255</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">intense faith</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par dad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་དད།</span></li><li class="italic">abhśraddhā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="86f9a73a-b305-4559-b52c-1f3eae673abb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.256</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">inviolable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’khrug pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཁྲུག་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">akopya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e6690dbd-1d83-47f0-b8aa-3caee5c75d7e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.257</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Īśāna</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་ལྡན།</span></li><li class="italic">īśāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>“Powerful One,” an epithet that may refer to Śiva, Viṣṇu, Maheśvara, or other gods.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0ffa193c-6076-4c09-9990-63b8a598fa86" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.258</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jambu continent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bu’i gling</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བུའི་གླིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">Jāmbūdvīpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The name of the southern continent in Buddhist cosmology, which can signify either the known human world, or more specifically the Indian subcontinent, literally “the <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">jambu</em> island/continent.” Jambu is the name used for a range of plum-like fruits from trees belonging to the genus <em class="foreign">Szygium</em>, particularly <em class="foreign">Szygium jambos</em> and <em class="foreign">Szygium cumini</em>, and it has commonly been rendered “rose apple,” although “black plum” may be a less misleading term. Among various explanations given for the continent being so named, one (in the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Abhidharmakośa</cite>) is that a jambu tree grows in its northern mountains beside Lake Anavatapta, mythically considered the source of the four great rivers of India, and that the continent is therefore named from the tree or the fruit. Jambudvīpa has the Vajrāsana at its center and is the only continent upon which buddhas attain awakening.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86598882-1218-4887-8df3-6c016aa50628" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.259</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jñānasiddhi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">jñānasiddhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An eighth-century Indian paṇḍita who participated in translation from Sanskrit into Tibetan.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="b929d2da-435e-4f35-b08c-ec23315f0003" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.260</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyful</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nandā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="cb43148b-eca9-4075-a5cb-a1e1d03682c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.261</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kamalaśīla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad+ma’i ngang tshul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པདྨའི་ངང་ཚུལ།</span></li><li class="italic">kamalaśīla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Indian Buddhist scholar (ca. 740–795) who taught at Nālandā and accompanied Śāntarakṣita (725–788) to Tibet at the request of Tri Songdetsen.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="35279183-1623-4d46-81bb-47be5d30c36d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.262</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kauśika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kau shi ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཽ་ཤི་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kauśika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The personal name of Śakra, the god who presides over the Heaven of the Thirty-Three, and appears in many Buddhist texts, sometimes referred to using the epithet Indra, as both protector and disciple of the Buddha. In the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras he is an important interlocutor.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="4138c2cc-c4d5-4531-b99e-96164df4fbfa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.263</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">knowing of a self-existent one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang byung gi ye shes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་བྱུང་གི་ཡེ་ཤེས།</span></li><li class="italic">svayaṃbhūjñāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e8dd1ed0-b8ec-4610-a817-2f3c9cb4fd02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.264</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">knowing of all the paths</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lam gyi rnam pa shes pa, lam gyi rnam pa shes pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལམ་གྱི་རྣམ་པ་ཤེས་པ་ཉིད།, ལམ་གྱི་རྣམ་པ་ཤེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">margākārajñatā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The “complete knowing” characteristic of bodhisattvas, who must know all the paths to awakening as well as their own. It is the second of the eight topics of the <cite xml:lang="en">Ornament</cite>, and a key term in the long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras. While it is not found as such in this sūtra, according to the commentaries it is to be understood in certain specific instances of the term “the state of complete knowing” (q.v.). See <a href="/entity/passage/6268941f-41a7-4f3c-9b6a-b80740f30837"/>n.65</a>, and also <a href="/entity/passage/b1cbb855-2f3d-4d9e-ba90-a66843002f70"/>n.637</a> which mentions thirty-four aspects.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="984c7a94-e1eb-45a9-8a0d-4a56573a3727" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.265</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">knowing of someone who has complete knowing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad mkhyen pa’i ye shes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་མཁྱེན་པའི་ཡེ་ཤེས།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvajñajñāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4a34666f-5d46-4cf3-b840-671e08865a22" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.266</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kṣatriya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal rigs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་རིགས།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣatriya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"><p>One of the four main castes in the Indian social order, the one to which kings, rulers, and warriors belong.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1688b8b2-358d-4c9c-886c-02b937141c4f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.267</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lack a self, no-self, not an identity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag ma mchis pa, bdag med, bdag med, bdag med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག་མ་མཆིས་པ།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">anātman, anātman, anātman</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b9ea12ca-461a-42d6-ba89-441d4d33e69c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.268</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lack a self, no-self, not an identity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag ma mchis pa, bdag med, bdag med, bdag med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག་མ་མཆིས་པ།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">anātman, anātman, anātman</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="eb958323-b4e6-4ab1-a537-59dc1f948e20" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.269</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lack a self, no-self, not an identity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag ma mchis pa, bdag med, bdag med, bdag med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག་མ་མཆིས་པ།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།, བདག་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">anātman, anātman, anātman</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="df5717fb-5292-4fd3-836d-a774d4a26d45" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.270</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lack of provisions and security</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grub pa dang bde ba med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲུབ་པ་དང་བདེ་བ་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">ayogakṣema</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="31e421ca-33eb-45e3-a862-f67e5b3f3a51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.271</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lackluster</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid chung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་ཆུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">alpaujaska</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ec0f40ca-d8ec-461e-b9f7-7eb0563d39e5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.272</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lackluster perseverance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtson ’grus zhan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྩོན་འགྲུས་ཞན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">hīnavīrya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="02ebd558-a489-4c6e-a32d-ef1f799d847d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.273</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Licchavi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">li ts+tsha bI</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལི་ཙྪ་བཱི།</span></li><li class="italic">licchavi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the ruling clans of the Vṛji Republic, centered on the important city of Vaiśālī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="36a20e1d-63bb-45c3-86e6-796c075b9a4d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.274</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">life’s necessities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’tsho ba’i yo byad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཚོ་བའི་ཡོ་བྱད།</span></li><li class="italic">jīvitapariṣkāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b5178ed1-7a1a-45b5-a7f7-7d6a93a371ef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.275</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">likeness of bodhisattvas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’i gzugs brnyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་གཟུགས་བརྙན།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattva­pratirūpaka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ea37366c-4caa-4d9f-b7db-bde18445f43b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.276</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">limitless</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu ma mchis pa, mu med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་མ་མཆིས་པ།, མུ་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">aparyanta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="afcbf2a8-9863-4e93-ad1a-eb8770e61809" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.277</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">livelihood</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’tsho ba’i yo byad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཚོ་བའི་ཡོ་བྱད།</span></li><li class="italic">jīvitapariṣkāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="45006748-6d84-49aa-995d-80b7b8919021" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.278</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lovingly appreciated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid du ’ong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་དུ་འོང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">priya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e29599ec-2f85-4784-bab6-53a04c0d366e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.279</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">luminously clear</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od gsal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་གསལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prabhāsvarā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f3ace5f8-2bbc-4799-b325-9de48439e81f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.280</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lustful thought</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pa’i rtog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པའི་རྟོག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāmavitarka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="87681525-2530-4de6-8f90-3f876969cc0d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.281</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">made into a book, make it into a book, make the perfection of wisdom into a book</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bris te glegs bam du chud par byas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྲིས་ཏེ་གླེགས་བམ་དུ་ཆུད་པར་བྱས།</span></li><li class="italic">pustakagatāṃ kṛtvā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Note that the Tibetan would be rendered “write it and put it into book form.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0cf127c3-18a3-4d2e-a1e5-d7d0cd1218ad" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.282</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">made prominent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu phye ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prabhāvita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="764e2eca-b833-41f2-81f8-1d67bc589328" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.283</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">magical display</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdzu ’phrul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྫུ་འཕྲུལ།</span></li><li class="italic">ṛddhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The <span>supernatural powers</span> of a śrāvaka correspond to the first <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">abhijñā</em>: “Being one he becomes many, being many he becomes one; he becomes visible, invisible; goes through walls, ramparts and mountains without being impeded, just as through air; he immerses himself in the earth and emerges from it as if in water; he goes on water without breaking through it, as if on [solid] earth; he travels through the air crosslegged like a winged bird; he takes in his hands and touches the moon and the sun, those two wonderful, mighty beings, and with his body he extends his power as far as the Brahma world” (<cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Śūraṃgamasamādhisūtra</cite>, trans. Lamotte 2003). </p><p>The great <span>supernatural powers</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">maharddhi</em>) of bodhisattvas are “causing trembling, blazing, illuminating, rendering invisible, transforming, coming and going across obstacles, reducing or enlarging worlds, inserting any matter into one’s own body, assuming the aspects of those one frequents, appearing and disappearing, submitting everyone to one’s will, dominating the supernormal power of others, giving intellectual clarity to those who lack it, giving mindfulness, bestowing happiness, and finally, emitting beneficial rays” (<cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Śūraṃgamasamādhisūtra</cite>, trans. Lamotte 2003).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="691144a1-87c6-495c-bb6b-8ce8d204d2fc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.284</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">magical illusion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgyu ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྱུ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">māyā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a5054f16-971a-4b39-86fc-f728ba4a975d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.285</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">magical illusionist</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgyu ma byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྱུ་མ་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">māyākāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a17c4e73-ca3a-4635-8da7-8fa8954e5f7b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.286</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">magical incantation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rig sngags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིག་སྔགས།</span></li><li class="italic">vidyā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="dbbbe908-8b34-4212-bb98-569d77dd2730" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.287</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">magically created</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sprul pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲུལ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhinirmita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2b544135-cb9d-4634-bdb3-656dc11befca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.288</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">magically overpower</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang du bya ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་དུ་བྱ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">vaśīkaraṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0c1fb0dc-c5bf-48f6-9352-1590bd80b4f9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.289</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mahābrahma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs pa chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་པ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahābrahma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fourth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Great Brahmā.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1f3abb37-b921-44c5-8ec9-f37b36ccda0f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.290</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mahākāśyapa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od srung chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་སྲུང་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahākāśyapa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An arhat disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, from Magadha. he had the moniker “foremost in the practice of ascetic qualities.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0ce324e9-f379-4ddc-8502-055af5e696bc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.291</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mahākātyāyana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA t+yA ya na chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཱ་ཏྱཱ་ཡ་ན་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahākātyāyana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An arhat disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, from Avanti. He had the moniker “foremost in exegesis.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="b32358bd-b960-4a59-82e5-cb8abb91c901" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.292</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mahākoṣṭhila</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lto rings chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟོ་རིངས་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahākoṣṭhila</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An arhat disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, from Śrāvastī. He had the moniker “foremost in experiential knowledge.” Also spelled (Mahā-) Kauṣṭhila.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="34e9bd80-03ca-4582-8295-19dcf8d87219" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.293</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Maitreya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byams ma’i bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱམས་མའི་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">maitreya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A bodhisattva disciple of the Buddha Śākyamuni, destined to become the next buddha, and an interlocutor in the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.</p> </note>  <p>The bodhisattva Maitreya is an important figure in many Buddhist traditions, where he is unanimously regarded as the buddha of the future era. He is said to currently reside in the heaven of Tuṣita, as Śākyamuni’s regent, where he awaits the proper time to take his final rebirth and become the fifth buddha in the Fortunate Eon, reestablishing the Dharma in this world after the teachings of the current buddha have disappeared. Within the Mahāyāna sūtras, Maitreya is elevated to the same status as other central bodhisattvas such as Mañjuśrī and Avalokiteśvara, and his name appears frequently in sūtras, either as the Buddha’s interlocutor or as a teacher of the Dharma. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Maitreya</em> literally means “Loving One.” He is also known as Ajita, meaning “Invincible.”</p><p>For more information on Maitreya, see, for example, the introduction to <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/ed4cf305-d6eb-4835-a5cf-7483eb4b4396" title="Maitreya’s Setting Out">Maitreya’s Setting Out</a></cite> (Toh 198).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="81cf9257-e262-4402-94bc-c39477bba29e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.294</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">majesty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད།</span></li><li class="italic">tejas</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4a54a887-bdc2-4da3-978b-fba5a3ae0843" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_a9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.295</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">malevolence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">vyāpāda</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fa1b5e0e-0a14-4220-86ca-13d19ca5a449" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aa55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.296</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">malevolent spirit, nonhuman, superhuman spirit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">amanuṣya, amanuṣya, amanuṣya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="99bb787a-ca20-48c4-8489-690437768aef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.297</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">malevolent spirit, nonhuman, superhuman spirit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">amanuṣya, amanuṣya, amanuṣya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="1a7bdbc9-117c-465e-afc1-01604d1be599" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.298</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">malevolent spirit, nonhuman, superhuman spirit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa, mi ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།, མི་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">amanuṣya, amanuṣya, amanuṣya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cca61a77-75d5-4500-a990-23b3336c569d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.299</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Māra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད།</span></li><li class="italic">māra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A god of the desire realm who, in Buddhist scriptures, attempts to prevent the Buddha and others from attaining awakening, often by creating discord and arousing various gross or subtle afflictions. His name means “death.” He and his attendants (māras) personify the external and internal obstacles to awakening. See notes <a href="/entity/passage/157f8fe8-7b5c-4456-bf64-f5a7ee2b2d2c"/>n.153</a>and <a href="/entity/passage/f9106669-765f-4362-ad39-9b901e15c509"/>n.261</a>.</p> </note>  <p><em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Māra</em>, literally “death” or “maker of death,” is the name of the deva who tried to prevent the Buddha from achieving awakening, the name given to the class of beings he leads, and also an impersonal term for the destructive forces that keep beings imprisoned in saṃsāra: </p><p> (1) As a deva, Māra is said to be the principal deity in the Heaven of Making Use of Others’ Emanations (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">paranirmitavaśavartin</em>), the highest paradise in the desire realm. He famously attempted to prevent the Buddha’s awakening under the Bodhi tree‍—see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Play in Full</cite> (Toh 95), <a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/63e7748d-4287-4ccd-863b-a4345d3b5cb9" title="21.1">21.1</a>‍—and later sought many times to thwart the Buddha’s activity. In the sūtras, he often also creates obstacles to the progress of śrāvakas and bodhisattvas. (2) The devas ruled over by Māra are collectively called <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mārakāyika</em> or <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mārakāyikadevatā</em>, the “deities of Māra’s family or class.” In general, these māras too do not wish any being to escape from saṃsāra, but can also change their ways and even end up developing faith in the Buddha, as exemplified by Sārthavāha; see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Play in Full</cite> (Toh 95), <a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/8f8bf37f-8d7d-4607-b0ce-1c1d8b8d4cfb" title="21.14">21.14</a> and <a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/5c732ebc-ddbd-4887-b3be-4225aa96ac44" title="21.43">21.43</a>. (3) The term māra can also be understood as personifying four defects that prevent awakening, called (i) the divine māra (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">devaputra­māra</em>), which is the distraction of pleasures; (ii) the māra of Death (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mṛtyumāra</em>), which is having one’s life interrupted; (iii) the māra of the aggregates (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">skandhamāra</em>), which is identifying with the five aggregates; and (iv) the māra of the afflictions (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kleśamāra</em>), which is being under the sway of the negative emotions of desire, hatred, and ignorance.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="19ab4032-1233-40ea-a87e-cf9cd2176528" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ab55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.300</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Māra’s activity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud kyi las</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད་ཀྱི་ལས།</span></li><li class="italic">mārakarma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3d6bc85d-8d72-4494-b155-ae18f5f1978f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_abd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.301</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Māra’s realms</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud kyi gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད་ཀྱི་གནས།</span></li><li class="italic">mārabhavana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The god realms presided over by Māra.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e2fae2b3-0351-4880-9280-7ba1594c23e7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_abl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.302</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">medicinal herb</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsi, sman</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩི།, སྨན།</span></li><li class="italic">oṣadhi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="25e704f0-eaea-417e-851b-bd78c793aea4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_abt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.303</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">meditative concentration</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ting nge ’dzin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཏིང་ངེ་འཛིན།</span></li><li class="italic">samādhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Essentially a deeply focused mindset whose meditative object is framed by a particular, profound conception. On the individual meditative concentrations in this scripture, see notes <a href="/entity/passage/7c2e270d-92c2-4748-8a9d-565dbc570bb4"/>n.1377</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/3d5990c0-333e-4cc2-a98c-a20078a526b6"/>n.1379</a.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="736f3362-3366-477b-b195-2705a0c5c379" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ac55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.304</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">meditative state</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsam gtan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསམ་གཏན།</span></li><li class="italic">dhyāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p><em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Dhyāna</em> is defined as one-pointed abiding in an undistracted state of mind, free from afflicted mental states. Four states of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dhyāna</em> are identified as being conducive to birth within the form realm. In the context of the Mahāyāna, it is the fifth of the six perfections. It is commonly translated as “concentration,” “meditative concentration,” and so on.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f4171767-1ef8-4563-8b75-880d7a277b4b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_acd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.305</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">meet with a downfall</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par ’jig par ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་འཇིག་པར་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">vyavasādam āpatsyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d5ff6646-c39d-4f4b-8a22-8ed8ce3ba0c7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_acl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.306</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mendicant</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge sbyong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་སྦྱོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">śramaṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A general term applied to spiritual practitioners who live as ascetic mendicants. In Buddhist texts, the term usually refers to Buddhist monastics, but it can also designate a practitioner from other ascetic/monastic spiritual traditions. In this context <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">śramaṇa</em> is often contrasted with the term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">brāhmaṇa</em> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bram ze</em>), which refers broadly to followers of the Vedic tradition. Any renunciate, not just a Buddhist, could be referred to as a śramaṇa if they were not within the Vedic fold. The epithet Great Śramaṇa is often applied to the Buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="71984920-52bd-485c-9f8f-1b4d1cb73d33" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_act5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.307</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mental attitude</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད།</span></li><li class="italic">manas</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0e166dd4-a656-4475-b775-bd17ecf51231" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ad55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.308</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mental factor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems las byung ba’i chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ལས་བྱུང་བའི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">caitasika dharma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f58dc403-82f3-4cc0-b66a-e5bfc72d65a7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_add5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.309</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mindfulness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dran pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">smṛti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>This is the faculty that enables the mind to maintain its attention on a referent object, counteracting the arising of forgetfulness, which is a great obstacle to meditative stability. The root <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">smṛ</em> may mean “to recollect” but also simply “to think of.” Broadly speaking, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">smṛti</em>, commonly translated as “mindfulness,” means to bring something to mind, not necessarily something experienced in a distant past but also something that is experienced in the present, such as the position of one’s body or the breath.</p><p>Together with alertness (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samprajāna</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">shes bzhin</em>), it is one of the two indispensable factors for the development of calm abiding (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">śamatha</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">zhi gnas</em>). </p></div></div></div></div><div id="ad0b5c96-5b65-496d-bb1c-0e4fa6ad3bf4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_adl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.310</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">citta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>In this scripture wherever the term “mindset” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">citta</foreign>) appears alone (i.e., not in a compound like <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">bodhicitta</foreign>), it may refer to the mindset of awakening, or to a proper mindset directly related to it, or to an improper mindset antithetical to it, or to the immediate content of any of these three senses of the word <distinct>mindset</distinct>. See the introduction, <a href="/entity/passage/3096ba3b-a647-489c-9b20-8673274fb8aa"/>i.92</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="3edf7e6e-07aa-4706-b817-7c28c11ecf5d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_adt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.311</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mindset free from worldly influences</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zag pa med pa’i sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟག་པ་མེད་པའི་སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">anāsravacitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0762121b-91b4-401f-88bd-8ce6afdba30f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ae55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.312</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mindset of awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhicitta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Although the Sanskrit word <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">citta</foreign> (in the compound <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">bodhicitta</foreign>) has both cognitive and affective aspects difficult to render accurately in a single English word, the term <distinct>mindset</distinct> has been adopted in the sense of a complex mental state constantly arising in each moment, shaped by particular past actions that affect the way one sees, thinks, feels, interprets, and acts moment to moment. See the introduction, <a href="/entity/passage/3096ba3b-a647-489c-9b20-8673274fb8aa"/>i.92</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1555911b-f1ee-41d3-bae0-6626043c0181" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.313</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mindset that lacks trust</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems ma dad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་མ་དད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aprasannacitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="16a78887-72ec-43c3-96c5-c7ab4ac325f6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ael5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.314</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">miraculous power</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mthus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐུས།</span></li><li class="italic">anubhāva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2d48235b-3905-4980-8c6a-1ebed1174133" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aet5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.315</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">miraculously created</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par sprul pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་སྤྲུལ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhinirmita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8b3d0df1-bab7-4984-9231-ecc4b7e5493f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_af55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.316</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mixed, mixed-up</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu ’dres pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་འདྲེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃkīrṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The term is used in two senses, “mixed up with” (confused or polluted by) and “mixed together with others.” See notes <a href="/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17"/>n.1094</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/c4ede759-d915-49a8-b469-b3579ecfec25"/>n.1100</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1edbce5c-7c22-429e-9fa2-11fdfaa759bb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_afd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.317</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">monk</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge slong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་སློང་།</span></li><li class="italic">bhikṣu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhikṣu</em>, often translated as “monk,” refers to the highest among the eight types of prātimokṣa vows that make one part of the Buddhist assembly. The Sanskrit term literally means “beggar” or “mendicant,” referring to the fact that Buddhist monks and nuns‍—like other ascetics of the time‍—subsisted on alms (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhikṣā</em>) begged from the laity. </p><p>In the Tibetan tradition, which follows the Mūlasarvāstivāda Vinaya, a monk follows 253 rules as part of his moral discipline. A nun (<em class="foreign">bhikṣuṇī</em>; <em class="foreign">dge slong ma</em>) follows 364 rules. A novice monk (<em class="foreign">śrāmaṇera</em>; <em class="foreign">dge tshul</em>) or nun (<em class="foreign">śrāmaṇerikā</em>; <em class="foreign">dge tshul ma</em>) follows thirty-six rules of moral discipline (although in other vinaya traditions novices typically follow only ten).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c631dfec-eda1-482a-beb9-d373eb05c177" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_afl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.318</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Most Joyful</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་མཆོག</span></li><li class="italic">nandottamā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="179b4e7f-2bdd-4436-afb1-14d48d876d46" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.319</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Most Patient</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་མཆོག</span></li><li class="italic">kṣamottamā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="f43df1f0-e329-4224-929b-cfb956aa7aae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ag55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.320</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mother who nurses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">dhatrī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5df5f323-69f8-42ce-88a5-d8fee60b5d11" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_agd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.321</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">motivated by sense pleasures</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pa’i gzhis</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པའི་གཞིས།</span></li><li class="italic">kāmanidāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fa61575c-ddb5-4f50-823e-c6faf936c117" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_agl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.322</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">muslin fabric from Kāśi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ka shi ka’i gos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་ཤི་ཀའི་གོས།</span></li><li class="italic">kāśikavastra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Kāśi is usually understood as the city of the Kāśi people, Vārāṇasī, known for its fine textiles.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0c06ba3e-efda-4685-b775-759637a9db8e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_agt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.323</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">natural body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngo bo nyid sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོ་བོ་ཉིད་སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">svābhāvikakāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4b3ebecf-a9c7-4879-af93-23f6a94d45ec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ah55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.324</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">natural outcome</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyu mthun pa, rgyu ’thun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུ་མཐུན་པ།, རྒྱུ་འཐུན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">niṣyanda</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="74b824d5-12c7-4083-8066-97d55028a5cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ahd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.325</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">naturally effortless</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhun gyis grub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷུན་གྱིས་གྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anābhoga</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7a0d3ca6-db81-4491-aca9-4bb795417c97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ahl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.326</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nature of not existing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngo bo nyid med pa’i rang bzhin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོ་བོ་ཉིད་མེད་པའི་རང་བཞིན།</span></li><li class="italic">abhāvasvabhāva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9950adcc-b7d9-4b88-9095-656f47759bbd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.327</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">negative consequence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">doṣa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="34a76066-4934-4da1-aff3-783e78f7f249" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ai55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.328</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">negative propensity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bag la nyal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བག་ལ་ཉལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">anuśaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="571789ba-014e-4c20-b93d-507e7821001c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.329</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Never Flowing Away</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འབབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avivāhā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1a3ee47d-0c12-41ef-b0c3-880e8a471746" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ail5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.330</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">never goes close</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nye bar mi rtogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེ་བར་མི་རྟོགས།</span></li><li class="italic">nopaiti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="26e77994-e832-43f0-898f-17c9988c9ae9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ait5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.331</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">never lacking</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma bral ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་བྲལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">avirahita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6b13fc98-09b7-4746-87ea-7f8e8a712005" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.332</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ngok Loden Sherab</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rngog blo ldan shes rab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྔོག་བློ་ལྡན་ཤེས་རབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>(1059–1109)</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="74e5b0b0-113c-4446-b539-a7fec74ead2d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ajd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.333</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nihilism</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">uccheda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The extreme philosophical view that rejects rebirth and the law of karma by considering that causes (and thus actions) do not have effects and that the self, being the same as one or all of the aggregates (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">skandhas</em>), ends at death. Commonly translated as “nihilism” or, more literally, as “view of annihilation.” It is often mentioned along with its opposite view, the extreme of eternalism or permanence.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f1854e76-8f2d-4f37-bf1b-124aa89b3a21" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ajl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.334</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nine incremental states of abiding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mthar gyis gnas pa’i snyoms par ’jug pa dgu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐར་གྱིས་གནས་པའི་སྙོམས་པར་འཇུག་པ་དགུ</span></li><li class="italic">navānupūrva­vihāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/e535b245-d129-406d-981e-df22f68753d9"/>n.628</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="aa0118df-2e53-4473-85e7-b0bfd8a6873b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ajt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.335</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nirmāṇarati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’phrul dga</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཕྲུལ་དག</span></li><li class="italic">nirmāṇarati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fifth god realm of desire, meaning “Delighting in Emanation.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="b2383130-0fab-4470-a4da-b8535af34c9e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ak55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.336</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nirvāṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mya ngan las ’das pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nirvāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/f0c7b280-283d-4c70-9c3e-e6cbf1f229e5"/>n.229</a>.</p> </note> <p>In Sanskrit, the term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">nirvāṇa</em> literally means “extinguishment” and the Tibetan <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mya ngan las ’das pa</em> literally means “gone beyond sorrow.” As a general term, it refers to the cessation of all suffering, afflicted mental states (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kleśa</em>), and causal processes (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">karman</em>) that lead to rebirth and suffering in cyclic existence, as well as to the state in which all such rebirth and suffering has permanently ceased.</p><p>More specifically, three main types of nirvāṇa are identified. (1) The first type of nirvāṇa, called nirvāṇa with remainder (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sopadhiśeṣanirvāṇa</em>), is the state in which arhats or buddhas have attained awakening but are still dependent on the conditioned aggregates until their lifespan is exhausted. (2) At the end of life, given that there are no more causes for rebirth, these aggregates cease and no new aggregates arise. What occurs then is called nirvāṇa without remainder (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN"> anupadhiśeṣanirvāṇa</em>), which refers to the unconditioned element (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dhātu</em>) of nirvāṇa in which there is no remainder of the aggregates. (3) The Mahāyāna teachings distinguish the final nirvāṇa of buddhas from that of arhats, the nirvāṇa of arhats not being considered ultimate. The buddhas attain what is called nonabiding nirvāṇa (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">apratiṣṭhitanirvāṇa</em>), which transcends the extremes of saṃsāra and nirvāṇa, i.e., existence and peace. This is the nirvāṇa that is the goal of the Mahāyāna path.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="19009de0-0a92-4893-a82c-5ac504052794" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_akd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.337</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nirvāṇa dimension</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mya ngan las ’das pa’i dbyings</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པའི་དབྱིངས།</span></li><li class="italic">nirvāṇadhātu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An unconditioned space beyond the three conditioned realms of existence in which worthy ones are said to abide. See <a href="/entity/passage/f0c7b280-283d-4c70-9c3e-e6cbf1f229e5"/>n.229</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="8e1bf387-a49c-4da0-b1cd-0adf5b685e30" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_akl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.338</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">no possibility</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnas med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནས་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">asthāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="dff74475-8897-4600-839e-010d5966b459" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_akt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.339</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">noble</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">cang shes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཅང་ཤེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ājāneya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/24673f44-ecbf-4e64-bbd8-7869e7c15fe2"/>n.73</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="c71c642f-e80f-4a1c-a2b7-c447711abfb3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_al55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.340</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">non-Buddhist wandering ascetic</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu stegs can gzhan kun tu rgyu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་སྟེགས་ཅན་གཞན་ཀུན་ཏུ་རྒྱུ།</span></li><li class="italic">anyatīrthyaparivrājaka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e8052e35-e7a0-4c24-a8c6-dcf42039f956" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ald5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.341</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nonattachment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chags pa med pa, ma chags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆགས་པ་མེད་པ།, མ་ཆགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṅga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See also “free of attachment” and “unattached.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="ab1a7cab-b996-4342-a1a8-69e0ab712c60" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_all5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.342</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nonexistence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nāstitā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="62baa549-d606-4ded-bd44-16fc5c2f2562" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_alt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.343</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nonoccurence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’byung ba med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྱུང་བ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṃbhava</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0fb30863-ae01-49e2-8786-49b866b5448d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_am55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.344</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not arisen</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma skyes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་སྐྱེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anutpānna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3b01b128-95a5-4c99-bbbd-9f75cb38aeab" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_amd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.345</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not assured</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nges pa ma yin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངེས་པ་མ་ཡིན།</span></li><li class="italic">aniyata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b847cb23-9087-42ca-9971-5edc1e7b756c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.346</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not be left to go astray</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chud zos par gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུད་ཟོས་པར་གྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">mā praṇaṃkṣīt</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="21a75be0-1502-4347-b719-4db95a363cf2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_amt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.347</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not being found to exist</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avidyamāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6074d31e-6c5c-40a7-9eb3-838530a2c879" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_an55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.348</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not being something permanent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ther zug tu gnas pa ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐེར་ཟུག་ཏུ་གནས་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">akūṭasthatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6d36102c-6a9b-404a-8ce3-679bb37803ba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_and5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.349</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not deflated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’gong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འགོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">nāvalīyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="775db351-7635-44f1-b090-e3f651a1564a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_anl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.350</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not depressed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu mi zhum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་མི་ཞུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">na saṃlīyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="44233a84-bbfa-4d9f-a55a-19326625f2fb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ant5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.351</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not differentiating</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbyer mi phyed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབྱེར་མི་ཕྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṃbhedana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0c54e749-10c0-431c-83c0-129b6d86a251" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ao55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.352</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not experienced as existing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">na saṃvidyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="884a4f94-d266-43b6-a77a-331278f6f89b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.353</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not finding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma ’tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་འཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">avindan</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d6b0df4d-5eaf-4d6f-bdd2-e71e4f152194" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.354</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not free of dwelling</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnas pa dang bral ba ma lags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནས་པ་དང་བྲལ་བ་མ་ལགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aviṣṭhitaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c1107eab-0344-42d0-a10b-9fb3e60276a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.355</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not frightened</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi dngang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་དངང་།</span></li><li class="italic">notrasyati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="500fe14b-c431-404f-9b1a-89125cb30a3a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ap55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.356</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not identifying</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yang dag par rjes su ma mthong na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡང་དག་པར་རྗེས་སུ་མ་མཐོང་ན།</span></li><li class="italic">asamanupaśyan</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="028c8c16-0513-4dae-9e1b-14c834880ede" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_apd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.357</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not mentally perceiving</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma dmigs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་དམིགས།</span></li><li class="italic">anupalabhamāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2d6561f9-cd54-4539-8d5b-286e9ad332a9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_apl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.358</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not really existent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yang dag pa ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡང་དག་པ་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asadbhūtatva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2683095c-4a8b-4b93-a0f5-cb42d263f8e2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_apt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.359</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not stricken with terror, stricken with terror</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu skrag pa dang ldan par mi ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་སྐྲག་པ་དང་ལྡན་པར་མི་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">na saṃtrāsam āpadyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="12850e8f-bca6-487d-b286-8a071e49491f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.360</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not sunk in despondency, sunk in despondency</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bag ’khums par mi ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བག་འཁུམས་པར་མི་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">na viṣādaṃ saṃpadyate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="57efd00f-92ad-481a-a867-0f0b22f88085" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.361</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not terrified</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu mi skrag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་མི་སྐྲག</span></li><li class="italic">na saṃtrasyati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="169b497b-90ea-4a3b-83ea-4c9a94a20c99" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.362</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">not truly coming into being</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par ma grub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་མ་གྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anabhinirvṛtti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4391bb6c-a04e-4568-937b-27ca2642cda1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.363</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">null</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhi ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞི་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">śānta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"><p>Usually translated as “at peace” or “quelled,” but here most often referring to the cessation or absence of something. See <a href="/entity/passage/57742f30-25ee-4261-a5e1-61b06d0151fb"/>n.433</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/78416b69-0bf2-4dc7-8403-b5dae67609de"/>n.609</a>. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e7651bdc-ad43-4eeb-b69a-0277776d2ba5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ar55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.364</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nun</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge slong ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་སློང་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhikṣuṇī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhikṣuṇī</em>, often translated as “nun,” refers to the highest among the eight types of prātimokṣa vows that make one part of the Buddhist assembly. The Sanskrit term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhikṣu</em> (to which the female grammatical ending <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">ṇī</em> is added) literally means “beggar” or “mendicant,” referring to the fact that Buddhist nuns and monks‍—like other ascetics of the time‍—subsisted on alms (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhikṣā</em>) begged from the laity. In the Tibetan tradition, which follows the Mūlasarvāstivāda Vinaya, a bhikṣuṇī follows 364 rules and a bhikṣu follows 253 rules as part of their moral discipline.</p><p>For the first few years of the Buddha’s teachings in India, there was no ordination for women. It started at the persistent request and display of determination of Mahāprajāpatī, the Buddha’s stepmother and aunt, together with five hundred former wives of men of Kapilavastu, who had themselves become monks. Mahāprajāpatī is thus considered to be the founder of the nun’s order.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="60ce141a-06aa-498d-ac9e-01a8df259ad5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ard5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.365</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">objects of sensual desire</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pa’i yon tan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པའི་ཡོན་ཏན།</span></li><li class="italic">kāmaguṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="535f62eb-5191-45b6-84cb-bab8291e180d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_arl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.366</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">occupation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rjes su sbyor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྗེས་སུ་སྦྱོར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">anuyoga</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="734b3564-a7dd-4385-a525-d62e413e770d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_art5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.367</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">occupied with</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtson par byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྩོན་པར་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">anuyuktaḥ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d4e3a866-9c0c-43b0-a4c5-ed2d2d65c27b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_as55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.368</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">on the bodhisattva path</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’i theg pa can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་ཐེག་པ་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattvayānika</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="33bb7c17-c48c-470f-936b-94aa51abd9bf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_asd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.369</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">one billion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bye ba brgya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱེ་བ་བརྒྱ།</span></li><li class="italic">koṭīśata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c3f73b51-40e1-4b68-8859-8a105851b92e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_asl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.370</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">one quintillion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bye ba khrag khrig brgya stong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱེ་བ་ཁྲག་ཁྲིག་བརྒྱ་སྟོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">koṭī­niyuta­śata­sahasra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="64105151-6806-4ecf-9b65-72dbaacc4d62" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ast5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.371</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">one second</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thang gcig</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐང་གཅིག</span></li><li class="italic">lava</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="bf343427-6de2-4bc9-8df0-f1237ea4caad" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_at55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.372</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">one trillion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bye ba brgya stong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱེ་བ་བརྒྱ་སྟོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">koṭī­śata­sahasra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="41d53369-fb3a-4635-ac77-cdd3d19898e1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_atd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.373</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">one who gives birth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyed par byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེད་པར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">janayitrī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ed7270eb-cf0d-4e4a-9c32-77fb454281a5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_atl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.374</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">oriented toward</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon du byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་དུ་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">abhimukha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="064d24a6-3da5-4e30-bed5-7b6c0e0a5820" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_att5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.375</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">outcaste among bodhisattvas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’ gdol pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའ་གདོལ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­sattva­caṇḍāla</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="bf032068-576a-414b-b7e7-6c9ecc4dee0b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_au55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.376</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">outshone</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zil gyis mnan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟིལ་གྱིས་མནན།</span></li><li class="italic">abhibhūta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f295a6f0-ace2-43ed-b63c-96bcb8785083" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.377</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">overexcited</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ya ya por mi ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡ་ཡ་པོར་མི་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">notplavate</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2322dec6-dd73-46cc-a3cc-3dadbf72bf2e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.378</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">own unique human body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag gi dngos po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག་གི་དངོས་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">ātmabhāva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/afcfacf3-e7c1-416a-8ac2-2bc54b5e739d"/>n.279</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="839fbe36-2bd3-4dc5-a69b-4509251afefe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_aut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.379</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">own unique physical body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag gi dngos po’i sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག་གི་དངོས་པོའི་སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">ātmabhāvaśarīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/afcfacf3-e7c1-416a-8ac2-2bc54b5e739d"/>n.279</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="684d1298-bd22-4009-ac47-91c522c12893" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_av55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.380</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pain, painful, suffering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdug bsngal ba, sdug bsngal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྡུག་བསྔལ་བ།, སྡུག་བསྔལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">duḥkha, duḥkha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The first of the four truths of the noble ones. The term “suffering” includes all essentially unsatisfactory experiences of life in cyclic existence, whether physical or mental. These comprise (1) the suffering of suffering, i.e., the physical sensations and mental experiences that are self-evident as suffering and toward which spontaneous feelings of aversion arise; (2) the suffering of change, i.e., all experiences that are normally recognized as pleasant and desirable, but which are nonetheless suffering in that persistent indulgence in these always results in changing attitudes of dissatisfaction and boredom; and (3) the suffering of the pervasive conditioning underlying the round of birth, aging, and death.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="999cad0b-8e8c-42d8-aac9-011a2dec26ca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_avd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.381</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pain, painful, suffering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdug bsngal ba, sdug bsngal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྡུག་བསྔལ་བ།, སྡུག་བསྔལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">duḥkha, duḥkha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The first of the four truths of the noble ones. The term “suffering” includes all essentially unsatisfactory experiences of life in cyclic existence, whether physical or mental. These comprise (1) the suffering of suffering, i.e., the physical sensations and mental experiences that are self-evident as suffering and toward which spontaneous feelings of aversion arise; (2) the suffering of change, i.e., all experiences that are normally recognized as pleasant and desirable, but which are nonetheless suffering in that persistent indulgence in these always results in changing attitudes of dissatisfaction and boredom; and (3) the suffering of the pervasive conditioning underlying the round of birth, aging, and death.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="08a8015c-bc31-48ae-8abb-2ac57ba086a5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_avl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.382</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Paranirmitavaśavartin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhan ’phrul dbang byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞན་འཕྲུལ་དབང་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">paranirmitavaśavartin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Sixth god realm of desire, meaning “Mastery over Transformations.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="067d251d-4033-4730-9128-e7a2bf7c2153" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_avt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.383</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">parapet</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mda’ yab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མདའ་ཡབ།</span></li><li class="italic">khoḍakaśīrṣa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ee377164-b3bf-418c-9d21-f9355667e19d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.384</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">parasite</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srin bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲིན་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṛmi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d6d6593b-25d3-4049-97b4-3615b3c1fe97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.385</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Parīttābha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od chung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་ཆུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">Parīttābha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fifth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Little Radiance.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="af0dc62d-7832-49f4-b7b8-18fca7272c22" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.386</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Parīttaśubha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge chung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་ཆུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">parīttaśubha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Eighth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Little Virtue.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="f8312a26-df41-417f-baed-6e401b1e5766" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.387</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">passing it by</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">g.yul las ’das</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཡུལ་ལས་འདས།</span></li><li class="italic">atikrāma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="80e88a46-a897-465d-884c-b724b1404eb0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.388</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">path of cultivation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsgom pa’i lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསྒོམ་པའི་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhāvanāmārga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fourth of the five paths.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="a1dfb7e4-c4f3-4dd3-8988-ff50731b6fcd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.389</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">path of no more training</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi slob pa’i lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་སློབ་པའི་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">aśaikṣamārga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fifth of the five paths.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="5b884783-353d-4b51-9f6e-5b8ab29c823b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.390</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">path of preliminary practice</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbyor ba’i lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྱོར་བའི་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">prayogyamārga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Second of the five paths.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6f632c62-dd2f-4261-a93d-6db315e8a6bf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.391</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">path of seeing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mthong ba’i lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོང་བའི་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">darśana­mārga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Third of the five paths.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="69068b19-1508-4f88-983b-aabcc7be72b5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.392</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">path of training</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">slob pa’i lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སློབ་པའི་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">śaikṣamārga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The term may encompass the first four of the five paths, as well as the first seven of the eight stages that culminate in the state of a worthy one. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="ed8b1c94-1480-4d76-8c69-9697a1b7c4c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.393</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Patient</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣamā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="4ed793e5-b927-44f6-8bb0-e3cab55c110f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.394</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pavilion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dkyil ’khor gyi khyams</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཀྱིལ་འཁོར་གྱི་ཁྱམས།</span></li><li class="italic">maṇḍalamāle</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5ada82eb-e5e4-4df5-873c-20b0f5055a46" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.395</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">peaceful ways of life</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhi bar spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞི་བར་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">śamacaryā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ca2b836f-95b4-4a1e-b05a-f4b892099782" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.396</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">peak</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mūrdhan</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The second of four stages or experiences of breaking through on the path of preliminary practice.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="78a7f55d-6537-4695-a1c0-71eb963a2a00" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.397</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">peaked temple</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khang pa brtsegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁང་པ་བརྩེགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kūṭāgāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="360ef9fa-cc6f-4f0f-9fd4-c4b67089fe23" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.398</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">perform an act of truth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bden pa’i byin gyi rlabs bya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེན་པའི་བྱིན་གྱི་རླབས་བྱ།</span></li><li class="italic">satyādhiṣṭhānaṃ kariṣyāmi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fffa4f81-7bfa-4102-9276-e4bfc613553f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.399</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">performing the practices</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spyad pa spyod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྱད་པ་སྤྱོད།</span></li><li class="italic">cārikāṃ caranti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0177978e-49fe-4595-9bb7-50c69b0eb938" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.400</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">physical actualization</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sku yongs su grub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐུ་ཡོངས་སུ་གྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāyapariniṣpatti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cbb7e210-529e-41ff-babe-2a5a692b6915" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.401</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">physical body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdag gi dngos po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདག་གི་དངོས་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">ātmabhāva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/afcfacf3-e7c1-416a-8ac2-2bc54b5e739d"/>n.279</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="2fc4f126-3bd7-41b7-ac24-617906330f5c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.402</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">physical relic</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">śarīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/afcfacf3-e7c1-416a-8ac2-2bc54b5e739d"/>n.279</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6ee48068-c346-4c86-9de7-86f897d4e85b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.403</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">physically deformed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbyibs mi sdug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབྱིབས་མི་སྡུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">duḥsaṃsthāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="aaeba2e6-a279-4a6d-af18-709a428b75ee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.404</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pinnacle of reality</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yang dag pa’i mtha’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡང་དག་པའི་མཐའ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhūtakoṭi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>This term has three meanings: (1) the ultimate nature, (2) the experience of the ultimate nature, and (3) the quiescent state of a worthy one (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">arhat</em>) to be avoided by bodhisattvas.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6d37f084-ca6a-4365-a2a6-94c3267bc2b5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.405</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pinnacle of worldly things</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig rten pa’i chos kyi mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་རྟེན་པའི་ཆོས་ཀྱི་མཆོག</span></li><li class="italic">laukikāgradharma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The fourth of four stages or experiences of breaking through on the path of preliminary practice.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="534064f3-2b6e-47b2-9275-ae41efa5275a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.406</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">power of memory</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzungs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟུངས།</span></li><li class="italic">dhāraṇī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dhāraṇī</em> has the sense of something that “holds” or “retains,” and so it can refer to the special capacity of practitioners to memorize and recall detailed teachings. It can also refer to a verbal expression of the teachings‍—an incantation, spell, or mnemonic formula‍—that distills and “holds” essential points of the Dharma and is used by practitioners to attain mundane and supramundane goals. The same term is also used to denote texts that contain such formulas.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2f6ea888-548c-45fa-b0a9-6b11c1beea03" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.407</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">powerful energy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahaujaska</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d152f48e-5c78-4465-ad19-68f03a7830f2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.408</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">practice generosity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbyin pa byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྱིན་པ་བྱིན།</span></li><li class="italic">dānaṃ dattaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="481b8064-38df-4eae-9abc-c7a6f6277834" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.409</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">practice of ascetic qualities, sorts of ascetic qualities, types of ascetic qualities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbyangs pa’i yon tan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྱངས་པའི་ཡོན་ཏན།</span></li><li class="italic">dhutaguṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b55c8245-cea0-4e2a-9687-2a85a37beb8d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.410</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Prajāpati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skye dgu’i bdag po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེ་དགུའི་བདག་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">prajāpati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Literally “Lord of Beings,” an epithet designating a god of the Brahmā realm but also referring to Śiva, Viṣṇu, and others.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="17005e7a-e029-42eb-a4ed-ad8f20880fb7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.411</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Prasenajit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsal rgyal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསལ་རྒྱལ།</span></li><li class="italic">prasenajit</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>King of the powerful kingdom of Kośala, centered on the city of Śrāvasti. He was a contemporary of the Buddha Śākyamuni, becoming his disciple and patron.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6568d3d5-ad8d-41c7-8b38-be0d49a874ce" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.412</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pregnant</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbrum ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྲུམ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">gurviṇī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="3ad6f2dc-0ca5-4a52-b962-3a386f6efbc8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.413</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">preliminary practice</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su sbyang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་སྦྱང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṛtaparikarma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/cfa524c8-530f-42c5-84f4-76db1acd64db"/>n.1024</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="f8c8ec2d-b6d2-44e6-8bb4-e6e34938f56f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.414</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">prey on weakness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glags lta ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླགས་ལྟ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">avatāragaveṣin</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="773a28c0-d269-4a83-add8-cf1a172979ae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.415</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">principal characteristics of a great person</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyes bu chen po’i mtshan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེས་བུ་ཆེན་པོའི་མཚན།</span></li><li class="italic">mahā­puruṣa­lakṣaṇāni</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2e6ab6d0-661a-4953-a0ea-8227e8db9f31" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.416</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">proceeded based on faith, proceeding based on faith, proceeds based on faith</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dad pas rjes su ’brang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དད་པས་རྗེས་སུ་འབྲང་།</span></li><li class="italic">śraddhānusāri</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="73ffcea3-c020-438d-897b-328f0090cdfe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.417</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">profit greatly</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnyed pa legs par rnyed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྙེད་པ་ལེགས་པར་རྙེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">lābhāḥ sulabdhā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a2963fa5-8af6-4003-9a92-f499ea9c2212" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.418</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Puṇyaprasava</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsod nams ’phel</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསོད་ནམས་འཕེལ།</span></li><li class="italic">puṇyaprasava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The twelfth of the thirteen levels of the god realm of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Increasing Merit.” In some versions of the longer Prajñāpāramitā sūtras, which list sixteen realms instead of thirteen, this god realm has the name Apramāṇabṛhat (Tib. <foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="term">tshad med che ba</foreign>). </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="e938eacd-cc4a-4165-805c-e640d2d846fe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.419</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pūrṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">pūrṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Of the several arhat disciples of the Buddha with the name Pūrṇa, this is Pūrṇa Maitrāyaṇīputra, Pūrṇa the son of Maitrāyaṇī. He is a Śākyan who became an arhat under the guidance of his uncle Ājñātakauṇḍinya before meeting the Buddha (his mother Maitrāyaṇī was Ājñātakauṇḍinya’s sister). He was considered “foremost in teaching.” See the 84000 Knowledge Base article <ref target="https://84000.co/kb-articles/disciples-named-purna#pura-maitrayaiputra">“Disciples Named Pūrṇa.”</ref> </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="cedb8cf4-9d58-40cb-976e-0f841d70f50a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.420</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">qualities of a buddha, quality of a buddha, quality of the buddha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">buddhadharma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="da120fb0-fc39-419b-9f2e-d54611ad0639" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.421</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">quantify</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grangs su gtogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲངས་སུ་གཏོགས།</span></li><li class="italic">gaṇanā kṛtā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5d05565c-7425-4bfd-bd3c-e6512ac83dd2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.422</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rājagṛha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal po’i khab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་པོའི་ཁབ།</span></li><li class="italic">rājagṛha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The ancient capital of Magadha prior to its relocation to Pāṭaliputra during the Mauryan dynasty, Rājagṛha is one of the most important locations in Buddhist history. The literature tells us that the Buddha and his saṅgha spent a considerable amount of time in residence in and around Rājagṛha‍—in nearby places, such as the Vulture Peak Mountain (Gṛdhrakūṭaparvata), a major site of the Mahāyāna sūtras, and the Bamboo Grove (Veṇuvana)‍—enjoying the patronage of King Bimbisāra and then of his son King Ajātaśatru. Rājagṛha is also remembered as the location where the first Buddhist monastic council was held after the Buddha Śākyamuni passed into parinirvāṇa. Now known as Rajgir and located in the modern Indian state of Bihar.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="684a5a75-847b-4219-9ec1-eea81f33f645" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_b9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.423</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ratnaketu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i tog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་ཏོག</span></li><li class="italic">ratnaketu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A bodhisattva named in this scripture as presently living in the buddhafield of the Buddha Akṣobhya.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="c64a4d19-2f1a-4884-94d5-de59f7215265" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ba55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.424</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ready mind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems bde ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་བདེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">kalyacitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="eac0590f-cb36-4ca8-8fe6-d939c279cf6e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.425</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">real body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sku dam pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐུ་དམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">satkāya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>For an explanation of the term <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">satkāya</foreign> in this sense, used in such contexts as that of the Buddha’s body, as at <a href="/entity/passage/0115ac3b-9f32-44d4-bbce-c7cd0e5ce9c1"/>4.2</a>, compared to the more usual “transitory collection,” see <a href="/entity/passage/d60694a0-b636-4e83-b104-ec86a6012cd1"/>n.341</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="142a40b5-25c5-4943-a946-b060ea85a380" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.426</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">realizing the inexhaustible</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi zad pa mngon par bsgrub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཟད་པ་མངོན་པར་བསྒྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">akṣayābhinirhāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2dc8942a-1031-478b-b5b2-7aeffce30f22" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.427</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">rebuff</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi mthun par rjod par</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་མཐུན་པར་རྗོད་པར།</span></li><li class="italic">prativāṇī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b9a61e36-059d-4e4a-a7f9-571be03108f9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.428</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">referent of the word</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhi’i don</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞིའི་དོན།</span></li><li class="italic">padārtha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8a9caeff-2d39-411f-bc8d-cc742eee6aa6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.429</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">refine</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su dag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་དག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pariśuddhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Sanskrit syntax uses the noun “refinement,” often translated as “purification.” </p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="12bd0868-347f-44e7-a828-bfece3f113f9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.430</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">regional king</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mkhar gyi rgyal po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཁར་གྱི་རྒྱལ་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">koṭṭarāja</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="280eec93-756a-42ca-ad23-701012f25a46" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.431</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">reliant</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nye bar brtan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེ་བར་བརྟན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">upastabdha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d4c8daa3-6129-4c68-9b07-48fa3a7973b6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.432</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">relinquish</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prahīna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9d1b2cb9-d22d-4300-86e4-3541a30b7763" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.433</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">repeatedly practices, repeatedly practicing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">goms pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གོམས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ābhyāsata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ef6ab2e1-1656-4ac2-909e-91650d605c4d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.434</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">replete with all excellent qualities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa thams cad kyi mchog dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་མཆོག་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvākāravaropeta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="707c77e9-456a-4996-887a-8e8cc1cd9503" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.435</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rinchen Chökyong Zangpo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zha lu lo tsA ba rin chen chos skyong bzang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞ་ལུ་ལོ་ཙཱ་བ་རིན་ཆེན་ཆོས་སྐྱོང་བཟང་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Scholar and translator also known as Zhalu Lotsawa (1441–1527). Renowned particularly for his expertise in Sanskrit. See bio at <ref target="https://treasuryoflives.org/biographies/view/Chokyong-Zangpo/11285">Treasury of Lives</ref>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="b3117f6c-8b33-404c-93db-0e331ab39488" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bd55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.436</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rinchen Zangpo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin chen bzang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་ཆེན་བཟང་པོ།</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a98fb9e4-a24c-4692-864b-0a863947bcb4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bdd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.437</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">rise above, rising above</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par ’phags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་འཕགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhyudgata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b22c6e0e-bb50-4565-8f11-7809e85ba449" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bdl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.438</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">root of virtue, roots of virtue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba’i rtsa ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བའི་རྩ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">kuśalamūla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>According to most lists (specifically those of the Pāli and some Abhidharma traditions), the (three) roots of virtue or the roots of the good or wholesome states (of mind) are what makes a mental state good or bad; they are identified as the opposites of the three mental “poisons” of greed, hatred, and delusion. Actions based on the roots of virtue will eventually lead to future happiness. The <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Dharmasaṃgraha</cite>, however, lists the three roots of virtue as (1) the mind of awakening, (2) purity of thought, and (3) freedom from egotism (Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">trīṇi kuśala­mūlāni</em> | <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bodhi­cittotpādaḥ</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">āśayaviśuddhiḥ</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">ahaṃkāramama­kāraparityāgaśceti</em>|). </p></div></div></div></div><div id="c7fa2a32-c71f-43ed-8ce3-d769f5bfd939" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bdt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.439</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sadāprarudita</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag tu ngu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་ཏུ་ངུ།</span></li><li class="italic">sadāprarudita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The bodhisttava protagonist of the final chapters of this scripture, whose indefatigable quest for the perfection of wisdom forms an exemplary narrative found also in the <cite xml:lang="en">Twenty-Five Thousand</cite> but not in the other long Perfection of Wisdom sūtras.</p> </note>  <p>A bodhisattva famous for his quest for the Dharma and for his devotion to the teacher. It is told that Sadāprarudita, in order to make offerings to the bodhisattva Dharmodgata and request the Prajñāpāramitā teachings, sets out to sell his own flesh and blood. After receiving a first set of teachings, Sadāprarudita waits seven years for the bodhisattva Dharmodgata, his teacher, to emerge from meditation. When he receives signs this is about to happen, he wishes to prepare the ground for the teachings by settling the dust. Māra makes all the water disappear, so Sadāprarudita decides to use his own blood to settle the dust. He is said to be practicing in the presence of Buddha Bhīṣma­garjita­nirghoṣa­svara. His name means "Ever Weeping", on account of the numerous tears he shed until he found the teachings. </p><p>His story is told in detail by the Buddha in <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="https://read.84000.co/translation/toh10.html" title="The Perfection of Wisdom in Eighteen Thousand Lines">The Perfection of Wisdom in Eighteen Thousand Lines</a></cite> (Toh 10, ch. 85–86), and can be found quoted in several works, such as <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Words of My Perfect Teacher</cite> (<cite class="title text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">kun bzang bla ma’i zhal lung</cite>) by Patrul Rinpoche.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="39606232-7abe-46f6-835e-51128b461ce9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_be55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.440</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śakra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brgya byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྒྱ་བྱིན།</span></li><li class="italic">śakra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An epithet of Indra, the god who presides over the Heaven of the Thirty-Three, and appears in many Buddhist texts, usually referred to using this name and addressed by his personal name Kauśika, as both protector and disciple of the Buddha. In the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras he is an important interlocutor.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="1832c605-dce5-4def-b570-22d8bf717b5d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.441</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śākya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shAkya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱཀྱ།</span></li><li class="italic">śākya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Name of the ancient tribe in which the Buddha was born as a prince; their kingdom was based to the east of Kośala, in the foothills near the present-day border of India and Nepal, with Kapilavastu as its capital.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cb964334-adc9-4c58-9b74-5659b1047a31" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.442</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śākyasena</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">śākyasena</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An eighth-century Indian paṇḍita who participated in translation from Sanskrit into Tibetan.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="3df1bcb6-86da-4978-8191-8dbd8f56b919" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bet5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.443</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śāriputra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shA ri’i bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱ་རིའི་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">śāriputra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>One of the Buddha’s closest and most able śrāvaka disciples, who had the moniker “foremost in learning”; also known as Śāradvatīputra. While in some Mahāyāna sūtras he is almost ridiculed in his role as an interlocutor representing the limited view of the disciples’ awakening, in the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras he is treated with respect but nevertheless expresses an understanding less vast than that of Subhūti, also a disciple.</p> </note>  <p>One of the principal śrāvaka disciples of the Buddha, he was renowned for his discipline and for having been praised by the Buddha as foremost of the wise (often paired with Maudgalyā­yana, who was praised as foremost in the capacity for miraculous powers). His father, Tiṣya, to honor Śāriputra’s mother, Śārikā, named him Śāradvatīputra, or, in its contracted form, Śāriputra, meaning “Śārikā’s Son.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="de4c86bf-cc48-4608-9fa1-da94cf561735" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.444</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">secluded, seclusion, void</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dben pa, dben pa, dben pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབེན་པ།, དབེན་པ།, དབེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">viveka, viveka, vivikta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The term along with “voidness” (q.v.), has a variety of meanings, including empty and emptiness, and is also rendered in this text as “void” (q.v.) in other contexts. See also <a href="/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17"/>n.1094</a>.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="843397c4-de1c-4e2f-94c8-7f6447c071d5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.445</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">secluded, seclusion, void</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dben pa, dben pa, dben pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབེན་པ།, དབེན་པ།, དབེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">viveka, viveka, vivikta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The term, along with “voidness” (q.v.), has a range of meanings, including empty and emptiness, but also a connotation of separation, rendered in this text as “seclusion” (q.v.) in certain contexts. See also <a href="/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17"/>n.1094</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="06616fd0-7838-4433-a3e6-d142d6f50b29" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.446</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">secluded, seclusion, void</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dben pa, dben pa, dben pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབེན་པ།, དབེན་པ།, དབེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">viveka, viveka, vivikta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Often also translated in this text as “devoid.” See also “voidness,” “void,” “seclusion,” and <a href="/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17"/>n.1094</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="efacd175-91b7-484b-bfa8-68325bbdd6b2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.447</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">seeing the knowing of liberation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grol ba’i ye shes mthong ba, rnam par grol ba’i ye shes gzigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲོལ་བའི་ཡེ་ཤེས་མཐོང་བ།, རྣམ་པར་གྲོལ་བའི་ཡེ་ཤེས་གཟིགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vimukti­jñāna­darśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The direct witnessing of the distinctive knowing of liberation. One of the five “masses” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">skandha</foreign>) particular to bodhisattvas. See notes <a href="/entity/passage/fe462982-6a3a-4b98-91e0-4c3b3cc314d9"/>n.69</a> and <a href="/entity/passage/ff25491f-137c-4103-884c-d2c385feecbd"/>n.399</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6a04e588-3afb-493b-b72a-f4c294a63f4e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bg55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.448</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sign, superficial feature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshan ma, mtshan ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚན་མ།, མཚན་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">nimitta, nimitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5475bf32-88c2-4471-9cf6-eff28ffb3061" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bgd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.449</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sign, superficial feature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshan ma, mtshan ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚན་མ།, མཚན་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">nimitta, nimitta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>An inherent quality, like, for instance, the whiteness of a (white) cow. See <a href="/entity/passage/1af2e9ed-1e0a-4774-b0c7-87414484171b"/>n.881</a><!--note 874-->.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="f1b4c1aa-966e-462d-bb08-966fc8af7528" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bgl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.450</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">six changes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par ’gyur ba drug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་འགྱུར་བ་དྲུག</span></li><li class="italic">ṣaḍvikāraḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The movements and sounds of the earthquakes that accompany a tathāgata’s realization of perfect awakening. See <a href="/entity/passage/f059a41a-2c11-4352-b06d-13ec1e6bdb18"/>n.870</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="cd0f4fae-60bd-44f4-a329-c3cf62644124" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bgt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.451</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">small-minded</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">blo chung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བློ་ཆུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">alpabuddhi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="91eb4850-6549-4ee5-ae57-ec33c68112f1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.452</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">solitary realizer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang sangs rgyas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་སངས་རྒྱས།</span></li><li class="italic">pratyekabuddha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Someone who has realized an awakening comparable to that of an arhat but without hearing the teachings of a buddha, on his or her own in isolation, and does not teach a path to others.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="41253775-b217-44fb-8aff-7d84d261319e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bhd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.453</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sorrow Free</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mya ngan bral</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱ་ངན་བྲལ།</span></li><li class="italic">śokavigataṃ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of the four gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="7fe7eeef-cc10-4e6b-ab6f-7f42a2725573" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bhl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.454</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sorrowless</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mya ngan med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱ་ངན་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">aśoka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of the four gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="512bf5e4-ce16-4a44-9470-314d880dbc52" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.455</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">source of qualities, ultimate realm of things</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi dbyings, chos kyi dbyings</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་དབྱིངས།, ཆོས་ཀྱི་དབྱིངས།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmadhātu, dharmadhātu</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="11e511b8-43dc-46a3-9026-37be0e9ad47d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bi55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.456</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">source of qualities, ultimate realm of things</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi dbyings, chos kyi dbyings</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་དབྱིངས།, ཆོས་ཀྱི་དབྱིངས།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmadhātu, dharmadhātu</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="97a4deca-2db4-4fd3-9943-31e3a6c22619" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.457</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">spiritual qualities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba’i chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བའི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">kalyāṇadharma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c6eeefbc-2b12-4439-986c-1c38ae18a036" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.458</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śreṇika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phreng ba can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྲེང་བ་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">śreṇika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A non-Buddhist wandering ascetic who converts to Buddhism and in the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras exemplifies one who attains understanding through faith.</p> </note>  <p>A mendicant whose encounter with the Buddha and acceptance of him as the tathāgata features in the Prajñāpāramitā sūtras as evidence that the Buddha’s omniscience is not something to be understood through signs or characteristics. Also known as Śreṇika Vatsagotra. </p><p>The three different renderings of his name in Tibetan‍—<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">sde can</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">phreng ba can</em>, and <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bzo sbyangs</em> (which may correspond to Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Seniṣka</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Prakniṣka</em>, and <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Śaniṣka</em>)‍—are taken as markers for three different Tibetan translations of the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Aṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</cite>, as mentioned in the catalog of the Phukdrak (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">phug brag</em>) Kangyur and the Thamphü (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">tham phud</em>) of the Fifth Dalai Lama, Ngawang Lozang Gyatso.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="57c937d0-b335-4e93-b9ad-8534fa62a493" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.459</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">state of a worthy one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgra bcom pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགྲ་བཅོམ་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">arhattva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="06c4dd9a-a7f6-41fb-8826-06c47108934b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.460</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śubhakṛtsna</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge rgyas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་རྒྱས།</span></li><li class="italic">śubhakṛtsna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Tenth of the thirteen god realms of form that correspond to the four meditative concentrations, meaning “Most Extensive Virtue.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="394ccfa8-a88d-4d4a-82ef-d7e988d2fc9b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bjd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.461</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Subhāṣita</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">subhāṣita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A tenth-century Indian paṇḍita who participated in translation from Sanskrit into Tibetan.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="22f9f523-3d5f-4683-ac40-82bee1ab5a5f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bjl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.462</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Subhūti</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab ’byor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་འབྱོར།</span></li><li class="italic">subhūti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A disciple of the Buddha whose uniquely important role in the Perfection of Wisdom sūtras is to express and draw out the Buddha’s teaching on the perfection of wisdom, at the Buddha’s instigation, for the benefit of the audience of bodhisattvas although he himself is not among their number. Hari’s gloss: “He whose mental gift (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">bhūtiḥ</foreign>&lt;<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">sampatti</foreign>) is brilliance is (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">su</foreign>&lt;<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">śobhanā</foreign>) foremost among those dwelling without conflict.” See also <a href="/entity/passage/ce682850-4446-4e92-b9e4-da871259b68d"/>n.100</a>, and for more on Subhūti see the introduction to the <cite xml:lang="en">Twenty-Five Thousand</cite>, <ref target="/translation/toh9.html#UT22084-026-001-21005">i.78–90</ref>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="922c15ba-fbb8-4764-be97-54a49a39229b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bjt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.463</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">subsidiary characteristics</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dpe byad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཔེ་བྱད།</span></li><li class="italic">anuvyañjanāni</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The eighty secondary physical characteristics of a buddha and of other great beings (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mahāpuruṣa</em>), which include such details as the redness of the fingernails and the blackness of the hair. They are considered “minor” in terms of being secondary to the thirty-two major marks or signs of a great being.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8af97a5c-29da-4eee-8ca2-2bc0522459c9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.464</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">subtle hints</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thabs phra mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐབས་ཕྲ་མོ།</span></li><li class="italic">sūkṣmeṇopāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f587b001-44f4-4048-845d-8952d22f1ea5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.465</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">subtle mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems rgya chen po ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོ་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">avipulāni cittāni</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fd67b187-10df-4d63-a298-e1aa3ba34613" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.466</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sudarśana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shin tu mthong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིན་ཏུ་མཐོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">sudarśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Fourth of the five pure abodes, meaning “Extreme Insight.” Also the name of the principal city of the Heaven of the Thirty-Three.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="4463e381-57dd-4277-b078-a2fcf2af7b22" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.467</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śuddhāvāsa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnas gtsang ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནས་གཙང་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">śuddhāvāsa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The five pure abodes. See <a href="/entity/passage/8431e98a-cd2a-4cbb-a00c-b946ba863519"/>n.206</a>.</p> </note>  <p>The five Pure Abodes are the highest heavens of the Form Realm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">rūpadhātu</em>). They are called “pure abodes” because ordinary beings (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">pṛthagjana</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">so so’i skye bo</em>) cannot be born there; only those who have achieved the fruit of a non-returner (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">anāgāmin</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">phyir mi ’ong</em>) can be born there. A summary presentation of them is found in the third chapter of Vasubandhu's <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">Abhidharmakośa</cite>, although they are repeatedly mentioned as a set in numerous sūtras, tantras, and vinaya texts.</p><p>The five Pure Abodes are the last five of the seventeen levels of the Form Realm. Specifically, they are the last five of the eight levels of the upper Form Realm‍—which corresponds to the fourth meditative concentration (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dhyāna</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bsam gtan</em>)‍—all of which are described as “immovable” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">akopya</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mi g.yo ba</em>) since they are never destroyed during the cycles of the destruction and reformation of a world system. In particular, the five are Abṛha (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mi che ba</em>), the inferior heaven; Atapa (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mi gdung ba</em>), the heaven of no torment; Sudṛśa (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">gya nom snang</em>), the heaven of sublime appearances; Sudarśana (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">shin tu mthong</em>), the heaven of the most beautiful to behold; and Akaniṣṭha (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">’og min</em>), the highest heaven.</p><p>Yaśomitra explains their names, stating: (1) because those who abide there can only remain for a fixed amount of time, before they are plucked out (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√bṛh</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bṛṃhanti</em>) of that heaven, or because it is not as extensive (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">abṛṃhita</em>) as the others in the pure realms, that heaven is called the inferior heaven (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">abṛha</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mi che ba</em>); (2) since the afflictions can no longer torment (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√tap</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">tapanti</em>) those who reside there because of their having attained a particular samādhi, or because their state of mind is virtuous, they no longer torment (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√tap</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">tāpayanti</em>) others, this heaven, consequently, is called the heaven of no torment (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">atapa</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mi gdung ba</em>); (3) since those who reside there have exceptional (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">suṣṭhu</em>) vision because what they see (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√dṛś</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">darśana</em>) is utterly pure, that heaven is called the heaven of sublime appearances (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sudṛśa</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">gya nom snang</em>); (4) because those who reside there are beautiful gods, that heaven is called the heaven of the most beautiful to behold (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sudarśana</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">shin tu mthong</em>); and (5) since it is not lower (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">na kaniṣṭhā</em>) than any other heaven because there is no other place superior to it, this heaven is called the highest heaven (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">akaniṣṭha</em>; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">’og min</em>) since it is the uppermost.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="28dac5fc-1872-4ce1-87e8-e8ddfab20425" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bl55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.468</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sudharma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos bzang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་བཟང་།</span></li><li class="italic">sudharma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The assembly hall in the center of Sudarśana, the city in the Heaven of the Thirty-Three (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Trāyastriṃśa</em>). It has a central throne for Indra (Śakra) and thirty-two thrones arranged to its right and left for the other thirty-two devas that make up the eponymous thirty-three devas of Indra’s paradise. Indra’s own palace is to the north of this assembly hall.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2ba8f490-deb6-46b9-b264-c9a4235d2d42" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.469</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sudṛśa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gya nom snang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྱ་ནོམ་སྣང་།</span></li><li class="italic">sudṛśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Third of the five pure abodes, meaning “Attractive.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="f204ed92-9b0b-444c-8ddd-e7c13c7036db" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.470</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">supernormal supports</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdzu ’phrul gyi rkang pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྫུ་འཕྲུལ་གྱི་རྐང་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ṛddhipādaḥ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c0bb1887-4c4e-40b7-8df3-101f6b271c23" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_blt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.471</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">supported, utterly supported</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su bzung ba, yongs su gzung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་གཟུང་བ།, ཡོངས་སུ་བཟུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">parigṛhīta, parigṛhītā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="169c2ad8-dc41-4a8b-81d2-fa783b5d4211" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.472</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">supported, utterly supported</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su bzung ba, yongs su gzung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་གཟུང་བ།, ཡོངས་སུ་བཟུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">parigṛhīta, parigṛhītā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/4c68459b-28b8-4884-800f-3b78d5baf15e"/>n.307</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="6882b83e-6d4d-4178-8652-768c0ab6b718" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.473</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">supreme perfection</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pha rol tu son pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕ་རོལ་ཏུ་སོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">paramapārami</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4f4f5cf1-9362-4864-aad0-7a01354e4536" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.474</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">taking what is not given</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma byin par len pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་བྱིན་པར་ལེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">adattādāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ba88d417-b0e3-432a-babf-877a261cff8b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.475</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">tathāgata</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">de bzhin gshegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དེ་བཞིན་གཤེགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">tathāgata</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">tathāgata</foreign> is a buddha, one who has come from or gone to (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">āgata</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">gata</foreign>) the actual nature (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">tathā</foreign>), often etymologized as one who has “come to the way things are.” Ratnākaraśānti also glosses a tathāgata as one who has clarified the actual way things are (see <a href="/entity/passage/97d0c84e-f8c1-471c-9804-492a53eda3b7"/>n.255</a>).</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="6fea0604-1e66-4e5e-b771-83205bf1c70d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.476</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Temperate</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nges pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">niyatā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of one of eight lotus pools in each of the gardens of Dharmodgata’s estate in Gandhavatī.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="bb4fb512-0bd3-4e79-994c-c6cf9d432a02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.477</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">temple hall</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dkyil ’khor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཀྱིལ་འཁོར།</span></li><li class="italic">abhramaṇḍapa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7dac2a1e-1ed3-4816-9b8d-4e9ae2fd9a0d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.478</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ten powers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stobs bcu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོབས་བཅུ།</span></li><li class="italic">daśabala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/e78cd953-87e6-4025-93ae-0d19169f228e"/>n.124</a><!--note 122-->.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="13b45b8e-d487-4bd2-beeb-aae9daae6fd8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.479</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ten virtuous ways of acting</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba bcu’i las kyi lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བ་བཅུའི་ལས་ཀྱི་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">daśa­kuśala­karma­patha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c8930b91-fdcb-40b8-ab5f-b63ffcafc7a7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bo55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.480</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">thing that produces merit, thing that produces the merit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsod nams bya ba’i dngos po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསོད་ནམས་བྱ་བའི་དངོས་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">puṇyakriyāvastu</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e1ec55ce-1999-4c91-9f2d-3096113283c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.481</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">things and nonthings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngos po dang dngos po med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངོས་པོ་དང་དངོས་པོ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhāvābhāva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c542957b-778b-4c58-9fd1-cd0bce29cc00" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.482</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">thirty-seven factors in awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi phyogs kyi chos sum cu rtsa bdun</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཕྱོགས་ཀྱི་ཆོས་སུམ་ཅུ་རྩ་བདུན།</span></li><li class="italic">saptatriṃśad bodhipakṣā dharmā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/f293ea18-7a51-49aa-b184-f1a1f975484f"/>n.219</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="5d31124e-6a79-41ff-9dc5-d20638b00ecd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.483</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">totality of causes and conditions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyu dang rkyen tshogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུ་དང་རྐྱེན་ཚོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">hetu­pratyaya­sāmagrī</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2539148a-b7d6-49c3-9dc3-aa394305d054" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.484</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">transgression</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ltung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">āpatti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="14e898b0-8447-497a-98d1-743dc14f6632" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bpd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.485</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">transitory collection</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig tshogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་ཚོགས།</span></li><li class="italic">satkāya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The mistaken focus of an important category of false views regarding there being a “self” that is related in various ways to the “collection” that is made up of the “transitory” constituents of experience or “constituents underlying the clinging to existence” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">skandha</foreign>s). See also <a href="/entity/passage/86caf8af-7627-4997-a6f9-09dfb7cb8de9"/>n.1343</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="9c39d3c9-58f0-4cdc-b4f6-dd7ef1c06f1c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bpl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.486</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">trivial</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngan ngon</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངན་ངོན།</span></li><li class="italic">avaraka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="dd571a94-b6b3-4e5a-acb3-f5c0068a3df0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bpt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.487</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">true nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmatā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The real nature, true quality, or condition of things. Throughout Buddhist discourse this term is used in two distinct ways. In one, it designates the relative nature that is either the essential characteristic of a specific phenomenon, such as the heat of fire and the moisture of water, or the defining feature of a specific term or category. The other very important and widespread way it is used is to designate the ultimate nature of all phenomena, which cannot be conveyed in conceptual, dualistic terms and is often synonymous with emptiness or the absence of intrinsic existence.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9a355540-ffac-4b2c-a67b-05ab60c4cc16" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.488</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">truth body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmakāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="df752960-7e84-45ca-b93c-11183cc9ce04" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.489</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tuṣita</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་ལྡན།</span></li><li class="italic">tuṣita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Tuṣita (or sometimes Saṃtuṣita), literally “Joyous” or “Contented,” is one of the six heavens of the desire realm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kāmadhātu</em>). In standard classifications, such as the one in the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Abhidharmakośa</cite>, it is ranked as the fourth of the six counting from below. This god realm is where all future buddhas are said to dwell before taking on their final rebirth prior to awakening. There, the Buddha Śākyamuni lived his preceding life as the bodhisattva Śvetaketu. When departing to take birth in this world, he appointed the bodhisattva Maitreya, who will be the next buddha of this eon, as his Dharma regent in Tuṣita. For an account of the Buddha’s previous life in Tuṣita, see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Play in Full</cite> (Toh 95), <a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/943039c8-c5ca-4a10-a536-2dd2c725aba6" title="2.12">2.12</a>, and for an account of Maitreya’s birth in Tuṣita and a description of this realm, see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="/entity/work/61476bf4-b4db-4e4d-9993-60d347cf1769" title="The Sūtra on Maitreya’s Birth in the Heaven of Joy">The Sūtra on Maitreya’s Birth in the Heaven of Joy</a></cite>, (Toh 199).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d54f7db2-be22-4bb6-8953-4cb74728ec05" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.490</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">two extremes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtha’ gnyis</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐའ་གཉིས།</span></li><li class="italic">antadvaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d55b254c-92cb-4882-95c0-71542c62ee69" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.491</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">types of extrasensory knowledge</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par shes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་ཤེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhijñā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>As in other texts, mentions are made of five or six types. The five are (1) the knowledge of various types of magical powers, (2) the divine ear faculty, (3) the knowledge of others’ mindsets, (4) the knowledge that remembers occurrences in previous lives, (5) the divine eye faculty, all these first five being considered “mundane” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">laukika</foreign>) achievements resulting from the fourth <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">dhyāna</foreign>; they are therefore common to non-Buddhist practitioners. The sixth is (6) knowledge of the exhaustion of worldly influences (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">āsravakṣaya</foreign>), which is a supramundane (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">lokottara</foreign>) achievement resulting from <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">vipaśyana</foreign>. For explanations of the first five, see <a href="/entity/passage/81812b8a-d1e3-40ba-b7bf-c518ea28d2b7"/>n.382</a><!--note 375-->.</p> </note></div></div></div></div><div id="f0880e20-93b5-4e57-ba47-88569677dc6a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_br55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.492</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ultimate resort</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dpung gnyen</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཔུང་གཉེན།</span></li><li class="italic">parāyaṇaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ec668581-6d76-4685-b567-c8bc7cb3c41e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_brd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.493</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unattached</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma chags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཆགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asaṅga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See also “free of attachment” and “nonattachment.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0221f7aa-d9bb-49b9-86af-d8e716ace9af" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_brl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.494</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unchanged, untransformed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par ma bsgyur ba, ’gyur ba med pa’o</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགྱུར་བ་མེད་པའོ།, རྣམ་པར་མ་བསྒྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">avikṛtā, avikṛtā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="774c8de1-4765-408e-8e62-1a0b0dee8cd4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_brt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.495</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unchanged, untransformed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par ma bsgyur ba, ’gyur ba med pa’o</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགྱུར་བ་མེད་པའོ།, རྣམ་པར་མ་བསྒྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">avikṛtā, avikṛtā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cd35d9e4-576e-4c60-9d07-144110b0c808" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bs55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.496</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unconditioned</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par ’dus ma byas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་འདུས་མ་བྱས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anabhisaṃskṛta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4434d430-b51a-4219-b09a-897de5306704" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bsd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.497</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unconscionable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glo ba la gcags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གློ་བ་ལ་གཅགས།</span></li><li class="italic">kaukṛtyaṃ</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d0bf98ce-1d85-4751-abd2-a3da0982fbd4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bsl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.498</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">uncreated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma bgyis pa, ma byas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་བགྱིས་པ།, མ་བྱས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">akṛtā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="21334d35-f81a-462d-8f11-3159cec591aa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.499</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">under the influence of Māra’s magical power</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud kyi byin gyis brlabs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད་ཀྱི་བྱིན་གྱིས་བརླབས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">mārādhiṣṭhita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="46f2a296-7357-49fe-ae2e-19a49ada7bc0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.500</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">undifferentiable actual nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhan ma yin pa’i de bzhin nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞན་མ་ཡིན་པའི་དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">ananyatathatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="7c1799ea-7242-4208-a69e-5412a2e29c2d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_btd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.501</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unenmeshed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma gtogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་གཏོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aparyāpanna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2c1636de-e437-4af8-8145-08cb7335d974" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_btl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.502</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unentangled</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma chags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཆགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asakta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9212e3e6-5e47-4184-955a-8d5c84543d8c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_btt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.503</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unequaled</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mnyam pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཉམ་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">atulya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f58a3224-f54a-4976-b3c5-9c1583342572" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bu55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.504</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unfalsifiable actual nature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma log pa’i de bzhin nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ལོག་པའི་དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">avitathatā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="310dc75f-b046-4d4e-bf5d-d180a968fbb5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.505</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unfrightened mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid mi skrag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་མི་སྐྲག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anuttrastamānasa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9fcae89e-a2a1-4758-bd41-dbff4d145fb6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.506</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unharmed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma snad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་སྣད།</span></li><li class="italic">anupahata</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d59dc8d2-9f9d-4fcc-83f7-6a956fc587cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_but5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.507</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">uninjured</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma smas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་སྨས།</span></li><li class="italic">akṛta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="8d017774-aa9d-4033-a6a0-fda55fba03c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.508</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unlimited</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aparimāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The Tibetan translates both <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">apramāṇa</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">aparimāṇa</foreign> as <foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="term">tshad med pa</foreign>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="36a946e2-7f4b-4c18-ae03-46864436b78f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.509</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unproliferating</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spros pa ma mchis pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲོས་པ་མ་མཆིས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">aprapañca</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2019b5f0-cfe4-4d1d-92b5-73a9245488bd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.510</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unshared</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thun mong ma lags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐུན་མོང་མ་ལགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asādhāraṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a4b4781f-82e4-4c69-835c-0d5e48c47a02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_bvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.511</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unsurpassable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zil gyis mi non pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟིལ་གྱིས་མི་ནོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anabhibhūta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="025da177-4bdf-47b4-b3f7-639bedf16eb9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.512</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unsurpassed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bla na med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བླ་ན་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anuttara</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0938e97e-16e8-4dc8-90a9-f0e0a58c7160" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.513</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unvirtuous friend</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdig pa’i grogs po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྡིག་པའི་གྲོགས་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">pāpamitra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="af03d367-aed3-4d32-aeb7-e599064f4c82" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.514</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">unwavering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྟན།</span></li><li class="italic">dṛḍha</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a46d6a95-a6d5-49af-8068-a26aab200bea" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.515</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">uphold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">rakṣati</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ad7eee76-e531-4c8d-a6e7-c74cf30a718c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.516</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">uplifted mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems rab tu bzung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་རབ་ཏུ་བཟུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">pragṛhītāni cittāni</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9ee5c550-3cb3-445a-a658-565f8bfd3d45" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.517</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vaijayanta Palace</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par rgyal ba’i khang pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་རྒྱལ་བའི་ཁང་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vaijayanta­prāsāda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The palace of Śakra (Indra) in the Heaven of the Thirty-Three.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="85a0e3f1-ad8c-44ce-839f-8903612b40ba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.518</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vajrapāṇi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lag na rdo rje</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལག་ན་རྡོ་རྗེ།</span></li><li class="italic">vajrapāṇi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Vajrapāṇi means “Wielder of the Vajra.” In the Pali canon, he appears as a yakṣa guardian in the retinue of the Buddha. In the Mahāyāna scriptures he is a bodhisattva and one of the “eight close sons of the Buddha.” In the tantras, he is also regarded as an important Buddhist deity and instrumental in the transmission of tantric scriptures. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="91107107-3f31-4442-8365-9099041efadf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.519</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">venerable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshe dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚེ་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayuṣmān</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A term of address for monks, meaning “blessed in life.” “fortunate,” “possessed of life’s (joy).” See <a href="/entity/passage/9afe2818-6a0a-487f-84cb-ea3d9a38f626"/>n.81</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="803ba49d-1a79-42c7-a363-0cde26f4d5e4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.520</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">virtuous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">kalyāṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d40bc2f8-5a66-4112-b5c8-799cc534a17b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.521</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">virtuous and unvirtuous qualities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba dang mi dge ba’i chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བ་དང་མི་དགེ་བའི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">kuśalākuśala­dharma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cb1774cb-402d-465e-a33f-c45b2edb5bae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.522</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">virtuous friend</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba’i bshes gnyen</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བའི་བཤེས་གཉེན།</span></li><li class="italic">kalyāṇamitra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="1258a233-15e6-4285-8209-e64d216a9798" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.523</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">vital faculty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srog gi dbang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲོག་གི་དབང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">jīvitendriya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="76fb6812-3e9d-4c5b-98d9-aee79d4a61e9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.524</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">voidness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dben pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབེན་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">viviktatva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Often meaning the state of being isolated, solitary, or secluded, but also “lacking (something),” and almost synonymous with “emptiness.” See also “void” and “secluded,” translations of the related term <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">viveka</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn">dben pa</foreign>) and <a href="/entity/passage/5a40e91c-acae-48bf-b029-614b1fa3fd17"/>n.1094</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="9704e772-b86a-4db9-ae36-ab2e91f2cd8d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.525</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">vulnerability</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླགས།</span></li><li class="italic">avatāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d86dc1c3-f802-46fe-9bd6-4b2321d77a32" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.526</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vulture Peak</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya rgod kyi phung po’i ri</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་རྒོད་ཀྱི་ཕུང་པོའི་རི།</span></li><li class="italic">gṛdhrakūṭa-parvata</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The Gṛdhra­kūṭa, literally Vulture Peak, was a hill located in the kingdom of Magadha, in the vicinity of the ancient city of Rājagṛha (modern-day Rajgir, in the state of Bihar, India), where the Buddha bestowed many sūtras, especially the Great Vehicle teachings, such as the Prajñāpāramitā sūtras. It continues to be a sacred pilgrimage site for Buddhists to this day.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="23e021ed-df6a-4f14-a93a-9727a988896c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.527</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">warming up, warmth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">drod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲོད།</span></li><li class="italic">ūṣman</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The first of four stages or experiences of breaking through on the path of preliminary practice.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="8e5153df-d01f-4825-a3b3-d9f0bea924df" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.528</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">way of proceeding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshig gi rnam grangs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚིག་གི་རྣམ་གྲངས།</span></li><li class="italic">padaparyāya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Ratnākara’s gloss suggests that <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">pada</foreign> here means a “step” along the path rather than the Tibetan translation as “word” (<foreign xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="term">tshig</foreign>).</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="23e821ec-fd7d-4f83-8f04-52fd5cb1324c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.529</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">weak mindset</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems dman pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་དམན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">hīnacitta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4ec70a92-384a-4cf4-a887-4dc5f099cd7c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.530</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">weak-minded</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">blo dman pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བློ་དམན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">mandabuddhi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f3510365-2649-4ff1-ba02-c61e0063975c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.531</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">weak-willed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems pa dman pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་པ་དམན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">hīnasattva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="da3119d6-8309-4c6c-9706-e9b94b7d8e4b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.532</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wheel of Dharma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi ’khor lo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་འཁོར་ལོ།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmacakra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="61d00384-8938-4c76-8fdf-5266156492db" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.533</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">white water lilies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku mu da</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་མུ་ད།</span></li><li class="italic">kumuda</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ac00ca2c-1928-488a-958e-103e94448fb0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.534</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wisdom truth body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ye shes chos kyi sku</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡེ་ཤེས་ཆོས་ཀྱི་སྐུ།</span></li><li class="italic">jñānadharma–kāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2b0d3a59-d064-4f37-895c-4dcaf017a5bc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.535</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wish to come near</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’ong ’dod par ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོང་འདོད་པར་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">upasaṃkramitavyaṃ maṃsyante</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="10cd4b1f-a54e-4fb3-a141-1425c2be756f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.536</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">without any constituents remaining</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phung po lhag ma med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕུང་པོ་ལྷག་མ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anupadhiśeṣa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="ee5e5a9f-ef48-49c8-9807-70dc161a1005" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.537</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">without equal</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mnyam pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཉམ་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asama</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="321cd27d-0c6e-44b0-8da9-89d54c1e9891" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.538</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">without forsaking</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtson pa ma bor bar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྩོན་པ་མ་བོར་བར།</span></li><li class="italic">anikṣiptadhura</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="4f22fb11-9da9-4711-a6b3-72dbd6ac9ed4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.539</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">world system</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig rten gyi khams</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཁམས།</span></li><li class="italic">lokadhātu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">lokadhātu</em> refers to a single four continent world-system illumined by a sun and moon, with a Mount Meru at its center and an encircling ring of mountains at its periphery, and with the various god realms above, thus including the desire, form, and formless realms.</p><p>The term can also refer to groups of such world-systems in multiples of thousands. A universe of one thousand such world-systems is called a chiliocosm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sāhasra­loka­dhātu</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">stong gi ’jig rten gyi khams</em>); one thousand such chiliocosms is called a dichiliocosm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dvisāhasralokadhātu</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">stong gnyis kyi ’jig rten gyi khams</em>); and one thousand such dichiliocosms is called a trichiliocosm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">trisāhasra­loka­dhātu</em>, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">stong gsum gyi 'jig rten gyi khams</em>). A trichiliocosm is the largest universe described in Buddhist cosmology.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86981a5b-d566-434a-8400-2956eadee2b8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.540</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">worldly influences</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">āsrava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>See <a href="/entity/passage/fe462982-6a3a-4b98-91e0-4c3b3cc314d9"/>n.69</a>.</p> </note>  <p>Literally, “to flow” or “to ooze.” Mental defilements or contaminations that “flow out” toward the objects of cyclic existence, binding us to them. Vasubandhu offers two alternative explanations of this term: “They cause beings to remain (<em class="foreign">āsayanti</em>) within saṃsāra” and “They flow from the Summit of Existence down to the Avīci hell, out of the six wounds that are the sense fields” (<cite class="title">Abhidharma­kośa­bhāṣya</cite> 5.40; Pradhan 1967, p. 308). The Summit of Existence (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhavāgra</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">srid pa’i rtse mo</em>) is the highest point within saṃsāra, while the hell called Avīci (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mnar med</em>) is the lowest; the six sense fields (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">āyatana</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">skye mched</em>) here refer to the five sense faculties plus the mind, i.e., the six internal sense fields.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3fcaec25-ccff-4616-b4f0-bc31081cb012" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.541</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">worthy one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgra bcom pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགྲ་བཅོམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">arhat</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>A “worthy one” (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">arhat</foreign>) refers to a disciple who has reached the final stage of a disciple’s realization. Indian scholars gave six or more etymologies for <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">arhat</foreign>. This translation follows the etymology “someone who is worthy,” i.e., worthy of the generosity (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">niṇḍārha</foreign>) of others and worthy of the veneration (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">pūjārha</foreign>) of others. Note that Tibetan translators follow a different one: “someone who has eliminated the enemies” <foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">(ari</foreign>+<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">hatavān</foreign>), i.e., the emotional defilements. See <a href="/entity/passage/878933d3-acc1-4ed3-8303-e73285f08705"/>n.68</a>.</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="0bfd188b-9094-4805-bdd7-9758fcacf5f7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.542</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Yāma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’thab bral</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཐབ་བྲལ།</span></li><li class="italic">yāma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>Third god realm of desire, meaning “strifeless.”</p> </note> </div></div></div></div><div id="895a0815-88b6-4871-8b34-fa2ab5208e06" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_c7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.543</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Yellow-Flowered</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi me tog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་མེ་ཏོག</span></li><li class="italic">suvarṇapuṣpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><note type="definition"> <p>The name of the future tathāgata that the woman Gaṅgadevī is foreordained to become by the Buddha, in the narrative found in all the long Perfection of Wisdom scriptures. </p> </note> </div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-state="inactive" data-orientation="horizontal" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-bibliography" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-bibliography" tabindex="0" data-slot="tabs-content" class="mt-2 ring-offset-background focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 pb-8 data-[state=inactive]:hidden"><div class="flex flex-col w-full"><div id="bibliography" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2nanpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-5 mt-6">b.</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><h2 class="font-serif font-light text-primary scroll-m-20 text-xl @c/sidebar:mt-4 mt-6 @c/sidebar:pb-2 pb-3 @c/sidebar:text-left text-center section-title">Bibliography</h2></div></div><div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-6"><div class="flex flex-col gap-4"><div id="Primary Sources-0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_5d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-0.5 mt-4">b.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Primary Sources</div></div></div><div id="adb88bfe-4f95-49ab-aff6-c130cc84f59c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_26d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Mitra, Rajendralala, ed. <em>Aṣṭasāhasrikā</em>. Bibliotheca Indica nos. 603, 620, 629, 645, 671, and 690. Calcutta: Asiatic Society of Bengal, 1888.</p> </div></div></div><div id="be912b4b-4140-4cce-ae8a-98bbc31c7bfe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2ad7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.2</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Wogihara, Unrai, ed. <em>Abhisamayālaṃkār’ālokā Prajñapāramitāvyākhyā (Commentary on Aṣṭasāhasrikā-Prajñāpāramitā) by Haribhadra Together With the Text Commented On</em>. Series D, vols. I and II. Tokyo: The Toyo Bunko, 1932–35.</p> </div></div></div><div id="c4ff9a17-6b06-47ed-b2e2-0c550f307cb9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2ed7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.3</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Vaidya, P. L., ed. <em>Aṣṭasāhasrikā Prajñāpāramitā: With Haribhadra’s Commentary called Āloka</em>. Buddhist Sanskrit Texts no. 4. Darbhanga: The Mithila Institute, 1960.</p> </div></div></div><div id="db9832eb-d1b0-4421-a50e-6115757d7175" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2id7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.4</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Jaini, Padmanabh S., ed. <em>Sāratamā: A Pañjikā on the Aṣṭasāhasrikā Prajñāpāramitā Sūtra by Ratnākaraśānti</em>. Tibetan Sanskrit Works Series, 18. Patna: Kashi Prasad Jayaswal Research Institute, 1979. (For a Sanskrit critical edition of chapter 1, see Seton 2016, Appendix I.)</p> </div></div></div><div id="70ae3de5-be17-471c-a574-ca92a2e5f129" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2md7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.5</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p> <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa</em> (<em>Aṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</em>). Toh 12, Degé Kangyur vol. 33 (brgyad stong, ka), folios 1.b–286.a.</p> </div></div></div><div id="6a3ddf33-0268-484d-994e-1334e38cad1f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2qd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.6</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p> <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa</em>. bka’ ’gyur (dpe bsdur ma) [Comparative Edition of the Kangyur], krung go’i bod rig pa zhib ’jug ste gnas kyi bka’ bstan dpe sdur khang (The Tibetan Tripitaka Collation Bureau of the China Tibetology Research Center). 108 volumes. Beijing: krung go’i bod rig pa dpe skrun khang (China Tibetology Publishing House), 2006–9, vol. 33, pp. 33–723.</p> </div></div></div><div id="94012056-1bdf-409c-8432-7c3f93c50719" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2ud7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.7</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p> <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa</em> (<em>Aṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</em>). H 11, Lhasa Kangyur vol. 29 (brgyad stong pa, a), folios 1.a–523.a. (BDRC: <a href="http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/MW26071_0011">MW26071</a>).</p> </div></div></div><div id="d36eec93-e68e-4819-a3e2-ceead205cc63" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_32d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.8</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Ārya Vimuktisena.<em> mngon rtogs rgyan gyi ’grel pa</em> (<em>Abhisamayālaṃkāra­vṛtti</em>). Toh 3787, Degé Tengyur vol. 80 (shes phyin, ka), folios 13.a–212.a. </p> </div></div></div><div id="3a5b6fac-de14-4102-8f18-e0293ccc62e8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_36d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.9</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Haribhadra. <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa’i bshad pa mngon par rtogs pa’i rgyan gyi snang ba</em> (<em>Aṣṭasāhasrikā­prajñā­paramita­vyākhyānābhi­samayālaṃkārālokā</em>) [“Light”]. Toh 3791, Degé Tengyur vol. 85 (shes phyin, cha), folios 1.b–341.a.</p> </div></div></div><div id="34b351d7-e53f-416d-8573-673baf59c84d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_3ad7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.10</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Maitreya-Asaṅga. [<em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa’i man ngag gi bstan bcos</em>] <em>mngon par rtogs pa’i rgyan</em> (<em>Abhisamayālaṃkāra-</em>[<em>nāma­prajñā­pāramitopadeśa­śāstra­kārikā</em>]) [<em>Ornament of Clear Realization</em>]. Toh 3786, Degé Tengyur vol. 80 (shes phyin, ka), folios 1.b–13.a; also TPD 49: 3–30. </p> </div></div></div><div id="9a7d8498-1e4c-41c1-bb10-cc09a2169939" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_3ed7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.11</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Ratnākaraśānti (rin chen ’byung gnas zhi ba). <em>’phags pa shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa brgyad stong pa’i dka’ ’grel snying po mchog</em> (<em>Sāratamā­nāmaaryāṣṭa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā­pañjikā</em>). Toh 3803, Degé Tengyur vol. 89 (shes phyin, tha), folios 1.a–230.a; also TPD 53: 711–1317. (For a Tibetan critical edition of chapter one, see Seton 2016, Appendix I.)</p> </div></div></div><div id="3311015b-d599-4d93-a99b-98566c33c757" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_3id7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.12</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Ratnākaraśānti. <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa’i man ngag</em> (<em>Prajñā­pāramitopadeśa</em>). Toh 4079, Degé Tengyur vol. 138 (sems tsam, hi), folios 133.b–162.b.</p> </div></div></div></div><div class="flex flex-col gap-4"><div id="Secondary References-1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_5l7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-0.5 mt-4">b.2</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Secondary References</div></div></div><div id="604452a7-05be-49a6-87a0-885bacfae1d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_g6l7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Kasawara, K., F. Max Müller, and H. Wenzel, eds. <em>The Dharmasaṃgraha: An Ancient Collection of Buddhist Technical Terms</em>. Anecdotia Oxoniensia, Aryan Series vol. I, part V. Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1885. Online at <a href="https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.311567">Internet Archive</a>. For translation and transliteration see Ānandajoti 2017.</p> </div></div></div><div id="8a4f20e6-5bbf-430a-9156-7728eb2163ed" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_gal7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.2</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Kramer, Jowita (ed.). <em>Sthiramati’s Pañcaskandhakavibhāṣā</em>. Part I: Critical Edition, Part II: Diplomatic Edition. Beijing/Vienna: China Tibetology Publishing House/Austrian Academy of Sciences Press, 2014.</p> </div></div></div><div id="e9dff8a2-da2a-4e03-9ea4-472b9945c0dd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_gel7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.3</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Chim Namkha Drak (mchims nam mkha’ grags). <em>jo bo rin po che dpal ldan a ti sha’i rnam thar rgyas pa yongs grags</em> [<em>Biography of Atīśa, Zhö edition</em>]. In <em>mkhas dbang rag+hu wIra dang lokesha tsan+dra rnam gnyis kyis nyar tshags byas pa’i dpe tshogs</em> vol. 29, edited by Raghu Vira and Lokesh Chandra: 49–237 (Roman page numbers). New Delhi, 1982. BDRC: <a href="http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/MW1KG26281_EFECD3">MW1KG26281_EFECD3</a>. </p> </div></div></div><div id="413c1221-dc67-4296-be48-27edaa320921" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_gil7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.4</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Jampa Samten. <em>phug brag bka’ ’gyur bris ma’i dkar chag: A Catalogue of the Phug-brag Manuscript Kanjur</em>. Dharamsala: LTWA, 1992. BDRC: <a href="http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/W1KG15416">W1KG15416</a>.</p> </div></div></div><div id="97757e42-7647-4693-afea-8c296b75b1c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_gml7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.5</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Olkha Lelung Lobsang Trinlé (’ol kha / dga’ sle lung blo bzang ’phrin las). Narthang Catalog (Detailed). <em>bka’ ’gyur rin po che’i gsung par srid gsum rgyan gcig rdzu ’phrul shing rta’i dkar chag ngo mtshar bkod pa rgya mtsho’i lde mig</em>. Scans in: Narthang Kangyur (snar thang bka’ ’gyur), vol. 102, pp. 663–909. BDRC: <a href="http://purl.bdrc.io/resource/W22703">W22703</a>. Transcribed in: bka’ ’gyur (dpe bsdur ma) [Comparative Edition of the Kangyur], krung go’i bod rig pa zhib ’jug ste gnas kyi bka’ bstan dpe sdur khang (The Tibetan Tripitaka Collation Bureau of the China Tibetology Research Center). 108 volumes. Beijing: krung go’i bod rig pa dpe skrun khang (China Tibetology Publishing House), 2006–9, vol. 106, pp. 71–306.</p> </div></div></div><div id="f0b7172d-f522-40c4-9b44-eb43345d2e33" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_gql7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.6</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Perfection of Wisdom in One Hundred Thousand Lines</em> (<em>Śata­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</em>, <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa stong phrag brgya pa</em>, Toh 8). Translated by Gareth Sparham. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2024.</p> </div></div></div><div id="c46268ad-8615-4d9a-b2dc-9255cbb23d0e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_gul7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.7</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Perfection of Wisdom in Twenty-Five Thousand Lines</em> (<em>Pañcaviṃśati­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</em>, <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa stong phrag nyi shu lnga pa</em>, Toh 9). Translated by the Padmakara Translation Group. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2023.</p> </div></div></div><div id="ecd4aaf1-1ec0-4da6-811f-dd04d2b0e194" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_h2l7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.8</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Perfection of Wisdom in Eighteen Thousand Lines</em> (<em>Aṣṭādaśa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</em>, <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa khri brgyad stong pa</em>, Toh 10). Translated by Gareth Sparham. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2022.</p> </div></div></div><div id="ffd9aa4f-cc43-46f2-9ba2-d743dd853dae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_h6l7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.9</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Perfection of Wisdom in Ten Thousand Lines</em> (<em>Daśa­sāhasrikā­prajñā­pāramitā</em>, <em>shes rab kyi pha rol tu phyin pa khri pa</em>, Toh 11). Translated by the Padmakara Translation Group. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2018.</p> </div></div></div><div id="a3cdd2d2-d729-4551-aaef-ba8576391c56" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_hal7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.10</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Chapter on Going Forth</em> (<em>Pravrajyāvastu</em>, <em>rab tu ’byung ba’i gzhi</em>, chapter 1 of <em>Vinayavastu</em>, Toh 1). Translated by Robert Miller. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2018.</p> </div></div></div><div id="0505c90b-dae8-47a9-978e-3a3d175efffd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_hel7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.11</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000.<em>The Dhāraṇī “Entering Into Nonconceptuality”</em> (<em>Avikalpapraveśadhāraṇī</em>, <em>rnam par mi rtog par ’jug pa’i gzungs</em>, Toh 142). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2020.</p> </div></div></div><div id="fed4b16a-d762-411e-9b96-0fd595747f35" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_hil7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.12</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>Distinctly Ascertaining the Meanings</em> (<em>Arthaviniścaya</em>, <em>don rnam par nges pa’i chos kyi rnam grangs</em>, Toh 317). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2021.</p> </div></div></div><div id="64e422d7-a5d0-4e77-855f-8835ece1b963" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_hml7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.13</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Sūtra of the Wheel of Dharma</em> (<em>Dharmacakrasūtra</em>, <em>chos kyi ’khor lo’i mdo</em>, Toh 337). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2018.</p> </div></div></div><div id="6f57ed71-9e1b-43a2-910d-db05923b1dc0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_hql7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.14</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Teaching on the Purification Practices from the Path to Liberation</em> (<em>Vimukti­mārga­dhuta­guṇa­nirdeśa</em>, Toh 306). Translated by Sue Roach. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, forthcoming.</p> </div></div></div><div id="a1d2a513-8c8e-431a-8fd7-f41688583a4a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_hul7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.15</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Teaching of Vimalakīrti</em> (<em>Vimala­kīrti­nirdeśa­sūtra</em>, <em>dri ma med par grags pas bstan pa’i mdo</em>, Toh 176). Translated by Robert A. F. Thurman. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2017.</p> </div></div></div><div id="35add0a0-92c9-432f-b859-49496ed3c72e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_i2l7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.16</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>The Ten Bhūmis</em> (<em>Daśabhūmika</em>, <em>su bcu pa</em>, Toh 44, ch. 31). Translated by Peter Alan Roberts. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2021.</p> </div></div></div><div id="a3200699-d432-4f7a-b973-9858d330aa2b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_i6l7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.17</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>84000. <em>Upholding the Roots of Virtue</em> (<em>Kuśala­mūla­saṃparigraha</em>, <em>dge ba’i rtsa ba yongs su ’dzin pa</em>, Toh 101). Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee. Online publication. 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha, 2020.</p> </div></div></div><div id="b78852ef-4e2a-4bf0-8bd6-c52eeb68db0c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ial7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.18</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Anālayo, Bhikkhu. “<a href="https://www.buddhismuskunde.uni-hamburg.de/pdf/5-personen/analayo/sixty-two-views.pdf">The ‘Sixty-two Views’—A Comparative Study</a>.” <em>Fuyan Buddhist Studies</em> no. 5, pp. 23–42. Hsinchu: Fuyan Buddhist Institute, 2010. </p> </div></div></div><div id="7d450560-7466-4d3d-b0c5-53ed7479d4a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_iel7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.2.19</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Ānandajoti, Bhikkhu (tr.). <em>Dharmasaṅgraha: The Dharma Collection</em>. Online publication. <a href="https://ancient-buddhis